B040C001V001	40	1	1	The book of the genealogy of Jesus Christ, the Son of David, the Son of Abraham:
B040C001V002	40	1	2	Abraham fathered Isaac, Isaac fathered Jacob, and Jacob fathered Judah and his brothers.
B040C001V003	40	1	3	Judah fathered Perez and Zerah by Tamar, Perez fathered Hezron, and Hezron fathered Ram.
B040C001V004	40	1	4	Ram fathered Amminadab, Amminadab fathered Nahshon, and Nahshon fathered Salmon.
B040C001V005	40	1	5	Salmon fathered Boaz by Rahab, Boaz fathered Obed by Ruth, Obed fathered Jesse,
B040C001V006	40	1	6	and Jesse fathered David the king. David the king fathered Solomon by her who had been the wife of Uriah.
B040C001V007	40	1	7	Solomon fathered Rehoboam, Rehoboam fathered Abijah, and Abijah fathered Asa.
B040C001V008	40	1	8	Asa fathered Jehoshaphat, Jehoshaphat fathered Joram, and Joram fathered Uzziah.
B040C001V009	40	1	9	Uzziah fathered Jotham, Jotham fathered Ahaz, and Ahaz fathered Hezekiah.
B040C001V010	40	1	10	Hezekiah fathered Manasseh, Manasseh fathered Amon, and Amon fathered Josiah.
B040C001V011	40	1	11	Josiah fathered Jeconiah and his brothers at the time of the captivity in Babylon.
B040C001V012	40	1	12	And after the captivity in Babylon, Jeconiah fathered Shealtiel, and Shealtiel fathered Zerubbabel.
B040C001V013	40	1	13	Zerubbabel fathered Abiud, Abiud fathered Eliakim, and Eliakim fathered Azor.
B040C001V014	40	1	14	Azor fathered Zadok, Zadok fathered Achim, and Achim fathered Eliud.
B040C001V015	40	1	15	Eliud fathered Eleazar, Eleazar fathered Matthan, and Matthan fathered Jacob.
B040C001V016	40	1	16	And Jacob fathered Joseph the husband of Mary, of whom was born Jesus who is called Christ.
B040C001V017	40	1	17	So all the generations from Abraham till David [were] fourteen generations, from David until the captivity in Babylon [were] fourteen generations, and from the captivity in Babylon until the Christ [were] fourteen generations.
B040C001V018	40	1	18	Now the birth of Jesus Christ was like this: After His mother Mary had been betrothed to Joseph, before they came together, she was found pregnant by the Holy Spirit.
B040C001V019	40	1	19	Then Joseph her husband, being righteous and not wanting to make her a public example, purposed to put her away secretly.
B040C001V020	40	1	20	But while he was thinking about these things, behold, an angel of the Lord appeared to him in a dream, saying, "Joseph, son of David, do not fear to take unto [you] Mary your wife, for that which is begotten in her is of the Holy Spirit.
B040C001V021	40	1	21	And she shall bring forth a Son, and you shall call His name JESUS, for He shall save His people from their sins."
B040C001V022	40	1	22	Now all this came to pass that the thing spoken by the Lord through the prophet might be fulfilled, saying,
B040C001V023	40	1	23	"Behold, the virgin shall be with child, and shall bring forth a Son, and they shall call His name Immanuel,"which is translated, "God with us."
B040C001V024	40	1	24	Then Joseph, having been aroused from sleep, did as the angel of the Lord had ordered him and took to [him] his wife,
B040C001V025	40	1	25	but did not know her till she brought forth her firstborn Son. And he called His name JESUS.
B040C002V001	40	2	1	Now after Jesus was born in Bethlehem of Judea, in the days of Herod the king, behold, wise men from the East arrived in Jerusalem,
B040C002V002	40	2	2	saying, "Where is He who has been born King of the Jews? For we have seen His star in the East, and have come to worship Him."
B040C002V003	40	2	3	But when Herod the king heard this, he was troubled, and all Jerusalem with him.
B040C002V004	40	2	4	And having gathered together all the chief priests and scribes of the people, he inquired from them where the Christ would be born.
B040C002V005	40	2	5	So they said to him, "In Bethlehem of Judea, for thus it is written by the prophet:
B040C002V006	40	2	6	'But you, Bethlehem, in the land of Judah, are by no means least among the rulers of Judah; for out of you shall come forth a Ruler who will shepherd My people Israel.' "
B040C002V007	40	2	7	Then Herod, secretly having called the wise men, ascertained from them the time that the star appeared.
B040C002V008	40	2	8	And having sent them to Bethlehem, he said, "Go and carefully search for the young Child, and as soon as you find [Him], report back to me, so that I also may come and worship Him."
B040C002V009	40	2	9	When they heard the king, they departed; and behold, the star which they had seen in the East went before them, till it came and stood over where the young Child was.
B040C002V010	40	2	10	And when they saw the star, they rejoiced with exceedingly great joy.
B040C002V011	40	2	11	And having come into the house, they saw the young Child with Mary His mother, and falling down, they worshipped Him, and opening their treasures, they presented gifts to Him: gold, frankincense, and myrrh.
B040C002V012	40	2	12	And having been divinely instructed in a dream not to return to Herod, they withdrew into their own country by another way.
B040C002V013	40	2	13	Now when they had departed, behold, an angel of the Lord appeared to Joseph in a dream, saying, "Arise, and take along the young Child and His mother, flee to Egypt, and stay there until I tell you; for Herod is about to seek the young Child to destroy Him."
B040C002V014	40	2	14	When he arose, he took along the young Child and His mother by night and withdrew into Egypt,
B040C002V015	40	2	15	and was there until the death of Herod, so that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the Lord through the prophet, saying, "Out of Egypt I called My Son."
B040C002V016	40	2	16	Then Herod, seeing that he had been deceived by the wise men, was greatly enraged; and he sent and executed all the boys in Bethlehem and in all its districts, from two years old and under, according to the time which he had ascertained from the wise men.
B040C002V017	40	2	17	Then was fulfilled what was spoken by Jeremiah the prophet, saying:
B040C002V018	40	2	18	"A voice was heard in Ramah, lamentation and weeping, and great mourning, Rachel weeping for her children, refusing to be comforted, because they are no more."
B040C002V019	40	2	19	Now after Herod died, behold, an angel of the Lord appeared in a dream to Joseph in Egypt,
B040C002V020	40	2	20	saying, "Arise, and take with [you] the young Child and His mother, and go into the land of Israel, for those who were seeking the life of the young Child have died."
B040C002V021	40	2	21	Then he rose and took along the young Child and His mother, and came into the land of Israel.
B040C002V022	40	2	22	But hearing that Archelaus was reigning over Judea instead of his father Herod, he was afraid to go there. And being divinely instructed in a dream, he withdrew into the regions of Galilee.
B040C002V023	40	2	23	And when he arrived, he settled down in a city called Nazareth, so that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the prophets, "He would be called a Nazarene."
B040C003V001	40	3	1	In those days John the Baptist arrived preaching in the wilderness of Judea,
B040C003V002	40	3	2	and saying, "Repent, for the kingdom of heaven is at hand!"
B040C003V003	40	3	3	For this is he who was spoken of by the prophet Isaiah, saying: "A voice of one crying in the wilderness: 'Prepare the way of the LORD; make His paths straight.' "
B040C003V004	40	3	4	And John himself had his clothing [made] from camel's hair, with a leather belt around his waist; and his food was locusts and wild honey.
B040C003V005	40	3	5	Then Jerusalem, and all Judea, and all the region around the Jordan were going out to him
B040C003V006	40	3	6	and they were being baptized by him in the Jordan, confessing their sins.
B040C003V007	40	3	7	But seeing many of the Pharisees and Sadducees coming to his baptism, he said to them, "Brood of vipers! Who warned you to flee from the coming wrath?
B040C003V008	40	3	8	Therefore produce fruits worthy of repentance,
B040C003V009	40	3	9	and do not think to say among yourselves, 'We have Abraham as our father.' For I say to you that God is able to raise up children to Abraham out of these stones.
B040C003V010	40	3	10	But even now, the ax is laid to the root of the trees. Therefore every tree not producing good fruit is cut down and thrown into the fire.
B040C003V011	40	3	11	I indeed baptize you with water unto repentance, but He who is coming after me is mightier than I, whose sandals I am not worthy to carry. He will baptize you with [the] Holy Spirit,
B040C003V012	40	3	12	whose winnowing shovel is in His hand, and He will thoroughly purge His threshing floor, and He will gather His wheat into the barn; but the chaff He will burn up with unquenchable fire."
B040C003V013	40	3	13	Then Jesus arrived from Galilee to John at the Jordan, to be baptized by him.
B040C003V014	40	3	14	But John [tried to ]prevent Him, saying, "I have need to be baptized by You, and You are coming to me?"
B040C003V015	40	3	15	But Jesus answered and said to him, "Permit it now, for thus it is fitting for us to fulfill all righteousness."Then he permitted Him.
B040C003V016	40	3	16	And having been baptized, Jesus came up immediately from the water; and behold, the heavens were opened to Him, and He saw the Spirit of God descending like a dove and coming upon Him.
B040C003V017	40	3	17	And behold, a voice came out of the heavens, saying, "This is My beloved Son, in whom I have found delight."
B040C004V001	40	4	1	Then Jesus was led up into the wilderness by the Spirit, to be tempted by the devil.
B040C004V002	40	4	2	And having fasted forty days and forty nights, afterward He was hungry.
B040C004V003	40	4	3	And approaching Him, the tempter said, "If You are the Son of God, speak so that these stones may become bread."
B040C004V004	40	4	4	But He answered and said, "It is written, 'Man shall not live by bread alone, but by every word that proceeds out of the mouth of God.' "
B040C004V005	40	4	5	Then the devil took Him up into the holy city, and set Him on the pinnacle of the temple,
B040C004V006	40	4	6	and said to Him, "If You are the Son of God, throw Yourself down. For it is written: 'He shall give His angels orders concerning you,' and, 'In their hands they will lift you up, lest you dash your foot against a stone.' "
B040C004V007	40	4	7	Jesus said to him, "Again, it is written, 'You shall not tempt the LORD your God.' "
B040C004V008	40	4	8	Again, the devil took Him up on a very high mountain, and showed Him all the kingdoms of the world, and their glory.
B040C004V009	40	4	9	And he said to Him, "All these things will I give You, if You will fall down and worship me."
B040C004V010	40	4	10	Then Jesus said to him, "Get behind Me, Satan! For it is written, 'You shall worship the LORD your God, and Him alone you shall serve.' "
B040C004V011	40	4	11	Then the devil left Him, and behold, angels came and ministered to Him.
B040C004V012	40	4	12	Now when Jesus heard that John had been imprisoned, He departed into Galilee.
B040C004V013	40	4	13	And leaving Nazareth behind, He came and settled down in Capernaum, which is by the sea, in the regions of Zebulun and Naphtali,
B040C004V014	40	4	14	so that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by Isaiah the prophet, saying:
B040C004V015	40	4	15	"The land of Zebulun and the land of Naphtali, by the way of the sea, beyond the Jordan, Galilee of the Gentiles,
B040C004V016	40	4	16	the people sitting in darkness have seen a great light, and to those who sat in the land and the shadow of death, light sprang up on them."
B040C004V017	40	4	17	From that time Jesus began to preach and to say, "Repent, for the kingdom of heaven is at hand."
B040C004V018	40	4	18	Now as He was walking alongside the Sea of Galilee, He saw two brothers, Simon called Peter, and Andrew his brother, casting a net into the sea; for they were fishermen.
B040C004V019	40	4	19	Then He said to them, "Come after Me, and I will make you fishers of men."
B040C004V020	40	4	20	They immediately left their nets and followed Him.
B040C004V021	40	4	21	And having gone forth from there, He saw two other brothers, James the [son] of Zebedee, and John his brother, in the boat with Zebedee their father, mending their nets. And He called them.
B040C004V022	40	4	22	And immediately they left the boat and their father, and followed Him.
B040C004V023	40	4	23	And Jesus went about all of Galilee, teaching in their synagogues, preaching the gospel of the kingdom, and healing every disease and every illness among the people.
B040C004V024	40	4	24	And the report of Him went throughout all Syria; and they brought to Him all those who were ill, and [who were ]suffering with various diseases and torments, and those who were demon-possessed, epileptics, and paralytics; and He healed them.
B040C004V025	40	4	25	And large crowds followed Him from Galilee and from Decapolis, and Jerusalem, and Judea, and beyond the Jordan.
B040C005V001	40	5	1	And seeing the crowds, He went up into the mountain, and after He had sat down, His disciples approached Him.
B040C005V002	40	5	2	And opening His mouth, He began to teach them, saying:
B040C005V003	40	5	3	"Blessed [are] the poor in spirit, for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V004	40	5	4	Blessed [are] those who mourn, for they will be comforted.
B040C005V005	40	5	5	Blessed [are] the meek, for they shall inherit the earth.
B040C005V006	40	5	6	Blessed [are] those who hunger and thirst after righteousness, for they shall be filled.
B040C005V007	40	5	7	Blessed [are] the merciful, for they shall obtain mercy.
B040C005V008	40	5	8	Blessed [are] the pure in heart, for they shall see God.
B040C005V009	40	5	9	Blessed [are] the peacemakers, for they shall be called sons of God.
B040C005V010	40	5	10	Blessed [are] those who have been persecuted for righteousness' sake, for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V011	40	5	11	"Blessed are you whenever they revile you, and they persecute you, and they say all kinds of evil against you falsely for My sake.
B040C005V012	40	5	12	Rejoice and be exceedingly glad, for great is your reward in heaven, for so they persecuted the prophets who were before you.
B040C005V013	40	5	13	"You are the salt of the earth; but if the salt becomes tasteless, with what shall it be salted? It is then good for nothing but to be thrown out and to be trampled underfoot by men.
B040C005V014	40	5	14	You are the light of the world. A city that is set on a hill cannot be hidden.
B040C005V015	40	5	15	Nor do they light a lamp and put it under a basket, but on a lampstand, and it shines on everything in the house.
B040C005V016	40	5	16	Thus let your light shine before men, so that they may see your good works, and they may glorify your Father who is in heaven.
B040C005V017	40	5	17	"Do not think that I came to abolish the Law or the Prophets. I did not come to abolish, but to fulfill.
B040C005V018	40	5	18	For assuredly I say to you, until heaven and earth may pass away, one iota or one tittle shall by no means pass away from the law until all things are fulfilled.
B040C005V019	40	5	19	Whoever therefore shall break one of the least of these commandments, and shall teach men thus, will be called least in the kingdom of heaven; but whoever does [them] and teaches [them], he shall be called great in the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V020	40	5	20	For I say to you, that unless your righteousness exceeds the righteousness of the scribes and Pharisees, you shall by no means enter the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V021	40	5	21	"You have heard that it was said to the ancients, 'You shall not kill,' and whoever kills will be liable to the judgment.
B040C005V022	40	5	22	But I say to you that whoever gets angry with his brother without cause will be liable to the judgment. And whoever says to his brother, 'Empty-head!' will be liable to the council. But whoever says, ' fool!' will be liable to the fiery hell.
B040C005V023	40	5	23	Therefore if you offer your gift on the altar, and there you remember that your brother has something against you,
B040C005V024	40	5	24	leave your gift there before the altar, and go, first be reconciled with your brother, and then come and offer your gift.
B040C005V025	40	5	25	Make friends with your adversary quickly, while you are on the road with him, lest your adversary hand you over to the judge, and the judge hand you over to the officer, and you be cast into prison.
B040C005V026	40	5	26	Assuredly I say to you, you will by no means get out of there till you have paid the last penny.
B040C005V027	40	5	27	"You have heard that it was said, 'You shall not commit adultery.'
B040C005V028	40	5	28	But I say to you, that whoever looks at a woman in order to lust after her has already committed adultery [with] her in his heart.
B040C005V029	40	5	29	If your right eye causes you to stumble, pluck it out and cast it from you; for it is better for you that one of your members be lost, than for your whole body to be cast into hell.
B040C005V030	40	5	30	And if your right hand causes you to stumble, cut it off and cast it from you; for it is better for you that one of your members be lost, than for your whole body to be cast into hell.
B040C005V031	40	5	31	"Furthermore it has been said, 'Whoever divorces his wife, let him give her a divorce certificate.'
B040C005V032	40	5	32	"But I say to you that whoever divorces his wife, except for a matter of sexual immorality, makes her commit adultery; and whoever marries a divorcee commits adultery.
B040C005V033	40	5	33	"Again you have heard that it was said to the ancients, 'You shall not swear falsely, but you shall pay your oaths to the Lord.'
B040C005V034	40	5	34	"But I say to you, do not swear at all: neither by heaven, for it is God's throne;
B040C005V035	40	5	35	nor by the earth, for it is His footstool; nor by Jerusalem, for it is the city of the great King.
B040C005V036	40	5	36	Nor shall you swear by your head, because you are not able to make one hair white or black.
B040C005V037	40	5	37	But let your word be 'Yes', 'yes,'; [or ]'No,' 'no.' For whatever is more than these is from the evil [one].
B040C005V038	40	5	38	"You have heard that it was said, 'An eye for an eye and a tooth for a tooth.'
B040C005V039	40	5	39	But I say to you not to resist an evil person. But whoever shall slap you on your right cheek, turn to him the other also.
B040C005V040	40	5	40	And to the [one] desiring to sue you and to take your tunic, let him have your cloak also.
B040C005V041	40	5	41	And whoever compels you to go one mile, go with him two.
B040C005V042	40	5	42	Give to the [one] asking you, and to the [one] desiring to borrow from you, do not turn away.
B040C005V043	40	5	43	"You have heard that it was said, 'You shall love your neighbor, and you shall hate your enemy.'
B040C005V044	40	5	44	But I say to you, love your enemies, bless those who curse you, do good to those who hate you, and pray for those who mistreat you and persecute you,
B040C005V045	40	5	45	so that you may prove to be sons of your Father in heaven; because He makes His sun rise on the evil and on the good, and He sends rain on the just and on the unjust.
B040C005V046	40	5	46	For if you love those who love you, what reward have you? Do not even the tax collectors do the same?
B040C005V047	40	5	47	And if you greet your friends only, what more are you doing [than others]? Do not even the tax collectors do so?
B040C005V048	40	5	48	You therefore be perfect, just as your Father in heaven is perfect.
B040C006V001	40	6	1	"Take care not to be doing your charitable giving before men, so as to be seen by them. Otherwise, you have not a reward from your Father in heaven.
B040C006V002	40	6	2	Whenever therefore you do charitable giving, do not sound a trumpet before you as the hypocrites do in the synagogues and in the streets, so that they may be praised by men. Assuredly I say to you, they receive their reward in full.
B040C006V003	40	6	3	But when you do charitable giving, do not let your left hand know what your right hand is doing,
B040C006V004	40	6	4	so that your charitable giving may be in secret; and your Father, who sees in secret, will Himself reward you openly.
B040C006V005	40	6	5	"And whenever you pray, you shall not be like the hypocrites, because they love to pray standing in the synagogues, and on the streetcorners, so that they may be seen by men. Assuredly I say to you, that they receive their reward in full.
B040C006V006	40	6	6	But you, whenever you pray, enter into your room, and when you have shut your door, pray to your Father who is in secret; and your Father, who sees in secret, will reward you openly.
B040C006V007	40	6	7	But when you pray, do not babble like the heathen, for they think that they will be heard for their many words.
B040C006V008	40	6	8	Therefore do not be like them. For your Father knows what things[ ]you have need of before you ask Him.
B040C006V009	40	6	9	Therefore pray in this manner: Our Father in heaven, hallowed be Your name.
B040C006V010	40	6	10	Your kingdom come, Your will be done, on earth as [it is ]in heaven.
B040C006V011	40	6	11	Give us this day our daily bread.
B040C006V012	40	6	12	And forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors.
B040C006V013	40	6	13	And lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from the evil [one]. For Yours is the kingdom and the power and the glory forever. Amen.
B040C006V014	40	6	14	"For if you forgive men their trespasses, your heavenly Father will also forgive you.
B040C006V015	40	6	15	But if you do not forgive men their trespasses, neither will your Father forgive your trespasses.
B040C006V016	40	6	16	"Moreover, when you fast, do not become gloomy, like the hypocrites, for they disfigure their faces that they may appear to men [to be] fasting. Assuredly I say to you, that they receive their reward in full.
B040C006V017	40	6	17	But you, when you fast, anoint your head and wash your face,
B040C006V018	40	6	18	so that you do not appear to men [to be] fasting, but to your Father in secret; and your Father, who sees in secret, will reward you.
B040C006V019	40	6	19	"Do not lay up for yourselves treasures on the earth, where moth and rust corrupt, and where thieves dig through and steal;
B040C006V020	40	6	20	but lay up for yourselves treasures in heaven, where neither moth nor rust corrupts, and where thieves do not dig through and steal.
B040C006V021	40	6	21	For where your treasure is, there your heart will be also.
B040C006V022	40	6	22	"The lamp of the body is the eye. If therefore your eye is sound, your whole body will be full of light.
B040C006V023	40	6	23	But if your eye is evil, your whole body will be dark. If therefore the light that is in you is darkness, how great is that darkness!
B040C006V024	40	6	24	"No one is able to serve two masters; for either he will hate the one, and he will love the other, or else he will be devoted to the one, and he will despise the other. You cannot serve God and money.
B040C006V025	40	6	25	"Because of this I say to you, do not worry [about ]your life-what you shall eat, or what you shall drink-nor [about] your body, what you shall put on. Is not life more than food and the body [more than] clothing?
B040C006V026	40	6	26	Look at the birds of the air, for they neither sow nor reap, nor do they gather into barns; yet your heavenly Father feeds them. Are you not worth more than they?
B040C006V027	40	6	27	Which of you by worrying is able to add one cubit to his stature?
B040C006V028	40	6	28	So why do you worry about clothes? Consider the lilies of the field, how they grow; they neither labor, nor spin;
B040C006V029	40	6	29	and yet I say to you, that not even Solomon in all his glory was arrayed like one of these.
B040C006V030	40	6	30	But if God thus clothes the grass of the field, which exists today, and tomorrow is cast into the oven, [will He] not much more [clothe] you, [O you] of little faith?
B040C006V031	40	6	31	Therefore do not worry, saying, 'What shall we eat?' or 'What shall we drink?' or 'What shall we put on?'
B040C006V032	40	6	32	"For after all these things the Gentiles seek. For your heavenly Father knows that you need all these things.
B040C006V033	40	6	33	But seek first the kingdom of God and His righteousness, and all these things shall be added to you.
B040C006V034	40	6	34	Therefore do not worry about tomorrow, for tomorrow will worry about its own affairs. Each day has enough trouble of its own.
B040C007V001	40	7	1	"Judge not, lest you be judged.
B040C007V002	40	7	2	For with what judgment you judge, you will be judged; and with what measure you measure, it will be measured [back] to you.
B040C007V003	40	7	3	And why do you look at the speck in your brother's eye, but do not notice the plank in your own eye?
B040C007V004	40	7	4	Or how will you say to your brother, 'Permit me to remove the speck from your eye'; and look, [there is] a plank in your own eye?
B040C007V005	40	7	5	Hypocrite! First remove the plank out of your own eye, and then you will see clearly to remove the speck out of your brother's eye.
B040C007V006	40	7	6	Do not give what is holy to the dogs; nor cast your pearls before swine, lest they trample them under their feet, and turn and tear you in pieces.
B040C007V007	40	7	7	"Ask, and it shall be given to you; seek, and you shall find; knock, and it shall be opened to you.
B040C007V008	40	7	8	For everyone that asks receives, and he that seeks finds, and to him that knocks, it shall be opened.
B040C007V009	40	7	9	Or what man is there among you who, if his son should ask for bread, will give to him a stone?
B040C007V010	40	7	10	And if he should ask for a fish, he will give to him a serpent?
B040C007V011	40	7	11	If you then, being evil, know how to give good gifts to your children, by how much more will your Father who is in heaven give good things to those who ask Him!
B040C007V012	40	7	12	Therefore, whatever you want men to do to you, thus also you do to them, for this is the Law and the Prophets.
B040C007V013	40	7	13	"Enter in through the narrow gate; because wide is the gate, and broad is the way which leads to destruction, and many are those who enter in through it.
B040C007V014	40	7	14	How narrow the gate, and confined the way which leads to life, and there are few who find it!
B040C007V015	40	7	15	"But beware of false prophets, who come to you in sheep's clothing, but inwardly they are ravenous wolves.
B040C007V016	40	7	16	You will know them by their fruits. Do men gather grape clusters from thorns, or figs from thistles?
B040C007V017	40	7	17	Thus every good tree produces good fruit, but a rotten tree produces evil fruit.
B040C007V018	40	7	18	A good tree cannot produce evil fruit, nor can a rotten tree produce good fruit.
B040C007V019	40	7	19	Every tree not producing good fruit is cut down and cast into the fire.
B040C007V020	40	7	20	Consequently, by their fruits you shall know them.
B040C007V021	40	7	21	"Not everyone who says to Me, 'Lord, Lord,' will enter the kingdom of heaven, but he who does the will of My Father who is in heaven.
B040C007V022	40	7	22	Many will say to Me in that day, 'Lord, Lord, did we not prophesy in Your name, and in Your name we cast out demons, and in Your name we did many mighty works?'
B040C007V023	40	7	23	"And then I will confess to them, 'I never knew you! Depart from Me, you who work iniquity!'
B040C007V024	40	7	24	"Therefore, everyone who hears these words of Mine and does them, I will compare him to a wise man who built his house upon the rock:
B040C007V025	40	7	25	and the rain came down, and the floods came, and the winds blew and fell against that house; and it did not fall, for it had been founded upon the rock.
B040C007V026	40	7	26	And everyone who hears these words of Mine and does not do them, will be compared to a foolish man who built his house on the sand:
B040C007V027	40	7	27	and the rain came down, and the floods came, and the winds blew and beat on that house; and it fell. And its fall was great."
B040C007V028	40	7	28	And so it was, when Jesus finished these words, the crowds were astonished at His teaching,
B040C007V029	40	7	29	for He taught them as one having authority, and not like the scribes.
B040C008V001	40	8	1	When He had come down from the mountain, great crowds followed Him.
B040C008V002	40	8	2	And behold, a leper came and worshipped Him, saying, "Lord, if You are willing, You can make me clean."
B040C008V003	40	8	3	And reaching out His hand, Jesus touched him, saying, "I am willing; be cleansed."Immediately his leprosy was cleansed.
B040C008V004	40	8	4	And Jesus said to him, "See that you tell no one; but go, show yourself to the priest, and offer the gift which Moses commanded, as a testimony to them."
B040C008V005	40	8	5	Now when He had entered Capernaum, a centurion approached Him, begging Him,
B040C008V006	40	8	6	and saying, "Lord, my servant has been laid up in the house a paralytic, being tormented terribly."
B040C008V007	40	8	7	And Jesus said to him, "I will come and heal him."
B040C008V008	40	8	8	The centurion answered and said, "Lord, I am not worthy that You should come under my roof. But just say the word and my servant will be healed.
B040C008V009	40	8	9	For I also am a man under authority, having soldiers under me. And I say to this [one], 'Go,' and he goes; and to another, 'Come,' and he comes; and to my servant, 'Do this,' and he does it."
B040C008V010	40	8	10	When Jesus heard it, He marveled, and said to those who were following, "Assuredly, I say to you, I have not found such great faith, not even in Israel!
B040C008V011	40	8	11	And I say to you that many shall come from east and west, and recline [to eat] with Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob in the kingdom of heaven;
B040C008V012	40	8	12	but the sons of the kingdom will be cast out into outer darkness. There will be weeping and gnashing of teeth."
B040C008V013	40	8	13	Then Jesus said to the centurion, "Go; and as you believed, may it be unto you."And his servant was healed that same hour.
B040C008V014	40	8	14	Now when Jesus had come into Peter's house, He saw his wife's mother having been laid up, and burning with fever.
B040C008V015	40	8	15	And He touched her hand, and the fever left her; and she got up, and began to serve Him.
B040C008V016	40	8	16	When evening had come, they brought to Him many who were demon-possessed. And He cast out the spirits with a word, and He healed all that were ill,
B040C008V017	40	8	17	so that it might be fulfilled which was spoken through Isaiah the prophet, saying: "He Himself took our infirmities, and bore our diseases."
B040C008V018	40	8	18	And when Jesus saw great crowds around Him, He gave orders to depart to the other side.
B040C008V019	40	8	19	Then a certain scribe approached, and said to Him, "Teacher, I will follow You wherever You go."
B040C008V020	40	8	20	And Jesus said to him, "Foxes have dens, and birds of the air have nests, but the Son of Man has nowhere to lay His head."
B040C008V021	40	8	21	Then another of His disciples said to Him, "Lord, permit me first to go and bury my father."
B040C008V022	40	8	22	But Jesus said to him, "Follow Me, and leave the dead to bury their own dead."
B040C008V023	40	8	23	Now when He got into a boat, His disciples followed Him.
B040C008V024	40	8	24	And behold, a great tempest arose on the sea, so that the boat was covered by waves; but He was sleeping.
B040C008V025	40	8	25	Then the disciples came and awoke Him, saying, "Lord, save us! We are perishing!"
B040C008V026	40	8	26	But He said to them, "Why are you fearful, O [you] of little faith?"Then having risen, He rebuked the winds and the sea, and there was a great calm.
B040C008V027	40	8	27	So the men marveled, saying, "What kind [of Man] is this, that even the winds and the sea obey Him?"
B040C008V028	40	8	28	And when He came to the other side, to the region of the Gergesenes, [there] met Him two demon-possessed [men], coming out of the tombs; exceedingly violent, so that no one was able to pass by that way.
B040C008V029	40	8	29	And suddenly they cried out, saying, "What have we to do with You, Jesus, Son of God? Have You come here to torment us before the time?"
B040C008V030	40	8	30	Now there was far off from them a herd of many swine feeding.
B040C008V031	40	8	31	So the demons implored Him, saying, "If You cast us out, permit us to go off into the herd of swine."
B040C008V032	40	8	32	And He said to them, "Go."So they came out, and went off into the herd of swine. And behold, the whole herd of swine rushed violently down the steep bank into the sea, and died in the waters.
B040C008V033	40	8	33	Then those who tended them fled; and going off into the city, they reported everything, including what had happened to the demon-possessed [men].
B040C008V034	40	8	34	And behold, the whole city came out to meet Jesus. And seeing Him, they implored Him that He might go away from their region.
B040C009V001	40	9	1	And getting into the boat, He crossed over and went into His own city.
B040C009V002	40	9	2	And behold, they were carrying a paralytic to Him lying on a bed. And when Jesus saw their faith, He said to the paralytic, "Have courage, child; your sins are forgiven you."
B040C009V003	40	9	3	And at once some of the scribes said among themselves, "This Man blasphemes!"
B040C009V004	40	9	4	But Jesus, perceiving their thoughts, said, "Why do you think evil in your hearts?
B040C009V005	40	9	5	For which is easier, to say, 'Your sins are forgiven,' or to say, 'Arise and walk'?
B040C009V006	40	9	6	But that you may know that the Son of Man has authority on the earth to forgive sins"-then He said to the paralytic, "Arise, take up your bed, and go to your house."
B040C009V007	40	9	7	And having arisen, he went off to his house.
B040C009V008	40	9	8	Now when the crowds saw, they marveled and glorified God, who had given such authority to men.
B040C009V009	40	9	9	And as Jesus passed on from there, He saw a man named Matthew sitting at the tax office. And He said to him, "Follow Me."And arising, he followed Him.
B040C009V010	40	9	10	Now it came to pass, as He reclined [to eat] in the house, that behold, many tax collectors and sinners, having come, were reclining [to eat] with Jesus and His disciples.
B040C009V011	40	9	11	And when the Pharisees saw this, they said to His disciples, "Why does your Teacher eat with tax collectors and sinners?"
B040C009V012	40	9	12	When Jesus heard that, He said to them, "Those who are healthy have no need of a physician, but those who are ill.
B040C009V013	40	9	13	But go and learn what this means: 'I desire mercy and not sacrifice.' For I did not come to call [the ]righteous, but sinners, to repentance."
B040C009V014	40	9	14	Then the disciples of John approached Him, saying, "Why do we and the Pharisees fast often, but Your disciples do not fast?"
B040C009V015	40	9	15	And Jesus said to them, "Can the groomsmen mourn as long as the bridegroom is with them? But the days will come when the bridegroom will be taken away from them, and then they will fast.
B040C009V016	40	9	16	No one puts on a patch of a piece of unshrunk cloth on an old garment; for it takes away its completeness from the garment, and the tear is made worse.
B040C009V017	40	9	17	Nor do they put new wine into old wineskins, or else the wineskins burst, and the wine spills out, and the wineskins will be ruined. But they put new wine into new wineskins, and both are preserved."
B040C009V018	40	9	18	As He spoke these things to them, behold, a certain leader came and worshipped Him, saying, "My daughter has just died, but come and lay Your hand on her, and she shall live."
B040C009V019	40	9	19	So Jesus arose and followed him, likewise His disciples.
B040C009V020	40	9	20	And behold, a woman hemorrhaging for twelve years, approaching from behind, touched the hem of His garment.
B040C009V021	40	9	21	For she said to herself, "If only I may touch His garment, I will be healed."
B040C009V022	40	9	22	But Jesus, turning around and seeing her, said, "Take courage, daughter; your faith has healed you."And the woman was healed from that hour.
B040C009V023	40	9	23	And when Jesus came into the house of the leader, and saw the flute players and the crowd making a commotion,
B040C009V024	40	9	24	He said to them, "Make room, for the girl has not died, but she is sleeping."And they were ridiculing Him.
B040C009V025	40	9	25	But when the crowd had been put out, He went in and grasped her hand, and the little girl arose.
B040C009V026	40	9	26	And the report of this went out into that whole land.
B040C009V027	40	9	27	And as Jesus passed by from there, two blind [men] followed Him, crying out and saying, "Son of David, have pity on us!"
B040C009V028	40	9	28	And when He came into the house, the blind [men] approached Him, and Jesus said to them, "Do you believe that I am able to do this?"They said to Him, "Yes, Lord."
B040C009V029	40	9	29	Then He touched their eyes, saying, "According to your faith, let it be unto you."
B040C009V030	40	9	30	And their eyes were opened. And Jesus sternly warned them, saying, "See [that you] let no one know."
B040C009V031	40	9	31	But they, having gone out, spread the news about Him in that whole land.
B040C009V032	40	9	32	And as they were going out, behold, they brought to Him a mute man, being demon-possessed.
B040C009V033	40	9	33	And when the demon was cast out, the mute spoke. And the crowds marveled, saying, "It was never seen like this in Israel!"
B040C009V034	40	9	34	But the Pharisees said, "By the ruler of the demons He casts out demons."
B040C009V035	40	9	35	And Jesus was going about all the cities and villages, teaching in their synagogues, and preaching the gospel of the kingdom, and healing every illness and every disease among the people.
B040C009V036	40	9	36	But seeing the crowds, He was moved with compassion for them, because they were harassed and prostrated, like sheep having no shepherd.
B040C009V037	40	9	37	Then He said to His disciples, "Indeed the harvest is plentiful, but the workers are few.
B040C009V038	40	9	38	Therefore pray to the Lord of the harvest, that He may send forth workers into His harvest."
B040C010V001	40	10	1	And summoning His twelve disciples, He gave them authority over unclean spirits, to cast them out, and to heal every disease and every illness.
B040C010V002	40	10	2	Now the names of the twelve apostles are these: first, Simon, who was called Peter, and Andrew his brother; James the [son] of Zebedee, and John his brother;
B040C010V003	40	10	3	Philip and Bartholomew; Thomas and Matthew the tax collector; James the [son] of Alphaeus, and Lebbaeus, who was surnamed Thaddaeus;
B040C010V004	40	10	4	Simon the Canaanite, and Judas Iscariot, who also betrayed Him.
B040C010V005	40	10	5	These twelve Jesus sent forth, commanding them, saying, "Do not go in the way of the Gentiles, and do not enter [any] city of the Samaritans.
B040C010V006	40	10	6	But go rather to the lost sheep of the house of Israel.
B040C010V007	40	10	7	And as you go, preach, saying, 'The kingdom of heaven is at hand.'
B040C010V008	40	10	8	"Heal the sick, cleanse the lepers, cast out demons. Freely you have received, freely give.
B040C010V009	40	10	9	Do not acquire gold nor silver nor copper in your money belts,
B040C010V010	40	10	10	not a knapsack for the road, nor two tunics, nor sandals, nor staffs; for a worker is worthy of his food.
B040C010V011	40	10	11	And whatever city or village you enter, inquire who in it is worthy, and stay there until you go out.
B040C010V012	40	10	12	And as you enter into a household, greet it.
B040C010V013	40	10	13	And if indeed the house should be worthy, let your peace come upon it. But if it should not be worthy, let your peace return to you.
B040C010V014	40	10	14	And whoever will not receive you nor hear your words, when you depart from that house or city, shake off the dust from your feet.
B040C010V015	40	10	15	Assuredly I say to you, it will be more tolerable for the land of Sodom and Gomorrah in the day of judgment than for that city!
B040C010V016	40	10	16	"Behold, I am sending you forth like sheep in the midst of wolves. Therefore be as wise as serpents and innocent as doves.
B040C010V017	40	10	17	But beware of men, for they will hand you over to councils and they will flog you in their synagogues.
B040C010V018	40	10	18	And you will be brought before governors and kings for My sake, as a testimony to them and to the nations.
B040C010V019	40	10	19	But whenever they hand you over, do not worry how or what you should speak. For it will be given to you in that hour what you should speak;
B040C010V020	40	10	20	for you are not the [ones] speaking, but the Spirit of your Father who is speaking in you.
B040C010V021	40	10	21	Now brother will hand over brother to death, and a father his child; and children will rise up against parents, and put them to death.
B040C010V022	40	10	22	And you will be hated by all [people ]for My name's sake. But he who endures to the end shall be saved.
B040C010V023	40	10	23	But whenever they persecute you in this city, flee to another. For assuredly I say to you, by no means will you have gone through the cities of Israel before the Son of Man comes.
B040C010V024	40	10	24	A disciple is not above his teacher, nor a servant above his master.
B040C010V025	40	10	25	It is enough for a disciple that he become like his teacher, and the servant like his master. If they have called the master of the house Beelzebub, how much more will they call his household members!
B040C010V026	40	10	26	Therefore do not fear them. For nothing is concealed that shall not be unveiled, and secret that shall not be made known.
B040C010V027	40	10	27	"What I say to you in the dark, say in the light; and what you hear in the ear, proclaim on the housetops.
B040C010V028	40	10	28	And do not fear those who kill the body but cannot kill the soul. But rather fear Him who is able to destroy both the soul and the body in hell.
B040C010V029	40	10	29	Are not two sparrows sold for a copper coin? And not one of them shall fall on the ground apart from the [will] of your Father.
B040C010V030	40	10	30	But even the hairs of your head are all numbered.
B040C010V031	40	10	31	Therefore do not fear; you are worth more than many sparrows.
B040C010V032	40	10	32	"Therefore whoever who will confess Me before men, I also will confess Him before My Father who is in heaven.
B040C010V033	40	10	33	But whoever denies Me before men, I also will deny him before My Father who is in heaven.
B040C010V034	40	10	34	"Do not suppose that I came to bring peace on earth. I did not come to bring peace, but a sword.
B040C010V035	40	10	35	For I have come to 'turn a man against his father, and a daughter against her mother, and a daughter-in-law against her mother-in-law';
B040C010V036	40	10	36	and 'a man's enemies [will be] his own household members.'
B040C010V037	40	10	37	He who loves father or mother more than Me is not worthy of Me. And he who loves son or daughter more than Me is not worthy of Me.
B040C010V038	40	10	38	And he who does not take his cross and follow after Me is not worthy of Me.
B040C010V039	40	10	39	He who finds his life will lose it, and he who loses his life for My sake will find it.
B040C010V040	40	10	40	"He that receives you receives Me, and he that receives Me receives Him who sent Me.
B040C010V041	40	10	41	He that receives a prophet in the name of a prophet shall receive a prophet's reward. And he that receives a righteous [man] in the name of a righteous [man] shall receive a righteous [man's] reward.
B040C010V042	40	10	42	And whoever gives one of these little [ones] only a cup of cold water in the name of a disciple, assuredly I say to you, he shall by no means lose his reward."
B040C011V001	40	11	1	Now it came to pass, when Jesus finished directing His twelve disciples, that He moved on from there to teach and to preach in their cities.
B040C011V002	40	11	2	And when John had heard in prison about the works of the Messiah, having sent two of his disciples,
B040C011V003	40	11	3	he said to Him, "Are You the Coming One, or do we look for a different [one]?"
B040C011V004	40	11	4	Jesus answered and said to them, "Go and report to John the things which you hear and see:
B040C011V005	40	11	5	The blind receive sight, and the lame[ ]walk; the lepers are cleansed, and the deaf[ ]hear; the dead[ ]are raised up, and the poor have the gospel preached to them.
B040C011V006	40	11	6	And blessed is the [one] who is not offended because of Me."
B040C011V007	40	11	7	Now as these men were going, Jesus began to say to the crowds concerning John: "What did you go out into the wilderness to see? A reed shaken by the wind?
B040C011V008	40	11	8	But what did you go out to see? A man clothed in soft garments? Indeed, those who wear soft garments are in kings' houses.
B040C011V009	40	11	9	But what did you go out to see? A prophet? Yes, I say to you, and far more [than] a prophet.
B040C011V010	40	11	10	For this is he about whom it is written: 'Behold, I send My messenger before Your face, who will prepare Your way before You.'
B040C011V011	40	11	11	"Assuredly I say to you, among [those] born of women there has not risen one greater than John the Baptist; but he that is least in the kingdom of heaven is greater than he.
B040C011V012	40	11	12	And from the days of John the Baptist until now the kingdom of heaven suffers violence, and violent men seize it.
B040C011V013	40	11	13	For all the prophets and the law prophesied until John.
B040C011V014	40	11	14	And if you are willing to receive it, he is Elijah, the [one] who is about to come.
B040C011V015	40	11	15	He who has ears to hear, let him hear!
B040C011V016	40	11	16	But to what shall I compare this generation? It is similar to children who sit in the marketplaces and call to their playmates,
B040C011V017	40	11	17	and say, 'We played the flute for you, and you did not dance; We mourned to you, and you did not lament.'
B040C011V018	40	11	18	"For John came neither eating nor drinking, and they say, 'He has a demon.'
B040C011V019	40	11	19	"The Son of Man came eating and drinking, and they say, 'Look, a glutton and a drunkard, a friend of tax collectors and sinners!' And so wisdom is justified by her children."
B040C011V020	40	11	20	Then He began to reproach the cities in which His very many miracles had been done, because they did not repent:
B040C011V021	40	11	21	"Woe to you, Chorazin! Woe to you, Bethsaida! Because if the miracles which were done in you had been done in Tyre and Sidon, they would have repented long ago in sackcloth and ashes.
B040C011V022	40	11	22	Nevertheless I say to you, it will be more tolerable for Tyre and Sidon in the day of judgment than for you.
B040C011V023	40	11	23	And you, Capernaum, the [one] having been exalted to heaven, you will be brought down to Hades; because if the miracles which were done in you had been done in Sodom, it would have remained to this day.
B040C011V024	40	11	24	But I say to you that it will be more tolerable for the land of Sodom in the day of judgment than for you."
B040C011V025	40	11	25	At that time Jesus answered and said, "I praise You, Father, Lord of heaven and earth, that You have hidden these things from the wise and prudent, and have revealed them to babes.
B040C011V026	40	11	26	Yes, Father, for so it seemed good in Your sight.
B040C011V027	40	11	27	All things have been delivered to Me by My Father, and no one fully knows the Son except the Father, nor does anyone fully know the Father except the Son, and [the one] to whom the Son wills to reveal [Him].
B040C011V028	40	11	28	Come to Me, all you who labor and are burdened, and I will give you rest.
B040C011V029	40	11	29	Take My yoke upon you and learn from Me, for I am gentle and lowly in heart, and you will find rest for your souls.
B040C011V030	40	11	30	For My yoke is easy and My burden is light."
B040C012V001	40	12	1	At that time Jesus went through the grainfields on the Sabbath. And His disciples became hungry, and they began to pluck heads of grain and to eat.
B040C012V002	40	12	2	But when the Pharisees saw it, they said to Him, "Look, Your disciples are doing what is not lawful to do on the Sabbath!"
B040C012V003	40	12	3	But He said to them, "Have you not read what David did when he became hungry, he and those who were with him:
B040C012V004	40	12	4	how they entered the house of God, and ate the showbread which was not lawful for him to eat, nor for those who were with him, except only for the priests?
B040C012V005	40	12	5	Or have you not read in the law that on the Sabbath the priests in the temple profane the Sabbath, and are guiltless?
B040C012V006	40	12	6	Yet I say to you that [One] greater[ than] the temple is here.
B040C012V007	40	12	7	But if you had known what this means, 'I desire mercy and not sacrifice,' you would not have condemned the guiltless.
B040C012V008	40	12	8	For the Son of Man is Lord of the Sabbath."
B040C012V009	40	12	9	And having departed from there, He went into their synagogue.
B040C012V010	40	12	10	And behold, there was a man who had a withered hand. And they asked Him, saying, "Is it lawful to heal on the Sabbath?"-that they might accuse Him.
B040C012V011	40	12	11	Then He said to them, "What man is there among you who shall have one sheep, and if it should fall into a ditch on the Sabbath, will not lay hold of it and lift it out?
B040C012V012	40	12	12	How much more valuable then is a man than a sheep! So then it is lawful to do good on the Sabbath."
B040C012V013	40	12	13	Then He said to the man, "Stretch out your hand."And he stretched it out, and it was restored whole like the other.
B040C012V014	40	12	14	But the Pharisees went out and plotted against Him, how they might destroy Him.
B040C012V015	40	12	15	But when Jesus knew it, He withdrew from there. And great crowds followed Him, and He healed them all.
B040C012V016	40	12	16	And He warned them that they should not make Him known,
B040C012V017	40	12	17	so that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by Isaiah the prophet, saying,
B040C012V018	40	12	18	"Behold, My Servant whom I have chosen, My Beloved in whom My soul is well pleased! I will put My Spirit upon Him, and He will announce justice to the Gentiles.
B040C012V019	40	12	19	He will not quarrel nor cry out, nor will anyone hear His voice in the streets.
B040C012V020	40	12	20	A bruised reed He shall not break, and a smoldering wick He shall not quench, till He bring forth justice to victory;
B040C012V021	40	12	21	And in His name [the] nations shall hope."
B040C012V022	40	12	22	Then one was brought to Him who was demon-possessed, blind and mute; and He healed him, so that the blind and mute [man] both spoke and saw.
B040C012V023	40	12	23	And all the crowds were amazed and said, "This is not the Son of David, [is it]?"
B040C012V024	40	12	24	But the Pharisees, having heard, said, "This [Man] does not cast out demons except by Beelzebub, ruler of the demons."
B040C012V025	40	12	25	But Jesus, knowing their thoughts, said to them: "Every kingdom being divided against itself is made desolate, and every city or house being divided against itself shall not stand.
B040C012V026	40	12	26	And if Satan casts out Satan, he is divided against himself. How then will his kingdom stand?
B040C012V027	40	12	27	And if I cast out demons by Beelzebub, by whom do your sons cast [them] out? Therefore they shall be your judges.
B040C012V028	40	12	28	But if I cast out demons by the Spirit of God, surely the kingdom of God has come upon you.
B040C012V029	40	12	29	Or how is one able to enter a strong [man's] house to plunder his goods, unless he first binds the strong [man]? And then he will plunder his household.
B040C012V030	40	12	30	He who is not with Me is against Me, and he who does not gather with Me scatters.
B040C012V031	40	12	31	"Therefore I say to you, every sin and blasphemy shall be forgiven unto men, but the blasphemy against the Spirit shall not be forgiven unto men.
B040C012V032	40	12	32	And whoever says a word against the Son of Man, it shall be forgiven him; but whoever speaks against the Holy Spirit, it shall not be forgiven him, either in this age, or in the coming [one.]
B040C012V033	40	12	33	"Either make the tree good and its fruit good, or else make the tree rotten and its fruit rotten; for a tree is known by its fruit.
B040C012V034	40	12	34	Brood of vipers! How can you, being evil, speak good things? For out of the abundance of the heart the mouth speaks.
B040C012V035	40	12	35	A good man out of his good treasure brings forth good things, and an evil man out of his evil treasure brings forth evil things.
B040C012V036	40	12	36	But I say to you, that for every idle word men may speak, they will give account of it in the day of judgment.
B040C012V037	40	12	37	For by your words you shall be justified, and by your words you shall be condemned."
B040C012V038	40	12	38	Then some of the scribes and Pharisees answered, saying, "Teacher, we wish to see a sign from You."
B040C012V039	40	12	39	But He answered and said to them, "An evil and adulterous generation seeks after a sign, and no sign will be given to it except the sign of the prophet Jonah.
B040C012V040	40	12	40	For just as Jonah was three days and three nights in the belly of the great fish, so will the Son of Man be three days and three nights in the heart of the earth.
B040C012V041	40	12	41	The men of Nineveh shall stand up in the judgment with this generation and shall condemn it, because they repented at the preaching of Jonah; and behold, a greater[ than] Jonah [is] here.
