B040C013V001	40	13	1	On the same day Jesus went out of the house and sat beside the sea.
B040C013V002	40	13	2	And great crowds were gathered together to Him, so that He got into the boat and sat; and the crowd stood on the shore.
B040C013V003	40	13	3	And He spoke to them many things in parables, saying: "Behold, a sower went out to sow.
B040C013V004	40	13	4	And as he sowed, some seed fell alongside the road; and the birds came and devoured them.
B040C013V005	40	13	5	But others fell on the stony ground, where it did not have much earth; and immediately it sprang up, because it had no depth of earth.
B040C013V006	40	13	6	But when the sun rose, it was scorched, and because it had no root, it withered away.
B040C013V007	40	13	7	But others fell among thorns, and the thorns sprang up and choked them out.
B040C013V008	40	13	8	But others fell on good ground and it was yielding fruit: some a hundred[fold], some sixty, some thirty.
B040C013V009	40	13	9	He who has ears to hear, let him hear!"
B040C013V010	40	13	10	And the disciples approached and said to Him, "Why do You speak to them in parables?"
B040C013V011	40	13	11	He answered and said to them, "To you it has been given to know the mysteries of the kingdom of heaven, but to them it has not been given.
B040C013V012	40	13	12	For whoever has, to him more shall be given, and he shall be in abundance; but whoever does not have, even what he has shall be taken away from him.
B040C013V013	40	13	13	Therefore I speak to them in parables, because seeing they do not see, and hearing they do not hear, nor do they understand.
B040C013V014	40	13	14	And in them is fulfilled the prophecy of Isaiah, which says: 'Hearing you shall hear and by no means understand, and seeing you shall see and by no means perceive.
B040C013V015	40	13	15	For the heart of this people has become dull, and their ears are hard of hearing, and their eyes have closed, lest they should see with their eyes, and hear with their ears, lest they should understand with their hearts and turn back, that I should heal them.'
B040C013V016	40	13	16	"But blessed are your eyes because they see, and your ears, because they hear.
B040C013V017	40	13	17	For assuredly I say to you, that many prophets and righteous [men] desired to see what you see, and they did not see, and to hear what you hear, and they did not hear."
B040C013V018	40	13	18	"Therefore hear the parable of the sower:
B040C013V019	40	13	19	When anyone hears the word of the kingdom, and does not understand, then the evil [one] comes and snatches away what was sown in his heart. This is the [seed] being sown beside the road.
B040C013V020	40	13	20	But the [seed] sown on stony ground, is he who hears the word and immediately receives it with joy;
B040C013V021	40	13	21	yet he has no root in himself, but is short-lived. For when tribulation or persecution comes because of the word, immediately he falls away.
B040C013V022	40	13	22	But the [seed] sown in the thorns is he who hears the word, and the anxiety of this age, and the deceitfulness of riches chokes out the word, and it becomes fruitless.
B040C013V023	40	13	23	But the [seed] sown on the good ground is he who hears the word and understands it, who indeed bears fruit and produces: some a hundred[fold], some sixty, some thirty."
B040C013V024	40	13	24	Another parable He set before them, saying: "The kingdom of heaven is like a man sowing good seed in his field.
B040C013V025	40	13	25	But while the men were sleeping, his enemy came and sowed tares among the wheat and went away.
B040C013V026	40	13	26	But when the stalk had sprouted and produced fruit, then the tares also appeared.
B040C013V027	40	13	27	So the servants of the master of the house approached and said to him, 'Sir, [was it ]not good seed you sowed in your field? From where then does it have tares?'
B040C013V028	40	13	28	"He said to them, 'An enemy has done this.' So the servants said to him, 'Do you wish then that we should go and gather them up?'
B040C013V029	40	13	29	"But he said, 'No, lest gathering up the tares you also uproot the wheat with them.
B040C013V030	40	13	30	Leave both to grow together until the harvest; and at the time of harvest I will say to the reapers, "First gather together the tares, and bind them into bundles to burn them, but gather together the wheat into my barn."' "
B040C013V031	40	13	31	Another parable He set before them, saying: "The kingdom of heaven is like a mustard seed, which a man took and sowed in his field,
B040C013V032	40	13	32	which indeed is smaller [than] all the seeds; but whenever it is grown, it is greater [than] the garden vegetables and becomes a tree, so that the birds of the air come and nest in its branches."
B040C013V033	40	13	33	Another parable He spoke to them: "The kingdom of heaven is like leaven, which a woman took and mixed in with three measures of meal, until the whole was leavened."
B040C013V034	40	13	34	Jesus spoke all these things in parables to the crowds, and without a parable He did not speak to them,
B040C013V035	40	13	35	so that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the prophet, saying: "I will open My mouth in parables; I will utter things having been hidden from the foundation of the world."
B040C013V036	40	13	36	Then having dismissed the crowds, Jesus went into the house. And His disciples came to Him, saying, "Explain to us the parable of the tares of the field."
B040C013V037	40	13	37	He answered and said to them: "He that sows the good seed is the Son of Man.
B040C013V038	40	13	38	And the field is the world, and the good seed, these are the sons of the kingdom, but the tares are the sons of the evil [one].
B040C013V039	40	13	39	The enemy who sowed them is the devil, the harvest is the end of the age, and the reapers are the angels.
B040C013V040	40	13	40	Therefore just as the tares are gathered and burned with fire, thus it will be at the end of this age.
B040C013V041	40	13	41	The Son of Man will send forth His angels, and they will gather out of His kingdom all things that offend, and those who work iniquity,
B040C013V042	40	13	42	and will cast them into the furnace of fire. There will be weeping and gnashing of teeth.
B040C013V043	40	13	43	Then the righteous will shine forth like the sun in the kingdom of their Father. He who has ears to hear, let him hear!"
B040C013V044	40	13	44	"Again, the kingdom of heaven is like treasure having been hidden in a field, which a man found and hid; and for joy over it, he went and sold everything he had, and bought that field."
B040C013V045	40	13	45	"Again, the kingdom of heaven is like a merchant seeking beautiful pearls,
B040C013V046	40	13	46	who, when he found one very precious pearl, went and sold everything he had and bought it."
B040C013V047	40	13	47	"Again, the kingdom of heaven is like a dragnet having been cast into the sea, and gathering some of every kind,
B040C013V048	40	13	48	which, when it was filled, they pulled up on the shore; and sitting down, they collected the good into vessels, but the rotten they threw out.
B040C013V049	40	13	49	Thus it shall be at the end of the age: the angels shall go forth and separate the evil from among the righteous,
B040C013V050	40	13	50	and cast them into the furnace of fire. There will be weeping and gnashing of teeth."
B040C013V051	40	13	51	Jesus said to them, "Have you understood all these things?"They said to Him, "Yes, Lord."
B040C013V052	40	13	52	Then He said to them, "Therefore every scribe having become a disciple in the kingdom of heaven is like a householder who brings out of his treasure new and old [things]."
B040C013V053	40	13	53	Now it came to pass, when Jesus had finished these parables, He went away from there.
B040C013V054	40	13	54	And coming into His hometown, He began to teach them in their synagogue, so that they were astonished and said, "Where did this Man get this wisdom and the powerful works?
