B040C014V001	40	14	1	At that time Herod the tetrarch heard the report [about] Jesus,
B040C014V002	40	14	2	and said to his servants, "This is John the Baptist; he has been raised from the dead, and therefore these powers are at work in him."
B040C014V003	40	14	3	For Herod had laid hold of John and bound him, and put him in prison on account of Herodias, his brother Philip's wife.
B040C014V004	40	14	4	For John said to him, "It is not lawful for you to have her."
B040C014V005	40	14	5	Though desiring to kill him, he feared the crowd, because they counted him as a prophet.
B040C014V006	40	14	6	Now when Herod's birthday was being celebrated, the daughter of Herodias danced before them, and she pleased Herod.
B040C014V007	40	14	7	Therefore he promised with an oath to give her whatever she should ask.
