B040C015V001	40	15	1	Then the scribes and Pharisees who were from Jerusalem approached Jesus, saying,
B040C015V002	40	15	2	"Why do Your disciples transgress the tradition of the elders? For they do not wash their hands whenever they eat bread."
B040C015V003	40	15	3	He answered and said to them, "Why do you also transgress the commandment of God on account of your tradition?
B040C015V004	40	15	4	For God commanded, saying, 'Honor your father and your mother'; and, 'He who curses father or mother, with death let him die.'
B040C015V005	40	15	5	But you say, 'Whoever says to his father or mother, "[It is] a gift [to God], whatever profit you might have received from me"-
B040C015V006	40	15	6	then by no means should he honor his father or mother.' Thus you have nullified the commandment of God for the sake of your tradition.
B040C015V007	40	15	7	Hypocrites! Well did Isaiah prophesy about you, saying,
B040C015V008	40	15	8	'These people draw near to Me with their mouth, and they honor Me with their lips, but their heart is far away from Me.
B040C015V009	40	15	9	And in vain they worship Me, teaching as doctrines the commandments of men.' "
B040C015V010	40	15	10	And having summoned the crowd, He said to them, "Hear and understand:
B040C015V011	40	15	11	Not what goes into the mouth defiles a man; but what comes out of the mouth, this defiles a man."
B040C015V012	40	15	12	Then His disciples approached and said to Him, "You know that when the Pharisees heard this message they were offended?"
B040C015V013	40	15	13	But He answered and said, "Every plant which My heavenly Father has not planted will be uprooted.
B040C015V014	40	15	14	Leave them alone. They are blind guides of the blind. And if the blind guides the blind, both will fall into a ditch."
