B040C015V018	40	15	18	But those things which proceed out of the mouth come from the heart, and they defile a man.
B040C015V019	40	15	19	For out of the heart come forth evil thoughts, murders, adulteries, fornications, thefts, false witness, blasphemies.
B040C015V020	40	15	20	These are the things which defile a man, but to eat with unwashed hands does not defile a man."
B040C015V021	40	15	21	And going out from there, Jesus withdrew into the region of Tyre and Sidon.
B040C015V022	40	15	22	And behold, a Canaanite woman coming forth from that region cried out to Him, saying, "Have mercy on me, O Lord, Son of David! My daughter is severely demon-possessed."
B040C015V023	40	15	23	But He answered her not a word. And His disciples approached and urged Him, saying, "Send her away, for she cries out after us."
B040C015V024	40	15	24	But He answered and said, "I was not sent except to the lost sheep of the house of Israel."
B040C015V025	40	15	25	Then she came and worshipped Him, saying, "Lord, help me!"
B040C015V026	40	15	26	But He answered and said, "It is not good to take the children's bread and to throw [it] to the little dogs."
B040C015V027	40	15	27	But she said, "Yes, Lord, for even the little dogs eat from the crumbs falling from their masters' table."
B040C015V028	40	15	28	Then Jesus answered and said to her, "O woman, great is your faith! Let it be to you as you desire."And her daughter was healed from that very hour.
B040C015V029	40	15	29	And moving on from there, Jesus came alongside the Sea of Galilee, and going up into a mountain, He sat down there.
