B040C016V001	40	16	1	Then the Pharisees and Sadducees came, and testing [Him], they asked Him to show them a sign out of heaven.
B040C016V002	40	16	2	He answered and said to them, "When evening comes you say, 'Fine weather, for the sky is red'.
B040C016V003	40	16	3	And in the morning, 'Today [will be ]stormy, for the sky is red and overcast.' Hypocrites! Indeed you know how to discern the face of the sky, but you cannot discern the signs of the times.
B040C016V004	40	16	4	An evil and adulterous generation seeks after a sign, and no sign will be given to it except the sign of the prophet Jonah."And leaving them behind He went away.
B040C016V005	40	16	5	Now when His disciples had come to the other side, they forgot to take bread.
