B040C016V028	40	16	28	Assuredly I say to you, there are some standing here who will by no means taste death till they see the Son of Man coming in His kingdom."
B040C017V001	40	17	1	Now after six days Jesus took Peter, James, and John his brother, and led them up on a high mountain in private;
B040C017V002	40	17	2	and He was transfigured before them, and His face shone like the sun, and His clothes became as white as the light.
B040C017V003	40	17	3	And behold, Moses and Elijah appeared to them, talking with Him.
B040C017V004	40	17	4	Then Peter answered and said to Jesus, "Lord, it is good for us to be here; if You desire, let us make here three tents: one for You, one for Moses, and one for Elijah."
B040C017V005	40	17	5	While he was still speaking, behold, a bright cloud overshadowed them; and behold, a voice [came] out of the cloud, saying, "This is My beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased. Hear Him!"
B040C017V006	40	17	6	And when the disciples heard this, they fell on their faces and they were greatly afraid.
B040C017V007	40	17	7	But Jesus approached and touched them and said, "Arise, and do not be afraid."
