B040C017V014	40	17	14	And when they came to the crowd, a man approached Him, kneeling to Him, and saying,
B040C017V015	40	17	15	"Lord, have pity on my son, for he is moonstruck and suffers severely; for he often falls into the fire and often into the water.
B040C017V016	40	17	16	So I brought him to Your disciples, but they were not able to heal him."
B040C017V017	40	17	17	Then Jesus answered and said, "O unfaithful and perverted generation, how long shall I be with you? How long shall I bear with you? Bring him here to Me."
B040C017V018	40	17	18	And Jesus rebuked the demon, and it came out from him; and the boy was healed from that very hour.
