B040C017V027	40	17	27	Nevertheless, lest we offend them, go to the sea, and cast in a hook, and take the first fish coming up. And when you have opened its mouth, you will find a coin; taking that, give it to them for Me and you."
B040C018V001	40	18	1	At that time the disciples came to Jesus, saying, "Who then is [the ]greater in the kingdom of heaven?"
B040C018V002	40	18	2	Then Jesus called a little child, and set him in their midst,
B040C018V003	40	18	3	and said, "Assuredly I say to you, unless you are converted and become as little children, you shall by no means enter the kingdom of heaven.
B040C018V004	40	18	4	Therefore whoever humbles himself as this little child, he is the greater in the kingdom of heaven.
B040C018V005	40	18	5	And whoever receives one such little child in My name, receives Me.
B040C018V006	40	18	6	"But whoever causes one of these little ones who believe in Me to stumble, it would be better for him that a huge millstone be hanged on his neck, and he be drowned in the depth of the sea.
B040C018V007	40	18	7	Woe to the world because of offenses! For offenses must come, but woe to that man through whom the offense comes!
B040C018V008	40	18	8	And if your hand or your foot causes you to stumble, cut them off and cast [them] from you. It is better for you to enter into life lame or maimed, than having two hands or two feet, to be thrown into the eternal fire.
B040C018V009	40	18	9	And if your eye causes you to stumble, pluck it out and cast it from you. It is better for you to enter into life with one eye, than having two eyes, to be thrown into the fiery hell.
B040C018V010	40	18	10	"See that you do not despise one of these little [ones], for I say to you that in heaven their angels always see the face of My Father who is in heaven.
B040C018V011	40	18	11	For the Son of Man came to save that which was lost.
B040C018V012	40	18	12	What do you think? If a certain man has a hundred sheep, and one of them goes astray, does he not leave the ninety-nine on the mountains, and go and search for the [one ]gone astray?
B040C018V013	40	18	13	And if he happens to find it, assuredly I say to you that he rejoices over it more than over the ninety-nine which did not go astray.
B040C018V014	40	18	14	Thus it is not the will before your Father who is in heaven that one of these little ones should perish.
B040C018V015	40	18	15	"And if your brother sins against you, go and show him his fault between you and him alone. If he hears you, you have won your brother.
B040C018V016	40	18	16	But if he does not hear, take along with you one or two more, so that 'by the mouth of two or three witnesses every word may be established.'
B040C018V017	40	18	17	But if he refuses to hear them, tell it to the assembly. But if he refuses even to hear the assembly, let him be to you as a heathen and a tax collector.
B040C018V018	40	18	18	Assuredly I say to you, whatever you bind on earth shall have been bound in heaven, and whatever you loose on earth shall have been loosed in heaven.
B040C018V019	40	18	19	Again, assuredly I say to you that if two of you agree on earth about anything that they may ask, it will be done for them by My Father in heaven.
B040C018V020	40	18	20	For where two or three are gathered together in My name, I am there in their midst."
B040C018V021	40	18	21	Then Peter came to Him and said, "Lord, how often shall my brother sin against me, and I forgive him? Up to seven times?"
B040C018V022	40	18	22	Jesus said to him, "I do not say to you, up to seven times, but up to seventy- seven [times.]
B040C018V023	40	18	23	Therefore the kingdom of heaven is like a certain king who wanted to settle accounts with his servants.
B040C018V024	40	18	24	And when he began to settle up, one debtor was brought to him [owing] ten thousand talents.
B040C018V025	40	18	25	But since he had nothing with which to repay, his master commanded that he be sold, with his wife and children and everything that he had, and to be repaid.
B040C018V026	40	18	26	Therefore falling down before him, the servant said, 'Master, have patience with me, and I will repay everything to you.'
B040C018V027	40	18	27	"And having compassion, the master of that servant released him, and forgave him the loan.
B040C018V028	40	18	28	But when that servant went out, he found one of his fellow servants who owed him a hundred denarii. And taking hold of him, he was choking him, saying, 'Pay me what you owe!'
