B040C020V001	40	20	1	"For the kingdom of heaven is like a certain landowner who went out early in the morning to hire workers for his vineyard.
B040C020V002	40	20	2	And having agreed with the workers for a denarius a day, he sent them into his vineyard.
B040C020V003	40	20	3	And going out about the third hour, he saw others standing idle in the marketplace.
B040C020V004	40	20	4	And said to them, 'You also go into the vineyard, and whatever may be right I will give you.' So they went.
B040C020V005	40	20	5	Again going out about the sixth and the ninth hour, he did likewise.
B040C020V006	40	20	6	And about the eleventh hour, going out he found others standing idle, and said to them, 'Why do you stand here idle all day?'
B040C020V007	40	20	7	"They said to him, 'Because no one has hired us.' He said to them, 'You also go into the vineyard, and whatever is right you shall receive.'
B040C020V008	40	20	8	"So when evening came, the owner of the vineyard said to his foreman, 'Call the workers and pay them their wages, beginning with the last to the first.'
B040C020V009	40	20	9	"And when those came [who were hired] about the eleventh hour, they each received a denarius.
B040C020V010	40	20	10	But when the first came, they supposed that they would receive more; and they also received each a denarius.
B040C020V011	40	20	11	And when they had received it, they began grumbling against the landowner,
B040C020V012	40	20	12	saying, 'These last [men] have worked only one hour, and you made them equal to us who have borne the burden and the heat of the day.'
B040C020V013	40	20	13	"But he answered one of them and said, 'Friend, I am not wronging you. Did you not agree with me for a denarius?
B040C020V014	40	20	14	Take what is yours and go. But I want to give to this last [man] the same as to you.
B040C020V015	40	20	15	Is it not lawful for me to do what I wish with my own [things]? Or is your eye evil because I am good?'
B040C020V016	40	20	16	"Thus the last shall be first, and the first last. For many are called, but few [are ]chosen."
B040C020V017	40	20	17	And as Jesus was going up to Jerusalem, He took aside the twelve disciples privately on the road, and He said to them,
B040C020V018	40	20	18	"Behold, we are going up to Jerusalem, and the Son of Man will be betrayed to the chief priests and scribes, and they will condemn Him to death,
B040C020V019	40	20	19	and they will hand Him over to the Gentiles to mock and to scourge and to crucify. And the third day He shall rise again."
