B040C021V042	40	21	42	Jesus said to them, "Have you never read in the Scriptures: 'The stone which the builders rejected has become the chief cornerstone. This was the LORD's doing, and it is marvelous in our eyes'?
B040C021V043	40	21	43	"Therefore I say to you, the kingdom of God shall be taken away from you, and it shall be given to a nation producing the fruits of it.
B040C021V044	40	21	44	And he who falls on this stone will be broken to pieces; but on whomever it falls, it will grind him to powder."
B040C021V045	40	21	45	Now when the chief priests and Pharisees heard His parables, they knew that He was speaking about them.
B040C021V046	40	21	46	And seeking to seize Him, they feared the crowds, since they considered Him as a prophet.
B040C022V001	40	22	1	And Jesus answered and spoke to them again in parables, saying,
B040C022V002	40	22	2	"The kingdom of heaven is like a certain king who arranged a wedding for his son,
B040C022V003	40	22	3	and sent out his servants to call those who were invited to the wedding; and they did not want to come.
B040C022V004	40	22	4	Again, he sent out other servants, saying, 'Say to those who are invited, "See, I have prepared my dinner; my oxen and fatted cattle are killed, and all things [are] ready. Come to the wedding."'
B040C022V005	40	22	5	"But not caring, they went away, one to his own field, another to his business.
B040C022V006	40	22	6	And the rest seized his servants, mistreated [them], and killed [them].
B040C022V007	40	22	7	And when that king heard, he was furious. And he sent out his troops, and he destroyed those murderers, and he burned up their city.
B040C022V008	40	22	8	Then he said to his servants, 'The wedding indeed is ready, but those who were invited were not worthy.
B040C022V009	40	22	9	Therefore go into the highways, and as many as you find, invite to the wedding.'
B040C022V010	40	22	10	"So those servants went out into the highways and gathered together all whom they found, both bad and good. And the wedding [hall] was filled with guests.
B040C022V011	40	22	11	But when the king came in to see the guests, he saw a man there not dressed with wedding clothes.
B040C022V012	40	22	12	So he said to him, 'Friend, how did you come in here not having wedding clothes?' And he was speechless.
B040C022V013	40	22	13	Then the king said to the servants, 'Tie him up hands and feet, take him away, and cast [him] into outer darkness; there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.'
B040C022V014	40	22	14	"For many are called, but few are chosen."
B040C022V015	40	22	15	Then the Pharisees went and plotted how they might trap Him in His speech.
B040C022V016	40	22	16	And they sent their disciples to Him with the Herodians, saying, "Teacher, we know that You are true, and teach the way of God in truth; nor do You show favoritism to anyone.
B040C022V017	40	22	17	Tell us, therefore, what do You think? Is it lawful to pay taxes to Caesar, or not?"
B040C022V018	40	22	18	But Jesus, knowing their wickedness, said, "Why do you test Me, [you] hypocrites?
B040C022V019	40	22	19	Show Me the tax money."So they brought Him a denarius.
B040C022V020	40	22	20	And He said to them, "Whose image and inscription is this?"
B040C022V021	40	22	21	They said to Him, "Caesar's."And He said to them, "Render therefore to Caesar the things that are Caesar's, and to God the things that are God's."
B040C022V022	40	22	22	When they had heard these words, they marveled, and leaving Him, they went away.
B040C022V023	40	22	23	The same day the Sadducees, who say there is no resurrection, came to Him, and they questioned Him,
B040C022V024	40	22	24	saying: "Teacher, Moses said that if a man dies, having no children, his brother shall marry his wife as next of kin, and shall raise up offspring for his brother.
B040C022V025	40	22	25	Now there were with us seven brothers. The first died, after having married, and having no offspring, he left his wife to his brother.
B040C022V026	40	22	26	Likewise the second also, and the third, up to the seventh.
B040C022V027	40	22	27	Last of all the woman died also.
B040C022V028	40	22	28	Therefore, in the resurrection, whose wife of the seven will she be? For [they] all had her."
B040C022V029	40	22	29	Jesus answered and said to them, "You err, not knowing the Scriptures, nor the power of God.
B040C022V030	40	22	30	For in the resurrection neither do they marry, nor are they given in marriage, but they are like angels of God in heaven.
B040C022V031	40	22	31	But concerning the resurrection of the dead, have you not read what was spoken to you by God, saying,
B040C022V032	40	22	32	'I am the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob'? God is not the God of the dead, but of the living."
B040C022V033	40	22	33	And when the crowds heard [this], they were astonished at His teaching.
B040C022V034	40	22	34	But when the Pharisees heard that He had silenced the Sadducees, they gathered together.
B040C022V035	40	22	35	Then one of them, a lawyer, asked Him a question, testing Him, and saying,
B040C022V036	40	22	36	"Teacher, which is the great commandment in the law?"
B040C022V037	40	22	37	Jesus said to him, "'You shall love the LORD your God with all your heart, and with all your soul, and with all your mind.'
B040C022V038	40	22	38	This is the first and great commandment.
B040C022V039	40	22	39	And the second is like it: 'You shall love your neighbor as yourself.'
B040C022V040	40	22	40	On these two commandments hang all the Law and the Prophets."
B040C022V041	40	22	41	And when the Pharisees were gathered together, Jesus asked them,
B040C022V042	40	22	42	saying, "What do you think about the Christ? Whose Son is He?"They said to Him, "David's."
B040C022V043	40	22	43	He said to them, "How then does David in the Spirit call Him 'Lord,' saying:
B040C022V044	40	22	44	'The LORD said to my Lord, "Sit at My right hand, till I make Your enemies a footstool for Your feet"'?
B040C022V045	40	22	45	"If David therefore calls Him 'Lord,' how is He his Son?"
B040C022V046	40	22	46	And no one was able to answer Him a word, nor from that day on did anyone dare question Him any longer.
B040C023V001	40	23	1	Then Jesus spoke to the crowds and to His disciples,
B040C023V002	40	23	2	saying: "The scribes and the Pharisees sit on Moses' seat.
B040C023V003	40	23	3	Therefore whatever they may say to you to observe, observe and do, but do not do according to their works; for they say, and do not do.
B040C023V004	40	23	4	For they bind heavy burdens, hard to bear, and lay [them] on men's shoulders; but they do not desire to move them with their finger.
B040C023V005	40	23	5	But all their works they do in order to be seen by men. They make their phylacteries broad and they enlarge the borders of their garments.
B040C023V006	40	23	6	They love the first couch in the suppers, and the best seats in the synagogues,
B040C023V007	40	23	7	and greetings in the marketplaces, and to be called by men, 'Rabbi, Rabbi.'
B040C023V008	40	23	8	"But you, do not be called 'Rabbi'; for One is your Teacher, the Christ, and you are all brothers.
B040C023V009	40	23	9	Do not call [anyone] on earth your father; for One is your Father, He who is in heaven.
B040C023V010	40	23	10	Neither be called teachers; for One is your Teacher, the Christ.
B040C023V011	40	23	11	But the greatest of you shall be your servant.
B040C023V012	40	23	12	And whoever shall exalt himself will be humbled, and whoever shall humble himself will be exalted.
B040C023V013	40	23	13	But woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! Because you devour widows' houses, and for a pretense make long prayers. Therefore you will receive greater condemnation.
B040C023V014	40	23	14	Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! Because you shut up the kingdom of heaven before men; for you do not enter, nor do you allow those who are entering to go in.
B040C023V015	40	23	15	Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! Because you travel around land and sea to make one proselyte, and whenever he becomes [one], you make him twice as much a son of hell as you.
B040C023V016	40	23	16	Woe to you, blind guides, who say, 'Whoever swears by the temple, it is nothing; but whoever swears by the gold of the temple, is obligated.'
B040C023V017	40	23	17	"Fools and blind! For which is greater, the gold or the temple that sanctifies the gold?
B040C023V018	40	23	18	And, 'Whoever swears by the altar, it is nothing; but whoever swears by the gift that is on it, is obligated.'
B040C023V019	40	23	19	"Fools and blind! For which is greater, the gift or the altar that sanctifies the gift?
B040C023V020	40	23	20	Therefore he that swears by the altar, swears by it and by all the things on it.
B040C023V021	40	23	21	He that swears by the temple, swears by it and by Him who dwelt in it.
B040C023V022	40	23	22	And he that swears by heaven, swears by the throne of God and by Him who sits on it.
B040C023V023	40	23	23	Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! Because you pay tithes of mint and dill and cummin, and have neglected the more important [things] of the law: justice and mercy and faith. These things you should have done, and not have neglected the others.
B040C023V024	40	23	24	Blind guides, you who strain out a gnat, but swallow a camel!
B040C023V025	40	23	25	Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! Because you clean the outside of the cup and dish, but inside they are full of greed and unrighteousness.
B040C023V026	40	23	26	Blind Pharisee, first clean the inside of the cup and dish, so that the outside of them may be clean also.
B040C023V027	40	23	27	Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! For you are like whitewashed tombs, which indeed appear beautiful outwardly, but inside are full of dead men's bones and of all uncleanness.
B040C023V028	40	23	28	Thus also you outwardly appear righteous to men, but inside you are full of hypocrisy and lawlessness.
B040C023V029	40	23	29	Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! Because you build the tombs of the prophets and adorn the monuments of the righteous,
B040C023V030	40	23	30	and say, 'If we had lived in the days of our fathers, we would not have been partakers with them in the blood of the prophets.'
B040C023V031	40	23	31	"So that you testify against yourselves that you are sons of those who killed the prophets.
B040C023V032	40	23	32	And you, fill up then, the measure of your fathers' guilt.
B040C023V033	40	23	33	Serpents! Brood of vipers! How shall you escape from the condemnation of hell?
B040C023V034	40	23	34	Therefore, behold, I send you prophets, wise [men], and scribes: some of them you will kill and you will crucify, and [some] of them you will flog in your synagogues and you will persecute from city to city,
B040C023V035	40	23	35	so that on you may come all the righteous blood being shed on the earth, from the blood of righteous Abel to the blood of Zechariah, son of Berechiah, whom you murdered between the temple and the altar.
B040C023V036	40	23	36	Assuredly I say to you, all these things shall come upon this generation.
B040C023V037	40	23	37	"O Jerusalem, Jerusalem, [you] who kills the prophets and stones those who are sent to her! How often would I have gathered your children together, as a hen gathers her chicks under her wings, but you were not willing!
B040C023V038	40	23	38	Behold, your house is left to you desolate.
B040C023V039	40	23	39	For I say to you, you shall by no means see Me from now until you say, 'Blessed [is] He who comes in the name of the LORD!' "
B040C024V001	40	24	1	Then Jesus went out and departed from the temple, and His disciples came to [Him] to point out to Him the buildings of the temple.
B040C024V002	40	24	2	But Jesus said to them, "Do you not see all these things? Assuredly I say to you, by no means will a stone be left here upon a stone, which shall not be thrown down."
B040C024V003	40	24	3	And as He was sitting on the Mount of Olives, the disciples came to Him privately, saying, "Tell us, when shall these things be? And what [shall be] the sign of Your coming, and of the end of the age?"
B040C024V004	40	24	4	And Jesus answered and said to them: "Take heed that no one deceives you.
B040C024V005	40	24	5	For many will come in My name, saying, 'I am the Christ,' and they will deceive many.
B040C024V006	40	24	6	And you will hear of wars and rumors of wars. See [that] you are not disturbed; for all these things must come to pass, but the end is not yet.
B040C024V007	40	24	7	For nation shall rise up against nation, and kingdom against kingdom, and there will be famines, pestilences, and earthquakes in various places.
B040C024V008	40	24	8	But all these things[ are ]the beginning of sorrows.
B040C024V009	40	24	9	Then they will hand you over to tribulation and they will kill you, and you will be hated by all nations, on account of My name.
B040C024V010	40	24	10	And then many will fall away, and they will betray one another, and they will hate one another.
B040C024V011	40	24	11	Then many false prophets will be raised up, and they will deceive many.
B040C024V012	40	24	12	And because lawlessness will increase, the love of many will grow cold.
B040C024V013	40	24	13	But he who endures to the end shall be saved.
B040C024V014	40	24	14	And this good news of the kingdom will be proclaimed in all the world for a testimony to all the nations, and then the end will come.
B040C024V015	40	24	15	"Therefore when you see the 'abomination of desolation,' spoken of through Daniel the prophet, standing in the holy place"(whoever reads, let him understand),
B040C024V016	40	24	16	then let those who are in Judea flee upon the mountains.
B040C024V017	40	24	17	Let the [one] on the housetop not go down to take the things out of his house.
B040C024V018	40	24	18	And let the [one] in the field not turn back to take his clothes.
B040C024V019	40	24	19	But woe to those [women ]who are pregnant, and to the [women] nursing a baby in those days!
B040C024V020	40	24	20	But pray that your flight may not take place in winter, nor [on] the Sabbath.
B040C024V021	40	24	21	For then there shall be great tribulation, such as has not been since the beginning of the world until now, nor by any means shall be.
B040C024V022	40	24	22	And unless those days were cut short, no flesh would be saved; but for the elect's sake, those days will be cut short.
B040C024V023	40	24	23	Then if someone says to you, 'Look, here is the Christ!' or 'There!' do not believe [it].
B040C024V024	40	24	24	For false christs and false prophets will be raised up, and they will show great signs and wonders so as to deceive, if possible, even the elect.
B040C024V025	40	24	25	See, I have told you in advance.
B040C024V026	40	24	26	Therefore if they should say to you, 'Look, He is in the desert!' do not go out; or 'Look, He is in the inner rooms!' do not believe [it].
B040C024V027	40	24	27	For as the lightning comes out from the east and flashes to the west, so shall also be the coming of the Son of Man.
B040C024V028	40	24	28	For wherever the carcass may be, there the eagles will be gathered together.
B040C024V029	40	24	29	"Immediately after the tribulation of those days, the sun shall be darkened, and the moon shall not give its light; and the stars shall fall from heaven, and the powers of the heavens shall be shaken.
B040C024V030	40	24	30	And then shall appear the sign of the Son of Man in heaven, and then all the tribes of the earth shall mourn, and they shall see the Son of Man coming on the clouds of heaven with power and great glory.
B040C024V031	40	24	31	And He shall send His angels with a great sound of a trumpet, and they shall gather together His elect from the four winds, from one end of heaven to the other.
B040C024V032	40	24	32	"Now learn this parable from the fig tree: Whenever its branch already becomes tender and puts forth leaves, you know that summer is near.
B040C024V033	40	24	33	So you also, whenever you see all these things, know that it is near-at the doors!
B040C024V034	40	24	34	Assuredly I say to you, this generation shall by no means pass away till all these things are fulfilled.
B040C024V035	40	24	35	Heaven and earth shall pass away, but My words shall by no means pass away.
B040C024V036	40	24	36	"But concerning that day and hour no one knows, not even the angels of heaven, but My Father only.
B040C024V037	40	24	37	But just as the days of Noah [were], so also shall be the coming of the Son of Man.
B040C024V038	40	24	38	For just as they were in the days before the flood, eating and drinking, marrying and giving in marriage, until the day that Noah entered into the ark,
B040C024V039	40	24	39	and they didn't know [a thing] until the flood came and took [them] all away, so also shall be the coming of the Son of Man.
B040C024V040	40	24	40	Then two will be in the field: one will be taken, and one will be left.
B040C024V041	40	24	41	Two will be grinding at the mill: one will be taken, and one will be left.
B040C024V042	40	24	42	Watch therefore, for you do not know in what hour your Lord is coming.
B040C024V043	40	24	43	But know this, that if the master of the house had known in what hour the thief was coming, he would have kept watch, and he would not have allowed his house to be broken into.
B040C024V044	40	24	44	For this reason you also must be ready, for at an hour that you think not, the Son of Man comes.
B040C024V045	40	24	45	"Who then is a faithful and wise servant, whom his master appointed over his household, to give them food in due season?
B040C024V046	40	24	46	Blessed is that servant whom his master, when he comes, will find so doing.
B040C024V047	40	24	47	Assuredly I say to you that he will make him ruler over all his possessions.
B040C024V048	40	24	48	But if that evil servant should say in his heart, 'My master is delaying to come,'
B040C024V049	40	24	49	"and should begin to beat his fellow servants, and to eat and drink with the drunkards,
B040C024V050	40	24	50	the master of that servant will come on a day which he does not expect, and in an hour which he does not know,
B040C024V051	40	24	51	and he will cut him in two, and will appoint his share with the hypocrites. There shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.
B040C025V001	40	25	1	"Then shall the kingdom of heaven be likened unto ten virgins, who having taken their lamps, went out to meet the bridegroom.
B040C025V002	40	25	2	Now five of them were wise, and five [were] foolish.
B040C025V003	40	25	3	Those who [were] foolish, having taken their lamps, did not take oil with them,
B040C025V004	40	25	4	but the wise took oil in their vessels along with their lamps.
B040C025V005	40	25	5	But while the bridegroom was delayed, they all became drowsy and slept.
B040C025V006	40	25	6	And at midnight a cry was heard: 'Behold, the bridegroom is coming; go out to meet him!'
B040C025V007	40	25	7	"Then all those virgins arose, and they trimmed their lamps.
B040C025V008	40	25	8	And the foolish said to the wise, 'Give us [some] of your oil, for our lamps are going out.'
B040C025V009	40	25	9	"But the wise answered, saying, 'No, lest there should not be enough for you and us; but go rather to those who sell, and buy for yourselves.'
B040C025V010	40	25	10	"But as they went away to buy, the bridegroom came, and those who were ready went in with him to the wedding; and the door was shut.
B040C025V011	40	25	11	Afterward the remaining virgins came also, saying, 'Lord, Lord, open to us!'
B040C025V012	40	25	12	"But he answered and said, 'Assuredly I say to you, I do not know you.'
B040C025V013	40	25	13	"Watch therefore, for you do not know the day nor the hour in which the Son of Man is coming.
B040C025V014	40	25	14	"For [it is ]as[ if] a man leaving on a journey, who called his own servants and handed over his possessions to them.
B040C025V015	40	25	15	And to the one he gave five talents, and to another two, and to another one, to each according to his own ability; and immediately he went on a journey.
B040C025V016	40	25	16	Then the [one] receiving the five talents went and traded with them, and made five other talents.
B040C025V017	40	25	17	And likewise the [one receiving the ]two gained two more also.
B040C025V018	40	25	18	But the [one] receiving one went away and dug in the ground, and hid his lord's money.
B040C025V019	40	25	19	Then after much time, the lord of those servants came and settled accounts with them.
B040C025V020	40	25	20	And the [one] who had received five talents came and brought five other talents, saying, 'Lord, you delivered to me five talents; look, I gained five more talents besides them.'
B040C025V021	40	25	21	"His lord said to him, 'Well done, good and faithful servant; you were faithful over a few things, I will make you ruler over many things. Enter into the joy of your lord.'
B040C025V022	40	25	22	"And also the [one ]receiving the two talents came and said, 'Lord, you delivered to me two talents; look, I have gained two more talents besides them.'
B040C025V023	40	25	23	"His lord said to him, 'Well done, good and faithful servant; you have been faithful over a few things, I will make you ruler over many things. Enter into the joy of your lord.'
B040C025V024	40	25	24	"Then the [one] having received the one talent came and said, 'Lord, I knew you, that you are a hard man, reaping where you did not sow, and gathering where you did not scatter.
B040C025V025	40	25	25	And being afraid, I went off and hid your talent in the ground. Look, you have what is yours.'
B040C025V026	40	25	26	"But his lord answered and said to him, 'You wicked and slothful servant, you knew that I reap where I did not sow, and gather where I did not scatter.
B040C025V027	40	25	27	Therefore you should have deposited my money with the bankers, and at my coming I would have received what is mine with interest.
B040C025V028	40	25	28	Therefore take the talent from him, and give it to him who has the ten talents.
B040C025V029	40	25	29	For to everyone who has, [more] shall be given, and he shall have abundance; but to him who does not have, even what he has shall be taken away from him.
B040C025V030	40	25	30	And cast the useless servant into the darkness outside. There shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.'
B040C025V031	40	25	31	"And when the Son of Man comes in His glory, and all the holy angels with Him, then will He sit upon His glorious throne.
B040C025V032	40	25	32	All the nations will be gathered before Him, and He will separate them one from another, as a shepherd separates the sheep from the goats.
B040C025V033	40	25	33	And He will set the sheep on His right hand, but the goats on [His] left.
B040C025V034	40	25	34	Then the King will say to those on His right hand, 'Come, you blessed of My Father, inherit the kingdom prepared for you from the foundation of the world:
B040C025V035	40	25	35	for I was hungry and you gave Me food; I was thirsty and you gave Me drink; I was a stranger and you took Me in;
B040C025V036	40	25	36	I was naked and you clothed Me; I was sick and you visited Me; I was in prison and you came to Me.'
B040C025V037	40	25	37	"Then the righteous will answer Him, saying, 'Lord, when did we see You hungry and feed You, or thirsty and give You drink?
B040C025V038	40	25	38	When did we see You a stranger and take You in, or naked and clothe You?
B040C025V039	40	25	39	Or when did we see You sick, or in prison, and come to You?'
B040C025V040	40	25	40	"And the King will answer and say to them, 'Assuredly I say to you, inasmuch as you did it to one of the least of these My brothers, you did it to Me.'
B040C025V041	40	25	41	"Then He will also say to those on the left, 'Depart from Me, you cursed, into the eternal fire prepared for the devil and his angels:
B040C025V042	40	25	42	for I was hungry and you gave Me no food; I was thirsty and you gave Me no drink;
B040C025V043	40	25	43	I was a stranger and you did not take Me in, naked and you did not clothe Me, sick and in prison and you did not visit Me.'
B040C025V044	40	25	44	"Then they also will answer, saying, 'Lord, when did we see You hungry or thirsty or a stranger or naked or sick or in prison, and we did not minister to You?'
B040C025V045	40	25	45	"Then He will answer them, saying, 'Assuredly I say to you, inasmuch as you did not do it to one of the least of these, neither did you do it to Me.'
B040C025V046	40	25	46	"And these shall go away into eternal punishment, but the righteous into eternal life."
B040C026V001	40	26	1	Now it came to pass, when Jesus had finished all these words, that He said to His disciples,
B040C026V002	40	26	2	You know that after two days the Passover takes place, and the Son of Man will be handed over to be crucified."
B040C026V003	40	26	3	Then the chief priests, the scribes, and the elders of the people were assembled into the court of the high priest, who was called Caiaphas,
B040C026V004	40	26	4	and plotted to take Jesus by guile and kill Him.
B040C026V005	40	26	5	But they said, "Not during the feast, lest a disturbance take place among the people."
B040C026V006	40	26	6	And when Jesus was in Bethany in the house of Simon the leper,
B040C026V007	40	26	7	a woman came to Him having an alabaster [flask] of very expensive perfume, and she began to pour it on His head as He reclined to eat.
B040C026V008	40	26	8	But when His disciples saw it, they became indignant, saying, "Why this waste?
B040C026V009	40	26	9	For this perfume could have been sold for much, and have been given to the poor."
B040C026V010	40	26	10	But when Jesus became aware of it, He said to them, "Why do you trouble the woman? For she has done a beautiful work for Me.
B040C026V011	40	26	11	For you have the poor with you always, but Me you do not have always.
B040C026V012	40	26	12	For this [woman], having put this perfume on My body, she did [it] for My burial.
B040C026V013	40	26	13	Assuredly I say to you, wherever this gospel is proclaimed in the whole world, what this [woman] did will be spoken as a memorial to her."
B040C026V014	40	26	14	Then one of the twelve, called Judas Iscariot, went to the chief priests
B040C026V015	40	26	15	and said, "What are you willing to give me if I deliver Him to you?"And they weighed out for him thirty silver [coins].
B040C026V016	40	26	16	And from then [on] he sought an opportunity to betray Him.
B040C026V017	40	26	17	Now on the first day of the Feast of the Unleavened Bread, the disciples came to Jesus, saying to Him, "Where do You desire [that] we shall prepare for You to eat the Passover?"
B040C026V018	40	26	18	And He said, "Go into the city to a certain man, and say to him, 'The Teacher says, "My time is near; at your house I will keep the Passover with My disciples."' "
B040C026V019	40	26	19	So the disciples did as Jesus had directed them; and they prepared the Passover.
B040C026V020	40	26	20	And when it was evening, He was reclining [to eat] with the twelve.
B040C026V021	40	26	21	Now while they were eating, He said, "Assuredly I say to you, that one of you will betray Me."
B040C026V022	40	26	22	And becoming exceedingly sorrowful, each of them began to say to Him, "[Surely] not I am [the one], Lord?"
B040C026V023	40	26	23	He answered and said, "He who dipped his hand with Me in the bowl will betray Me.
B040C026V024	40	26	24	Indeed, the Son of Man goes just as it is written about Him, but woe to that man through whom the Son of Man is betrayed! It would have been good for that man if he had not been born."
B040C026V025	40	26	25	Then Judas, the [one] betraying Him, answered and said, "[Surely ]not I am [the one], Rabbi?"He said to him, "You have said [it]."
B040C026V026	40	26	26	And as they were eating, Jesus took the bread, and giving thanks, He broke [it], and gave [it] to the disciples and said, "Take, eat; this is My body."
B040C026V027	40	26	27	Then He took the cup, and gave thanks, and gave [it] to them, saying, "Drink of it, all [of you],
B040C026V028	40	26	28	for this is My blood of the new covenant, which is shed for many, for the forgiveness of sins.
B040C026V029	40	26	29	But I say to you, that I will by no means drink of this fruit of the vine from now [on,] until that day when I drink it new with you in My Father's kingdom."
B040C026V030	40	26	30	And having sung hymns, they went out to the Mount of Olives.
B040C026V031	40	26	31	Then Jesus said to them, "All of you will be made to stumble because of Me on this night, for it is written: 'I will strike the Shepherd, and the sheep of the flock will be scattered.'
B040C026V032	40	26	32	"But after I have been raised, I will go before you to Galilee."
B040C026V033	40	26	33	Peter answered and said to Him, "Even if all are made to stumble because of You, yet I will never be made to stumble."
B040C026V034	40	26	34	Jesus said to him, "Assuredly I say to you that on this night, before [the] rooster crows, you will deny Me three times."
B040C026V035	40	26	35	Peter said to Him, "Even if I have to die with You, by no means will I deny You!"And likewise said all the disciples.
B040C026V036	40	26	36	Then Jesus came with them to a place called Gethsemane, and said to the disciples, "Sit here while I go off and pray [over] there."
B040C026V037	40	26	37	And taking along Peter and the two sons of Zebedee, He began to be sorrowful and deeply distressed.
B040C026V038	40	26	38	Then Jesus said to them, "My soul is deeply grieved, to the point of death. Stay here and keep watch with Me."
B040C026V039	40	26	39	He went a little farther and fell on His face, and prayed, saying, "O My Father, if it is possible, let this cup pass from Me; nevertheless, not as I will, but as You [will]."
B040C026V040	40	26	40	Then He came to the disciples and found them sleeping, and said to Peter, "What? Were you not strong [enough] to watch with Me one hour?
B040C026V041	40	26	41	Watch and pray, lest you enter into temptation. Indeed the spirit is willing, but the flesh is weak."
B040C026V042	40	26	42	Again, a second time, He went away and prayed, saying, "O My Father, if this cup cannot pass away from Me unless I drink it, let Your will be done."
B040C026V043	40	26	43	And He came and found them sleeping again, for their eyes were heavy.
B040C026V044	40	26	44	And leaving them, He went away again, and prayed a third time, saying the same words.
B040C026V045	40	26	45	Then He came to His disciples and said to them, "Sleep now, and rest. Behold, the hour is at hand, and the Son of Man is being betrayed into the hands of sinners.
B040C026V046	40	26	46	Rise up, let us be going. See, he who betrays Me is at hand."
B040C026V047	40	26	47	And while He was still speaking, behold, Judas, one of the twelve came, and with him a great crowd with swords and clubs, [sent] from the chief priests and elders of the people.
B040C026V048	40	26	48	Now the [one] betraying Him had given them a sign, saying, "Whomever I shall kiss, He is [the One]; seize Him."
B040C026V049	40	26	49	And immediately he went up to Jesus and said, "Greetings, Rabbi!"and kissed Him.
B040C026V050	40	26	50	But Jesus said to him, "Friend, why have you come?"Then they came and laid hands on Jesus and seized Him.
B040C026V051	40	26	51	And behold, one of those with Jesus stretched out his hand and drew his sword, and striking the servant of the high priest, he cut off his ear.
B040C026V052	40	26	52	But Jesus said to him, "Put your sword back into its place, for all those who take the sword shall perish by the sword.
B040C026V053	40	26	53	Or do you think that I cannot now call upon My Father, and He will furnish Me with more than twelve legions of angels?
B040C026V054	40	26	54	How then would the Scriptures be fulfilled, that it must happen thus?"
B040C026V055	40	26	55	In that hour Jesus said to the crowds, "Have you come out as against a robber, with swords and clubs to arrest Me? I sat daily with you, teaching in the temple, and you did not seize Me.
B040C026V056	40	26	56	But all this has happened so that the Scriptures of the prophets may be fulfilled."Then all the disciples forsook Him and fled.
B040C026V057	40	26	57	And those having seized Jesus led [Him] away to Caiaphas the high priest, where the scribes and the elders were gathered together.
B040C026V058	40	26	58	But Peter was following Him from a distance, up to the courtyard of the high priest. And entering inside, he sat down with the attendants to see the end.
B040C026V059	40	26	59	Now the chief priests, the elders, and all the Sanhedrin were seeking false witnesses against Jesus, so that they might put Him to death,
B040C026V060	40	26	60	and they did not find [any]. And though many false witnesses came forward, they did not find [any]. But at last two false witnesses came forward
B040C026V061	40	26	61	and said, "This [Man] said, 'I am able to destroy the temple of God, and after three days to rebuild it.' "
B040C026V062	40	26	62	And standing up the high priest said to Him, "Do You answer nothing? What is it these men are testifying against You?"
B040C026V063	40	26	63	But Jesus kept silent. And the high priest answered and said to Him, "I adjure You by the living God: Tell us if You are the Christ, the Son of God!"
B040C026V064	40	26	64	Jesus said to him, "You said [it]. Nevertheless, I say to you, from now [on,] you will see the Son of Man sitting at the right hand of the Power, and coming on the clouds of heaven."
B040C026V065	40	26	65	Then the high priest tore his clothes, saying, "He has blasphemed! What further need do we have of witnesses? Look, now you have heard His blasphemy!
B040C026V066	40	26	66	What do you think?"They answered and said, "He is deserving of death."
B040C026V067	40	26	67	Then they spat in His face, and beat Him with [their] fists; and they slapped [Him,]
B040C026V068	40	26	68	saying, "Prophesy to us, Christ! Who is he that struck You?"
B040C026V069	40	26	69	Now Peter sat outside in the courtyard. And a servant girl came to him, saying, "You also were with Jesus of Galilee."
B040C026V070	40	26	70	But he denied it before them all, saying, "I do not know what you are saying."
B040C026V071	40	26	71	And when he had gone out to the gateway, another [girl] saw him and said to them there, "This [man] was with Jesus the Nazarene."
B040C026V072	40	26	72	But again he denied with an oath, "I do not know the Man!"
B040C026V073	40	26	73	And after a little [while], those standing by came up and said to Peter, "Surely you also are one of them, for your accent gives you away."
B040C026V074	40	26	74	Then he began to curse and swear, saying, "I do not know the Man!"And immediately a rooster crowed.
B040C026V075	40	26	75	And Peter remembered the word of Jesus which He said to him, "Before the rooster crows, you will deny Me three times."And going out, he wept bitterly.
B040C027V001	40	27	1	When morning came, all the chief priests and elders of the people plotted against Jesus, so as to put Him to death.
B040C027V002	40	27	2	And having bound Him, they led Him away and delivered Him to Pontius Pilate the governor.
B040C027V003	40	27	3	Then Judas, the [one] betraying Him, seeing that He was condemned, feeling regret, returned the thirty silver [coins] to the chief priests and elders,
B040C027V004	40	27	4	saying, "I have sinned by betraying innocent blood."And they said, "What is [that] to us? You see to it!"
B040C027V005	40	27	5	And throwing the silver [coins] in the sanctuary, he departed; and going away, he hanged himself.
B040C027V006	40	27	6	But the chief priests, taking the silver [coins] said, "It is not lawful to put them into the temple treasury, since they are the price of blood."
B040C027V007	40	27	7	And taking counsel, they bought with them the potter's field, to bury strangers in.
B040C027V008	40	27	8	Therefore that field has been called the Field of Blood to this day.
B040C027V009	40	27	9	Then was fulfilled the thing spoken through Jeremiah the prophet, saying, "And they took the thirty [coins], the value of Him who was priced, whom they of the sons of Israel priced,
B040C027V010	40	27	10	"and they gave them for the potter's field, as the LORD directed me."
B040C027V011	40	27	11	Now Jesus stood before the governor. And the governor asked Him, saying, "Are You the King of the Jews?"So Jesus said to him, "It is as you say."
B040C027V012	40	27	12	And while He was being accused by the chief priests and elders, He answered nothing.
B040C027V013	40	27	13	Then Pilate said to Him, "Do You not hear how many things they testify against You?"
B040C027V014	40	27	14	And He answered him not one word, so that the governor was greatly amazed.
B040C027V015	40	27	15	Now at the feast, the governor was accustomed to release to the crowd one prisoner whom they wished.
B040C027V016	40	27	16	And they had then a notorious prisoner called Barabbas.
B040C027V017	40	27	17	Therefore when they had assembled, Pilate said to them, "Whom do you wish [that] I should release to you, Barabbas, or Jesus who is called Christ?"
B040C027V018	40	27	18	For he knew that they had handed Him over because of envy.
B040C027V019	40	27	19	Now as he was sitting on the judgment seat, his wife sent to him, saying, "Have nothing to do with that just Man, for I have suffered many things today in a dream because of Him."
B040C027V020	40	27	20	But the chief priests and elders persuaded the crowds that they should ask for Barabbas, but they should destroy Jesus.
B040C027V021	40	27	21	The governor answered and said to them, "Which of the two do you wish me to release to you?"They said, "Barabbas!"
B040C027V022	40	27	22	Pilate said to them, "What then shall I do with Jesus who is called Christ?"They all said to him, "Let Him be crucified!"
B040C027V023	40	27	23	Then the governor said, "Why, what evil did He do?"But they cried out all the more, saying, "Let Him be crucified!"
B040C027V024	40	27	24	And Pilate, seeing that nothing was being gained, but rather a riot was starting, taking water, he washed his hands clean in front of the crowd, saying, "I am innocent of the blood of this just [Man]. You see to it."
B040C027V025	40	27	25	And all the people answered and said, "His blood [be] on us and on our children."
B040C027V026	40	27	26	Then he released Barabbas to them; and having scourged Jesus, he delivered Him to be crucified.
B040C027V027	40	27	27	Then the soldiers of the governor, having taken Jesus to the Praetorium, gathered the whole garrison around Him.
B040C027V028	40	27	28	And having stripped Him, they put a scarlet robe on Him.
B040C027V029	40	27	29	When they had twisted a crown of thorns, they put it on His head, and a reed in His right hand. And kneeling before Him, they mocked Him, saying, "Hail, King of the Jews!"
B040C027V030	40	27	30	And spitting on Him, they took the reed and were striking [Him] on His head.
B040C027V031	40	27	31	And when they had mocked Him, they stripped Him of the robe, and dressed Him in His own clothes, and led Him away in order to crucify [Him].
B040C027V032	40	27	32	And going out, they found a man of Cyrene, Simon by name. Him they pressed into service that he might carry His cross.
B040C027V033	40	27	33	And coming to a place called Golgotha, that is to say, Place of a Skull,
B040C027V034	40	27	34	they gave Him sour wine mingled with gall to drink. But having tasted it, He would not drink.
B040C027V035	40	27	35	And having crucified Him, they divided His clothes among themselves,[ ]casting lots.
B040C027V036	40	27	36	And sitting down, they guarded Him there.
B040C027V037	40	27	37	And they put up over His head the crime having been written [against] Him: THIS IS JESUS THE KING OF THE JEWS.
B040C027V038	40	27	38	Then they crucified two thieves with Him, one on His right, and another on His left.
B040C027V039	40	27	39	And those passing by were blaspheming Him, shaking their heads
B040C027V040	40	27	40	and saying, "You[ ]who destroy the temple and build it in three days, save Yourself! If You are the Son of God, come down from the cross."
B040C027V041	40	27	41	Likewise the chief priests also, mocking [Him ]with the scribes and elders, and Pharisees, said,
B040C027V042	40	27	42	He saved others; Himself He cannot save. If He is the King of Israel, let Him now come down from the cross, and we will believe on Him.
B040C027V043	40	27	43	He trusted in God; let Him deliver Him now if He'll [have] Him; for He said, 'I am the Son of God.' "
B040C027V044	40	27	44	Even the thieves who were crucified with Him were reviling Him with the same [insult].
B040C027V045	40	27	45	Now from the sixth hour until the ninth hour, darkness came upon all the land.
B040C027V046	40	27	46	And about the ninth hour Jesus cried out with a loud voice, saying, "Eli, Eli, lima sabachthani?"that is, "My God, My God, why have You forsaken Me?"
B040C027V047	40	27	47	Some of those standing [by], when they heard this, said, "This [Man] is calling Elijah!"
B040C027V048	40	27	48	Immediately one of them ran and took a sponge, and filled it with sour wine and put it around a reed, and offered it to Him to drink.
B040C027V049	40	27	49	But the rest said, "Leave [Him] alone; let us see if Elijah is coming to save Him."
B040C027V050	40	27	50	But Jesus, again crying out with a loud voice, released His spirit.
B040C027V051	40	27	51	And behold, the veil of the temple was torn in two from top to bottom; and the earth was shaken, and the rocks were split,
B040C027V052	40	27	52	and the tombs were opened; and many bodies of the saints who had passed away were raised;
B040C027V053	40	27	53	and coming forth out of the tombs after His resurrection, they entered into the holy city and appeared to many.
B040C027V054	40	27	54	So when the centurion and those with him guarding Jesus, when they saw the earthquake and the things that had happened, they were greatly afraid, saying, "Truly this was the Son of God!"
B040C027V055	40	27	55	And there were many women there observing from a distance, who followed Jesus from Galilee, ministering to Him,
B040C027V056	40	27	56	among whom were Mary Magdalene, Mary the mother of James and Joses, and the mother of the sons of Zebedee.
B040C027V057	40	27	57	Now when evening had come, there came a rich man from Arimathea, named Joseph, who himself had also become a disciple of Jesus.
B040C027V058	40	27	58	This [man] went to Pilate and asked for the body of Jesus. Then Pilate commanded the body to be given to him.
B040C027V059	40	27	59	And taking the body, Joseph wrapped it up in a clean linen cloth,
B040C027V060	40	27	60	and placed it in his new tomb which he had cut in the rock; and having rolled a large stone [against] the door of the tomb, he departed.
B040C027V061	40	27	61	And Mary Magdalene was there, and the other Mary, sitting opposite the grave.
B040C027V062	40	27	62	On the next day, which is after the Preparation [Day], the chief priests and Pharisees were gathered together to Pilate,
B040C027V063	40	27	63	saying, "Sir, we remember that that deceiver said while He was still alive, 'After three days I will rise.'
B040C027V064	40	27	64	"Therefore command that the grave be made secure until the third day, lest His disciples come by night and steal Him, and say to the people, 'He was raised from the dead.' So the last deception will be worse [than] the first."
B040C027V065	40	27	65	Pilate said to them, "You have a guard; go make it as secure as you know [how]."
B040C027V066	40	27	66	So they went and secured the grave, sealing the stone, with the guard.
B040C028V001	40	28	1	But after [the] Sabbath, at the dawning toward [the] first [day] of the week, Mary Magdalene and the other Mary came to see the tomb.
B040C028V002	40	28	2	And behold, a great earthquake occurred; for an angel of the Lord, having come down out of heaven, came and rolled back the stone from the door, and sat on it.
B040C028V003	40	28	3	And His appearance was like lightning, and his clothing as white as snow.
B040C028V004	40	28	4	And the guards were shaken for fear of him, and became like dead [men].
B040C028V005	40	28	5	But the angel answered and said to the women, "Do not be afraid, for I know that you seek Jesus who was crucified.
B040C028V006	40	28	6	He is not here! For He is risen, just as He said. Come; see the place where the Lord was lying.
B040C028V007	40	28	7	And go quickly and tell His disciples that He is risen from the dead, and behold, He is going before you into Galilee; there you will see Him. Behold, I have told you."
B040C028V008	40	28	8	And going out quickly from the tomb with fear and great joy, they ran to report to His disciples.
B040C028V009	40	28	9	And as they were going to report to His disciples, that behold, Jesus met them, saying, "Rejoice!"So they came and held His feet and worshipped Him.
B040C028V010	40	28	10	Then Jesus said to them, "Do not be afraid. Go, report to My brothers that they should go to Galilee, and there they will see Me."
B040C028V011	40	28	11	Now while they were going, behold, some of the guard came into the city and reported to the chief priests everything that had happened.
B040C028V012	40	28	12	When they had assembled with the elders and taking counsel, they gave sufficient silver [coins] to the soldiers,
B040C028V013	40	28	13	saying, "Tell them, 'His disciples came at night and stole Him away while we were sleeping.'
B040C028V014	40	28	14	"And if this reaches the governor's ears, we will influence him and make you secure."
B040C028V015	40	28	15	So they took the silver and did as they were instructed. And this saying has been widely spread among the Jews until this day.
B040C028V016	40	28	16	Then the eleven disciples went to Galilee, to the mountain which Jesus had appointed for them.
B040C028V017	40	28	17	When they saw Him, they worshipped Him; but some doubted.
B040C028V018	40	28	18	And Jesus came and spoke to them, saying, "All authority in heaven and on earth has been given to Me.
B040C028V019	40	28	19	Go [therefore] and make disciples of all the nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit,
B040C028V020	40	28	20	teaching them to observe everything that I have commanded you; and lo, I am with you always, even to the end of the age."Amen.
B041C001V001	41	1	1	. THE BEGINNING OF THE GOSPEL OF JESUS CHRIST, THE SON OF GOD.
B041C001V002	41	1	2	As it is written in the Prophets: "Behold, I send My messenger before Your face, who will prepare Your way before You."
B041C001V003	41	1	3	"A voice of one crying in the wilderness: 'In the wilderness prepare the way of the LORD; make His paths straight.' "
B041C001V004	41	1	4	John came baptizing in the wilderness and preaching a baptism of repentance for the forgiveness of sins.
B041C001V005	41	1	5	And all the Judean country and the inhabitants of Jerusalem went out to him and were all baptized by him in the Jordan River, confessing their sins.
B041C001V006	41	1	6	Now John was clothed with camel's hair and with a leather belt around his waist, and was eating locusts and wild honey.
B041C001V007	41	1	7	And he was preaching, saying, "There comes One after me who is stronger than me, of whom I am not worthy to stoop down and to loose the strap of His[ ]sandal.
B041C001V008	41	1	8	I baptized you in water, but He will baptize you in the Holy Spirit."
B041C001V009	41	1	9	It came to pass in those days that Jesus came from Nazareth of Galilee, and was baptized by John in the Jordan.
B041C001V010	41	1	10	And immediately, coming up from the water, He saw the heavens parting and the Spirit coming down upon Him like a dove.
B041C001V011	41	1	11	Then a voice came from the heavens, "You are My beloved Son, in whom I have found delight."
B041C001V012	41	1	12	And immediately the Spirit drove Him into the wilderness.
B041C001V013	41	1	13	And He was there in the wilderness forty days, being tempted by Satan, and was with the wild animals; and the angels were ministering to Him.
B041C001V014	41	1	14	Now after John was imprisoned, Jesus came to Galilee, preaching the gospel of the kingdom of God,
B041C001V015	41	1	15	and saying, "The time has been fulfilled, and the kingdom of God is at hand. Repent, and believe in the gospel."
B041C001V016	41	1	16	And as He was walking alongside the Sea of Galilee, He saw Simon and Andrew his brother casting a net into the sea; for they were fishermen.
B041C001V017	41	1	17	Then Jesus said to them, "Come after Me, and I will make you become fishers of men."
B041C001V018	41	1	18	And immediately leaving their nets they followed Him.
B041C001V019	41	1	19	And having gone forth from there a little, He saw James the son of Zebedee, and John his brother, who also were in the boat mending their nets.
B041C001V020	41	1	20	And immediately He called them. And after they left their father Zebedee in the boat with the hired workers, they went away after Him.
B041C001V021	41	1	21	And they were going into Capernaum. And immediately on the Sabbath, He entered the synagogue and began teaching.
B041C001V022	41	1	22	And they were astonished at His doctrine, for He was teaching them as one who had authority, and not as the scribes.
B041C001V023	41	1	23	Now there was a man in their synagogue with an unclean spirit, and he cried out,
B041C001V024	41	1	24	saying, "Let us alone! What have we to do with You, Jesus of Nazareth? Have You come to destroy us? I know who You are-the Holy One of God!"
B041C001V025	41	1	25	But Jesus rebuked him, saying, "Be silent, and come out of him!"
B041C001V026	41	1	26	And when the unclean spirit threw him into a convulsion, and crying out with a loud voice, came out from him.
B041C001V027	41	1	27	Then they were all amazed, so that they were disputing among themselves, saying, "What is this? What new doctrine is this, that He commands even the unclean spirits with authority, and they obey Him?"
B041C001V028	41	1	28	And immediately the report of Him went out into the whole surrounding region of Galilee.
B041C001V029	41	1	29	And immediately when they went out from the synagogue, they came to the house of Simon and Andrew, with James and John.
B041C001V030	41	1	30	And the mother-in-law of Simon was lying sick with a fever, and immediately they spoke to Him about her.
B041C001V031	41	1	31	So He came and He raised her up, grasping her hand; and immediately the fever left her. And she began to serve them.
B041C001V032	41	1	32	Now when evening came, when the sun set, they were bringing to Him all those who were ill, and those who were demon-possessed.
B041C001V033	41	1	33	And the whole city was gathered together at the door.
B041C001V034	41	1	34	And He healed many who were ill with various diseases, and He cast out many demons; and He did not allow the demons to speak, because they knew who He was.
B041C001V035	41	1	35	And in the very early morning before dawn, He arose and He went out, and went away to a deserted place; and there He was praying.
B041C001V036	41	1	36	And Simon and those who were with Him sought Him out.
B041C001V037	41	1	37	When they found Him, they said to Him, "Everyone is looking for You."
B041C001V038	41	1	38	But He said to them, "Let us go to the neighboring towns, that I may preach there also, because for this reason I have come forth."
B041C001V039	41	1	39	And He was preaching in their synagogues throughout all Galilee, and casting out demons.
B041C001V040	41	1	40	Then a leper came to Him, beseeching Him, kneeling before Him and saying to Him, "If You are willing, You are able to cleanse me."
B041C001V041	41	1	41	And Jesus, being moved with compassion, [and] reaching out His hand, touched him, and said to him, "I am willing, be cleansed."
B041C001V042	41	1	42	And when He said this, immediately the leprosy left from him, and he was cleansed.
