B041C014V056	41	14	56	For many were testifying falsely against Him, but their testimonies were not the same.
B041C014V057	41	14	57	Then some stood up and were testifying falsely against Him, saying,
B041C014V058	41	14	58	"We heard Him saying, 'I will destroy this temple made with hands, and after three days I will build another [one ]not made with hands.' "
B041C014V059	41	14	59	But not even in this way was their testimony the same.
B041C014V060	41	14	60	And the high priest stood up and came forward and questioned Jesus, saying, "Do You answer nothing? What are these men testifying against You?"
B041C014V061	41	14	61	But He kept silent and answered nothing. Again the high priest was questioning Him, saying to Him, "Are You the Christ, the Son of the Blessed?"
B041C014V062	41	14	62	And Jesus said, "I am. And you will see the Son of Man sitting at the right hand of the Power, and coming with the clouds of heaven."
B041C014V063	41	14	63	Then the high priest tore his clothes and said, "What further need do we have of witnesses?
B041C014V064	41	14	64	You have heard the blasphemy! How does it appear to you?"And they all condemned Him to be deserving of death.
B041C014V065	41	14	65	Then some began to spit on Him, and to blindfold Him, and to beat Him with [their] fists, and to say to Him, "Prophesy!"And the attendants were striking Him with slaps [to the face.]
B041C014V066	41	14	66	Now as Peter was below in the courtyard, one of the servant girls of the high priest came.
B041C014V067	41	14	67	And when she saw Peter warming himself, she looked at him and said, "You also were with Jesus the Nazarene."
B041C014V068	41	14	68	But he denied it, saying, "I neither know nor understand what you are saying."And he went outside into the forecourt, and a rooster crowed.
B041C014V069	41	14	69	And the servant girl seeing him again, began to say to those standing by, "This [man] is one of them."
B041C014V070	41	14	70	But again he was denying [it]. And a little later those who were standing by said to Peter again, "Truly you are one of them; for you are also a Galilean, and your accent is like [theirs]."
B041C014V071	41	14	71	Then he began to curse and to swear, "I do not know this Man whom you are speaking of"
B041C014V072	41	14	72	And for the second [time] a rooster crowed. Then Peter remembered the word that Jesus had said to him, "Before a rooster crows twice, you will deny Me three times."And when he thought about it, he began to weep.
B041C015V001	41	15	1	Immediately, in the morning, the chief priests held a consultation, along with the elders and scribes and the whole Sanhedrin; and having bound Jesus, they led [Him] away, and delivered [Him] to Pilate.
B041C015V002	41	15	2	Then Pilate asked Him, "Are You the King of the Jews?"And He answered and said to him, "You are saying [what is so]."
B041C015V003	41	15	3	And the chief priests were accusing Him of many things.
B041C015V004	41	15	4	Then Pilate questioned Him again, saying, "Do You answer nothing? See how many things they testify against You!"
B041C015V005	41	15	5	But Jesus no longer answered anything, so that Pilate marveled.
B041C015V006	41	15	6	Now at the feast he would release one prisoner to them, whomever they would request.
B041C015V007	41	15	7	And there was one called Barabbas, having been bound with his fellow rebels, who had committed murder in the rebellion.
B041C015V008	41	15	8	Then the crowd cried out and began to request [that] just as always he would do [this] for them.
B041C015V009	41	15	9	But Pilate answered them, saying, "Do you desire that I release to you the King of the Jews?"
B041C015V010	41	15	10	For he knew that because of envy the chief priests had delivered Him up.
B041C015V011	41	15	11	But the chief priests stirred up the crowd, so that he should rather release Barabbas to them.
B041C015V012	41	15	12	But Pilate answered and said to them again, "What then do you desire [that] I should do [with Him ]whom you call King of the Jews?"
B041C015V013	41	15	13	And again they cried, "Crucify Him!"
B041C015V014	41	15	14	But Pilate said to them, "Why, what evil did He do?"But they cried out all the more, "Crucify Him!"
B041C015V015	41	15	15	So Pilate, wanting to gratify the crowd, released Barabbas to them; and he delivered up Jesus, after he had Him flogged, so that He might be crucified.
B041C015V016	41	15	16	Then the soldiers led Him away into the courtyard, which is the Praetorium, and assembled the whole garrison.
B041C015V017	41	15	17	And they clothed Him with purple; and they twisted a crown of thorns, and they put it around His head,
B041C015V018	41	15	18	and they began to salute Him, "Hail, King of the Jews!"
B041C015V019	41	15	19	And they were striking His head with a reed and were spitting on Him; and bowing the knee, they [mockingly ]worshipped Him.
B041C015V020	41	15	20	And when they had mocked Him, they stripped Him of the purple, and dressed Him in His own clothing. And led Him out so that they might crucify Him.
B041C015V021	41	15	21	And they pressed into service a certain [man] [that was] passing by [named] Simon, a Cyrenian, the father of Alexander and Rufus, as he was coming from the country, that he might carry His cross.
B041C015V022	41	15	22	And they brought Him to the place [called ]Golgotha, which is translated, Place of a Skull.
B041C015V023	41	15	23	And they gave Him wine mingled with myrrh to drink, but He did not take it.
B041C015V024	41	15	24	And having crucified Him, they divided His clothes by casting lots over them,[ to determine] who would take what.
B041C015V025	41	15	25	Now it was the third hour, and they crucified Him.
B041C015V026	41	15	26	And there was the inscription of His charge having been inscribed: THE KING OF THE JEWS.
B041C015V027	41	15	27	And together with Him they crucified two bandits, one on His right side and the one on His left.
B041C015V028	41	15	28	So the Scripture was fulfilled which says, "And He was numbered with the transgressors."
B041C015V029	41	15	29	And those passing by were blaspheming Him, shaking their heads and saying, "Aha! You who destroy the temple and build it in three days,
B041C015V030	41	15	30	save Yourself, and come down from the cross!"
B041C015V031	41	15	31	Likewise the chief priests also, mocking [Him] to each other with the scribes said, "He saved others; Himself He is not able to save.
B041C015V032	41	15	32	Let the Christ, the King of Israel, come down now from the cross, so that we may see and believe Him."Even those who were crucified with Him were reviling Him.
B041C015V033	41	15	33	Now when the sixth hour had come, darkness came upon the whole land until the ninth hour.
B041C015V034	41	15	34	And at the ninth hour Jesus cried out with a loud voice, saying, "Eloi, Eloi, lima sabachthani?"which is translated, "My God, My God, why have You forsaken Me?"
B041C015V035	41	15	35	Some of those standing by when they heard, said, "Look, He is calling Elijah."
B041C015V036	41	15	36	And one, running and having filled a sponge [with] vinegar, and having put it around a reed, was giving a drink to Him, saying, "Leave Him alone; let us see if Elijah is coming to take Him down."
B041C015V037	41	15	37	And Jesus, uttering a loud cry, expired.
B041C015V038	41	15	38	Then the veil of the temple was torn in two from top to bottom.
B041C015V039	41	15	39	Now when the centurion who stood across from Him saw that He cried out like this and breathed His last, he said, "Truly this Man was the Son of God!"
B041C015V040	41	15	40	There were also women looking on from a distance, among whom were both Mary Magdalene, Mary the mother of James the Less and of Joses, and Salome,
B041C015V041	41	15	41	who also would follow Him and would minister to Him when He was in Galilee; and many other women who had come up together with Him to Jerusalem.
B041C015V042	41	15	42	And now evening having come, since it was Preparation Day, which is the day before the Sabbath,
B041C015V043	41	15	43	Joseph of Arimathea, a prominent council member, who was himself waiting for the kingdom of God, coming and taking courage, he went in to Pilate and asked for the body of Jesus.
B041C015V044	41	15	44	And Pilate wondered if He was already dead; and having summoned the centurion, he questioned him if He had been dead long.
B041C015V045	41	15	45	And when he found out from the centurion, he granted the body to Joseph.
B041C015V046	41	15	46	And having bought linen cloth, and having taken Him down, he wrapped Him in the linen cloth and set Him down in a tomb which had been cut out of a rock, and rolled a stone upon the door of the tomb.
B041C015V047	41	15	47	And Mary Magdalene and Mary [the mother] of Joses were observing where He was placed.
B041C016V001	41	16	1	Now when the Sabbath was past, Mary Magdalene, and Mary[ the mother] of James, and Salome bought spices, so that they might come and anoint Him.
B041C016V002	41	16	2	And very early on the first day of the week, they came to the tomb when the sun had risen.
B041C016V003	41	16	3	And they said to one another, "Who will roll away the stone from the door of the tomb for us?"
B041C016V004	41	16	4	And having looked up, they saw that the stone had been rolled away-for it was exceedingly large.
B041C016V005	41	16	5	And entering into the tomb, they saw a young man sitting on the right clothed with a white robe, and they were alarmed.
B041C016V006	41	16	6	But he said to them, "Do not be alarmed. You are seeking Jesus the Nazarene, who was crucified. He has arisen! He is not here! See the place where they put Him.
B041C016V007	41	16	7	But go, say to His disciples, and Peter, that He is going before you into Galilee; there you shall see Him, just as He said to you."
B041C016V008	41	16	8	And going out, they fled from the tomb, but trembling and amazement held them; and they said nothing to anyone, for they were afraid.
B041C016V009	41	16	9	Now having arisen early on the first day of the week, He appeared first to Mary Magdalene, from whom He had cast out seven demons.
B041C016V010	41	16	10	She went and reported to those who had been with Him, as they were grieving and weeping.
B041C016V011	41	16	11	And those, when they heard that He was alive and had been seen by her, [they ]disbelieved.
B041C016V012	41	16	12	After that, He appeared in a different form to two of them as they were going into the country.
B041C016V013	41	16	13	And those returned and reported it to the rest; but neither did they believe them.
B041C016V014	41	16	14	Afterwards He appeared to the eleven as they were reclining at the table; and He rebuked their unbelief and hardness of heart, because they did not believe those who saw Him after He had been raised.
B041C016V015	41	16	15	And He said to them, "Go into all the world and proclaim the gospel to all creation.
B041C016V016	41	16	16	He that believes and is baptized shall be saved; but he that does not believe shall be condemned.
B041C016V017	41	16	17	And these signs shall accompany those who have believed: In My name they shall cast out demons; they shall speak with new tongues;
B041C016V018	41	16	18	they shall pick up serpents; and if they drink anything deadly, it shall by no means hurt them; they shall lay hands on [the] sick, and they shall be well."
B041C016V019	41	16	19	So then, after the Lord had spoken to them, He was taken up into heaven, and sat down at the right hand of God.
B041C016V020	41	16	20	And they went out and preached everywhere, the Lord working with [them] and confirming the word through the accompanying signs. Amen.
B042C001V001	42	1	1	Since many have attempted to arrange a narrative about the matters which have taken place among us,
B042C001V002	42	1	2	just as those who from the beginning were eyewitnesses and ministers of the word delivered [them] to us,
B042C001V003	42	1	3	it seemed good to me also, having followed up accurately all things from above, to write to you in orderly fashion, most distinguished Theophilus,
B042C001V004	42	1	4	so that you may know the certainty of those things in which you were instructed.
B042C001V005	42	1	5	There was in the days of Herod, the king of Judea, a certain priest named Zacharias, of the division of Abijah. His wife was of the daughters of Aaron, and her name was Elizabeth.
B042C001V006	42	1	6	And they were both righteous before God, walking in all the commandments and ordinances of the Lord blameless.
B042C001V007	42	1	7	But they had no children, because Elizabeth was barren, and they were both well advanced in years.
B042C001V008	42	1	8	So it was, that while he was serving as priest before God in the order of his division,
B042C001V009	42	1	9	according to the custom of the priesthood, he was selected to burn incense when he entered into the temple of the Lord.
B042C001V010	42	1	10	And all the multitude of the people were praying outside at the hour of incense.
B042C001V011	42	1	11	Then an angel of the Lord appeared to him, standing on the right side of the altar of incense.
B042C001V012	42	1	12	And when Zacharias saw him, he was troubled, and fear fell upon him.
B042C001V013	42	1	13	But the angel said to him, "Do not be afraid, Zacharias, because your prayer has been heard; and your wife Elizabeth will bear a son to you, and you shall call his name John.
B042C001V014	42	1	14	And you will have joy and gladness, and many will rejoice at his birth.
B042C001V015	42	1	15	For he shall be great before the Lord, and shall drink neither wine nor strong drink. He will also be filled with the Holy Spirit, while still in his mother's womb.
B042C001V016	42	1	16	And he will turn many of the sons of Israel to the Lord their God.
B042C001V017	42	1	17	And he himself will go before Him in the spirit and power of Elijah, 'to turn the hearts of the fathers to the children,' and the disobedient to the wisdom of the righteous, to make ready a people prepared for the Lord."
B042C001V018	42	1	18	And Zacharias said to the angel, "How shall I know this? For I am an old man, and my wife is well advanced in years."
B042C001V019	42	1	19	And the angel answered and said to him, "I am Gabriel, who stands before God, and I was sent to speak to you and to proclaim the good news to you of these things[.]
B042C001V020	42	1	20	But behold, you shall be silent and not able to speak until the day these things take place, because you did not believe my words which shall be fulfilled in their season."
B042C001V021	42	1	21	And the people waited for Zacharias, and they marveled at his delaying in the temple.
B042C001V022	42	1	22	But having come out, he was unable to speak to them; and they recognized that he had seen a vision in the temple, for he was making signs to them and remained speechless.
B042C001V023	42	1	23	And it happened, as soon as the days of his service were fulfilled, that he went away to his house.
B042C001V024	42	1	24	Now after those days Elizabeth his wife conceived; and stayed in seclusion five months, saying,
B042C001V025	42	1	25	"Thus the Lord has dealt with me, in the days when He looked on [me], to take away my reproach among men."
B042C001V026	42	1	26	Now in the sixth month the angel Gabriel was sent by God to a city of Galilee named Nazareth,
B042C001V027	42	1	27	to a virgin betrothed to a man named Joseph, of the house of David. The virgin's name [was] Mary.
B042C001V028	42	1	28	And the angel came to her and said, "Greetings, O favored [one], the Lord is with you; blessed [are] you among women!"
B042C001V029	42	1	29	But when she saw [him], she was greatly perplexed by his saying, and she wondered what sort of greeting this was.
B042C001V030	42	1	30	Then the angel said to her, "Fear not, Mary, for you have found grace with God.
B042C001V031	42	1	31	And behold, you shall conceive in your womb and bring forth a Son, and you shall call His name JESUS.
B042C001V032	42	1	32	He shall be great, and shall be called the Son of the Most High; and the Lord God shall give Him the throne of His father David.
B042C001V033	42	1	33	And He shall reign over the house of Jacob forever, and of His kingdom there shall be no end."
B042C001V034	42	1	34	Then Mary said to the angel, "How can this be, since I do not know a man?"
B042C001V035	42	1	35	And the angel answered and said to her, "The Holy Spirit shall come upon you, and the power of the Most High shall overshadow you; therefore, also, that Holy Baby which is to be born shall be called the Son of God.
B042C001V036	42	1	36	And behold, Elizabeth your relative has also conceived a son in her old age; and this is now the sixth month for she who was called barren.
B042C001V037	42	1	37	For with God nothing shall be impossible."
B042C001V038	42	1	38	Then Mary said, "Behold the maidservant of the Lord! May it be to me according to your word."And the angel departed from her.
B042C001V039	42	1	39	Now Mary rose up in those days and traveled into the hill country with haste, to a city of Judah,
B042C001V040	42	1	40	and entered the house of Zacharias and greeted Elizabeth.
B042C001V041	42	1	41	And it came to pass, that when Elizabeth heard the greeting of Mary, that the baby leaped in her womb; and Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Spirit.
B042C001V042	42	1	42	Then she spoke out with a loud voice and said, "Blessed are you among women, and blessed is the fruit of your womb!
B042C001V043	42	1	43	And why am I favored thus, that the mother of my Lord should come to me?
B042C001V044	42	1	44	For behold, as soon as the voice of your greeting sounded in my ears, the baby leaped for joy in my womb.
B042C001V045	42	1	45	And blessed is she who has believed, because there shall be a fulfillment to the things having been spoken to her from the Lord."
B042C001V046	42	1	46	And Mary said: "My soul magnifies the Lord,
B042C001V047	42	1	47	and my spirit has rejoiced in God my Savior.
B042C001V048	42	1	48	Because He looked upon the lowly state of His maidservant; for behold, henceforth all generations will call me blessed.
B042C001V049	42	1	49	For He that is mighty has done great things for me, and holy is His name.
B042C001V050	42	1	50	And His mercy is on those who fear Him from generation to generation.
B042C001V051	42	1	51	He has shown strength with His arm; He has scattered the proud in the imagination of their hearts.
B042C001V052	42	1	52	He has overthrown the mighty from their thrones, and exalted the lowly.
B042C001V053	42	1	53	He has filled the hungry with good things, and the rich He has sent away empty.
B042C001V054	42	1	54	He has helped His servant Israel, in remembrance of His mercy,
B042C001V055	42	1	55	As He spoke to our fathers, to Abraham and to his seed forever."
B042C001V056	42	1	56	And Mary remained with her about three months, and she returned to her house.
B042C001V057	42	1	57	Now Elizabeth's full time came for her to be delivered, and she bore a son.
B042C001V058	42	1	58	And when her neighbors and relatives heard how the Lord had shown great mercy to her, they rejoiced with her.
B042C001V059	42	1	59	Now it came to pass on the eighth day, [that] they came to circumcise the child; and they started to call him by the name of his father, Zacharias.
B042C001V060	42	1	60	His mother answered and said, "No; he shall be called John."
B042C001V061	42	1	61	But they said to her, "There is no one among your relatives who is called by this name."
B042C001V062	42	1	62	So they made signs to his father about what he wished him to be called.
B042C001V063	42	1	63	And asking for a writing tablet, he wrote, saying, "His name is John."And they all marveled.
B042C001V064	42	1	64	Immediately his mouth was opened and his tongue loosed, and he started to speak, praising God.
B042C001V065	42	1	65	Then fear came on all who lived around them; and all these things were being talked about throughout all the hill country of Judea.
B042C001V066	42	1	66	And all those who heard them kept them in their hearts, saying, "What kind of child will this be?"And the hand of the Lord was with him.
B042C001V067	42	1	67	Now his father Zacharias was filled with the Holy Spirit, and he prophesied, saying,
B042C001V068	42	1	68	"Blessed be the Lord God of Israel, for He has visited and redeemed His people,
B042C001V069	42	1	69	and has raised up a horn of salvation for us in the house of His servant David,
B042C001V070	42	1	70	as He spoke by the mouth of His holy prophets, who have been since the world began,
B042C001V071	42	1	71	that we should be saved from our enemies and from the hand of all who hate us,
B042C001V072	42	1	72	to perform the mercy [promised] to our fathers and to remember His holy covenant,
B042C001V073	42	1	73	the oath which He swore to our father Abraham:
B042C001V074	42	1	74	to grant us that we, being delivered from the hand of our enemies, might serve Him without fear,
B042C001V075	42	1	75	in holiness and righteousness before Him all the days of our life.
B042C001V076	42	1	76	"And you, child, will be called the prophet of the Highest; for you will go before the face of the Lord to prepare His ways,
B042C001V077	42	1	77	to give knowledge of salvation to His people by the remission of their sins,
B042C001V078	42	1	78	through the tender mercy of our God, with which the Dayspring from on high has visited us;
B042C001V079	42	1	79	to give light to them that sit in darkness and [in ]the shadow of death, to guide our feet into the way of peace."
B042C001V080	42	1	80	So the child grew and became strong in spirit, and was in the deserts till the day of his manifestation to Israel.
B042C002V001	42	2	1	And it came to pass in those days that a decree went out from Caesar Augustus that a census be taken of all the empire.
B042C002V002	42	2	2	This census [was ]the first [one] while Quirinius was governing Syria.
B042C002V003	42	2	3	And all were traveling to be registered, each to his own city.
B042C002V004	42	2	4	Joseph also went up from Galilee, out of the city of Nazareth, into Judea, to the city of David, which is called Bethlehem, because he was of the house and family of David,
B042C002V005	42	2	5	to be registered with Mary, his betrothed wife, who was pregnant.
B042C002V006	42	2	6	So it was, that while they were there, the days were completed [for] her to bear.
B042C002V007	42	2	7	And she bore her firstborn Son, and wrapped Him in swaddling cloths, and laid Him in a manger, because there was no place for them in the inn.
B042C002V008	42	2	8	And shepherds were in the same country, living in the fields and keeping watch over their flock by night.
B042C002V009	42	2	9	And behold, an angel of the Lord stood before them, and the glory of the Lord shone around them, and they were greatly afraid.
B042C002V010	42	2	10	Then the angel said to them, "Fear not, for behold, I bring you good tidings of great joy which will be to all people.
B042C002V011	42	2	11	For unto you is born this day in the city of David a Savior, who is Christ the Lord.
B042C002V012	42	2	12	And this [will be] the sign to you: You will find a Baby wrapped in swaddling cloths, lying in a manger."
B042C002V013	42	2	13	And suddenly there was with the angel a multitude of the heavenly host praising God and saying:
B042C002V014	42	2	14	"Glory to God in the highest, and on earth peace, goodwill toward men!"
B042C002V015	42	2	15	So it was, when the angels had departed from them into heaven, that the shepherds said to one another, "Let us go then to Bethlehem and see this thing that has come to pass, which the Lord has made known to us."
B042C002V016	42	2	16	And they came with haste and found Mary and Joseph, and the Baby lying in a manger.
B042C002V017	42	2	17	And when they had seen Him, they made widely known the saying which was told them concerning this Child.
B042C002V018	42	2	18	And all those who heard it marveled about the things spoken by the shepherds to them.
B042C002V019	42	2	19	But Mary treasured all these things and pondered [them] in her heart.
B042C002V020	42	2	20	Then the shepherds returned, glorifying and praising God for all the things that they had heard and seen, as it was spoken to them.
B042C002V021	42	2	21	And when eight days were completed, so they could circumcise Him, His name was called JESUS, the [name] given by the angel before He was conceived in the womb.
B042C002V022	42	2	22	Now when the days of their purification according to the law of Moses were completed, they brought Him to Jerusalem to present [Him] to the Lord
B042C002V023	42	2	23	(just as it is written in the law of the Lord, "Every male who opens the womb shall be called holy to the LORD"),
B042C002V024	42	2	24	and to offer a sacrifice according to what had been said in the law of the Lord, "A pair of doves or two young pigeons."
B042C002V025	42	2	25	And behold, there was a man in Jerusalem whose name was Simeon, and this man was just and devout, waiting for the Consolation of Israel, and the Holy Spirit was upon him.
B042C002V026	42	2	26	And it had been revealed to him by the Holy Spirit that he would not see death before he should see the Lord's Christ.
B042C002V027	42	2	27	So he came by the Spirit into the temple. And when the parents brought in the Child Jesus, that they might do for Him according to the custom of the law,
B042C002V028	42	2	28	he took Him up in his arms and blessed God and said:
B042C002V029	42	2	29	"Lord, now You are releasing Your servant in peace, according to Your word;
B042C002V030	42	2	30	for my eyes have seen Your salvation
B042C002V031	42	2	31	which You have prepared before the face of all peoples,
B042C002V032	42	2	32	a light for a revelation to the Gentiles, and a glory to Your people Israel."
B042C002V033	42	2	33	And Joseph and His mother were marveling at the things being spoken about Him.
B042C002V034	42	2	34	Then Simeon blessed them, and said to Mary His mother, "Behold, this Child is destined for the fall and rise of many in Israel, and for a sign which will be spoken against
B042C002V035	42	2	35	(yes, a sword will pierce through your own soul also), so that the thoughts of many hearts may be revealed."
