B042C006V038	42	6	38	Give, and it shall be given to you: good measure, pressed down and shaken and running over they shall give into your bosom. For with the same measure that you use, it shall be measured back to you."
B042C006V039	42	6	39	And He spoke a parable to them: "Can the blind lead the blind? Will they not both fall into the ditch?
B042C006V040	42	6	40	A disciple is not above his teacher, but everyone having been fully trained will be like his teacher.
B042C006V041	42	6	41	And why do you look at the speck in your brother's eye, but do not notice the plank in your own eye?
B042C006V042	42	6	42	Or how can you say to your brother, 'Brother, permit me to remove the speck which is in your eye,' when you yourself do not see the plank that is in your own eye? Hypocrite! First remove the plank out of your own eye, and then you will see clearly to remove the speck which is in your brother's eye.
B042C006V043	42	6	43	"For a good tree does not produce rotten fruit, nor does a rotten tree produce good fruit.
B042C006V044	42	6	44	For each tree is known by its own fruit. For men do not gather figs from thorns, nor do they gather grapes from a thorn bush.
B042C006V045	42	6	45	A good man out of the good treasure of his heart brings forth that which is good; and an evil man out of the evil treasure of his heart brings forth that which is evil. For out of the abundance of the heart his mouth speaks.
B042C006V046	42	6	46	"But why do you call Me 'Lord, Lord,' and do not do [the ]things which I say?
B042C006V047	42	6	47	Everyone who comes to Me, and hears My words and does them, I will show you to whom he is like:
B042C006V048	42	6	48	He is like a man building a house, who dug and went deep and laid a foundation on the rock. And when a flood occurred, the stream burst upon that house, and could not shake it, for it was founded on the rock.
B042C006V049	42	6	49	But he who hears and does not do is like a man building a house on the ground without a foundation, [against] which the stream burst upon; and immediately it fell. And the breaking of that house was great."
B042C007V001	42	7	1	Now when He finished all His sayings in the hearing of the people, He entered Capernaum.
B042C007V002	42	7	2	And a certain centurion's servant, who was highly valued by him, was sick and about to die.
B042C007V003	42	7	3	And when he heard about Jesus, he sent elders of the Jews to Him, asking Him that He might come and heal his servant.
B042C007V004	42	7	4	And when they came to Jesus, they begged Him earnestly, saying he was worthy for whom He should grant this,
B042C007V005	42	7	5	for he loves our nation, and he himself has built us a synagogue."
B042C007V006	42	7	6	Then Jesus went with them. And when He was already not far away from the house, the centurion sent friends to Him, saying to Him, "Lord, do not trouble Yourself, for I am not worthy that You should enter under my roof.
B042C007V007	42	7	7	Therefore I did not even consider myself worthy to come to You. But [just] say the word, and my servant shall be healed.
B042C007V008	42	7	8	For I also am a man appointed under authority, having soldiers under myself. And I say to one, 'Go,' and he goes; and to another, 'Come,' and he comes; and to my servant, 'Do this,' and he does [it]."
B042C007V009	42	7	9	When Jesus heard these things, He marveled at him, and turning to the crowd following Him, He said, "I say to you, I have not found such great faith, not even in Israel!"
B042C007V010	42	7	10	And when those who were sent returned to the house, they found the servant well who had been sick.
B042C007V011	42	7	11	Now it happened on the next [day], that He went into a city called Nain; and many of His disciples went with Him, and a great crowd.
B042C007V012	42	7	12	And when He came near the gate of the city, that behold, a dead man was being carried out, the only son of his mother; and she was a widow. And many people from the city was with her.
B042C007V013	42	7	13	When the Lord saw her, He had compassion on her and said to her, "Do not weep."
B042C007V014	42	7	14	Then He came and touched the open coffin, and those who carried him stood still. And He said, "Young man, I say to you, arise."
B042C007V015	42	7	15	So he who was dead sat up and began to speak. And He gave him to his mother.
B042C007V016	42	7	16	Then fear took hold of all, and they were glorifying God, saying, "A great prophet has risen up among us"; and, "God has visited His people."
B042C007V017	42	7	17	And this report about Him went out in all Judea, and all the surrounding region.
B042C007V018	42	7	18	Then the disciples of John reported to him concerning all these things.
B042C007V019	42	7	19	And summoning two of his disciples, John sent [them] to Jesus, saying, "Are You the Coming [One], or do we look for another?"
B042C007V020	42	7	20	And when they came to Him, the men said, "John the Baptist has sent us to You, saying, 'Are You the Coming [One], or do we look for another?' "
B042C007V021	42	7	21	And in that very hour He healed many from diseases, and torments, and evil spirits; and to many blind [people] He granted sight.
B042C007V022	42	7	22	Then Jesus answered and said to them, "Go and report to John what you have seen and heard: that the blind regain sight, the lame walk, the lepers are cleansed, the deaf hear, the dead are raised, the poor are evangelized.
B042C007V023	42	7	23	And blessed is he who is not offended because of Me."
B042C007V024	42	7	24	Now when John's messengers had departed, He began to speak to the crowds concerning John: "What have you gone out into the wilderness to see? A reed shaken by the wind?
B042C007V025	42	7	25	But what have you gone out to see? A man clothed in soft garments? Indeed those who are gorgeously appareled and live in luxury are in royal [palaces].
B042C007V026	42	7	26	But what have you gone out to see? A prophet? Yes, I say to you, and much more than a prophet.
B042C007V027	42	7	27	This is he about whom it is written: 'Behold, I send My messenger before Your face, who will prepare Your way before You.'
B042C007V028	42	7	28	"For I say to you, among those born of women there is not a greater prophet than John the Baptist; but he who is least in the kingdom of God is greater [than] he."
B042C007V029	42	7	29	And when all the people heard Him, even the tax collectors justified God, having been baptized with the baptism of John.
B042C007V030	42	7	30	But the Pharisees and lawyers rejected the counsel of God for themselves, because they had not been baptized by him.
B042C007V031	42	7	31	"Therefore to what shall I compare the men of this generation, and what are they like?
B042C007V032	42	7	32	They are like children sitting in the marketplace and calling to one another, saying: 'We played the flute for you, and you did not dance; we mourned for you, and you did not weep.'
B042C007V033	42	7	33	"For John the Baptist has come neither eating bread nor drinking wine, and you say, 'He has a demon.'
B042C007V034	42	7	34	The Son of Man has come eating and drinking, and you say, 'Look, a glutton and a drunkard, a friend of tax collectors and sinners!'
B042C007V035	42	7	35	And so wisdom is justified by all her children."
B042C007V036	42	7	36	Then one of the Pharisees asked Him to eat with him. And entering into the Pharisee's house, He reclined [to eat].
B042C007V037	42	7	37	And behold, a woman in the city who was a sinner, when she found out that He was reclining in the Pharisee's house, brought an alabaster flask of perfume,
B042C007V038	42	7	38	and standing by His feet behind Him weeping; and she began to wash His feet with her tears, and was wiping [them] with the hair of her head; and she was kissing His feet and anointing [them] with the perfume.
B042C007V039	42	7	39	Now when the Pharisee who had invited Him saw this, he spoke within himself, saying, "This [Man], if He were a prophet, would know who and what sort of woman [this is] who touches Him, for she is a sinner."
B042C007V040	42	7	40	And Jesus answered and said to him, "Simon, I have something to say to you."And he said, "Teacher, say it."
