B042C008V001	42	8	1	Now it came to pass afterward, that He was traveling through every city and village, preaching and proclaiming the gospel of the kingdom of God, and the twelve were with Him,
B042C008V002	42	8	2	and certain women who had been healed of evil spirits and infirmities; Mary called Magdalene, from whom seven demons had gone out,
B042C008V003	42	8	3	and Joanna the wife of Chuza, a supervisor of Herod, and Susanna, and many others who were ministering to them from their belongings.
B042C008V004	42	8	4	And when a large crowd had gathered, and the [people] came to Him from every city, He spoke by a parable:
B042C008V005	42	8	5	A sower went out to sow his seed. And as he sowed, some fell alongside the road; and it was trampled down, and the birds of the air devoured it.
B042C008V006	42	8	6	And other [seed] fell on rock; and when it grew up, it withered away because it had no moisture.
B042C008V007	42	8	7	And other [seed] fell among thorns, and when the thorns grew up with it, they choked it.
B042C008V008	42	8	8	But other [seed] fell into good ground, and when it grew up, it produced fruit a hundredfold."Saying these things He was calling out, "He who has ears to hear, let him hear!"
B042C008V009	42	8	9	Then His disciples asked Him, saying, "What does this parable mean?"
B042C008V010	42	8	10	And He said, "To you it has been given to know the mysteries of the kingdom of God, but to the rest [they are] in parables, that 'Seeing they may not see, and hearing they may not understand.'
B042C008V011	42	8	11	"Now this is the parable: The seed is the word of God.
B042C008V012	42	8	12	And those beside the road are they that hear; then the devil comes and takes away the word from their hearts, lest they believe and be saved.
B042C008V013	42	8	13	But those on the rock are they that, whenever they hear, receive the word with joy; and these have no root, who believe for a while and in time of testing fall away.
B042C008V014	42	8	14	And that which fell among thorns, these are those, who when they heard, go out and are choked with anxieties, riches, and pleasures of life, and bring no fruit to maturity.
B042C008V015	42	8	15	But that which fell on the good ground, these are such who when they heard the word, with a noble and good heart, hold on to it and bear fruit with endurance.
B042C008V016	42	8	16	"No one, when he has lit a lamp, covers it with a vessel or puts [it] under a bed, but sets it on a lampstand, so that those who enter may see the light.
B042C008V017	42	8	17	For there is nothing hidden which will not become manifest, nor anything concealed which will not be known and come to light.
B042C008V018	42	8	18	Therefore take heed how you hear. For whoever has, [more] shall be given to him; and whoever does not have, even what he thinks he has shall be taken away from him."
B042C008V019	42	8	19	Then His mother and brothers came to Him, and could not approach Him because of the crowd.
B042C008V020	42	8	20	And it was told Him by some, who said, "Your mother and Your brothers are standing outside, desiring to see You."
B042C008V021	42	8	21	But He answered and said to them, "My mother and My brothers are these who hear the word of God and do it."
