B042C013V020	42	13	20	Again He said, "To what shall I compare the kingdom of God?
B042C013V021	42	13	21	It is like leaven, which a woman took and hid in three measures of meal until it was all leavened."
B042C013V022	42	13	22	And He was traveling through various cities and villages, teaching, and journeying toward Jerusalem.
B042C013V023	42	13	23	Then one said to Him, "Lord, are there few who are saved?"And He said to them,
B042C013V024	42	13	24	Strive to enter through the narrow gate, because many, I say to you, will seek to enter and will not be able.
B042C013V025	42	13	25	When once the Master of the house has risen up and shuts the door, and you begin to stand outside and to knock at the door, saying, 'Lord, Lord, open for us,' and answering He will say to you, 'I do not know you, where you are from.'
B042C013V026	42	13	26	Then you will begin to say, 'We ate and drank in Your presence, and You taught in our streets.'
B042C013V027	42	13	27	But He will say, 'I tell you I do not know you, where you are from. Depart from Me, all you workers of iniquity.'
B042C013V028	42	13	28	There will be weeping and gnashing of teeth, when you see Abraham and Isaac and Jacob and all the prophets in the kingdom of God, but yourselves being cast out.
B042C013V029	42	13	29	And they will come from the east and the west, and the north and the south, and will recline [to eat] in the kingdom of God.
B042C013V030	42	13	30	And behold, there are last who shall be first, and there are first who shall be last."
B042C013V031	42	13	31	On that very day some Pharisees came, saying to Him, "Get out and go from here, for Herod wants to kill You."
B042C013V032	42	13	32	And He said to them, "Go and say to that fox, 'Behold, I cast out demons and perform cures today and tomorrow, and the third day I shall be perfected.'
B042C013V033	42	13	33	Nevertheless I must journey today, tomorrow, and the day following; for it is not possible [for] a prophet to perish outside of Jerusalem.
B042C013V034	42	13	34	"O Jerusalem, Jerusalem, the one who kills the prophets and stones those who are sent to her! How often I wanted to gather your children together, like a hen [gathers] her brood under her wings, but you were not willing!
B042C013V035	42	13	35	See! Your house is left to you desolate; and I say to you, you shall by no means see Me until [the time] comes when you say, 'Blessed is He who comes in the name of the LORD!' "
B042C014V001	42	14	1	Now it came to pass, when He came into the house of one of the rulers of the Pharisees to eat bread on the Sabbath, that they were watching Him closely.
B042C014V002	42	14	2	And behold, there was a certain man before Him who had dropsy.
B042C014V003	42	14	3	And Jesus, answering, spoke to the lawyers and Pharisees, saying, "Is it lawful to heal on the Sabbath?"
B042C014V004	42	14	4	But they were silent. And taking hold of him, He healed him, and let [him] go.
B042C014V005	42	14	5	Then He answered them, saying, "Which of you, having a son or an ox that has fallen into a pit, will not immediately pull him out on the Sabbath day?"
B042C014V006	42	14	6	And they were not able to answer Him regarding these things.
B042C014V007	42	14	7	So He told a parable to those who were invited, when He noted how they chose the places of honor, saying to them:
B042C014V008	42	14	8	Whenever you are invited by someone to a wedding celebration, do not sit down in the place of honor, lest one more honorable than you be invited by him;
B042C014V009	42	14	9	and he who invited you and him shall come and say to you, 'Give place to this [man],' and then you begin with shame to take the last place.
B042C014V010	42	14	10	But when you are invited, go and sit down in the last place, so that when he who invited you comes, he shall say to you, 'Friend, go up higher.' Then you will have glory in the presence of those who recline with you.
B042C014V011	42	14	11	For everyone who exalts himself shall be humbled, and he who humbles himself shall be exalted."
B042C014V012	42	14	12	Then He also said to him who invited Him, "When you give a dinner or a supper, do not call your friends, nor your brothers, nor your relatives, nor rich neighbors, lest they also invite you back, and you be repaid.
B042C014V013	42	14	13	But whenever you give a banquet, invite the poor, the crippled, the lame, the blind;
B042C014V014	42	14	14	and you will be blessed, because they do not have [anything] to repay you; for it will be repaid to you in the resurrection of the just."
B042C014V015	42	14	15	Now when one of those who sat at the table with Him heard these things, he said to Him, "Blessed is he who shall eat dinner in the kingdom of God!"
B042C014V016	42	14	16	Then He said to him, "A certain man gave a great dinner, and he invited many,
B042C014V017	42	14	17	and he sent his servant at dinnertime to say to those who were invited, 'Come, for all things are now ready.'
B042C014V018	42	14	18	But they all with one [accord] began to excuse themselves. The first said to him, 'I bought a field, and I must go and see it. I ask you, have me excused.'
B042C014V019	42	14	19	And another said, 'I bought five yoke of oxen, and I am going to test them. I ask you, have me excused.'
B042C014V020	42	14	20	Still another said, 'I have married a wife, and therefore I cannot come.'
B042C014V021	42	14	21	So that servant came and reported these things to his master. Then the master of the house, being angry, said to his servant, 'Go out quickly into the streets and lanes of the city, and bring in here the poor and the maimed and the lame and the blind.'
B042C014V022	42	14	22	And the servant said, 'Master, it is done as you commanded, and still there is room.'
B042C014V023	42	14	23	Then the master said to the servant, 'Go out into the roads and hedges, and compel [them] to come in, so that my house may be filled.
B042C014V024	42	14	24	For I say to you that none of those men who were invited shall taste of my supper.' "
B042C014V025	42	14	25	Now great crowds were traveling with Him. And turning, He said to them,
B042C014V026	42	14	26	If anyone comes to Me and does not hate his father and mother, wife and children, brothers and sisters, yes, and his own life also, he cannot be My disciple.
B042C014V027	42	14	27	And whoever does not bear his cross and come after Me cannot be My disciple.
B042C014V028	42	14	28	For which of you, intending to build a tower, [does] not first sit down and count up the cost, whether he has the resources to complete it?
B042C014V029	42	14	29	Lest perhaps after he has laid a foundation, and is not able to finish, all those who see it begin to mock him,
B042C014V030	42	14	30	saying, 'This man began to build and was not able to finish.'
B042C014V031	42	14	31	Or what king, going to engage another king in battle, [does] not sit down first and consider whether he is able with ten thousand to meet him who comes against him with twenty thousand?
B042C014V032	42	14	32	Otherwise, while the other is still far away, he sends a delegation and asks the [terms] for peace.
B042C014V033	42	14	33	So likewise, every one of you who does not renounce all his possessions cannot be My disciple.
B042C014V034	42	14	34	"Salt is good; but if the salt becomes tasteless, with what shall it be seasoned?
B042C014V035	42	14	35	It is neither fit for the land nor for the dunghill, but men cast it out. He who has ears to hear, let him hear!"
B042C015V001	42	15	1	Now all the tax collectors and the sinners were drawing near to Him to hear Him.
B042C015V002	42	15	2	And the Pharisees and scribes were grumbling, saying, "This man receives sinners and eats with them."
B042C015V003	42	15	3	And He told them this parable, saying:
B042C015V004	42	15	4	What man of you, having a hundred sheep, and loses one of them, does not leave behind the ninety-nine in the wilderness, and goes after the one having been lost until he finds it?
B042C015V005	42	15	5	And having found it, he puts [it] on his own shoulders, rejoicing.
B042C015V006	42	15	6	And coming into the house, he calls together his friends and neighbors, saying to them, 'Rejoice with me, for I have found my sheep which was lost!'
B042C015V007	42	15	7	I say to you that likewise [there] shall be more joy in heaven over one sinner repenting than over ninety-nine righteous who need no repentance.
B042C015V008	42	15	8	"Or what woman, having ten silver coins, if she loses one coin, does not light a lamp and sweep the house, and search carefully until she finds [it]?
B042C015V009	42	15	9	And when she finds it, she calls her friends and neighbors together, saying, 'Rejoice with me, for I have found the coin which I lost!'
B042C015V010	42	15	10	Just so, I say to you, there is joy in the presence of the angels of God over one sinner who repents."
B042C015V011	42	15	11	Then He said: "A certain man had two sons.
B042C015V012	42	15	12	And the younger of them said to his father, 'Father, give to me the share of the wealth which falls to [me].' So he divided to them his livelihood.
B042C015V013	42	15	13	And not many days after, having gathered together all things, the younger son went on a journey to a distant country, and there wasted his possessions with prodigal living.
B042C015V014	42	15	14	But when he had spent everything, there arose a severe famine throughout that country, and he began to be in need.
B042C015V015	42	15	15	Then he went and joined himself to a citizen of that country, and he sent him into his fields to feed swine.
B042C015V016	42	15	16	And he was longing to fill his stomach with the carob pods which the swine were eating, and no one gave him anything.
B042C015V017	42	15	17	But having come to himself, he said, 'How many of my father's hired servants have an abundance of bread, and I am perishing with hunger!
B042C015V018	42	15	18	I will arise and go to my father, and I will say to him, "Father, I have sinned against heaven and before you,
B042C015V019	42	15	19	and I am no longer worthy to be called your son. Make me like one of your hired servants."'
B042C015V020	42	15	20	And he arose and went to his father. But when he was still far off, his father saw him and was moved with compassion, and he ran and fell on his neck and kissed him.
B042C015V021	42	15	21	And the son said to him, 'Father, I have sinned against heaven and before you, and am no longer worthy to be called your son.'
B042C015V022	42	15	22	But the father said to his servants, 'Bring out the best robe and put [it] on him, and put a ring on his hand and sandals on his feet.
B042C015V023	42	15	23	And bring the fatted calf here and slaughter it, and let us eat and be merry;
B042C015V024	42	15	24	for this my son was dead and came to life, and he was lost and was found.' And they began to be merry.
B042C015V025	42	15	25	Now his older son was in the field. And as he came and drew near to the house, he heard music and dancing.
B042C015V026	42	15	26	And having summoned one of the servants, he was inquiring what these things might be.
B042C015V027	42	15	27	And he said to him, 'Your brother has come, and because he has received him back in good health, your father has killed the fatted calf.'
B042C015V028	42	15	28	But he was angry and would not go in. Therefore his father came out and began to plead with him.
B042C015V029	42	15	29	So he answered and said to his father, 'Lo, so many years I have been serving you and I never transgressed your commandment; and yet you never gave me a young goat, that I might make merry with my friends.
B042C015V030	42	15	30	But when this son of yours came, who has devoured your livelihood with prostitutes, you slaughtered the fatted calf for him.'
B042C015V031	42	15	31	And he said to him, 'Son, you are always with me, and all that I have is yours.
B042C015V032	42	15	32	But it was necessary to be merry and to rejoice, because your brother was dead and is alive again, and was lost and is found.' "
B042C016V001	42	16	1	He also said to His disciples: "There was a certain rich man who had a manager, and this [man] was accused to him as wasting his possessions.
B042C016V002	42	16	2	And calling him, he said to him, 'What is this I hear about you? Render an account of your management, for you can no longer be manager.'
B042C016V003	42	16	3	"Then the manager said within himself, 'What shall I do? For my master is taking the management away from me. I cannot dig; I am ashamed to beg.
B042C016V004	42	16	4	I know what I will do, so that whenever I am removed from the management, they will receive me into their houses.'
B042C016V005	42	16	5	And having summoned each one of his master's debtors to him, he said to the first, 'How much do you owe my master?'
B042C016V006	42	16	6	And he said, 'A hundred baths of olive oil.' So he said to him, 'Take your bill, and sit down quickly and write fifty.'
B042C016V007	42	16	7	Then he said to another, 'And how much do you owe?' So he said, 'A hundred measures of wheat.' And he said to him, 'Take your bill, and write eighty.'
B042C016V008	42	16	8	So the master praised the unrighteous manager because he had dealt shrewdly. For the sons of this age are shrewder in their own generation than the sons of light.
B042C016V009	42	16	9	And I say to you, make friends for yourselves by the mammon of unrighteousness, so that whenever you fail, they may receive you into the eternal dwellings.
B042C016V010	42	16	10	He that [is] faithful in what is least is faithful also in much; and he that is unjust in what is least is also unjust in much.
B042C016V011	42	16	11	Therefore if you were not faithful with the unrighteous mammon, who will entrust to you what is genuine?
B042C016V012	42	16	12	And if you were not faithful in what belongs to another, who will give to you what is yours?
B042C016V013	42	16	13	No servant can serve two masters, for either he will hate the one and love the other, or else he will be devoted to the one and despise the other. You cannot serve God and mammon."
B042C016V014	42	16	14	Now the Pharisees, who were lovers of money, were hearing all these things, and they were mocking Him.
B042C016V015	42	16	15	And He said to them, "You are those who justify yourselves before men, but God knows your hearts. Because that which is exalted among men is an abomination before God.
B042C016V016	42	16	16	The law and the prophets [were] until John. Since that time the kingdom of God has been preached, and everyone enters forcibly into it.
B042C016V017	42	16	17	And it is easier for heaven and earth to pass away than for one tittle of the law to fail.
B042C016V018	42	16	18	Everyone who divorces his wife and marries another commits adultery; and everyone who marries a woman who is divorced from her husband commits adultery.
B042C016V019	42	16	19	"Now there was a certain rich man who was clothed in purple and fine linen, enjoying himself splendidly every day.
B042C016V020	42	16	20	But there was a certain beggar named Lazarus, covered with sores, who had been placed at his gate,
B042C016V021	42	16	21	and longing to be fed with the crumbs which fell from the rich man's table. And even the dogs came and would lick his sores.
B042C016V022	42	16	22	And it came to pass that the beggar died, and he was carried away by the angels to Abraham's bosom. The rich man also died and was buried.
B042C016V023	42	16	23	And being in torments in Hades, he lifted up his eyes and saw Abraham from afar, and Lazarus in his bosom.
B042C016V024	42	16	24	Then he cried and said, 'Father Abraham, have mercy on me, and send Lazarus so that he may dip the tip of his finger in water and cool my tongue; for I am suffering in this flame.'
B042C016V025	42	16	25	But Abraham said, 'Child, remember that in your lifetime you received your good things, and likewise Lazarus bad things, but now here he is comforted and you are suffering.
B042C016V026	42	16	26	And besides all this, between us and you a great gulf has been fixed, so that those who desire to cross [over ]from here to you are not able, nor may those from there cross over to us.'
B042C016V027	42	16	27	Then he said, 'Therefore I beseech you, father, that you would send him to my father's house,
B042C016V028	42	16	28	for I have five brothers, so that he may testify to them, lest they also come to this place of torment.'
B042C016V029	42	16	29	Abraham said to him, 'They have Moses and the prophets; let them hear them.'
B042C016V030	42	16	30	And he said, 'No, father Abraham; but if someone from the dead should go to them, they will repent.'
B042C016V031	42	16	31	But he said to him, 'If they do not hear Moses and the prophets, neither will they be persuaded should one rise from the dead.' "
B042C017V001	42	17	1	Then He said to the disciples, "It is impossible for offenses not to come, but woe [to the one] through whom they do come!
B042C017V002	42	17	2	It would be better for him if a millstone were around his neck, and he be cast into the sea, than that he should offend one of these little ones.
B042C017V003	42	17	3	Take heed to yourselves. If your brother sins against you, rebuke him; and if he repents, forgive him.
B042C017V004	42	17	4	And if he sins against you seven times in a day, and seven times in a day he returns, saying, 'I repent,' you shall forgive him."
B042C017V005	42	17	5	And the apostles said to the Lord, "Increase our faith."
B042C017V006	42	17	6	So the Lord said, "If you have faith as a mustard seed, you can say to this mulberry tree, 'Be uprooted and be planted in the sea,' and it would obey you.
B042C017V007	42	17	7	And which of you, having a servant plowing or tending sheep, will say to him when he has come in from the field, 'Come and recline [to eat]'?
B042C017V008	42	17	8	But will he not say to him, 'Prepare something [that] I may dine, and gird yourself and serve me until I eat and drink, and afterward you will eat and drink'?
B042C017V009	42	17	9	Does he thank that servant because he did the things having been commanded? I think not.
B042C017V010	42	17	10	So likewise you, whenever you do all the things having been commanded to you, say, 'We are unprofitable servants. We have done what we ought to do.' "
B042C017V011	42	17	11	And it happened while He was traveling to Jerusalem that He passed through the midst of Samaria and Galilee.
B042C017V012	42	17	12	Then as He entered a certain village, there met Him ten men who were lepers, who stood at a distance.
