B042C017V036	42	17	36	- - -
B042C017V037	42	17	37	And they answered and said to Him, "Where, Lord?"So He said to them, "Wherever the body is, there the eagles will be gathered together."
B042C018V001	42	18	1	Then He spoke a parable to them, that one must always pray and not lose heart,
B042C018V002	42	18	2	saying: "A certain judge was in a certain city, who did not fear God nor have regard for men.
B042C018V003	42	18	3	Now there was a widow in that city; and she kept coming to him, saying, 'Give justice to me against my adversary.'
B042C018V004	42	18	4	And he did not want to for a time; but afterward he said within himself, 'although I do not fear God, nor have regard for man,
B042C018V005	42	18	5	yet because this widow bothers me I will give justice to her, lest she wear me out by forever coming to me.' "
B042C018V006	42	18	6	Then the Lord said, "Hear what the unjust judge said.
B042C018V007	42	18	7	And God, shall He not execute justice for His own elect, who cry out day and night to Him, and yet He is patient with them?
B042C018V008	42	18	8	I tell you that He will execute justice for them speedily. Nevertheless, when the Son of Man comes, will He really find faith on the earth?"
B042C018V009	42	18	9	Also He spoke this parable to some who trusted in themselves that they were righteous, and despised the others:
B042C018V010	42	18	10	Two men went up to the temple to pray, the one a Pharisee and the other a tax collector.
B042C018V011	42	18	11	The Pharisee stood and prayed thus with himself, 'God, I thank You that I am not like other men-swindlers, unjust, adulterers, or even like this tax collector.
B042C018V012	42	18	12	I fast twice a week, I tithe [on ]all things, as many as I acquire.'
B042C018V013	42	18	13	And the tax collector, standing far away, would not so much as lift his eyes towards heaven, but beat on his chest, saying, 'God, be merciful to me a sinner!'
B042C018V014	42	18	14	I say to you, this man went down to his house justified rather than the other; for everyone who exalts himself shall be humbled, and he who humbles himself shall be exalted."
B042C018V015	42	18	15	And they were bringing infants to Him, that He might touch them; but when the disciples saw it, they rebuked them.
B042C018V016	42	18	16	But Jesus, summoning them, said, "Allow the little children to come to Me, and do not forbid them; for of such is the kingdom of God.
B042C018V017	42	18	17	Assuredly I say to you, whoever does not receive the kingdom of God as a little child will by no means enter into it."
B042C018V018	42	18	18	Now a certain ruler asked Him, saying, "Good Teacher, what shall I do to inherit eternal life?"
B042C018V019	42	18	19	So Jesus said to him, "Why do you call Me good? No one is good except One, that is, God.
B042C018V020	42	18	20	You know the commandments: 'Do not commit adultery,' 'Do not murder,' 'Do not steal,' 'Do not bear false witness,' 'Honor your father and your mother.' "
B042C018V021	42	18	21	And he said, "All these I have kept from my youth."
