B042C022V059	42	22	59	Then after about one hour had passed, another was firmly insisting, saying, "Surely this fellow also was with Him, for he is a Galilean."
B042C022V060	42	22	60	But Peter said, "Man, I do not know what you are saying!"And immediately, while he was still speaking, a rooster crowed.
B042C022V061	42	22	61	And the Lord turned and looked at Peter. And Peter remembered the word of the Lord, how He had said to him, "Before a rooster crows, you will deny Me three times."
B042C022V062	42	22	62	And going outside, Peter wept bitterly.
B042C022V063	42	22	63	Now the men who were holding Jesus were mocking Him and beating [Him].
B042C022V064	42	22	64	And having blindfolded Him, they were striking His face and asking Him, saying, "Prophesy! Who is the one who struck You?"
B042C022V065	42	22	65	And many other things they blasphemously spoke against Him.
B042C022V066	42	22	66	And when it became day, the council of the elders of the people, the chief priests and scribes, came together and led Him into their council, saying,
B042C022V067	42	22	67	"If You are the Messiah, tell us."But He said to them, "If I tell you, you will by no means believe.
B042C022V068	42	22	68	But if I also question you, you will by no means answer Me or release [Me].
B042C022V069	42	22	69	Hereafter the Son of Man will sit on the right hand of the power of God."
B042C022V070	42	22	70	Then they all said, "Are You then the Son of God?"So He said to them, "You [rightly] say that I am."
B042C022V071	42	22	71	And they said, "What further testimony do we need? For we have heard it ourselves from His own mouth!"
B042C023V001	42	23	1	Then the whole multitude of them arose and led Him to Pilate.
B042C023V002	42	23	2	And they began to accuse Him, saying, "We found this [Man] perverting the nation, and forbidding to pay taxes to Caesar, saying that He Himself is Christ, a King."
B042C023V003	42	23	3	Then Pilate questioned Him, saying, "Are You the King of the Jews?"He answered him and said, "You are saying [what is] [so]."
B042C023V004	42	23	4	But Pilate said to the chief priests and the crowds, "I find no guilt in this Man."
B042C023V005	42	23	5	But they insisted, saying, "He stirs up the people, teaching throughout all Judea, beginning from Galilee to here."
B042C023V006	42	23	6	When Pilate heard of Galilee, he asked if the Man were a Galilean.
B042C023V007	42	23	7	And when he found out that He belonged to Herod's jurisdiction, he sent Him to Herod, who was also in Jerusalem in those days.
B042C023V008	42	23	8	Now when Herod saw Jesus, he was exceedingly glad; for he had desired for a long time to see Him, because he had heard many things about Him, and he was hoping to see some miracle being done by Him.
B042C023V009	42	23	9	Then he questioned Him with many words, but He answered him nothing.
B042C023V010	42	23	10	And the chief priests and scribes stood, vehemently accusing Him.
B042C023V011	42	23	11	Then Herod, with his men of war, having treated Him with contempt, and having mocked Him, arrayed Him in a gorgeous robe, and sent Him back to Pilate.
B042C023V012	42	23	12	That very day Pilate and Herod became friends with each other, for previously they had been at enmity with each other.
B042C023V013	42	23	13	And Pilate, having called together the chief priests, the rulers, and the people,
B042C023V014	42	23	14	said to them, "You have brought this Man to me, on the charge of misleading the people. And indeed, when I examined Him in your presence, I found no guilt in this Man in the matters which you bring as charges against Him;
B042C023V015	42	23	15	and neither [did] Herod, for I sent you back to him; and indeed nothing worthy of death has been done by Him.
B042C023V016	42	23	16	Therefore when I have flogged Him, I will release [Him.]"
B042C023V017	42	23	17	(for it was necessary for him to release one to them at the feast).
B042C023V018	42	23	18	But they all cried out together, saying, "Away with this [Man], and release to us Barabbas"-
B042C023V019	42	23	19	who because of a certain insurrection having occurred in the city had been thrown into prison, and for murder.
B042C023V020	42	23	20	Pilate, therefore, wishing to release Jesus, again called out to them.
B042C023V021	42	23	21	But they cried out, saying, "Crucify, crucify Him!"
B042C023V022	42	23	22	Then he said to them the third [time], "Why, what evil did He do? I have found no guilt deserving death in Him. Therefore when I have flogged Him, I will release [Him]."
B042C023V023	42	23	23	But they were insistent, demanding with loud voices that He be crucified. And their voices and [those] of the chief priests prevailed.
B042C023V024	42	23	24	So Pilate decided [that] their request should be carried out.
B042C023V025	42	23	25	And he released whom they were requesting, who because of insurrection and murder had been thrown into prison; but he delivered Jesus to their will.
B042C023V026	42	23	26	And as they led Him away, they laid hold of a certain man, Simon a Cyrenian, [as he was] coming from the country, and on him they laid the cross, that he might carry it behind Jesus.
B042C023V027	42	23	27	And a great multitude of the people followed Him, and women who also were mourning and lamenting Him.
B042C023V028	42	23	28	But Jesus, turning to them, said, "Daughters of Jerusalem, do not weep for Me, but weep for yourselves and for your children.
B042C023V029	42	23	29	For behold, the days are coming in which they will say, 'Blessed [are] the barren, and [the] wombs which did not give birth, and breasts which did not nurse!'
B042C023V030	42	23	30	Then they will begin 'to say to the mountains, "Fall on us!"and to the hills, "Cover us!"'
B042C023V031	42	23	31	For if they do these things in the green tree, what will happen in the dry?"
B042C023V032	42	23	32	And they also were leading two others with Him, evildoers, to be put to death.
B042C023V033	42	23	33	And when they came to the place which is called Calvary, there they crucified Him and the evildoers, one on the right, and one on the left.
B042C023V034	42	23	34	Then Jesus said, "Father, forgive them, for they know not what they do."And dividing His garments, they cast lots.
B042C023V035	42	23	35	And the people stood, observing. And the rulers with them also were sneering, saying, "He saved others; let Him save Himself if He is the Christ, the elect of God."
B042C023V036	42	23	36	The soldiers also mocked Him, coming and offering Him sour wine,
B042C023V037	42	23	37	and saying, "If You are the King of the Jews, save Yourself."
B042C023V038	42	23	38	And an inscription also was written over Him, in Greek, Latin, and Hebrew letters: THIS IS THE KING OF THE JEWS.
B042C023V039	42	23	39	Then one of the evildoers who were hanged blasphemed Him, saying, "If You are the Christ, save Yourself and us."
B042C023V040	42	23	40	But the other, answering, rebuked him, saying, "Do you not even fear God, seeing you are under the same condemnation?
B042C023V041	42	23	41	And we indeed justly, for we are receiving the due reward of our deeds; but this Man did nothing wrong."
B042C023V042	42	23	42	Then he said to Jesus, "Lord, remember me when You come in Your kingdom."
B042C023V043	42	23	43	And Jesus said to him, "Assuredly I say to you, today you shall be with Me in Paradise."
B042C023V044	42	23	44	Now it was about the sixth hour, and darkness came upon the whole land until the ninth hour.
B042C023V045	42	23	45	Then the sun was darkened, and the veil of the temple was torn in two.
B042C023V046	42	23	46	And Jesus, calling out with a loud voice, said, "Father, 'into Your hands I will commit My spirit.' "And after He said these things, He expired.
B042C023V047	42	23	47	And when the centurion saw what had happened, he glorified God, saying, "Certainly this was a righteous Man!"
B042C023V048	42	23	48	And all the crowds which came together for this spectacle, when they saw what had happened, beat their own chests and returned.
B042C023V049	42	23	49	But all His acquaintances, and the women who followed Him from Galilee, stood at a distance, watching these things.
B042C023V050	42	23	50	And behold, there was a man named Joseph, a council member, a good and just man
B042C023V051	42	23	51	(this [man] had not agreed to their decision and deed), from Arimathea, a city of the Jews, who himself was also waiting for the kingdom of God.
B042C023V052	42	23	52	This man went to Pilate and asked for the body of Jesus.
B042C023V053	42	23	53	And having taken it down, he wrapped it in a linen cloth, and put it in a tomb cut out of rock, where no one had ever lain before.
B042C023V054	42	23	54	That day was the Preparation; the Sabbath was drawing near.
B042C023V055	42	23	55	And the women who had come with Him from Galilee followed after, and they observed the tomb and how His body was placed.
B042C023V056	42	23	56	Then they returned and prepared spices and perfumes. And they rested on the Sabbath, according to the commandment.
B042C024V001	42	24	1	And on the first day of the week, very early in the morning, they, and certain other women with them, came to the tomb bringing the spices which they had prepared.
B042C024V002	42	24	2	But they found the stone having been rolled away from the tomb.
B042C024V003	42	24	3	And going in they did not find the body of the Lord Jesus.
B042C024V004	42	24	4	And it happened, as they were greatly perplexed about this, that behold, two men stood by them in dazzling apparel.
B042C024V005	42	24	5	Then, as they became afraid and bowed their faces to the ground, they said to them, "Why do you seek the living among the dead?
B042C024V006	42	24	6	He is not here, but is risen! Remember how He spoke to you when He was still in Galilee,
B042C024V007	42	24	7	saying, 'The Son of Man must be delivered into the hands of sinful men, and be crucified, and on the third day rise again.' "
B042C024V008	42	24	8	And they remembered His words.
B042C024V009	42	24	9	And returning from the tomb, they reported all these things to the eleven and to all the rest.
B042C024V010	42	24	10	It was Mary Magdalene, Joanna, Mary [the mother] of James, and the rest with them, who told these things to the apostles.
B042C024V011	42	24	11	And their words seemed like nonsense before them, and they disbelieved them.
B042C024V012	42	24	12	But Peter rose up and ran to the tomb; and stooping down, he saw the linen strips lying by themselves; and he departed, marveling to himself at what had happened.
B042C024V013	42	24	13	Now behold, two of them were traveling that same day to a village called Emmaus, which was about seven miles from Jerusalem.
B042C024V014	42	24	14	And they were conversing with one another about all these things which had happened.
B042C024V015	42	24	15	So it was, as they were conversing and discussing, that Jesus Himself drew near and started to travel with them.
B042C024V016	42	24	16	But their eyes were restrained, so that they did not recognize Him.
B042C024V017	42	24	17	And He said to them, "What [are ]these words which you are exchanging with one another as you walk, and you have a gloomy look?"
B042C024V018	42	24	18	Then the one whose name was Cleopas answered and said to Him, "Are You the only stranger in Jerusalem, and do not know what has happened in it in these days?"
B042C024V019	42	24	19	And He said to them, "What things?"So they said to Him, "The things concerning Jesus the Nazarene, who proved to be a man [who was ]a Prophet mighty in deed and word before God and all the people,
B042C024V020	42	24	20	and how the chief priests and our rulers handed Him over to be condemned to death, and they crucified Him.
B042C024V021	42	24	21	But we were hoping that it was He who was going to redeem Israel. Indeed, besides all this, today is the third day since these things happened.
B042C024V022	42	24	22	Moreover certain women of our group astonished us, after they arrived early at the tomb.
B042C024V023	42	24	23	And not finding His body, they came saying that they had also seen a vision of angels who said He was alive.
B042C024V024	42	24	24	And certain of those who were with us went to the tomb and found it thus just as also the women had said; but Him they did not see."
B042C024V025	42	24	25	Then He said to them, "O [you ]foolish, and slow of heart to believe in all that the prophets have spoken!
B042C024V026	42	24	26	Ought not the Christ to have suffered these things and to enter into His glory?"
B042C024V027	42	24	27	And beginning at Moses and all the Prophets, He expounded to them in all the Scriptures the things concerning Himself.
B042C024V028	42	24	28	Then they drew near to the village where they were going, and He made as though He was going farther.
B042C024V029	42	24	29	But they constrained Him, saying, "Stay with us, for it is toward evening, and the day is far spent."And He went in to stay with them.
B042C024V030	42	24	30	Now it came to pass, as He was reclining [to eat] with them, having taken bread, He blessed and broke it, and He gave [it] to them.
B042C024V031	42	24	31	Then their eyes were opened and they recognized Him; and He vanished from their sight.
B042C024V032	42	24	32	And they said to one another, "Was not our heart burning within us while He was speaking to us on the road, and while He was interpreting the Scriptures to us?"
B042C024V033	42	24	33	So they rose up that very hour and returned to Jerusalem, and they found the eleven and those who were with them gathered together,
B042C024V034	42	24	34	saying, "The Lord is risen indeed, and has appeared to Simon!"
B042C024V035	42	24	35	And they described the things that had happened on the road, and how He was known to them in the breaking of bread.
B042C024V036	42	24	36	Now as they said these things, Jesus Himself stood in the midst of them, and said to them, "Peace to you."
B042C024V037	42	24	37	But being alarmed and becoming fearful, they thought they saw a spirit.
B042C024V038	42	24	38	And He said to them, "Why are you troubled? And why do doubts arise in your hearts?
B042C024V039	42	24	39	Behold My hands and My feet, that it is I Myself. Handle Me and see, for a spirit does not have flesh and bones as you see I have."
B042C024V040	42	24	40	When He had said this, He showed them His hands and His feet.
B042C024V041	42	24	41	But as they still disbelieved for joy, and marveled, He said to them, "Do you have any food here?"
B042C024V042	42	24	42	So they gave Him a piece of a broiled fish and some honeycomb.
B042C024V043	42	24	43	And taking it, He ate [it ]in their presence.
B042C024V044	42	24	44	Then He said to them, "These are the words which I spoke to you while I was still with you, that all things must be fulfilled which were written in the Law of Moses and the Prophets and the Psalms concerning Me."
B042C024V045	42	24	45	And He opened their understanding, that they might comprehend the Scriptures.
B042C024V046	42	24	46	Then He said to them, "Thus it is written, and thus it was necessary for the Christ to suffer and to rise from the dead the third day,
B042C024V047	42	24	47	and that repentance and forgiveness of sins should be preached in His name to all nations, beginning at Jerusalem.
B042C024V048	42	24	48	And you are witnesses of these things.
B042C024V049	42	24	49	And behold, I am sending the Promise of My Father upon you; but tarry in the city of Jerusalem until you are endued with power from on high."
B042C024V050	42	24	50	And He led them out as far as Bethany, and lifting up His hands, He blessed them.
B042C024V051	42	24	51	And it happened, while He blessed them, that He was parted from them and was carried up into heaven.
B042C024V052	42	24	52	And after they had worshipped Him, they returned to Jerusalem with great joy,
B042C024V053	42	24	53	and they were continually in the temple praising and blessing God. Amen.
B043C001V001	43	1	1	In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God.
B043C001V002	43	1	2	He was in the beginning with God.
B043C001V003	43	1	3	All things came to be through Him, and without Him nothing came to be which has come to be.
B043C001V004	43	1	4	In Him was life, and the life was the light of men.
B043C001V005	43	1	5	And the light shines in the darkness, and the darkness did not apprehend it.
B043C001V006	43	1	6	There was a man sent from God, whose name [was] John.
B043C001V007	43	1	7	This [man] came for a testimony, so that he might testify concerning the Light, so that all through him might believe.
B043C001V008	43	1	8	He was not that Light, but [was sent] so that he might testify concerning the Light.
B043C001V009	43	1	9	That was the true Light which lightens every man coming into the world.
B043C001V010	43	1	10	He was in the world, and the world came to be through Him, and the world did not know Him.
B043C001V011	43	1	11	He came to His own, and His own did not receive Him.
B043C001V012	43	1	12	But as many as received Him, He gave them the authority to become children of God, to those who believe in His name;
B043C001V013	43	1	13	who were born, not of blood, nor of the will of the flesh, nor of the will of man, but of God.
B043C001V014	43	1	14	And the Word became flesh and dwelt among us, and we beheld His glory, the glory as of the only begotten of the Father, full of grace and truth.
B043C001V015	43	1	15	John testified concerning Him and has cried out, saying, "This was He of whom I said, 'He who comes after me, has come to be before me, because He was before me.' "
B043C001V016	43	1	16	And out of His fullness we have all received, and grace upon grace.
B043C001V017	43	1	17	For the law was given through Moses, but grace and truth came to be through Jesus Christ.
B043C001V018	43	1	18	No one has seen God at any time. The only begotten Son, He who is in the bosom of the Father, He has declared [Him].
B043C001V019	43	1	19	And this is the testimony of John, when the Jews sent priests and Levites from Jerusalem so that they might ask him, "Who are you?"
B043C001V020	43	1	20	He confessed, and did not deny, but confessed, "I am not the Messiah."
B043C001V021	43	1	21	And they asked him, "What then? Are you Elijah?"He said, "I am not.""Are you the Prophet?"And he answered, "No."
B043C001V022	43	1	22	Then they said to him, "Who are you, that we may give an answer to those who sent us? What do you say about yourself?"
B043C001V023	43	1	23	He said: "I am 'The voice of one crying in the wilderness: "Make straight the way of the LORD,"' just as Isaiah the prophet said."
B043C001V024	43	1	24	Now those who had been sent were from the Pharisees.
B043C001V025	43	1	25	And they asked him, saying, "Why then do you baptize if you are not the Christ, nor Elijah, nor the Prophet?"
B043C001V026	43	1	26	John answered them, saying, "I baptize with water, but there stands One among you whom you do not know.
B043C001V027	43	1	27	He is the [One ]who comes after me, who has come to be before me, of whom I am not worthy that I should loose the strap of His sandal."
B043C001V028	43	1	28	These things happened in Bethany, beyond the Jordan, where John was baptizing.
B043C001V029	43	1	29	The next day he saw Jesus coming toward him, and said, "Behold! The Lamb of God who takes away the sin of the world!
B043C001V030	43	1	30	This is the [One] about whom I said, 'After me comes a Man who ranks before me, because He was before me.'
B043C001V031	43	1	31	"I did not know Him; but that He should be made manifest to Israel, therefore I came baptizing with water."
B043C001V032	43	1	32	And John testified, saying, "I have beheld the Spirit coming down from heaven like a dove, and He remained upon Him.
B043C001V033	43	1	33	I did not know Him, but He who sent me to baptize with water said to me, 'Upon whom you see the Spirit descending and abiding on Him, this is He who baptizes with the Holy Spirit.'
B043C001V034	43	1	34	"And I have seen and have testified that this is the Son of God."
B043C001V035	43	1	35	Again, the next day, John stood with two of his disciples.
B043C001V036	43	1	36	And looking at Jesus as He [was] walking, he said, "Behold the Lamb of God!"
B043C001V037	43	1	37	The two disciples heard him speaking, and they followed Jesus.
B043C001V038	43	1	38	Then Jesus turned and observed them following, and said to them, "What are you seeking?"They said to Him, "Rabbi"(which is translated, Teacher), "where are You staying?"
B043C001V039	43	1	39	He said to them, "Come and see."They came and saw where He was staying, and they stayed with Him that day. It was about the tenth hour.
B043C001V040	43	1	40	One of the two who heard John speak, and followed Him, was Andrew, Simon Peter's brother.
B043C001V041	43	1	41	He first found his own brother Simon, and said to him, "We have found the Messiah"(which is translated, the Christ).
B043C001V042	43	1	42	And he led him to Jesus. Now when Jesus looked at him, He said, "You are Simon the son of Jonah. You shall be called Cephas"(which is translated, A Stone).
B043C001V043	43	1	43	On the next day He wanted to go to Galilee, and He found Philip and said to him, "Follow Me."
B043C001V044	43	1	44	Now Philip was from Bethsaida, the city of Andrew and Peter.
B043C001V045	43	1	45	Philip found Nathanael and said to him, "We have found the [One] about whom Moses wrote in the Law, and the Prophets-Jesus of Nazareth, the son of Joseph."
B043C001V046	43	1	46	And Nathanael said to him, "Can anything good come out of Nazareth?"Philip said to him, "Come and see."
B043C001V047	43	1	47	Jesus saw Nathanael coming toward Him, and said about him, "Behold, an Israelite indeed, in whom is no guile!"
B043C001V048	43	1	48	Nathanael said to Him, "From where do You know me?"Jesus answered and said to him, "Before Philip called you, while you were under the fig tree, I saw you."
B043C001V049	43	1	49	Nathanael answered and said to Him, "Rabbi, You are the Son of God! You are the King of Israel!"
B043C001V050	43	1	50	Jesus answered and said to him, "Because I said to you, 'I saw you under the fig tree,' do you believe? You will see greater things than these."
B043C001V051	43	1	51	And He said to him, "Most assuredly I say to you, from now on you shall see heaven opened, and the angels of God ascending and descending upon the Son of Man."
B043C002V001	43	2	1	And on the third day there was a wedding in Cana of Galilee, and the mother of Jesus was there.
B043C002V002	43	2	2	Now both Jesus and His disciples were invited to the wedding.
B043C002V003	43	2	3	And when the wine had given out, the mother of Jesus said to Him, "They have no wine."
B043C002V004	43	2	4	Jesus said to her, "Woman, what have I to do with you? My hour has not yet come."
B043C002V005	43	2	5	His mother said to the servants, "Whatever He may say to you, do."
B043C002V006	43	2	6	Now there were six stone water jars standing there, according to the purification rites of the Jews, each holding two or three measures.
B043C002V007	43	2	7	Jesus said to them, "Fill the water jars with water."And they filled them up to the top.
B043C002V008	43	2	8	And He said to them, "Draw out now, and carry [some] to the head steward."And they carried [it].
B043C002V009	43	2	9	Now when the head steward tasted the water which had become wine, and did not know where it came from (but the servants who had drawn the water knew), the head steward called the bridegroom
B043C002V010	43	2	10	and said to him, "Every man first sets out the good wine, and when they have well drunk, then the inferior. You have kept the good wine until now!"
B043C002V011	43	2	11	This beginning of the signs Jesus did in Cana of Galilee, and manifested His glory; and His disciples believed in Him.
B043C002V012	43	2	12	After this He went down to Capernaum, He, His mother, His brothers, and His disciples; and there they remained not many days.
B043C002V013	43	2	13	Now the Passover of the Jews was near, and Jesus went up to Jerusalem.
B043C002V014	43	2	14	And He found in the temple those who sold oxen and sheep and doves, and the moneychangers sitting there.
B043C002V015	43	2	15	And having made a scourge out of cords, He drove them all out of the temple, with the sheep and the oxen, and He poured out the coins of the moneychangers, and He overturned the tables.
B043C002V016	43	2	16	And He said to those selling the doves, "Take these things [away] from here! Do not make My Father's house a house of merchandise!"
B043C002V017	43	2	17	Then His disciples remembered that it was written, "The zeal for Your house will consume Me."
B043C002V018	43	2	18	Therefore the Jews answered and said to Him, "What sign do You show to us, since You do these things?"
B043C002V019	43	2	19	Jesus answered and said to them, "Destroy this temple, and in three days I will raise it up."
B043C002V020	43	2	20	Then the Jews said, "It has taken forty-six years to build this temple, and will You raise it up in three days?"
B043C002V021	43	2	21	But He was speaking about the temple of His body.
B043C002V022	43	2	22	Therefore, when He was raised up from among the dead, His disciples remembered that He spoke this [thing,] and they believed the Scripture and the word which Jesus had spoken.
B043C002V023	43	2	23	Now when He was in Jerusalem at the Passover, at the feast, many believed on His name, beholding the signs which He was doing.
B043C002V024	43	2	24	But Jesus did not trust Himself to them, because He knew all [men],
B043C002V025	43	2	25	and had no need that anyone should testify concerning man, for He himself knew what was in man.
B043C003V001	43	3	1	Now there was a man of the Pharisees whose name [was] Nicodemus, a ruler of the Jews.
B043C003V002	43	3	2	This [man] came to Him by night and said to Him, "Rabbi, we know that You have come from God [as] a teacher; for no one can do these signs that You do unless God is with him."
B043C003V003	43	3	3	Jesus answered and said to him, "Most assuredly, I say to you, unless someone is born again, he cannot see the kingdom of God."
B043C003V004	43	3	4	Nicodemus said to Him, "How can a man be born, being old? Can he enter a second time into his mother's womb and be born?"
B043C003V005	43	3	5	Jesus answered, "Most assuredly, I say to you, unless someone is born of water and of Spirit, he cannot enter the kingdom of God.
B043C003V006	43	3	6	That which is born of the flesh is flesh, and that which is born of the Spirit is spirit.
B043C003V007	43	3	7	Do not marvel that I said to you, 'You must be born again.'
B043C003V008	43	3	8	"The wind blows where it wills, and you hear its sound, but you do not know from where it comes and where it goes. So is everyone who has been born of the Spirit."
B043C003V009	43	3	9	Nicodemus answered and said to Him, "How can these things be?"
B043C003V010	43	3	10	Jesus answered and said to him, "Are you the teacher of Israel, and do not know these things?
B043C003V011	43	3	11	Most assuredly I say to you, that which We know, We speak, and that which We have seen, We bear witness to, and you do not receive Our witness.
B043C003V012	43	3	12	If I have told you earthly things and you do not believe, how will you believe if I tell you heavenly things?
B043C003V013	43	3	13	And no one has gone up into heaven except He who came down out of heaven, the Son of Man, who is in heaven.
B043C003V014	43	3	14	And just as Moses lifted up the serpent in the wilderness, even so must the Son of Man be lifted up,
B043C003V015	43	3	15	that everyone who believes in Him should not perish but have eternal life.
B043C003V016	43	3	16	For God so loved the world that He gave His only begotten Son, that whoever believes in Him should not perish but have everlasting life.
B043C003V017	43	3	17	For God did not send His Son into the world so that He might condemn the world, but that the world through Him might be saved.
B043C003V018	43	3	18	He who believes in Him is not condemned; but he who does not believe has been condemned already, because he has not believed in the name of the only begotten Son of God.
B043C003V019	43	3	19	And this is the condemnation, that the light has come into the world, and men loved the darkness more than the light, because their works were evil.
B043C003V020	43	3	20	For everyone that does evil hates the light and does not come to the light, lest his works be exposed.
B043C003V021	43	3	21	But he who does the truth comes to the light, that his works may be revealed, that they have been done in God."
B043C003V022	43	3	22	After these things Jesus, along with His disciples, came into the land of Judea, and there He was staying with them and He was baptizing.
B043C003V023	43	3	23	Now John also was baptizing in Aenon near Salem, because there was much water there. And they came and were baptized.
B043C003V024	43	3	24	For John was not yet cast into prison.
B043C003V025	43	3	25	Then there came to be a dispute between John's disciples and a Jew about purification.
B043C003V026	43	3	26	And they came to John and said to him, "Rabbi, He who was with you beyond the Jordan, to whom you have testified-behold, this [Man] is baptizing, and all [men] are coming to Him!"
B043C003V027	43	3	27	John answered and said, "A man can receive nothing unless it has been given to him from heaven.
B043C003V028	43	3	28	You yourselves bear witness that I said, 'I am not the Christ,' but, 'I have been sent before Him.'
B043C003V029	43	3	29	"He who has the bride is the bridegroom; but the friend of the bridegroom, who stands and hears him, rejoices greatly because of the voice of the bridegroom. Therefore my joy has been fulfilled.
B043C003V030	43	3	30	He must increase, but I must decrease.
B043C003V031	43	3	31	He who comes from above is above all; he who is from the earth is earthly and speaks of the earth. He who comes from heaven is above all.
B043C003V032	43	3	32	And what He has seen and heard, that He testifies; and no one receives His testimony.
B043C003V033	43	3	33	He who receives His testimony has certified that God is true.
B043C003V034	43	3	34	For He whom God has sent speaks the words of God, for God does not give the Spirit by measure.
B043C003V035	43	3	35	The Father loves the Son, and has given all things into His hand.
B043C003V036	43	3	36	He who believes in the Son has eternal life; and he who does not believe the Son will not see life, but the wrath of God abides on him."
B043C004V001	43	4	1	Therefore, when the Lord knew that the Pharisees had heard that Jesus was making and was baptizing more disciples than John
B043C004V002	43	4	2	(although Jesus Himself was not baptizing, but His disciples),
B043C004V003	43	4	3	He left Judea and went away into Galilee.
B043C004V004	43	4	4	But He needed to pass through Samaria.
B043C004V005	43	4	5	Therefore He came to a city of Samaria, which is called Sychar, near the piece of land which Jacob gave to his son Joseph.
B043C004V006	43	4	6	Now Jacob's well was there. Therefore Jesus, having become tired from the journey, was sitting thus by the well. It was about the sixth hour.
B043C004V007	43	4	7	A woman of Samaria came to draw water. Jesus said to her, "Give Me a drink."
B043C004V008	43	4	8	For His disciples had gone away into the city, that they might buy provisions.
B043C004V009	43	4	9	Then the woman of Samaria said to Him, "How is it that You, being a Jew, ask a drink from me, a Samaritan woman?"For Jews do not associate with Samaritans.
B043C004V010	43	4	10	Jesus answered and said to her, "If you had known the gift of God, and who it is that says to you, 'Give Me a drink,' you would have asked Him, and He would have given to you living water."
B043C004V011	43	4	11	The woman said to Him, "Sir, You have nothing to draw with, and the well is deep. Where then do You get that living water?
B043C004V012	43	4	12	Are You greater than our father Jacob,[ ]who gave us the well, and drank of it himself, as well as his sons and his livestock?"
B043C004V013	43	4	13	Jesus answered and said to her, "Whoever drinks of this water will thirst again,
B043C004V014	43	4	14	but whoever drinks of the water which I shall give him will by no means ever thirst again. But the water which I shall give him will become in him a fountain of water springing up into eternal life."
B043C004V015	43	4	15	The woman said to Him, "Sir, give me this water, that I may not thirst, nor come here to draw."
B043C004V016	43	4	16	Jesus said to her, "Go, call your husband, and come here."
B043C004V017	43	4	17	The woman answered and said, "I have no husband."Jesus said to her, "You have said well, 'I have no husband,'
B043C004V018	43	4	18	"for you have had five husbands, and [the one] whom you now have is not your husband; in this you have said truly."
B043C004V019	43	4	19	The woman said to Him, "Sir, I perceive that You are a prophet.
B043C004V020	43	4	20	Our fathers worshipped on this mountain, and you [Jews] say that in Jerusalem is the place where it is necessary to worship."
B043C004V021	43	4	21	Jesus said to her, "Woman, believe Me, the hour is coming when you will neither on this mountain, nor in Jerusalem, worship the Father.
B043C004V022	43	4	22	You worship what you do not know; we [Jews ]worship what we know, because salvation is of the Jews.
B043C004V023	43	4	23	But the hour is coming, and now is, when the true worshippers will worship the Father in spirit and truth; for the Father is seeking such to worship Him.
B043C004V024	43	4	24	God [is] Spirit, and those who worship Him must worship in spirit and truth."
B043C004V025	43	4	25	The woman said to Him, "I know that Messiah is coming"(who is called Christ). "When He comes, He will proclaim to us all things."
B043C004V026	43	4	26	Jesus said to her, "I am [He,] the [One ]speaking to you."
B043C004V027	43	4	27	And at this point His disciples came, and they marveled that He was speaking with a woman; however no one said, "What do You seek?"or, "Why are You speaking with her?"
B043C004V028	43	4	28	The woman then left her water jar, went her way into the city, and said to the men,
B043C004V029	43	4	29	Come, see a Man who told me everything I ever did. Could this be the Christ?"
B043C004V030	43	4	30	They went out of the city and were coming to Him.
B043C004V031	43	4	31	But in the meantime the disciples urged Him, saying, "Rabbi, eat."
B043C004V032	43	4	32	But He said to them, "I have food to eat of which you do not know."
B043C004V033	43	4	33	Therefore the disciples were saying to one another, "Has anyone brought Him [something] to eat?"
B043C004V034	43	4	34	Jesus said to them, "My food is to do the will of Him who sent Me, and to finish His work.
B043C004V035	43	4	35	Do you not say, 'There are still four months and the harvest comes'? Behold, I say to you, lift up your eyes and see the fields, for they are already white for harvest!
B043C004V036	43	4	36	And he who[ ]reaps receives wages, and gathers fruit unto eternal life, that both he who sows and he who reaps may rejoice together.
B043C004V037	43	4	37	For in this the saying is true: 'One sows and another reaps.'
B043C004V038	43	4	38	"I sent you to reap that for which you have not labored; others have labored, and you have entered into their labors."
B043C004V039	43	4	39	And many of the Samaritans of that city believed in Him because of the word of the woman testifying, "He told me everything I ever did."
B043C004V040	43	4	40	So when the Samaritans had come to Him, they were asking Him to stay with them; and He stayed there two days.
B043C004V041	43	4	41	And many more believed because of His word.
B043C004V042	43	4	42	Then they were saying to the woman, "No longer because of your speech do we believe, for we ourselves have heard and know that this is truly the Christ, the Savior of the world."
B043C004V043	43	4	43	Now after the two days He went out from there and went to Galilee.
B043C004V044	43	4	44	For Jesus Himself testified that a prophet has no honor in his own country.
B043C004V045	43	4	45	Therefore when He came into Galilee, the Galileans received Him, having seen all the things which He did in Jerusalem at the feast; for they also went to the feast.
B043C004V046	43	4	46	Then Jesus came again to Cana of Galilee where He made the water wine. And there was a certain nobleman whose son was sick in Capernaum.
B043C004V047	43	4	47	When he heard that Jesus had come out of Judea into Galilee, he went to Him and asked Him that He might come down and heal his son, for he was about to die.
B043C004V048	43	4	48	Then Jesus said to him, "Unless you [people] see signs and wonders, you will by no means believe."
B043C004V049	43	4	49	The nobleman said to Him, "Sir, come down before my child dies!"
B043C004V050	43	4	50	Jesus said to him, "Go; your son lives."And the man believed the word that Jesus spoke to him, and went away.
B043C004V051	43	4	51	And already as he was going, his servants met him and reported, saying, "Your child lives!"
B043C004V052	43	4	52	Then he inquired from them the hour at which he got better. And they said to him, "Yesterday at the seventh hour the fever left him."
B043C004V053	43	4	53	Therefore the father knew that it was at the same hour in which Jesus said to him, "Your son lives."And he himself believed, and his whole household.
B043C004V054	43	4	54	This again is the second sign Jesus did, after He had come out of Judea into Galilee.
B043C005V001	43	5	1	After these things there was a feast of the Jews, and Jesus went up to Jerusalem.
B043C005V002	43	5	2	Now there is in Jerusalem by the Sheep [Gate] a pool, which is called in Hebrew, Bethesda, having five porches.
B043C005V003	43	5	3	In these [porches] were lying a great multitude of those who were sick, blind, lame, paralyzed, waiting for the moving of the water.
B043C005V004	43	5	4	For an angel from time to[ ]time descended into the pool and stirred up the water; therefore the first [one] having gone in after the stirring up of the water, became well of whatever disease he was suffering.
B043C005V005	43	5	5	Now there was a certain man there who had an ailment [for ]thirty-eight years.
B043C005V006	43	5	6	When Jesus saw this [man] lying there, and knew that he already had been in [that condition] a long time, He said to him, "Do you wish to become well?"
B043C005V007	43	5	7	The sick man answered Him, "Sir, I do not have a man, so that whenever the water is stirred up, he may put me into the pool; but while I am coming, another descends before me."
B043C005V008	43	5	8	Jesus said to him, "Arise, take up your bed and walk."
B043C005V009	43	5	9	And immediately the man became well, and took up his bed, and began to walk. And that day was the Sabbath.
B043C005V010	43	5	10	Therefore the Jews said to the man who was healed, "It is the Sabbath; it is not lawful for you to carry your bed."
B043C005V011	43	5	11	He answered them, "He that made me whole, He said to me, 'Take up your bed and walk.' "
B043C005V012	43	5	12	Then they asked him, "Who is the Man who said to you, 'Take up your bed and walk'?"
B043C005V013	43	5	13	But the one who was healed did not know who it was, for Jesus had turned aside, while a crowd was in that place.
B043C005V014	43	5	14	After these things Jesus found him in the temple, and said to him, "See, you have become well. Sin no more, lest something worse may happen to you."
B043C005V015	43	5	15	The man went away and reported to the Jews that Jesus was the [One ]who had made him well.
B043C005V016	43	5	16	And on account of this the Jews began to persecute Jesus, and were seeking to kill Him, because He was doing these things on the Sabbath.
B043C005V017	43	5	17	But Jesus answered them, "My Father has been working until now, and I am working."
B043C005V018	43	5	18	Because of this the Jews were seeking all the more to kill Him, because not only was He breaking the Sabbath, but also He called God His own Father, making Himself equal with God.
B043C005V019	43	5	19	Then Jesus answered and said to them, "Most assuredly I say to you, the Son can do nothing of Himself, but what He sees the Father doing; for whatever He does, the Son also does in like manner.
B043C005V020	43	5	20	For the Father loves the Son, and shows to Him all things which He Himself does; and greater works than these He will show Him, so that you may marvel.
B043C005V021	43	5	21	For as the Father raises up the dead and gives life, thus also the Son gives life to whom He wills.
B043C005V022	43	5	22	For the Father judges no one, but He has given all judgment to the Son,
B043C005V023	43	5	23	so that all may honor the Son even as they honor the Father. He who does not honor the Son does not honor the Father who sent Him.
B043C005V024	43	5	24	"Most assuredly I say to you, he who hears My word and believes in Him who sent Me has everlasting life, and shall not come into judgment, but has passed from death into life.
B043C005V025	43	5	25	Most assuredly I say to you, that an hour is coming, and now is, when the dead will hear the voice of the Son of God; and those having heard shall live.
B043C005V026	43	5	26	For just as the Father has life in Himself, so He has granted the Son to have life in Himself,
B043C005V027	43	5	27	and has given Him authority to execute judgment also, because He is [the] Son of Man.
B043C005V028	43	5	28	Do not marvel at this; for an hour is coming in which all those in the tombs will hear His voice
B043C005V029	43	5	29	and shall come forth-those who have done good, to a resurrection of life, and those who have done evil, to a resurrection of condemnation.
B043C005V030	43	5	30	I can of My own self do nothing. Even as I hear, I judge; and My judgment is just, because I do not seek My own will but the will of the Father who sent Me.
B043C005V031	43	5	31	"If I testify of Myself, My testimony is not valid.
B043C005V032	43	5	32	There is another who testifies about Me, and I know that the testimony which He testifies concerning Me is true.
B043C005V033	43	5	33	You have sent to John, and he has testified to the truth.
B043C005V034	43	5	34	But I do not receive the testimony from man, but these things I say so that you may be saved.
B043C005V035	43	5	35	He was the burning and shining lamp, and you were willing to rejoice for a while in his light.
B043C005V036	43	5	36	But I have a testimony greater than John's; for the works which the Father gave to Me, that I should complete them, these very works which I do, testify of Me, that the Father has sent Me.
B043C005V037	43	5	37	And the Father Himself, who sent Me, has testified about Me. You have neither heard His voice at any time, nor seen His form.
B043C005V038	43	5	38	But you do not have His word abiding in you, because [Him ]whom He sent, Him you do not believe.
B043C005V039	43	5	39	You search the Scriptures, because you think [that] in them you have eternal life; and these are they which testify about Me.
B043C005V040	43	5	40	But you are unwilling to come to Me, so that you may have life.
B043C005V041	43	5	41	I do not receive glory from men.
B043C005V042	43	5	42	But I have known you, that you do not have the love of God in yourselves.
B043C005V043	43	5	43	I have come in My Father's name, and you do not receive Me; if another comes in his own name, him you will receive.
B043C005V044	43	5	44	How can you believe, who receive glory from one another, and do not seek the glory which is from the only God?
B043C005V045	43	5	45	Do not think that I will accuse you to the Father; there is one who accuses you-Moses, in whom you have hoped.
B043C005V046	43	5	46	For if you believed Moses, you would have believed Me; for he wrote about Me.
B043C005V047	43	5	47	But if you do not believe his writings, how will you believe My words?"
B043C006V001	43	6	1	After these things Jesus went over the Sea of Galilee, that is, of Tiberias.
B043C006V002	43	6	2	And a large crowd was following Him, because they were seeing His signs which He was doing upon those who were sick.
B043C006V003	43	6	3	And Jesus went up on the mountain, and there He sat down with His disciples.
B043C006V004	43	6	4	Now the Passover, the feast of the Jews, was near.
B043C006V005	43	6	5	Then Jesus lifted up His eyes, and seeing that a large crowd was coming toward Him, He said to Philip, "Where shall we buy bread, that these [people ]may eat?"
B043C006V006	43	6	6	But this He said to test him, for He Himself knew what He was about to do.
B043C006V007	43	6	7	Philip answered Him, "Two hundred denarii [worth of] bread is not enough for them, that each of them might receive a little."
B043C006V008	43	6	8	One of His disciples, Andrew, Simon Peter's brother, said to Him,
B043C006V009	43	6	9	There is a little boy here who has five barley loaves and two small fish, but what are they for so many?"
B043C006V010	43	6	10	Then Jesus said, "Make the people to recline."Now there was much grass in that place. Therefore the men reclined, in number about five thousand.
B043C006V011	43	6	11	And Jesus took the loaves, and having given thanks He distributed them to the disciples, and the disciples to those who were reclining; and likewise of the fish, as much as they wished.
B043C006V012	43	6	12	But when they were filled, He said to His disciples, "Gather up the leftover fragments, so that nothing may be lost."
B043C006V013	43	6	13	Therefore they gathered [them] up, and they filled twelve baskets of fragments from the five barley loaves which were left over by those who had eaten.
B043C006V014	43	6	14	Then those men, when they had seen the sign that Jesus did, said, "This is truly the Prophet who is to come into the world."
B043C006V015	43	6	15	Therefore Jesus, knowing that they were about to come and seize Him, that they might make Him king, withdrew to the mountain by Himself.
B043C006V016	43	6	16	Now when evening came, His disciples went down to the sea,
B043C006V017	43	6	17	and having entered into the boat, they were going across the sea to Capernaum. And darkness had already come, and Jesus had not come to them.
B043C006V018	43	6	18	And the sea was agitated by a great blowing wind.
B043C006V019	43	6	19	Therefore having rowed about three or four miles, they saw Jesus walking on the sea and drawing near to the boat; and they were frightened.
B043C006V020	43	6	20	But He said to them, "[It is] I AM; do not fear."
B043C006V021	43	6	21	Then they were willing to receive Him into the boat, and immediately the boat arrived at the land to which they were going.
B043C006V022	43	6	22	On the next day, when the crowd which had remained on the other side of the sea, having seen that there was no other boat there, except that one in which His disciples had entered, and that Jesus had not entered into the boat with His disciples, but His disciples had gone away alone-
B043C006V023	43	6	23	however, other boats came from Tiberias, near the place where they ate bread after the Lord had given thanks-
B043C006V024	43	6	24	when the crowd therefore saw that Jesus was not there, nor His disciples, they got into boats and came to Capernaum, seeking Jesus.
B043C006V025	43	6	25	And having found Him on the other side of the sea, they said to Him, "Rabbi, when did You come here?"
B043C006V026	43	6	26	Jesus answered them and said, "Most assuredly I say to you, you seek Me, not because you saw the signs, but because you ate from the loaves and were satisfied.
B043C006V027	43	6	27	Work not for the food which perishes, but for the food which abides unto everlasting life, which the Son of Man will give to you; for [upon] Him God the Father has set [His] seal."
B043C006V028	43	6	28	Then they said to Him, "What should we do, that we may work the works of God?"
B043C006V029	43	6	29	Jesus answered and said to them, "This is the work of God, that you believe in Him whom He sent."
B043C006V030	43	6	30	Therefore they said to Him, "What sign will You do then, so that we may see it and believe You? What work do You perform?
B043C006V031	43	6	31	Our fathers ate the manna in the wilderness; as it is written, 'He gave them bread from heaven to eat.' "
B043C006V032	43	6	32	Then Jesus said to them, "Most assuredly I say to you, Moses has not given you the bread from heaven, but My Father gives you the true bread from heaven.
B043C006V033	43	6	33	For the bread of God is He who comes down from heaven and gives life to the world."
B043C006V034	43	6	34	Then they said to Him, "Lord, give us this bread always."
B043C006V035	43	6	35	And Jesus said to them, "I am the bread of life. He who comes to Me shall never hunger, and he who believes in Me shall never thirst.
B043C006V036	43	6	36	But I told you that you have both seen Me and you do not believe.
B043C006V037	43	6	37	All that the Father gives Me shall come to Me, and the one who comes to Me I will by no means cast out.
B043C006V038	43	6	38	For I have come down from heaven, not that I might do My will, but the will of Him who sent Me.
B043C006V039	43	6	39	And this is the will of the Father who sent Me, that of all He has given Me, I should lose nothing, but should raise it up at the last day.
B043C006V040	43	6	40	And this is the will of Him who sent Me, that everyone who sees the Son and believes in Him may have eternal life; and I will raise him up at the last day."
B043C006V041	43	6	41	Therefore the Jews were murmuring about Him, because He said, "I am the bread which came down from heaven."
B043C006V042	43	6	42	And they were saying, "Is not this Jesus, the son of Joseph, whose father and mother we know? How then does this [Man] say, 'I have come down from heaven'?"
B043C006V043	43	6	43	Jesus therefore answered and said to them, "Do not murmur among yourselves.
B043C006V044	43	6	44	No one can come to Me unless the Father who sent Me should draw him; and I will raise him up at the last day.
B043C006V045	43	6	45	It is written in the prophets, 'And they shall all be taught of God.' Therefore everyone who hears from the Father, and has learned, comes to Me.
B043C006V046	43	6	46	Not that anyone has seen the Father, except He who is from God; He has seen the Father.
B043C006V047	43	6	47	Most assuredly I say to you, he who believes in Me has eternal life.
B043C006V048	43	6	48	I am the bread of life.
B043C006V049	43	6	49	Your fathers ate the manna in the wilderness, and died.
B043C006V050	43	6	50	This is the bread which comes down from heaven, that one may eat of it and not die.
B043C006V051	43	6	51	I am the living bread which came down from heaven. If anyone eats of this bread, he will live forever; and the bread that I shall give is My flesh, which I shall give for the life of the world."
B043C006V052	43	6	52	Therefore the Jews were contending with one another, saying, "How can this Man give us His flesh to eat?"
B043C006V053	43	6	53	Then Jesus said to them, "Most assuredly, I say to you, unless you eat the flesh of the Son of Man and drink His blood, you have no life in yourselves.
B043C006V054	43	6	54	Whoever eats My flesh and drinks My blood has eternal life, and I will raise him up in the last day.
B043C006V055	43	6	55	For My flesh truly is food, and My blood truly is drink.
B043C006V056	43	6	56	He who eats My flesh and drinks My blood abides in Me, and I in him.
B043C006V057	43	6	57	Just as the living Father sent Me, and I live because of the Father, so he who feeds on Me will live because of Me.
