B043C015V002	43	15	2	Every branch in Me which does not bear fruit He takes away; and every [branch] which bears fruit He prunes, so that it may bear more fruit.
B043C015V003	43	15	3	You are already clean because of the word which I have spoken to you.
B043C015V004	43	15	4	Abide in Me, and I in you. Just as the branch cannot bear fruit on its own, unless it abides in the vine, so neither can you unless you abide in Me.
B043C015V005	43	15	5	I am the vine, you [are] the branches. He who abides in Me, and I in him, bears much fruit; because apart from Me you can do nothing.
B043C015V006	43	15	6	If anyone does not abide in Me, he is cast out like a branch and dries up; and they gather them and throw [them] into the fire, and they are burned.
B043C015V007	43	15	7	If you abide in Me, and My words abide in you, you will ask what ever you may desire, and it shall be done for you.
B043C015V008	43	15	8	By this My Father is glorified, that you may bear much fruit; and you will become My disciples.
B043C015V009	43	15	9	"Just as the Father loved Me, I also have loved you; abide in My love.
B043C015V010	43	15	10	If you keep My commandments, you will abide in My love, just as I have kept My Father's commandments and I abide in His love.
B043C015V011	43	15	11	These things I have spoken to you, that My joy may abide in you, and that your joy may be full.
B043C015V012	43	15	12	This is My commandment, that you love one another as I have loved you.
B043C015V013	43	15	13	Greater love has no one than this, that one should lay down his life on behalf of his friends.
B043C015V014	43	15	14	You are My friends if you do what I command you.
B043C015V015	43	15	15	No longer do I call you servants, because a servant does not know what his master is doing; but I have called you friends, because all things which I heard from My Father I have made known to you.
B043C015V016	43	15	16	You did not choose Me, but I chose you, and appointed you, that you should go and bear fruit, and that your fruit should remain, so that whatever you may ask the Father in My name He may give to you.
B043C015V017	43	15	17	These things I command you, that you may love one another.
B043C015V018	43	15	18	"If the world hates you, you know that it hated Me before it hated you.
B043C015V019	43	15	19	If you were of the world, the world would love its own. Yet because you are not of the world, but I chose you out of the world, because of this the world hates you.
B043C015V020	43	15	20	Remember the word which I said to you, 'A servant is not greater than his master.' If they persecuted Me, they will also persecute you. If they kept My word, they will keep yours also.
B043C015V021	43	15	21	But all these things they will do to you for My name's sake, because they do not know Him who sent Me.
B043C015V022	43	15	22	If I had not come and spoken to them, they would have no sin, but now they have no excuse concerning their sin.
B043C015V023	43	15	23	He who hates Me hates My Father also.
B043C015V024	43	15	24	If I had not done the works among them which no one else has done, they would have no sin; but now they have both seen and they have hated both Me and My Father.
B043C015V025	43	15	25	But [this was] so that the word might be fulfilled which is written in their law, 'They hated Me without cause.'
B043C015V026	43	15	26	"But when the Helper comes, whom I shall send to you from the Father, the Spirit of truth who proceeds from the Father, He will testify about Me.
B043C015V027	43	15	27	And you also will testify, because you have been with Me from the beginning.
B043C016V001	43	16	1	"These things I have spoken to you, so that you should not be made to stumble.
B043C016V002	43	16	2	They will excommunicate you; but a time is coming when everyone who kills you will think that he is offering God a service.
B043C016V003	43	16	3	And these things they will do [to you ]because they did not know the Father nor Me.
B043C016V004	43	16	4	But these things I have spoken to you, so that when the time comes, you may remember them, that I told you. But these things I did not say to you from the beginning, because I was with you.
B043C016V005	43	16	5	"But now I am going to Him who sent Me, and none of you asks Me, 'Where are You going?'
B043C016V006	43	16	6	"But because I have spoken these things to you, sorrow has filled your heart.
B043C016V007	43	16	7	Nevertheless I speak the truth to you. It is profitable for you that I go away; for if I do not go away, the Helper will not come to you; but if I depart, I will send Him to you.
B043C016V008	43	16	8	And when He comes, He will convict the world of sin, and of righteousness, and of judgment:
B043C016V009	43	16	9	of sin, because they do not believe in Me;
B043C016V010	43	16	10	of righteousness, because I am going to My Father and you see Me no more;
B043C016V011	43	16	11	of judgment, because the ruler of this world has been judged.
B043C016V012	43	16	12	I still have many things to say to you, but you cannot bear them now.
B043C016V013	43	16	13	However, when He, the Spirit of truth, has come, He will guide you into all truth; for He will not speak on His own [authority], but whatever He hears He will speak; and He will announce to you things to come.
B043C016V014	43	16	14	He will glorify Me, for He will take from what is Mine and He will announce it to you.
B043C016V015	43	16	15	All things which the Father has are Mine. Therefore I said that He takes from what is Mine and will announce it to you.
B043C016V016	43	16	16	"A little [while] and you will not see Me; and again a little [while] and you will see Me, because I am going to the Father."
B043C016V017	43	16	17	Then [some] of His disciples said to one another, "What is this that He says to us, 'A little [while] and you will not see Me; and again a little [while] and you will see Me'; and, 'I am going to the Father'?"
B043C016V018	43	16	18	Therefore they said, "What is this that He says, 'A little [while]'? We do not understand what He is saying."
B043C016V019	43	16	19	Now Jesus knew that they were desiring to ask Him, and He said to them, "Are you inquiring with one another that I said, 'A little [while] and you will not see Me; and again a little [while] and you will see Me'?
B043C016V020	43	16	20	Most assuredly I say to you that you will weep and lament, but the world will rejoice; and you will be grieved, but your grief will be turned into joy.
B043C016V021	43	16	21	A woman, whenever she gives birth, has sorrow, because her hour has come; but whenever the child is born, she no longer remembers the anguish, on account of the joy that a human being has been born into the world.
B043C016V022	43	16	22	Therefore you also now have sorrow; but I will see you again and your heart will rejoice, and your joy no one will take from you.
B043C016V023	43	16	23	And in that day you will ask Me nothing. Most assuredly, I say to you, whatever you ask the Father in My name He will give you.
B043C016V024	43	16	24	Until now you have asked nothing in My name. Ask, and you will receive, that your joy may be full.
B043C016V025	43	16	25	"These things I have spoken to you in figures of speech; but the time is coming when I will no longer speak to you in figures of speech, but I will tell you plainly about the Father.
B043C016V026	43	16	26	In that day you will ask in My name, and I do not say to you that I will beseech the Father for you;
B043C016V027	43	16	27	for the Father Himself loves you, because you have loved Me, and have believed that I came forth from God.
B043C016V028	43	16	28	I came forth from the Father and I have come into the world. Again, I am leaving the world and I am going to the Father."
B043C016V029	43	16	29	His disciples said to Him, "See, now You are speaking plainly, and using no figure of speech!
B043C016V030	43	16	30	Now we are sure that You know all things, and have no need that anyone should question You. By this we believe that You came forth from God."
B043C016V031	43	16	31	Jesus answered them, "Now do you believe?
B043C016V032	43	16	32	Indeed a time is coming, and now has come, that you will be scattered, each to his own, and you will leave Me alone. And yet I am not alone, because the Father is with Me.
B043C016V033	43	16	33	These things I have spoken to you, that in Me you may have peace. In the world you have tribulation; but have courage, I have overcome the world."
B043C017V001	43	17	1	Jesus spoke these words, lifted up His eyes to heaven, and said: "Father, the time has come. Glorify Your Son, that Your Son also may glorify You,
B043C017V002	43	17	2	just as You have given Him authority over all flesh, so that He will give eternal life to all You have given Him.
B043C017V003	43	17	3	And this is eternal life, that they may know You, the only true God, and Jesus Christ, whom You have sent.
B043C017V004	43	17	4	I have glorified You on the earth. I have finished the work which You have given Me to do.
B043C017V005	43	17	5	And now, O Father, glorify Me alongside Yourself, with the glory which I had with You before the world was.
B043C017V006	43	17	6	I have manifested Your name to the men whom You have given Me out of the world. They were Yours, You have given them to Me, and they have kept Your word.
B043C017V007	43	17	7	Now they have known that all things which You have given Me are from You.
B043C017V008	43	17	8	Because I have given to them the words which You have given Me; and they have received [them], and they knew truly that I came forth from You; and they have believed that You sent Me.
B043C017V009	43	17	9	I pray for them. I do not pray for the world but for [those] whom You have given Me, for they are Yours.
B043C017V010	43	17	10	And all Mine are Yours, and Yours [are] Mine, and I have been glorified in them.
B043C017V011	43	17	11	And I am no longer in the world, yet these are in the world, and I am coming to You. Holy Father, keep them in Your name which You have given to Me, that they may be one just as We [are].
B043C017V012	43	17	12	When I was with them in the world, I kept them in Your name. [Those] whom You have given to Me I guarded; and not one of them is lost except the son of perdition, so that the Scripture might be fulfilled.
B043C017V013	43	17	13	But now I am coming to You, and these things I speak in the world, so that they may have My joy fulfilled in themselves.
B043C017V014	43	17	14	I have given them Your word; and the world has hated them because they are not of the world, just as I am not of the world.
B043C017V015	43	17	15	I do not ask that You should take them out of the world, but that You should keep them from the evil [one].
B043C017V016	43	17	16	They are not of the world, just as I am not of the world.
B043C017V017	43	17	17	Sanctify them by Your truth; Your word is truth.
B043C017V018	43	17	18	Just as You sent Me into the world, I also have sent them into the world.
B043C017V019	43	17	19	And for their sakes I sanctify Myself, that they also may be sanctified by [the] truth.
B043C017V020	43	17	20	"I am not praying for these alone, but also for those who believe in Me through their word;
B043C017V021	43	17	21	so that they all may be one, just as You, Father, are in Me, and I in You; that they also may be one in Us, so that the world may believe that You sent Me.
B043C017V022	43	17	22	And the glory which You have given to Me, I have given to them, so that they may be one just as We are one:
B043C017V023	43	17	23	I in them, and You in Me; so that they may be perfected in unity, and so that the world may know that You have sent Me, and You loved them just as You loved Me.
B043C017V024	43	17	24	Father, I desire that those also whom You gave Me may be with Me where I am, so that they may behold My glory which You gave to Me; because You loved Me before the foundation of the world.
B043C017V025	43	17	25	O righteous Father! Indeed the world did not know You, yet I knew You; and these knew that You sent Me.
B043C017V026	43	17	26	And I made known to them Your name, and I will make it known, so that the love [with] which You loved Me may be in them, and I in them."
B043C018V001	43	18	1	After saying these things, Jesus went out with His disciples across the winter stream Kidron, where there[ was] a garden, into which He and His disciples entered.
B043C018V002	43	18	2	Now Judas, the [one] betraying Him, also knew the place, because Jesus often gathered there also with His disciples.
B043C018V003	43	18	3	Then Judas, having taken the detachment [of soldiers], and attendants from the chief priests and Pharisees, came there with lanterns, torches, and weapons.
B043C018V004	43	18	4	Jesus therefore, knowing all things coming upon Him, went out and said to them, "Whom do you seek?"
B043C018V005	43	18	5	They answered Him, "Jesus the Nazarene."Jesus said to them, "I AM."And Judas, the [one] betraying Him, was standing with them.
B043C018V006	43	18	6	Therefore when He said to them, "I AM,"they stepped back and fell to the ground.
B043C018V007	43	18	7	Then He asked them again, "Whom do you seek?"And they said, "Jesus the Nazarene."
B043C018V008	43	18	8	Jesus answered, "I have told you that I AM! Therefore if you seek Me, allow these [men] to go,"
B043C018V009	43	18	9	so that the word might be fulfilled which He said, "[Those] whom You have given Me I have lost none."
B043C018V010	43	18	10	Then Simon Peter, having a sword, drew it and struck the servant of the high priest, and cut off his right ear. And the servant's name was Malchus.
B043C018V011	43	18	11	Then Jesus said to Peter, "Put your sword into the sheath. Shall I not drink the cup which My Father has given Me?"
B043C018V012	43	18	12	Then the detachment [of soldiers] and the captain and the attendants of the Jews arrested Jesus and bound Him.
B043C018V013	43	18	13	And they led Him away to Annas first, for he was the father-in-law of Caiaphas who was high priest that year.
B043C018V014	43	18	14	Now it was Caiaphas who advised the Jews that it was profitable for one man to perish for the people.
B043C018V015	43	18	15	And Simon Peter was following Jesus, as was the other disciple. Now that disciple was known to the high priest, and entered with Jesus into the courtyard of the high priest.
B043C018V016	43	18	16	But Peter stood at the door outside. Then the other disciple, who was known to the high priest, went out and spoke to the doorkeeper, and brought Peter in.
B043C018V017	43	18	17	Then the servant girl who kept the door said to Peter, "You are not also one of this Man's disciples, [are you]?"He said, "I am not."
B043C018V018	43	18	18	And the servants and attendants who had made a fire of coals stood there, for it was cold, and they were warming themselves. Now Peter was standing with them and warming himself.
B043C018V019	43	18	19	Then high priest asked Jesus about His disciples and His doctrine.
B043C018V020	43	18	20	Jesus answered him, "I spoke openly to the world. I always taught in synagogues and in the temple, where the Jews always come together, and in secret I spoke nothing.
B043C018V021	43	18	21	Why do you question Me? Question those who have heard Me, what I spoke to them. Indeed they know what I said."
B043C018V022	43	18	22	And when He had said these things, one of the attendants who stood by slapped Jesus with the palm of his hand, saying, "Is this how You answer the high priest?"
B043C018V023	43	18	23	Jesus answered him, "If I have spoken evil, testify of the evil; but if well, why do you strike Me?"
B043C018V024	43	18	24	Then Annas sent Him bound to Caiaphas the high priest.
B043C018V025	43	18	25	Now Simon Peter was standing and warming himself. Therefore they said to him, "You are not also [one] of His disciples, [are you]?"Then he denied it and said, "I am not!"
B043C018V026	43	18	26	One of the servants of the high priest, a relative of him whose ear Peter cut off, said, "Did I not see you in the garden with Him?"
B043C018V027	43	18	27	Peter then denied again; and immediately a rooster crowed.
B043C018V028	43	18	28	Then they led Jesus from Caiaphas to the Praetorium, and it was early morning. But they themselves did not enter into the Praetorium, lest they might be defiled, but so that they might eat the Passover.
B043C018V029	43	18	29	Then Pilate went out to them and said, "What accusation do you bring against this Man?"
B043C018V030	43	18	30	They answered and said to him, "If He were not an evildoer, we would not have delivered Him over to you."
B043C018V031	43	18	31	Then Pilate said to them, "You take Him and judge Him according to your law."Therefore the Jews said to him, "It is not lawful for us to kill anyone,"
B043C018V032	43	18	32	that the word of Jesus might be fulfilled which He said, signifying by what sort of death He was about to die.
B043C018V033	43	18	33	Then Pilate entered the Praetorium again, and called Jesus, and said to Him, "Are You the King of the Jews?"
B043C018V034	43	18	34	Jesus answered him, "For yourself do you say this, or did others tell you about Me?"
B043C018V035	43	18	35	Pilate answered, "Am I a Jew? Your own nation and the chief priests have delivered You to me. What have You done?"
B043C018V036	43	18	36	Jesus answered, "My kingdom is not of this world. If My kingdom were of this world, My servants would fight, so that I might not be delivered to the Jews; but now My kingdom is not from here."
B043C018V037	43	18	37	Pilate therefore said to Him, "Are You a king then?"Jesus answered, "You say [rightly] that I am a king. For this [reason] I have been born, and for this [reason] I have come into the world, that I should testify to the truth. Everyone who is of the truth hears My voice."
B043C018V038	43	18	38	Pilate said to Him, "What is truth?"And having said this, he went out again to the Jews, and said to them, "I find no fault in Him.
B043C018V039	43	18	39	"But you have a custom that I should release someone to you at the Passover. Therefore do you wish [that] I should release the King of the Jews?"
B043C018V040	43	18	40	Then they all cried out again, saying, "Not this [Man], but Barabbas!"Now Barabbas was a bandit.
B043C019V001	43	19	1	So then Pilate took Jesus and flogged [Him].
B043C019V002	43	19	2	And the soldiers twisted a crown out of thorns and put it on His head, and they put a purple robe around Him.
B043C019V003	43	19	3	And they kept saying, "Hail, King of the Jews!"And they were striking Him with their hands.
B043C019V004	43	19	4	Pilate then went out again, and said to them, "Behold, I am bringing Him out to you, so that you may know that I find no fault in Him."
B043C019V005	43	19	5	Then Jesus came out, wearing the crown of thorns and the purple robe. And Pilate said to them, "Behold, the Man!"
B043C019V006	43	19	6	Therefore, when the chief priests and the attendants saw Him, they cried out, saying, "Crucify, crucify Him!"Pilate said to them, "You take Him and crucify [Him], for I find no fault in Him."
B043C019V007	43	19	7	The Jews answered him, "We have a law, and according to our law He ought to die, because He made Himself the Son of God."
