B043C020V013	43	20	13	Then they said to her, "Woman, why are you weeping?"She said to them, "Because they have taken away my Lord, and I do not know where they put Him."
B043C020V014	43	20	14	And having said these things, she turned back and saw Jesus standing there, and did not know that it was Jesus.
B043C020V015	43	20	15	Jesus said to her, "Woman, why are you weeping? Whom do you seek?"She, supposing Him to be the gardener, said to Him, "Sir, if You carried Him away, tell me where You put Him, and I will take Him away."
B043C020V016	43	20	16	Jesus said to her, "Mary!"She turned and said to Him, "Rabboni!"(which means, Teacher).
B043C020V017	43	20	17	Jesus said to her, "Do not cling to Me, for I have not yet ascended to My Father; but go to My brothers and say to them, 'I am ascending to My Father and your Father, and to My God and your God.' "
B043C020V018	43	20	18	Mary Magdalene went reporting to the disciples that she had seen the Lord, and [that] He had spoken these things to her.
B043C020V019	43	20	19	Then, the same day at evening, being the first day of the week, when the doors were shut where the disciples were assembled, for fear of the Jews, Jesus came and stood in the midst, and said to them, "Peace to you."
B043C020V020	43	20	20	And having said this, He showed them His hands and His side. Then the disciples rejoiced when they saw the Lord.
B043C020V021	43	20	21	Therefore Jesus said to them again, "Peace to you! Just as the Father has sent Me, I also send you."
B043C020V022	43	20	22	And when He had said this, He breathed on them, and said to them, "Receive the Holy Spirit.
B043C020V023	43	20	23	If you forgive the sins of any, they are forgiven them; if you retain [the sins] of any, they have been retained."
B043C020V024	43	20	24	But Thomas, one of the twelve, the [one ]called the Twin, was not with them when Jesus came.
B043C020V025	43	20	25	The other disciples therefore said to him, "We have seen the Lord."So he said to them, "Unless I see in His hands the print of the nails, and put my finger into the print of the nails, and put my hand into His side, I will by no means believe."
B043C020V026	43	20	26	And after eight days His disciples were again inside, and Thomas with them. Jesus came, the doors having been closed, and stood in the midst, and said, "Peace to you!"
B043C020V027	43	20	27	Then He said to Thomas, "Bring your finger here, and see My hands; and bring your hand here, and put [it] into My side. Be not unbelieving, but believing."
B043C020V028	43	20	28	And Thomas answered and said to Him, "My Lord and my God!"
B043C020V029	43	20	29	Jesus said to him, "Because you have seen Me, you have believed. Blessed are those who have not seen and yet have believed."
B043C020V030	43	20	30	And truly Jesus did many other signs in the presence of His disciples, which are not written in this book;
B043C020V031	43	20	31	but these have been written so that you may believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God, and that [by ]believing you may have life in His name.
B043C021V001	43	21	1	After these things Jesus showed Himself again to the disciples at the Sea of Tiberias, and in this manner He showed Himself:
B043C021V002	43	21	2	Simon Peter, Thomas called the Twin, Nathanael of Cana in Galilee, the [sons] of Zebedee, and two others of His disciples were together.
B043C021V003	43	21	3	Simon Peter said to them, "I am going fishing."They said to him, "We are coming with you also."They went out and immediately got into the boat, and that night they caught nothing.
B043C021V004	43	21	4	But as daybreak had already come, Jesus stood upon the shore; however the disciples did not know that it was Jesus.
B043C021V005	43	21	5	Then Jesus said to them, "Children, have you any food?"They answered Him, "No."
B043C021V006	43	21	6	And He said to them, "Cast the net on the right side of the boat, and you will find [some]."Therefore they cast, and they were not able to haul it in because of the multitude of fish.
B043C021V007	43	21	7	Therefore that disciple whom Jesus loved said to Peter, "It is the Lord!"Now when Simon Peter heard that it was the Lord, he put on his outer garment (for he had removed it), and he threw himself into the sea.
B043C021V008	43	21	8	But the other disciples came in the little boat (for they were not far from the land, but about two hundred cubits), dragging the net with fish.
B043C021V009	43	21	9	Then as they got off onto the land, they saw a charcoal fire laid there, and fish placed on it, and bread.
B043C021V010	43	21	10	Jesus said to them, "Bring [some] of the fish which you have just caught."
B043C021V011	43	21	11	Simon Peter went up and hauled the net onto the land, full of large fish, one hundred and fifty-three; and although there were so many, the net was not torn.
B043C021V012	43	21	12	Jesus said to them, "Come, eat breakfast."Yet none of the disciples dared to question Him, "Who are You?"-knowing that it was the Lord.
B043C021V013	43	21	13	Jesus then came and took the bread and gave it to them, and likewise the fish.
B043C021V014	43	21	14	This [was] now the third time Jesus was manifested to His disciples, having been raised from the dead.
B043C021V015	43	21	15	So when they had eaten breakfast, Jesus said to Simon Peter, "Simon, [son] of Jonah, do you love Me more than these?"He said to Him, "Yes, Lord; You know that I care for You."He said to him, "Feed My lambs."
B043C021V016	43	21	16	He said to him again a second time, "Simon, [son] of Jonah, do you love Me?"He said to Him, "Yes, Lord; You know that I care for You."He said to him, "Shepherd My sheep."
B043C021V017	43	21	17	He said to him the third time, "Simon, [son] of Jonah, do you care for Me?"Peter was grieved because He said to him the third time, "Do you care for Me?"And he said to Him, "Lord, You know all things; You know that I care for You."Jesus said to him, "Feed My sheep.
B043C021V018	43	21	18	Most assuredly I say to you, when you were younger, you used to dress yourself and used to walk where you wished; but when you are old, you will stretch out your hands, and another will dress you and will carry [you] where you do not wish."
B043C021V019	43	21	19	But this He said, signifying by what kind of death he would glorify God. And when He had spoken this, He said to him, "Follow Me."
B043C021V020	43	21	20	Then Peter, turning around, saw the disciple whom Jesus loved following, who also had reclined on His chest at the supper, and said, "Lord, who is the one who betrays You?"
B043C021V021	43	21	21	Peter, seeing him, said to Jesus, "But Lord, what [about] this [man]?"
B043C021V022	43	21	22	Jesus said to him, "If I will that he remain till I come, what is [that] to you? You follow Me."
B043C021V023	43	21	23	Therefore this saying went out among the brothers that this disciple would not die. Yet Jesus did not say to him that he would not die, but, "If I will that he remain till I come, what is [that] to you?"
B043C021V024	43	21	24	This is the disciple who testifies of these things, and wrote these things; and we know that his testimony is true.
B043C021V025	43	21	25	And there are also many other things which Jesus did, which if they were written one by one, I suppose that not even the world itself would have room for the books which would be written. Amen.
B044C001V001	44	1	1	The former account I made concerning all things, O Theophilus, which Jesus began both to do and teach,
B044C001V002	44	1	2	until the day in which He was taken up, after He through the Holy Spirit had given commandments to the apostles whom He had chosen,
B044C001V003	44	1	3	to whom He also presented Himself alive after His suffering by many convincing proofs, appearing to them during forty days and speaking of the things concerning the kingdom of God.
B044C001V004	44	1	4	And being assembled together with them, He commanded them not to withdraw from Jerusalem, but to await for the Promise of the Father, "which,"He said, "you have heard from Me;
B044C001V005	44	1	5	for John baptized with water, but you shall be baptized with the Holy Spirit not many days from now."
B044C001V006	44	1	6	Therefore, when they had come together, they asked Him, saying, "Lord, will You at this time restore the kingdom to Israel?"
B044C001V007	44	1	7	And He said to them, "It is not for you to know times or seasons which the Father has placed in His own authority.
B044C001V008	44	1	8	But you shall receive power when the Holy Spirit has come upon you; and you shall be witnesses to Me in Jerusalem, and in all Judea and Samaria, and to the end of the earth."
B044C001V009	44	1	9	Now after He said these things, while they were beholding [Him], He was lifted up, and a cloud withdrew Him from their sight.
B044C001V010	44	1	10	And while they looked intently into heaven, while He was going, behold, two men stood along side them in white apparel,
B044C001V011	44	1	11	who also said, "Men of Galilee, why do you stand looking up into heaven? This [same] Jesus, who was taken up from you into heaven, will so come in like manner as you watched Him go into heaven."
B044C001V012	44	1	12	Then they returned to Jerusalem from the mount called Olivet, which is near Jerusalem, a Sabbath day's journey.
B044C001V013	44	1	13	And when they had entered, they went up into the upper room where they were staying; both Peter and James and John and Andrew, Philip and Thomas, Bartholomew and Matthew, James the son of Alphaeus and Simon the Zealot, and Judas the son of James.
B044C001V014	44	1	14	These were continuing with one mind in prayer and petition, together with the women and Mary the mother of Jesus, and with His brothers.
B044C001V015	44	1	15	And in those days Peter, rising up in the midst of the disciples (altogether the number of names was about a hundred and twenty), said,
B044C001V016	44	1	16	"Men, brothers; it was necessary [for] this Scripture to be fulfilled, which the Holy Spirit spoke before by the mouth of David concerning Judas, who became a guide to those who arrested Jesus;
B044C001V017	44	1	17	'for he was numbered with us and obtained a portion in this ministry.'"
B044C001V018	44	1	18	(Now this man purchased a field by means of the wages of[ his] iniquity,[ ] and falling headlong, he burst open in the middle and all his intestines gushed out.
B044C001V019	44	1	19	And it became known to all those dwelling in Jerusalem; so that field is called in their own language, Akel Dama, that is, Field of Blood.)
B044C001V020	44	1	20	"For it is written in the book of Psalms: 'Let his homestead become desolate, and let no one dwell in it'; and, 'May another take his office of overseer. '
B044C001V021	44	1	21	Therefore, of these men who have accompanied us in every time that the Lord Jesus went in and out among us,
B044C001V022	44	1	22	beginning from the baptism of John until the day in which He was taken up from us, one of these must become a witness with us of His resurrection."
B044C001V023	44	1	23	And they nominated two: Joseph who is called Barsabas, who was surnamed Justus, and Matthias.
B044C001V024	44	1	24	And they prayed and said, "You, O Lord, knower of all hearts, show whom You have chosen of these two
B044C001V025	44	1	25	to receive a portion in this ministry and apostleship, from which Judas turned aside to go to his own place."
B044C001V026	44	1	26	And they cast their lots. And the lot fell on Matthias; and he was numbered with the eleven apostles.
B044C002V001	44	2	1	And when the day of Pentecost had fully come, they were all with one accord in one place.
B044C002V002	44	2	2	And suddenly a sound came out of heaven, as being borne along by a violent wind, and it filled the whole house where they were sitting.
B044C002V003	44	2	3	Then there appeared to them divided tongues, as of fire, and one sat upon each of them.
B044C002V004	44	2	4	And they were all filled with the Holy Spirit, and began to speak in different languages, as the Spirit gave them utterance.
B044C002V005	44	2	5	And there were dwelling in Jerusalem Jews, devout men, from every nation of those under heaven.
B044C002V006	44	2	6	And when this sound occurred, the multitude came together, and were confounded, because they were hearing each one speaking in his own language.
B044C002V007	44	2	7	And they were all amazed and were marveling, saying to one another, "Behold, are not all these who are speaking Galileans?
B044C002V008	44	2	8	And how [is it that] we hear, each in our own language in which we were born?
B044C002V009	44	2	9	Parthians and Medes and Elamites, those dwelling in Mesopotamia, Judea and Cappadocia, Pontus and Asia,
B044C002V010	44	2	10	Phrygia and Pamphylia, Egypt and the parts of Libya toward Cyrene, visitors from Rome, both Jews and proselytes,
B044C002V011	44	2	11	Cretans and Arabs-we hear them speaking in our own tongues the mighty [deeds] of God."
B044C002V012	44	2	12	So they were all amazed and perplexed, saying to one another, "What might this mean?"
B044C002V013	44	2	13	Others were mocking and saying, "They are full of new wine."
B044C002V014	44	2	14	But Peter, standing up with the eleven, lifted up his voice and spoke out to them, "Men of Judea and all who dwell in Jerusalem, let this be known to you, and give ear to my words.
B044C002V015	44	2	15	"For these are not drunk, as you suppose, for it is just the third hour of the day.
B044C002V016	44	2	16	"But this is what was spoken by the prophet Joel:
B044C002V017	44	2	17	"And it shall be in the last days,"says God, "that I will pour My Spirit on all flesh, and your sons and your daughters shall prophesy; and your young men shall see visions, and your old men shall dream dreams;"
B044C002V018	44	2	18	"And on My menservants and on My maidservants I will pour out My Spirit in those days; and they shall prophesy.
B044C002V019	44	2	19	And I will give wonders in the heaven above, and signs on the earth below, blood and fire and vapor of smoke.
B044C002V020	44	2	20	The sun shall be changed into darkness, and the moon into blood, before the coming of the great and awesome Day of the Lord.
B044C002V021	44	2	21	And it shall be that everyone who calls on the name of the Lord shall be saved."
B044C002V022	44	2	22	"Men of Israel, hear these words: Jesus of Nazareth, a Man attested by God to you by miracles, wonders, and signs which God did through Him in your midst, just as you yourselves also know-
B044C002V023	44	2	23	Him, being delivered by the determined purpose and foreknowledge of God, you took, and by lawless hands, nailing [Him] to a cross, you killed [Him];
B044C002V024	44	2	24	whom God raised, [thus] doing away with the labor pains of death, because it was not possible for Him to be held by it.
B044C002V025	44	2	25	For David says concerning Him, "I foresaw the Lord always before Me, because He is at My right hand, that I may not be shaken.
B044C002V026	44	2	26	Therefore my heart was glad, and my tongue rejoiced; moreover my flesh also will dwell in hope.
B044C002V027	44	2	27	Because You will not abandon my soul in Hades, nor will You allow Your Holy One to see corruption.
B044C002V028	44	2	28	You have made known to me the ways of life; You will fill me full of joy in Your presence."
B044C002V029	44	2	29	"Men, brothers, let[ me] speak with boldness to you about the patriarch David, that he both died and was buried, and his tomb is with us to this day.
B044C002V030	44	2	30	"Therefore, being a prophet, and knowing that God had sworn with an oath to him that of the fruit of his loins, according to the flesh, He would raise up the Christ to seat [Him ]on his throne,
B044C002V031	44	2	31	foreseeing [this], he spoke about the resurrection of the Christ, "that His soul was not left in Hades, nor did His flesh see corruption."
B044C002V032	44	2	32	"This Jesus God has raised up, of which we all are witnesses."
B044C002V033	44	2	33	"Therefore having being exalted to the right hand of God, and having received from the Father the promise of the Holy Spirit, He poured out this which you now see and hear.
B044C002V034	44	2	34	"For David did not ascend into the heavens, but he says himself: `The LORD said to my Lord, "Sit at My right hand,
B044C002V035	44	2	35	Till I make Your enemies a footstool for Your feet."
B044C002V036	44	2	36	"Therefore let all the house of Israel know assuredly that God has made this Jesus, whom you crucified, both Lord and Christ."
B044C002V037	44	2	37	Now having heard this, they were cut to the heart, and they said to Peter and the rest of the apostles, "Men and brothers, what shall we do?"
B044C002V038	44	2	38	Then Peter said to them, "Repent, and let each of you be baptized in the name of Jesus Christ for the forgiveness of sins; and you shall receive the gift of the Holy Spirit.
B044C002V039	44	2	39	"For the promise is for you and for your children, and for all those afar off, as many as the Lord our God will call."
B044C002V040	44	2	40	And with many other words he testified and exhorted them, saying, "Be saved from this crooked generation."
B044C002V041	44	2	41	Then those who gladly received his word were baptized; and that day about three thousand souls were added.
B044C002V042	44	2	42	And they were continuing in the teaching of the apostles, and in fellowship, and in the breaking of bread, and in prayers.
B044C002V043	44	2	43	Then fear came upon every person, and many wonders and signs were taking place through the apostles.
B044C002V044	44	2	44	Now all who believed were together, and they had all things in common,
B044C002V045	44	2	45	and they were selling their possessions and goods, and were dividing them among all, to the degree that anyone had a need.
B044C002V046	44	2	46	So continuing daily with one accord in the temple, and breaking bread from house to house, they were sharing food with joy and simplicity of heart,
B044C002V047	44	2	47	praising God and having favor with all the people. And the Lord was adding to the church daily those who were being saved.
B044C003V001	44	3	1	Now Peter and John were going up together to the temple at the hour of prayer, [which was ]the ninth [hour].
B044C003V002	44	3	2	And a man lame from his mother's womb was being carried, whom they would lay each day at the gate of the temple which is called Beautiful, to ask alms from those who entered the temple;
B044C003V003	44	3	3	who, when he saw Peter and John about to enter into the temple, began asking for alms.
B044C003V004	44	3	4	And looking intently on him, Peter together with John, said "Look at us."
B044C003V005	44	3	5	And he fixed his attention on them, expecting to receive something from them.
B044C003V006	44	3	6	But Peter said, "Silver and gold I do not have, but [that ]which I do have, I give to you: In the name of Jesus Christ the Nazarene, get up and walk."
B044C003V007	44	3	7	And taking hold of him by his right hand, he raised [him]; and immediately his feet and ankles were strengthened.
B044C003V008	44	3	8	So he, leaping up, stood and walked and entered with them into the temple, walking and leaping, and praising God.
B044C003V009	44	3	9	And all the people saw him walking and praising God.
B044C003V010	44	3	10	Then they recognized that this was the one sitting for the alms at the Beautiful Gate of the temple; and they were filled with astonishment and amazement because of that which had happened to him.
B044C003V011	44	3	11	And while the lame man who had been healed held on to Peter and John, all the people ran together to them in the porch which is called Solomon's, utterly astonished.
B044C003V012	44	3	12	So when Peter saw [this], he replied to the people: "Men of Israel, why do you marvel at this? Or why look so intently at us, as though by our own power or godliness we had made him to walk?
B044C003V013	44	3	13	The God of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, the God of our fathers, glorified His Servant Jesus, whom you indeed delivered up and denied Him in the presence of Pilate, when he had decided to release Him.
B044C003V014	44	3	14	But you denied the Holy and Righteous One, and asked that a murderer be released to you,
B044C003V015	44	3	15	and killed the Author of life, whom God raised from the dead, of which we are witnesses.
B044C003V016	44	3	16	And on the basis of faith in His name, this [one ]whom you observe and know, was made strong by His name. And the faith, which is by Him, has given to him this wholeness before you all.
B044C003V017	44	3	17	And now, brothers, I know that you acted in ignorance, as your rulers did also.
B044C003V018	44	3	18	But those things which God announced beforehand by the mouth of all His prophets, that the Christ would suffer, He has thus fulfilled.
B044C003V019	44	3	19	Repent therefore and turn back, that your sins may be wiped away, in order that times of refreshing may come from the presence of the Lord,
B044C003V020	44	3	20	and that He may send He who had been ordained to be your Messiah, Jesus,
B044C003V021	44	3	21	whom[ ]heaven must receive until the times of restoration of all things, which God has spoken by the mouth of all His holy prophets since the world began.
B044C003V022	44	3	22	For Moses said to the fathers, 'The LORD our God will raise up for you a Prophet like me from your brothers. Him you shall hear in all things, whatever He says to you.
B044C003V023	44	3	23	'And it shall be that every person who does not hear that Prophet shall be utterly destroyed from among the people.'
B044C003V024	44	3	24	Yes, and all the prophets, from Samuel and his successors, as many as have spoken, have proclaimed these days.
B044C003V025	44	3	25	You are sons of the prophets, and of the covenant which God made with our fathers, saying to Abraham, 'And in your offspring all the families of the earth shall be blessed.'
B044C003V026	44	3	26	To you first, God, having raised up His Servant Jesus, sent Him to bless you, in turning away every one of you from your iniquities."
B044C004V001	44	4	1	Now while they were speaking to the people, the priests, the captain of the temple, and the Sadducees came upon them,
B044C004V002	44	4	2	being greatly disturbed because they were teaching the people and proclaiming in Jesus the resurrection of the dead.
B044C004V003	44	4	3	And they laid hands on them, and put them in custody until the next day, for it was already evening.
B044C004V004	44	4	4	However, many of those who heard the word believed; and the number of the men came to be about five thousand.
B044C004V005	44	4	5	Now it came to pass, on the next day, that their rulers, elders, and scribes were gathered together at Jerusalem,
B044C004V006	44	4	6	as well as Annas the high priest, Caiaphas, John, and Alexander, and as many as were of high priestly descent.
B044C004V007	44	4	7	And they brought them forward and began to inquire, "By what power or by what name have you done this?"
B044C004V008	44	4	8	Then Peter, having been filled with the Holy Spirit, said to them, "Rulers of the people and elders of Israel:
B044C004V009	44	4	9	If we today are being judged for a good work to a weak man, by what means he has been made well,
B044C004V010	44	4	10	let it be known to you all, and to all the people of Israel, that by the name of Jesus Christ the Nazarene, whom you crucified, whom God raised from the dead, by this[ name] this [man] stands here before you whole.
B044C004V011	44	4	11	This is the 'stone which was rejected by you, the builders, which became the chief cornerstone.'
B044C004V012	44	4	12	Nor is there salvation in no one else, for there is no other name under heaven which has been given among men by which we must be saved."
B044C004V013	44	4	13	Now when they observed the boldness of Peter and John, and understood that they were uneducated and untrained men, they marveled. And they recognized that they had been with Jesus.
B044C004V014	44	4	14	But because they saw standing with them the man who had been healed, they had nothing to say against [them].
B044C004V015	44	4	15	And they commanded them to go away outside the council, and began to confer among themselves,
B044C004V016	44	4	16	saying, "What shall we do to these men? For indeed, that a known sign has come to pass by them is evident to all those who are dwelling in Jerusalem, and we cannot deny it.
B044C004V017	44	4	17	But lest it be spread further among the people, let us threaten them with a threat, to speak no longer in this name."
B044C004V018	44	4	18	And summoning them, they commanded them not to speak at all nor to teach in the name of Jesus.
B044C004V019	44	4	19	But Peter and John answered them and said, "Whether it is right before God to hear you rather than God, you judge.
B044C004V020	44	4	20	For we can do none other but to speak the things which we saw and heard.
B044C004V021	44	4	21	So having threatened them further, they released them, finding no way of punishing them, on account of the people, because they all were glorifying God over that which had occurred.
B044C004V022	44	4	22	For the man was over forty, on whom had come about this sign of healing.
B044C004V023	44	4	23	And being released, they came to their own, and reported all that the chief priests and elders had said to them.
B044C004V024	44	4	24	So when they heard that, they raised their voice to God with one mind and said: "Lord, You are God, who made heaven and the earth and the sea, and all that is in them,
B044C004V025	44	4	25	who by the mouth of Your servant David have said: 'Why did the nations rage, and the people conspired vain things?
B044C004V026	44	4	26	The kings of the earth took their stand, and the rulers were assembled together against the LORD and against His Christ.'
B044C004V027	44	4	27	"For truly they were assembled against Your holy Servant Jesus, whom You anointed, both Herod and Pontius Pilate, with the Gentiles and the people of Israel,
B044C004V028	44	4	28	to do all that Your hand and Your counsel foreordained to come to pass.
B044C004V029	44	4	29	Now, Lord, look upon their threats, and grant to Your servants that with all boldness they may speak Your word,
B044C004V030	44	4	30	by extending Your hand to heal, and that signs and wonders may come about through the name of Your holy Servant Jesus."
B044C004V031	44	4	31	And when they had prayed, the place where they were gathered was shaken; and they were all filled with the Holy Spirit, and they spoke the word of God with boldness.
B044C004V032	44	4	32	Now the multitude of those who believed were of one heart and one soul; neither did anyone say that any of the things belonging to him was his own, but they had all things in common.
B044C004V033	44	4	33	And with great power the apostles were giving forth their witness of the resurrection of the Lord Jesus. And great grace was upon them all.
B044C004V034	44	4	34	Nor was there anyone needy among them; for all who were owners of lands or houses were selling them, and were bringing the proceeds of the things which had been sold,
B044C004V035	44	4	35	and were placing them beside the feet of the apostles; and they were distributing to each, to the degree that anyone had need.
B044C004V036	44	4	36	And Joses, who was also named Barnabas by the apostles (which is translated Son of Encouragement), a Levite, a Cyprian by nation,
