B044C014V005	44	14	5	And when an attempt was made by both the Gentiles and the[ ]Jews, together with their rulers, to mistreat and to stone them,
B044C014V006	44	14	6	they became aware of it and fled to the cities of Lycaonia, Lystra and Derbe, and to the surrounding region.
B044C014V007	44	14	7	And there, they were preaching the gospel.
B044C014V008	44	14	8	And a certain man in Lystra, powerless in his feet, was sitting, lame from his mother's womb, who had never walked.
B044C014V009	44	14	9	This [man] heard Paul speaking; who, gazing intently on him and seeing that he had faith to be healed,
B044C014V010	44	14	10	said with a loud voice, "Stand up straight on your feet!"And he was jumping and walking about.
B044C014V011	44	14	11	And the crowds, seeing what Paul did, raised their voice, saying in the Lycaonian language, "The gods have been made like men and have come down to us!"
B044C014V012	44	14	12	And Barnabas they called Zeus, and Paul, Hermes, since he was the leader in speaking.
B044C014V013	44	14	13	And the priest of Zeus, whose temple was before their city, bearing bulls and garlands to the gates, together with the crowds, was desiring to sacrifice [to them.]
B044C014V014	44	14	14	But when the apostles, Barnabas and Paul, heard this, they tore their clothes and rushed in to the crowd, crying out
B044C014V015	44	14	15	and saying, "Men! Why are you doing these things? We men are of the same nature as you, preaching the gospel to you, that you must turn from these useless things to the living God, who made the heaven, and the earth, and the sea, and all the things in them,
B044C014V016	44	14	16	who in the generations having gone by permitted all the Gentiles to walk in their ways.
B044C014V017	44	14	17	And yet He did not leave Himself without witness, in that He did good, giving to you rain from heaven and fruit bearing seasons, filling our hearts with food and gladness."
B044C014V018	44	14	18	And saying these things, they scarcely stopped the crowds from sacrificing to them.
B044C014V019	44	14	19	But there arrived from Antioch and Iconium [certain ]Jews, and having persuaded the crowds and having stoned Paul, they dragged [him] outside the city, thinking he was dead.
B044C014V020	44	14	20	But when the disciples encircled him, he stood and entered into the city. And the next day he went out together with Barnabas to Derbe.
B044C014V021	44	14	21	And having preached the gospel to that city and having made many disciples, they returned to Lystra, and Iconium, and Antioch,
B044C014V022	44	14	22	strengthening the souls of the disciples, urging [them] to continue in the faith, [saying, "]Through many tribulations we must enter into the kingdom of God."
B044C014V023	44	14	23	And having chosen elders for them in every church, [and ]having prayed with fasting, they commended them to the Lord in whom they had believed.
B044C014V024	44	14	24	And having crossed Pisidia, they came to Pamphylia.
B044C014V025	44	14	25	And having spoken the word in Perga, they went down to Attalia.
B044C014V026	44	14	26	From there they sailed to Antioch, from where they were commended to the grace of God for the work which they had completed.
B044C014V027	44	14	27	Now arriving and gathering the church together, they related all that God had done with them, and that He had opened the door of faith for the Gentiles.
B044C014V028	44	14	28	And they spent a long time there with the disciples.
B044C015V001	44	15	1	And certain men coming down from Judea were teaching the brothers, "If you are not circumcised in the custom of Moses, you cannot be saved."
B044C015V002	44	15	2	Therefore when there arose a serious dissension and debate with Paul and Barnabus, they determined that Paul and Barnabas and some others of them should go up to the apostles and elders in Jerusalem concerning this issue.
B044C015V003	44	15	3	Therefore, being sent forth by the church, they were passing through Phoenicia and Samaria, telling in detail [about] the conversion of the Gentiles; and they were causing great joy to all the brothers.
B044C015V004	44	15	4	And having come to Jerusalem, they were received by the church and the apostles and the elders; and they declared all that God had done with them.
B044C015V005	44	15	5	But some of those from the sect of the Pharisees rose up, saying, "It is necessary to circumcise them, and to command them to keep the law of Moses."
B044C015V006	44	15	6	And the apostles and elders gathered together to see about this matter.
B044C015V007	44	15	7	And after much dispute, Peter arose and said to them: "Men, brothers, you know that from early days God chose among us, that by my mouth the Gentiles should hear the word of the gospel and believe.
B044C015V008	44	15	8	And God, who knows the heart, bore witness to them by giving them the Holy Spirit, just as also [He did] to us,
B044C015V009	44	15	9	and made no distinction between us and them, purifying their hearts by faith.
B044C015V010	44	15	10	Now therefore, why do you test God by putting a yoke upon the neck of the disciples, which neither our fathers nor we were able to bear?
B044C015V011	44	15	11	But through the grace of the Lord Jesus, we believe that we will be saved in the same manner as they."
B044C015V012	44	15	12	Then all the multitude stopped speaking and listened to Barnabas and Paul telling as many signs and wonders as God had done among the Gentiles through them.
B044C015V013	44	15	13	Now after they had finished speaking, James answered, saying, "Men and brothers, listen to me:
B044C015V014	44	15	14	Simeon has declared how God first visited [them ]to take from the Gentiles a people for His name.
B044C015V015	44	15	15	And with this the words of the prophets agree, just as it is written:
B044C015V016	44	15	16	"After this I will return, and I will build again the tabernacle of David, which has fallen; and its ruins I will rebuild, and I will restore it,
B044C015V017	44	15	17	in order that the rest of men may seek out the LORD, and all the Gentiles who are called by My name, says the LORD who does all these things.'
B044C015V018	44	15	18	"Known from everlasting to God are all His works.
B044C015V019	44	15	19	Therefore I judge that we must not cause trouble for those who are turning to God from [among] the Gentiles;
B044C015V020	44	15	20	but that we write to them to abstain from things polluted by idols, and from sexual immorality, from things strangled, and [from] blood.
B044C015V021	44	15	21	"For Moses has had from ancient generations those who proclaim him in each city, being read in the synagogues from one Sabbath to another."
B044C015V022	44	15	22	Then it seemed best to the apostles and the elders, together with the whole church, to send men being chosen from them to Antioch, together with Paul and Barnabas, namely, Judas who was also named Barsabas, and Silas, leading men among the brothers.
B044C015V023	44	15	23	Writing by their hand these things: The apostles, the elders, and the brothers, to the brothers in Antioch, and Syria, and Cilicia who are of the Gentiles: Greetings.
B044C015V024	44	15	24	Inasmuch as we have heard that some went out from among us and troubled you with words, unsettling your souls, saying, 'that you must be circumcised and keep the law'-to whom we gave no [such] command-
B044C015V025	44	15	25	it seemed best to us, having come to be of the same mind, to send men being chosen to you, with our beloved Barnabas and Paul,
B044C015V026	44	15	26	men having given over their lives for the sake of the name of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B044C015V027	44	15	27	We have therefore sent Judas and Silas, who will also tell you the same things by word [of mouth].
B044C015V028	44	15	28	For it seemed best to the Holy Spirit, and to us, to put on you no greater burden except for these necessary things:
B044C015V029	44	15	29	that you abstain from meat offered to idols, and from blood, and from [anything] strangled, and from fornication; from which keeping yourselves back, you will do well. Farewell.
B044C015V030	44	15	30	Then having been dismissed, they came to Antioch; and having gathered the multitude together, they delivered the letter.
B044C015V031	44	15	31	And when they had read it, they rejoiced over its encouragement.
B044C015V032	44	15	32	Now Judas and Silas, themselves being prophets also, encouraged and strengthened the brothers with many words.
B044C015V033	44	15	33	And when time had passed, they were dismissed with peace from the brothers to the apostles.
B044C015V034	44	15	34	- - -
B044C015V035	44	15	35	But Paul and Barnabas spent time in Antioch, teaching and preaching the good news of the word of the Lord, with many others also.
B044C015V036	44	15	36	Then after some days Paul said to Barnabas, "Let us return now and visit our brothers in each city in which we proclaimed the word of the Lord, and see how they are doing."
B044C015V037	44	15	37	But Barnabas desired to take along with them John called Mark.
B044C015V038	44	15	38	But Paul considered it fitting not to take along with them the one who withdrew from them in Pamphylia, and who had not gone together with them to the work.
B044C015V039	44	15	39	Therefore a sharp disagreement arose so that they were separated from one another. And Barnabas, taking along Mark, sailed to Cyprus.
B044C015V040	44	15	40	But Paul, choosing Silas, departed, being given over to the grace of God by the brothers.
B044C015V041	44	15	41	And he passed through Syria and Cilicia, strengthening the churches.
B044C016V001	44	16	1	Now he arrived at Derbe and Lystra. And behold, a certain disciple was there named Timothy, the son of a certain Jewish woman who believed, but his father was Greek,
B044C016V002	44	16	2	who had a good testimony by the brothers in Lystra and Iconium.
B044C016V003	44	16	3	Paul wanted [Timothy] to accompany him, and taking him, he circumcised him because of the Jews who were in those places, for they all knew that his father was Greek.
B044C016V004	44	16	4	And as they were going through the cities, they were delivering to them the decrees to keep, which had been decided by the apostles and the elders at Jerusalem.
B044C016V005	44	16	5	Therefore the churches were strengthened in the faith, and were growing in number each day.
B044C016V006	44	16	6	Now when they had gone through Phrygia and the Galatian region, they were forbidden by the Holy Spirit from speaking the word in Asia,
B044C016V007	44	16	7	having come to Mysia they attempted to go to Bithynia, but the Spirit did not permit them.
B044C016V008	44	16	8	So they bypassed Mysia, and went down to Troas.
B044C016V009	44	16	9	And a vision appeared during the night to Paul. A certain man of Macedonia was standing, urging him, and saying, "Come across to Macedonia and help us."
B044C016V010	44	16	10	Now when he saw the vision, immediately we sought to go out to Macedonia, concluding that the Lord had called us to preach the gospel to them.
B044C016V011	44	16	11	Therefore, putting to sea from Troas, we ran a straight course to Samothrace, and the next day came to Neapolis,
B044C016V012	44	16	12	and from there to Philippi, which is chief of that part of Macedonia, a colony. And we were spending some days in that very city.
B044C016V013	44	16	13	And on the Sabbath day we went outside the city beside a river, where prayer was customarily made; and having sat down we spoke to the women who assembled together [there].
B044C016V014	44	16	14	And a certain woman named Lydia, a dealer of purple cloth of the city of Thyatira, who worshipped God, heard us, whose heart the Lord opened to give heed to the things spoken by Paul.
B044C016V015	44	16	15	And when she and her household were baptized, she urged us, saying, "If you have judged me to be faithful to the Lord, come to my house and stay."So she persuaded us.
B044C016V016	44	16	16	Now it came to pass, as we went to prayer, that a certain slave girl, having a spirit of Python, met us, who brought much profit to her masters by fortune telling.
B044C016V017	44	16	17	This girl, following after Paul and us, was crying out, saying, "These men are the servants of the Most High God, who proclaim to us the way of salvation."
B044C016V018	44	16	18	And this she did for many days. But Paul, being greatly annoyed and turning around, said to the spirit, "I command you in the name of Jesus Christ to come out of her."And he came out in that very hour.
B044C016V019	44	16	19	And when her masters saw that the hope of their profit was gone, they took Paul and Silas, and dragged [them] to the marketplace to the rulers.
B044C016V020	44	16	20	And bringing them to the magistrates they said, "These men, being Jews, are agitating our city;
B044C016V021	44	16	21	and they are proclaiming customs which are not lawful for us to receive or to do, since we are Romans."
B044C016V022	44	16	22	And the crowd rose up together against them; and the magistrates tore their clothes and ordered [men] to beat [them] with rods.
B044C016V023	44	16	23	And when they laid many strokes on them, they cast them into prison, commanding the prison keeper to keep them securely;
B044C016V024	44	16	24	who, having received such a command, cast them into the inner prison and fastened their feet in the stocks.
B044C016V025	44	16	25	Now about midnight Paul and Silas were praying and singing hymns to God, and the prisoners were listening to them.
B044C016V026	44	16	26	And suddenly there was a great earthquake, so that the foundations of the prison were shaken; and immediately all the doors were opened and all the bonds were loosed.
B044C016V027	44	16	27	And becoming awake, the prison keeper, seeing the doors of the prison open, drawing a sword, he was about to kill himself, supposing the prisoners to have escaped.
B044C016V028	44	16	28	But Paul called out with a loud voice, saying, "Do not harm yourself, for we are all here."
B044C016V029	44	16	29	And asking for a light he rushed in, and he came trembling, and fell before Paul and Silas,
B044C016V030	44	16	30	and he brought them forth outside and said, "Sirs, what must I do to be saved?"
B044C016V031	44	16	31	And they said, "Believe on the Lord Jesus Christ, and you shall be saved, you and your household."
B044C016V032	44	16	32	And they spoke the word of the Lord to him and to all those in his house.
B044C016V033	44	16	33	And taking them along in that same hour of the night and washed their wounds, and immediately he and all his family were baptized.
B044C016V034	44	16	34	And bringing them up into his house, he set a meal before them; and he rejoiced with his whole house, having believed in God.
B044C016V035	44	16	35	Now when it became day, the magistrates sent the officers, saying, "Release those men."
B044C016V036	44	16	36	And the prison keeper announced these words to Paul, saying, "The magistrates have sent so that you may be released. Now therefore depart, and go in peace."
B044C016V037	44	16	37	But Paul said to them, "They beat us publicly, although we were uncondemned Romans, and they cast [us] into prison, and now do they cast us out secretly? No indeed! Let them come themselves and lead us out."
B044C016V038	44	16	38	And the officers related to the magistrates these words, and they were afraid when they heard that they were Romans.
B044C016V039	44	16	39	And coming, they appealed to them, and bringing them out, they asked them to depart from the city.
B044C016V040	44	16	40	And coming out from the prison, they entered into [the house of] Lydia; and seeing the brothers, they encouraged them and departed.
B044C017V001	44	17	1	Now traveling through Amphipolis and Apollonia, they came to Thessalonica, where there was a synagogue of the Jews.
B044C017V002	44	17	2	And according to Paul's custom, he went in to them, and for three Sabbaths he reasoned with them from the Scriptures,
B044C017V003	44	17	3	interpreting and pointing out that it was necessary for the Christ to suffer, and to arise from the dead, and [saying ]that "This is the Christ, Jesus, whom I proclaim to you."
B044C017V004	44	17	4	And some of them were persuaded and were joined with Paul and Silas, both of the devout Greeks, a great multitude, and not a few of the chief women.
B044C017V005	44	17	5	And the Jews who did not believe [ ]took some wicked men from the marketplace, and forming a mob, [they ]threw the city into disorder, and came upon the house of Jason, and sought to bring them to the people.
B044C017V006	44	17	6	But when they did not find them, they dragged Jason and some brothers to the rulers of the city, crying out, "The men who have upset the whole world, these have come here, too;
B044C017V007	44	17	7	whom Jason has received; and these all practice contrary to the decrees of Caesar, saying there is another king-Jesus."
B044C017V008	44	17	8	And they troubled the crowd and the rulers of the city when they heard these things.
B044C017V009	44	17	9	And having taken the security bond from Jason and the rest, they released them.
B044C017V010	44	17	10	Then the brothers immediately sent Paul and Silas away during the night to Berea. When they arrived, they went into the synagogue of the Jews.
B044C017V011	44	17	11	And these were more noble-minded than[ ]those in Thessalonica, who received the word with all readiness, each day examining the Scriptures [to see ]whether these things might be so.
B044C017V012	44	17	12	Therefore many of them believed, and not a few of the prominent Greek women and men.
B044C017V013	44	17	13	But when the Jews from Thessalonica learned that the word of God was proclaimed by Paul in Berea, they came there also, agitating the crowds.
B044C017V014	44	17	14	Then immediately the brothers sent Paul away, to go toward the sea; but both Silas and Timothy remained there.
B044C017V015	44	17	15	And those conducting Paul brought him to Athens; and receiving a command for Silas and Timothy, that as quickly as possible they should come to him, they departed.
B044C017V016	44	17	16	And in Athens, while Paul waited for them, his spirit was provoked within him when he saw that the city was full of idols.
B044C017V017	44	17	17	Therefore he reasoned in the synagogue with the Jews and with the [Gentile] worshippers, and in the marketplace daily with those coming by.
B044C017V018	44	17	18	And also some of the Epicurean and of the Stoic philosophers were conversing with him. And some were saying, "What does this seed-picker wish to say?"But others [said], "He seems to be a proclaimer of foreign deities,"because he was preaching the good news of Jesus and the resurrection.
B044C017V019	44	17	19	And taking hold of him, they brought [him] to the Areopagus, saying, "Are we able to know what this new doctrine is you speak about?
B044C017V020	44	17	20	For you are bringing some strange things to our ears. Therefore we desire to know what these things might mean."
B044C017V021	44	17	21	Now all the Athenians and the strangers staying there as visitors spent their time in nothing other than to say or to hear some new thing.
B044C017V022	44	17	22	Then Paul stood in the midst of the Areopagus and said, "Men, Athenians, according to all things I perceive you as [being ]very religious;
B044C017V023	44	17	23	for as I passed by and considered the objects of your worship, I found also an altar on which it had been inscribed: TO THE UNKNOWN GOD. Therefore, [Him] whom being ignorant of you worship, this [One] I announce to you:
B044C017V024	44	17	24	The God who made the world and all the things in it, Him being Lord of heaven and earth, does not dwell in temples made by human hands,
B044C017V025	44	17	25	nor by the hands of men is He served, as though He needed anything, for He gives to all life, and breath, with respect to all things.
B044C017V026	44	17	26	And He made from one blood every nation of men to dwell upon all the face of the earth, and He ordained their preappointed times and the boundaries of their dwellings,
B044C017V027	44	17	27	[in order for them ]to seek the Lord, if perhaps indeed they might grope for Him and find [Him], and yet being indeed not far from each one of us;
B044C017V028	44	17	28	for in Him we live and move and have our being, as also some of your own poets have said, 'For we are also His offspring.'
B044C017V029	44	17	29	"Therefore, being the offspring of God, we ought not to suppose that the Godhead is like gold or silver or stone, something shaped by art and the imagination of man.
B044C017V030	44	17	30	So then these times of ignorance God overlooked, but now He commands all men everywhere to repent,
B044C017V031	44	17	31	because He has appointed a day in which He is going to judge the world in righteousness by [the] Man whom He has appointed, having given proof to all, by raising Him from the dead."
B044C017V032	44	17	32	But when they heard of the resurrection of the dead, some were scoffing, but others said, "We will hear you again concerning this."
B044C017V033	44	17	33	And thus Paul went forth from their midst.
B044C017V034	44	17	34	However, some men were joined to him and believed, among whom were also Dionysius the Areopagite, a woman named Damaris, and others with them.
B044C018V001	44	18	1	Now after these things, having departed from Athens, Paul came to Corinth.
B044C018V002	44	18	2	And he found a certain Jew named Aquila, a native of Pontus, having recently come from Italy with Priscilla his wife (because Claudius had ordered all the Jews to depart from Rome); he came to them,
B044C018V003	44	18	3	and because he was of the same trade, he remained with them and worked, for they were tentmakers by trade.
B044C018V004	44	18	4	And he reasoned in the synagogue every Sabbath, and persuaded both Jews and Greeks.
B044C018V005	44	18	5	Now when both Silas and Timothy came down from Macedonia, Paul was compelled by the Spirit, solemnly bearing witness to the Jews that Jesus is the Christ.
B044C018V006	44	18	6	But because they were opposing and blaspheming, he shook off his clothes and said to them, "Your blood [be] on your [own ]heads; I am clean. From now on I will go to the Gentiles."
B044C018V007	44	18	7	And having gone over from there, he went into the house of a certain [man] named Justus, who worshipped God, whose house was next door to the synagogue.
B044C018V008	44	18	8	And Crispus, the ruler of the synagogue, believed in the Lord, together with all his household. And many of the Corinthians, hearing, were believing and were being baptized.
B044C018V009	44	18	9	Now the Lord spoke to Paul by a vision in the night, [saying], "Do not fear, but speak, and do not keep silent;
B044C018V010	44	18	10	for I am with you, and no one will attack you to harm you; for I have many people in this city."
B044C018V011	44	18	11	And he settled [there] a year and six months, teaching the word of God among them.
B044C018V012	44	18	12	Now while Gallio was proconsul of Achaia, the Jews with one purpose rose up against Paul and brought him before the judgment seat,
B044C018V013	44	18	13	saying, "This [man] persuades men to worship God contrary to the law."
B044C018V014	44	18	14	And when Paul was about to open his mouth, Gallio said to the Jews, "If then it was some misdeed or wicked crime, O Jews, according to reason I would bear with you.
B044C018V015	44	18	15	But if it is a question about a word and names and your own law, see [to it] yourselves; for I do not wish to be a judge of these things."
B044C018V016	44	18	16	And he drove them away from the judgment seat.
B044C018V017	44	18	17	Then all the Greeks, taking hold of Sosthenes the ruler of the synagogue, were beating him before the judgment seat. And none of these things was a concern to Gallio.
B044C018V018	44	18	18	Now Paul still remained there a good while, then bid farewell to the brothers, and sailed away for Syria, and Priscilla and Aquila were with him. He had his hair cut off in Cenchrea, for he had taken a vow.
B044C018V019	44	18	19	And he arrived in Ephesus, and he left those [two] there; but he, having entered into the synagogue, reasoned with the Jews.
B044C018V020	44	18	20	And when they asked him to remain with them for a longer time, he did not consent,
B044C018V021	44	18	21	but bid farewell to them saying, "I must by all means keep this coming feast which is in Jerusalem; but I will return again to you, God willing."And he put out to sea from Ephesus.
B044C018V022	44	18	22	And having gone down to Caesarea, and having gone up and greeted the church, he went down to Antioch.
B044C018V023	44	18	23	After having spent some time there, he went out, going through in order the Galatian region and the Phrygian [region], strengthening all the disciples.
B044C018V024	44	18	24	Now a certain Jew named Apollos, a native of Alexandria, an eloquent man and mighty in the Scriptures, had arrived in Ephesus.
B044C018V025	44	18	25	This man had been instructed in the way of the Lord; and being fervent in spirit, he spoke and taught accurately the things about the Lord, although he knew only the baptism of John.
B044C018V026	44	18	26	And he began to speak boldly in the synagogue. And when Aquila and Priscilla heard him, they took him aside and explained to him the way of God more accurately.
B044C018V027	44	18	27	And when he desired to go across to Achaia, having urged him on, the brothers wrote to the disciples [there] to receive him; and when he arrived, he assisted greatly with those who had believed through grace;
B044C018V028	44	18	28	for he was powerfully refuting the Jews publicly, demonstrating by the Scriptures [that] Jesus was the Messiah.
B044C019V001	44	19	1	And it came about, while Apollos was in Corinth, that Paul, having gone through the interior regions, came to Ephesus. And finding some disciples
B044C019V002	44	19	2	[he] said to them, "Did you receive the Holy Spirit, having believed?"So they said to him, "We have not even heard whether there is a Holy Spirit."
B044C019V003	44	19	3	And he said to them, "Into what then were you baptized?"So they said, "Into John's baptism."
B044C019V004	44	19	4	But Paul said, "John indeed baptized with a baptism of repentance, saying to the people that they should believe in the One coming after him, that is, in Christ Jesus."
B044C019V005	44	19	5	And when they heard [this], they were baptized in the name of the Lord Jesus.
B044C019V006	44	19	6	And when Paul laid his hands on them, the Holy Spirit came upon them, and they spoke in tongues and prophesied.
B044C019V007	44	19	7	Now all the men were about twelve.
B044C019V008	44	19	8	And he entered into the synagogue and spoke boldly for three months, debating and persuading the things concerning the kingdom of God.
B044C019V009	44	19	9	But when some became hardened and disbelieving, speaking evil against the Way before the multitude, he withdrew from them and separated the disciples, each day debating in the school of a certain Tyrannus.
B044C019V010	44	19	10	Now this took place for two years, so that all who were dwelling in Asia heard the word of the Lord Jesus, both Jews and Greeks.
B044C019V011	44	19	11	And God was doing extraordinary miracles by the hands of Paul,
B044C019V012	44	19	12	so that even handkerchiefs or aprons from his skin were brought to those who were sick, and the diseases departed from them, and the evil spirits went out from them.
B044C019V013	44	19	13	Then some of the wandering Jews, exorcists, attempted to name the name of the Lord Jesus over those having the evil spirits, saying, "We adjure you by Jesus whom Paul preaches."
B044C019V014	44	19	14	Now there were seven sons of Sceva, a Jewish high priest, doing this.
B044C019V015	44	19	15	But the evil spirit answered and said, "Jesus I know, and Paul I recognize; but who are you?"
B044C019V016	44	19	16	Then the man in whom was the evil spirit leaped upon them, and having subdued them, prevailed against them, so that they ran out of the house naked and wounded.
B044C019V017	44	19	17	Now this became known to all both Jews and Greeks who were dwelling in Ephesus; and fear fell upon them all, and they were praising the name of the Lord Jesus.
B044C019V018	44	19	18	And many of those who had believed were coming, confessing and disclosing their deeds.
B044C019V019	44	19	19	And many of those who were practicing magic brought together their books and burned them up before everyone. And they counted up the prices of them, and [found it to be] fifty thousand [pieces] of silver.
B044C019V020	44	19	20	Thus the word of the Lord was growing powerfully and prevailed.
B044C019V021	44	19	21	When these things were fulfilled, Paul resolved in his spirit, having gone through Macedonia and Achaia, to go to Jerusalem, saying, "After I have been there, I must also see Rome."
B044C019V022	44	19	22	And having sent to Macedonia two of those who were ministering to him, Timothy and Erastus, he himself stayed on for a time in Asia.
B044C019V023	44	19	23	Now there arose during that time a serious disturbance concerning the Way.
B044C019V024	44	19	24	For a certain man named Demetrius, a silversmith, who made silver shrines of Artemis, providing no little trade [for] the craftsmen,
B044C019V025	44	19	25	whom he gathered, with the workers of similar occupation, and said: "Men, you know out of this trade is our prosperity.
B044C019V026	44	19	26	And you observe and hear that not only at Ephesus, but almost in all of Asia, this Paul has persuaded and turned away a great multitude, saying that they are not gods which are made by human hands.
B044C019V027	44	19	27	And not only is this business of ours in danger to come into disrepute, but also the temple of the great goddess Artemis may be despised and also her magnificence, about to be destroyed, she whom all Asia and the world worship."
B044C019V028	44	19	28	And hearing [this], and becoming full of anger, they were crying out saying, "Great is Artemis of the Ephesians!"
B044C019V029	44	19	29	And the whole city was filled with confusion, and they rushed with one purpose into the theater, having seized Gaius and Aristarchus, Macedonians, traveling companions of Paul.
B044C019V030	44	19	30	Now when Paul wished to enter in among the crowd, the disciples would not permit him.
B044C019V031	44	19	31	And also some of the officials of Asia, being friends with him, sent word to him and urged him not to present himself in the theater.
B044C019V032	44	19	32	Then others were calling out something different, for the assembly was confused, and the majority did not know for what reason they had come together.
B044C019V033	44	19	33	And from the crowd they brought forward Alexander, the Jews putting him forward. And Alexander motioned with his hand, and desired to make a defense to the people.
B044C019V034	44	19	34	But recognizing he was a Jew, there arose one voice from [them ]all, calling out for two hours, "Great is Artemis of the Ephesians!"
B044C019V035	44	19	35	And having quieted the crowd, the city clerk said: "Men of Ephesus, for what man is there who does not know that the city of the Ephesians is the temple keeper of the great goddess Artemis, and of the [image ]fallen from heaven?
B044C019V036	44	19	36	Therefore, since these things are undeniable, it is necessary for you to be quieted and to do nothing rash.
B044C019V037	44	19	37	For you brought these men, neither temple thieves nor blasphemers of your goddess.
B044C019V038	44	19	38	Therefore, if Demetrius and his fellow craftsmen have a word against anyone, the courts are in session, and there are proconsuls. Let them bring charges against one another.
B044C019V039	44	19	39	But if you are wanting to know anything about other [matters], it shall be determined by the lawful assembly.
B044C019V040	44	19	40	For we also are in danger of being accused of insurrection concerning today, there being no cause for which we will be able to give, [as ]an explanation for this commotion.
B044C019V041	44	19	41	And having said these things, he dismissed the assembly.
B044C020V001	44	20	1	Now after the disturbance had ceased, Paul, summoning the disciples and greeting them, went away to go to Macedonia.
B044C020V002	44	20	2	And going through those parts, and encouraging them with many words, he came to Greece
B044C020V003	44	20	3	and spent three months [there]. And as a plot by the Jews developed against him, as he was to put to sea for Syria, a decision came about to return through Macedonia.
B044C020V004	44	20	4	And Sopater, a Berean, was accompanying him to Asia-also Aristarchus of the Thessalonians, and Secundus, and Gaius of Derbe, and Timothy, and Tychicus and Trophimus, [the] Asians.
B044C020V005	44	20	5	These [men], having gone ahead, were waiting for us in Troas.
B044C020V006	44	20	6	And we sailed away after the Days of Unleavened Bread, from Philippi, and we came to them in Troas within five days, where we spent seven days.
B044C020V007	44	20	7	Now on the first [day] of the week, the disciples being assembled to break bread, Paul was discussing with them, being about to leave on the next day, and extended his message until midnight.
B044C020V008	44	20	8	And there were a considerable number of lamps in the upper room where we were assembled.
B044C020V009	44	20	9	And a certain young man named Eutychus sat in the window, being overwhelmed by a deep sleep. While Paul was speaking for a while longer, having been overwhelmed by sleep, he fell down from the third story and was taken up dead.
B044C020V010	44	20	10	But Paul, going down, fell upon him, and embracing him said, "Do not be troubled, for his life is in him."
B044C020V011	44	20	11	And going up and breaking bread and eating, and talking for a considerable time, until daybreak, thus he departed.
B044C020V012	44	20	12	And they brought the boy living, and they were encouraged greatly.
B044C020V013	44	20	13	Now we, having gone ahead on the ship, put to sea for Assos, from there intending to take Paul on board; for thus it had been arranged, since he intended to go on foot.
B044C020V014	44	20	14	And when he met us at Assos, having taken him aboard, we came to Mitylene.
B044C020V015	44	20	15	And having sailing away from there, on the next day we arrived opposite Chios. The following day we approached to Samos and remained in Trogyllium. The following day we came to Miletus.
B044C020V016	44	20	16	For Paul had decided to sail past Ephesus, in order that it might not happen to him to spend time in Asia; for he was hurrying, if it was possible for him to be in Jerusalem [on] the Day of Pentecost.
B044C020V017	44	20	17	Now from Miletus, having sent to Ephesus, he summoned the elders of the church.
B044C020V018	44	20	18	And when they were present with him, he said to them: "You know from the first day which I arrived in Asia, how I was with you the whole time,
B044C020V019	44	20	19	serving the Lord with all humility, and many tears and trials which happened to me by the plots of the Jews;
B044C020V020	44	20	20	how I kept back nothing that was profitable, but declared it to you, teaching you publicly and from house to house,
B044C020V021	44	20	21	solemnly bearing witness to both Jews and to Greeks, the repentance toward God and faith toward our Lord Jesus.
B044C020V022	44	20	22	And now behold, I, having been bound in the spirit, am going to Jerusalem, not knowing the things that will happen to me there,
B044C020V023	44	20	23	except that the Holy Spirit in every city is solemnly bearing witness, saying that bonds and tribulations are waiting for me.
B044C020V024	44	20	24	But I count myself as nothing; nor do I regard my life as valuable to myself, so that I may complete my course with joy, and the ministry which I received from the Lord Jesus, to bear solemn testimony to the gospel of the grace of God.
B044C020V025	44	20	25	And now behold, now I know that you all, among whom I have passed through preaching the kingdom of God, will no longer see my face.
B044C020V026	44	20	26	Therefore I testify to you this very day, that I am innocent of all blood.
B044C020V027	44	20	27	For I did not draw back from declaring to you the whole counsel of God.
B044C020V028	44	20	28	Therefore take heed to yourselves and to all the flock, in which the Holy Spirit placed you [as ]overseers, to shepherd the church of the Lord, and of God, which He purchased with His own blood.
B044C020V029	44	20	29	For I know this, that savage wolves will come in after my departure, not sparing the flock.
B044C020V030	44	20	30	Also from among you yourselves will arise men speaking things having been distorted, [in order] to draw away the disciples after them.
B044C020V031	44	20	31	Therefore be alert, remembering that for three years, night and day I did not cease, with tears, exhorting each one.
B044C020V032	44	20	32	So for the present, I entrust you, brothers, to God and to the word of His grace, which is able to build you up and give you an inheritance among all those who have been sanctified.
B044C020V033	44	20	33	I have desired the silver or gold or clothes of no one.
B044C020V034	44	20	34	You yourselves know that these hands rendered service to my needs, and those who were with me.
B044C020V035	44	20	35	By all things I have shown you, that thus laboring it is necessary to help [those] being weak, and to remember the words of the Lord Jesus, that He said, 'It is more blessed to give than to receive.' "
B044C020V036	44	20	36	And having said these things, he knelt down, together with them all, and prayed.
B044C020V037	44	20	37	And there was considerable weeping by all, and falling on Paul's neck, they kissed him,
B044C020V038	44	20	38	feeling pain most of all for the words which he said, that they were about to see his face no more. And they accompanied him to the ship.
B044C021V001	44	21	1	Now when it came to pass that we had put to sea, having withdrawn from them, running a straight course we came to Cos, and on the next [day] to Rhodes, and from there to Patara.
B044C021V002	44	21	2	And having found a ship crossing over to Phoenicia, we boarded it and put to sea.
B044C021V003	44	21	3	When we had sighted Cyprus, and had left it behind [on the ]left, we sailed to Syria, and put in to harbor in Tyre, for the ship was unloading its cargo.
B044C021V004	44	21	4	And having discovered disciples, we stayed there seven days. They said to Paul through the Spirit not to go up to Jerusalem.
B044C021V005	44	21	5	But when it came about that we had completed the days [there], having gone out we departed, all [of them] accompanying us, together with [their ]wives and children, until [we were] outside the city. And having bowed [our] knees on the shore, we prayed.
B044C021V006	44	21	6	And having greeted one another, we went up into the ship, and they returned to their own [homes].
B044C021V007	44	21	7	And completing our voyage from Tyre, we arrived in Ptolemais, and having greeted the brothers, we stayed one day with them.
B044C021V008	44	21	8	On the next day those accompanying Paul went forth and came to Caesarea, and entering into the house of Philip the evangelist, who was one of the seven, we stayed with him.
B044C021V009	44	21	9	Now this man had four virgin daughters who prophesied.
B044C021V010	44	21	10	And while we remained there several days, a certain prophet from Judea named Agabus came down.
B044C021V011	44	21	11	And coming to us and taking Paul's belt, and binding his feet and hands, he said, "Thus says the Holy Spirit, ' The man whose belt this is, the Jews will bind in this way in Jerusalem, and they will deliver [him] into the hands of the Gentiles.' "
B044C021V012	44	21	12	Now when we heard these things, both we and the local residents urged him not to go up to Jerusalem.
B044C021V013	44	21	13	Then Paul answered, "Why are you weeping and breaking my heart? For I am ready not only to be bound, but also to die at Jerusalem, for the name of the Lord Jesus."
B044C021V014	44	21	14	And when he remained unpersuaded, we were silent and said, "Let the will of the Lord be done."
B044C021V015	44	21	15	Now after those days, having prepared, we went up to Jerusalem.
B044C021V016	44	21	16	Also some of the disciples from Caesarea went with us and brought with them a certain Cypriot named Mnason, a long-standing disciple, with whom we would stay as a guest.
B044C021V017	44	21	17	And when we arrived in Jerusalem, the brothers gladly received us.
B044C021V018	44	21	18	On the next day Paul was going in with us to James, and all the elders were present.
B044C021V019	44	21	19	And having greeted them, he reported one by one those[ ]things which God had done among the Gentiles through his ministry.
B044C021V020	44	21	20	And hearing this, they were glorifying the Lord, saying to him, "You see, brother, how many thousands of Jews there are who have believed, and they are all zealous for the law;
B044C021V021	44	21	21	and they have been informed about you, that you are teaching defection from Moses, to all the Jews who are among the Gentiles, saying for them not to circumcise their children nor to walk in our customs.
B044C021V022	44	21	22	What then? It is necessary for an assembly to come together; for they will hear that you have come.
B044C021V023	44	21	23	Therefore do this, which we say to you: There[ ]are four men with us who have taken a vow upon themselves.
B044C021V024	44	21	24	Take them and purify yourself with them, and pay for them that they may have their head shaved, and that all may know that those things of which they have been informed about you are nothing, but [that] you are agreeing with and keeping the law yourself.
B044C021V025	44	21	25	But as for the Gentile believers, we wrote, having judged that they should keep no such thing, except that they should keep themselves from things offered to idols, from blood, and [from anything] strangled, and from fornication."
B044C021V026	44	21	26	Then Paul, having taken the men, on the next day having been purified with them, entered into the temple, [thus] giving notice to the completion of the days of the purification, until [the time] when the offering was offered in behalf of each one of them.
B044C021V027	44	21	27	Now when the seven days were about to be completed, the Jews from Asia, seeing him in the temple, were stirring up all the crowd and put their hands on him,
B044C021V028	44	21	28	crying out, "Men of Israel, help us! This is the man who is teaching all [people] everywhere against the people and the Law and this place; and furthermore he has brought Greeks into the temple and has defiled this holy place."
B044C021V029	44	21	29	For they had seen Trophimus the Ephesian in the city with him, whom they supposed that Paul had brought into the temple.
B044C021V030	44	21	30	And all the city was aroused; and there was a mob forming among the people, and taking hold of Paul they were dragging him outside the temple; and immediately the doors were shut.
B044C021V031	44	21	31	And seeking to kill him, a report went up to the commander of the garrison that all Jerusalem had been stirred up,
B044C021V032	44	21	32	who immediately having taken along soldiers and centurions, ran down among them. And when they saw the commander and the soldiers, they stopped beating Paul.
B044C021V033	44	21	33	And the commander, approaching, took hold of him, and ordered him to be bound with two chains; and he was inquiring who he might be and what he had done.
B044C021V034	44	21	34	But others among the crowd were crying out one thing and some another; and because he was unable to ascertain the truth because of the noise, he commanded him to be brought into the barracks.
B044C021V035	44	21	35	But when he arrived at the stairs, he had to be carried by the soldiers because of the violence of the crowd.
B044C021V036	44	21	36	For the multitude of the people was following, calling out, "take him away!"
B044C021V037	44	21	37	Then as Paul was about to be led into the barracks, he said to the commander, "Is it permitted from me to speak to you?"And he said, "Do you know Greek?
B044C021V038	44	21	38	Are you not then the Egyptian who rose up before these days, and led forth the four thousand men of the assassins into the wilderness?"
B044C021V039	44	21	39	But Paul said, "I am a Jew from Tarsus of Cilicia, a citizen of no obscure city; and I request of you, permit me to speak to the people."
B044C021V040	44	21	40	And permitting him, Paul stood on the stairs and motioned with his hand to the people. And when there was a great silence, he addressed them in the Hebrew language, saying,
B044C022V001	44	22	1	"Men, brothers and fathers, hear my defense to you now."
B044C022V002	44	22	2	And hearing that he was addressing them in the Hebrew language, they granted [him ]more silence. And he said:
B044C022V003	44	22	3	"I am indeed a Jew, having been born in Tarsus of Cilicia, but having been brought up in this city at the feet of Gamaliel, having been educated according to the exactness of the law of our forefathers, being zealous for God just as you all are today.
B044C022V004	44	22	4	I, who persecuted this Way to death, binding and handing over to prisons both men and women,
B044C022V005	44	22	5	as also the high priest testifies of me, along with the council of the elders, from whom I also received letters to the brothers, and went to Damascus in order to bring those who were there, having been bound, to Jerusalem, that they might be punished.
B044C022V006	44	22	6	Now it happened, as I was going and approaching Damascus, about midday, suddenly from heaven a great light shone about me.
B044C022V007	44	22	7	And I fell to the ground and heard a voice saying to me, 'Saul, Saul, why are you persecuting Me?'
B044C022V008	44	22	8	"So I answered, 'Who are You, Lord?' And He said to me, 'I am Jesus the Nazarene, whom you are persecuting.'
B044C022V009	44	22	9	"And those who were with me observed the light and became terrified, but they did not hear the voice of the [One] speaking to me.
B044C022V010	44	22	10	So I said, 'What shall I do, Lord?' And the Lord said to me, 'Arise and go into Damascus, and it will be told to you about all the[ ]things which it has been appointed for you to do.'
B044C022V011	44	22	11	"And since I could not see because of the brightness of that light, being led by the hand by those who were with me, I came into Damascus.
B044C022V012	44	22	12	And Ananias, a certain devout man according to the law, being testified of by all the Jews dwelling in Damascus,
B044C022V013	44	22	13	came to me and he stood and said to me, 'Brother Saul, see again.' And I, in that very hour, looked up at him.
B044C022V014	44	22	14	And he said, 'The God of our fathers has chosen you to know His will, and to see the Righteous One, and hear the voice from His mouth.
B044C022V015	44	22	15	For you shall be a witness for Him to all men of what you have seen and heard.
B044C022V016	44	22	16	And now, what are you going to do? Arise and be baptized, and wash away your sins, calling on the name of the Lord.'
B044C022V017	44	22	17	"And it happened to me, having returned to Jerusalem and praying in the temple, that I came to be in a trance,
B044C022V018	44	22	18	and saw Him saying to me, 'Hurry and go out quickly from Jerusalem, for they will not receive your witness about Me.'
B044C022V019	44	22	19	"And I said, 'Lord, they know that in every synagogue I was imprisoning and beating those believing on You.
B044C022V020	44	22	20	And when the blood of Your witness Stephen was shed, I myself was standing by consenting to his murder, and guarding the clothes of those murdering him.'
B044C022V021	44	22	21	"Then He said to me, 'Go, for I will send you far away to the Gentiles.' "
B044C022V022	44	22	22	Now they were listening to him until this statement, and they lifted their voice saying, "Take away such a [man] from the earth, for it is not fitting [for] him to live!"
B044C022V023	44	22	23	And as they were crying out and throwing off their clothes, and throwing dust in the air,
B044C022V024	44	22	24	the commander ordered him to be brought into the barracks, and said for him that he should be given a hearing with scourging, so that he might learn why they were crying thus against him.
B044C022V025	44	22	25	But as they were stretching him out with the thongs, Paul said to the centurion standing there, "Is it lawful for you to scourge a man who is a Roman, and uncondemned?"
