B045C015V019	45	15	19	in mighty signs and wonders, by the power of the Spirit of God, so that from Jerusalem and as far as Illyricum I have fully preached the gospel of Christ.
B045C015V020	45	15	20	And so eagerly striving to evangelize not where Christ was named, lest I should build upon the foundation of another,
B045C015V021	45	15	21	but as it is written: "To whom He was not announced, they shall see; and those who have not heard shall understand."
B045C015V022	45	15	22	For this reason I also have been hindered many times from coming to you.
B045C015V023	45	15	23	But now no longer having a place in these regions, and having a longing to come to you for many years,
B045C015V024	45	15	24	whenever I travel to Spain, I shall come to you. For I hope [while] traveling through to see you, and to be sent forward there by you, if I may be filled in part [from] you first.
B045C015V025	45	15	25	But now I am traveling to Jerusalem ministering to the saints.
B045C015V026	45	15	26	For Macedonia and Achaia thought it good to make some contribution for the poor among the saints in Jerusalem.
B045C015V027	45	15	27	For they thought it good, and they are their debtors. For if the Gentiles shared in spiritual things, they are obligated also to minister to them in material things.
B045C015V028	45	15	28	Therefore, having finished and having sealed to them this fruit, I shall go by way of you to Spain.
B045C015V029	45	15	29	But I know that coming to you, I shall come in the fullness of the blessing of the gospel of Christ.
B045C015V030	45	15	30	Now I beg you, brothers, through the Lord Jesus Christ, and through the love of the Spirit, to strive together with me in prayers to God on my behalf,
B045C015V031	45	15	31	that I may be delivered from those in Judea who do not believe, and that my service for Jerusalem may be acceptable to the saints,
B045C015V032	45	15	32	so that in joy I may come to you through the will of God, and may be refreshed together with you.
B045C015V033	45	15	33	Now the God of peace be with you all. Amen.
B045C016V001	45	16	1	I commend to you Phoebe our sister, who is a servant of the church in Cenchrea,
B045C016V002	45	16	2	so that you may receive her in the Lord in a manner worthy of the saints, and you may stand by her in whatever thing she may need from you; for indeed she has proved to be a helper of many and of myself also.
B045C016V003	45	16	3	Greet Prisca and Aquila, my fellow workers in Christ Jesus,
B045C016V004	45	16	4	who risked their own necks for my life, to whom not only I give thanks, but also all the churches of the Gentiles.
B045C016V005	45	16	5	And greet the church that is in their house. Greet my beloved Epaenetus, who is the firstfruits of Achaia to Christ.
B045C016V006	45	16	6	Greet Mary, who labored much for us.
B045C016V007	45	16	7	Greet Andronicus and Junia, my relatives and my fellow captives, who are notable among the apostles, who also were in Christ before me.
B045C016V008	45	16	8	Greet Amplias, my beloved in the Lord.
B045C016V009	45	16	9	Greet Urbanus, our fellow worker in Christ, and Stachys, my beloved.
B045C016V010	45	16	10	Greet Apelles, approved in Christ. Greet those from the [household] of Aristobulus.
B045C016V011	45	16	11	Greet Herodion, my relative. Greet those from the [household] of Narcissus who are in the Lord.
B045C016V012	45	16	12	Greet Tryphena and Tryphosa, who have labored in the Lord. Greet the beloved Persis, who labored much in the Lord.
B045C016V013	45	16	13	Greet Rufus, chosen in the Lord, and his mother and mine.
B045C016V014	45	16	14	Greet Asyncritus, Phlegon, Hermas, Patrobas, Hermes, and the brothers who are with them.
B045C016V015	45	16	15	Greet Philologus and Julia, Nereus and his sister, and Olympas, and all the saints who are with them.
B045C016V016	45	16	16	Greet one another with a holy kiss. The churches of Christ greet you.
B045C016V017	45	16	17	Now I urge you, brothers, to look out for those who cause divisions and offenses, contrary to the doctrine which you learned, and turn away from them.
B045C016V018	45	16	18	For such [people] do not serve our Lord Jesus Christ, but their own belly, and through smooth speech and flattering, they deceive the hearts of the innocent.
B045C016V019	45	16	19	For your obedience has become known to all. Therefore I rejoice on your behalf; but I want you to be wise in what is good, and innocent to what is evil.
B045C016V020	45	16	20	And the God of peace will crush Satan under your feet shortly. The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you.
B045C016V021	45	16	21	Timothy, my fellow worker, and Lucius, Jason, and Sosipater, my relatives, greet you.
B045C016V022	45	16	22	I, Tertius, the [one] writing this epistle, greet you in the Lord.
B045C016V023	45	16	23	Gaius, my host and the host of the whole church, greets you. Erastus, the treasurer of the city, greets you, and Quartus, the brother.
B045C016V024	45	16	24	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you all. Amen.
B045C016V025	45	16	25	(15:24) Now to Him who is able to establish you according to my gospel and the proclamation of Jesus Christ, according to [the] revelation of [the ]mystery kept secret since the world began,
B045C016V026	45	16	26	(15:25) but now made manifest, and by the prophetic Scriptures made known to all nations, according to the commandment of the eternal God, for obedience to the faith-
B045C016V027	45	16	27	(15:26) To the only wise God, through Jesus Christ, to whom be the glory forever! Amen
B046C001V001	46	1	1	Paul, called [to be] an apostle of Jesus Christ through the will of God, and Sosthenes our brother,
B046C001V002	46	1	2	to the church of God which is at Corinth, to those who have been sanctified in Christ Jesus, called [to be] saints, with all those who in every place are calling on the name of Jesus Christ our Lord, both theirs and ours:
B046C001V003	46	1	3	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B046C001V004	46	1	4	I thank my God always on your behalf for the grace of God which was given to you in Christ Jesus,
B046C001V005	46	1	5	that in everything you were enriched by Him in all speech and all knowledge,
B046C001V006	46	1	6	just as the testimony of Christ was confirmed in you,
B046C001V007	46	1	7	so that you are not lacking in any gift, eagerly awaiting the revelation of our Lord Jesus Christ,
B046C001V008	46	1	8	who will also confirm you until the end, [that you may be] unimpeachable in the day of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B046C001V009	46	1	9	God is faithful, by whom you were called into the fellowship of His Son, Jesus Christ our Lord.
B046C001V010	46	1	10	Now I beseech you, brothers, by the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, that you all speak the same thing, and that there be no divisions among you, but you be made complete in the same mind and in the same opinion.
B046C001V011	46	1	11	For it has been reported to me concerning you, my brothers, by those of Chloe's household, that there is quarreling among you.
B046C001V012	46	1	12	Now I say this, that each of you says, "I am of Paul,"and "I[ ]of Apollos,"and "I[ ]of Cephas,"and "I of Christ."
B046C001V013	46	1	13	Has Christ been divided? Was Paul crucified for you? Or were you baptized in the name of Paul?
B046C001V014	46	1	14	I thank God that I baptized none of you except Crispus and Gaius,
B046C001V015	46	1	15	lest anyone should say that I had baptized in my own name.
B046C001V016	46	1	16	Yes, I also baptized the household of Stephanas. Besides, I do not know whether I baptized anyone else.
B046C001V017	46	1	17	For Christ did not send me to baptize, but to preach the gospel, not in eloquent wisdom, lest the cross of Christ should be deprived of its power.
B046C001V018	46	1	18	For the message of the cross is foolishness to those who are perishing, but to us who are being saved it is the power of God.
B046C001V019	46	1	19	For it is written: "I will destroy the wisdom of the wise, and the understanding of the prudent I will annul."
B046C001V020	46	1	20	Where is the wise? Where is the scribe? Where is the philosopher of this age? Has not God made foolish the wisdom of this world?
B046C001V021	46	1	21	For since, in the wisdom of God, the world through wisdom did not know God, God was well pleased, through the foolishness of our preaching, to save those that believe.
B046C001V022	46	1	22	For Jews request a sign, and Greeks seek after wisdom;
B046C001V023	46	1	23	but we preach Christ crucified, to the Jews a stumbling block, and to the Greeks foolishness,
B046C001V024	46	1	24	but to those who are called, both Jews and Greeks, Christ the power of God and the wisdom of God.
B046C001V025	46	1	25	Because the foolishness of God is wiser than men, and the weakness of God is stronger than men.
B046C001V026	46	1	26	For you see your calling, brothers, that not many wise according to the flesh, not many powerful, not many noble, [are called].
B046C001V027	46	1	27	But God chose the foolish things of the world in order that He might humiliate the wise, and God chose the weak things of the world in order that He might humiliate the mighty[.]
B046C001V028	46	1	28	And the lowly things of the world, and the despised things God has chosen, and the things which are not, in order that He might nullify the things which are,
B046C001V029	46	1	29	so that no man may boast before God.
B046C001V030	46	1	30	But from Him you are in Christ Jesus, who became for us wisdom from God, and righteousness and sanctification and redemption;
B046C001V031	46	1	31	that, as it is written, "He that boasts, let him boast in the LORD."
B046C002V001	46	2	1	And I, brothers, when I came to you, did not come with excellence of speech or of wisdom, announcing to you the testimony of God.
B046C002V002	46	2	2	For I determined to know nothing among you except Jesus Christ and Him crucified.
B046C002V003	46	2	3	And I was with you in weakness, in fear, and in much trembling.
B046C002V004	46	2	4	And my message and my preaching [were] not with persuasive words of human wisdom, but in demonstration of the Spirit and of power,
B046C002V005	46	2	5	in order that your faith might not be in the wisdom of men, but in the power of God.
B046C002V006	46	2	6	However, we speak wisdom among those that are mature, but not the wisdom of this age, nor of the rulers of this age, who are being destroyed.
B046C002V007	46	2	7	But we speak the wisdom of God in a mystery, the [wisdom] having been hidden, which God foreordained before the ages for our glory,
B046C002V008	46	2	8	which none of the rulers of this age understood (for had they understood, they would not have crucified the Lord of glory).
B046C002V009	46	2	9	But as it is written: "Eye has not seen, nor ear heard, nor have entered into the heart of man, the things which God has prepared for those who love Him."
B046C002V010	46	2	10	But God has revealed [them] to us through His Spirit. For the Spirit searches all things, even the depths of God.
B046C002V011	46	2	11	For who among men knows the things of a man, except the spirit of the man which is in him? Even so, no one knows the things of God except the Spirit of God.
B046C002V012	46	2	12	Now we did not receive the spirit of the world, but the Spirit which is from God, in order that we might know the things freely given to us by God;
B046C002V013	46	2	13	which things we also speak, not in words taught in human wisdom, but in words taught by the Holy Spirit, comparing spiritual things with spiritual.
B046C002V014	46	2	14	But the natural man does not receive the things of the Spirit of God, for they are foolishness to him; nor can he know them, because they are spiritually discerned.
B046C002V015	46	2	15	But he that is spiritual discerns all things, yet he himself is discerned by no man.
B046C002V016	46	2	16	For "Who has known the mind of the LORD, that he may instruct Him?"But we have the mind of Christ.
B046C003V001	46	3	1	And I, brothers, was not able to speak to you as to spiritual, but as to carnal, as to babes in Christ.
B046C003V002	46	3	2	I gave you milk to drink, and not solid food; for you were not yet able [to receive it]. Indeed, neither are you now yet able;
B046C003V003	46	3	3	for you are still carnal. For where there are envy, strife, and divisions among you, are you not carnal, and walking according to human principles?
B046C003V004	46	3	4	For when one says, "I am of Paul,"and another, "I [am] of Apollos,"are you not carnal?
B046C003V005	46	3	5	Who then is Paul, and who is Apollos, but ministers through whom you believed, as the Lord has given to each one?
B046C003V006	46	3	6	I planted, Apollos watered, but God gives the increase.
B046C003V007	46	3	7	So then neither he who plants is anything, nor he who waters, but God who gives the increase.
B046C003V008	46	3	8	Now he who plants and he who waters are one, and each one will receive his own reward according to his own labor.
B046C003V009	46	3	9	For we are coworkers with God; you are God's field, you are God's building.
B046C003V010	46	3	10	According to the grace of God which was given to me, as a wise architect I have laid the foundation, but another builds on it. But let each one take heed how he builds on it.
B046C003V011	46	3	11	For no other foundation can anyone lay, other than that which is laid, which is Jesus Christ.
B046C003V012	46	3	12	Now if anyone builds on this foundation [with] gold, silver, precious stones, wood, hay, straw,
B046C003V013	46	3	13	each one's work shall be made manifest; for the Day shall reveal it, because it shall be revealed by fire; and the fire shall test each one's work, as to what sort it is.
B046C003V014	46	3	14	If anyone's work which he has built remains, he shall receive a reward.
B046C003V015	46	3	15	If anyone's work is burned up, he shall suffer loss; but he himself shall be saved, but so as through fire.
B046C003V016	46	3	16	Do you not know that you are the temple of God, and that the Spirit of God dwells in you?
B046C003V017	46	3	17	If anyone destroys the temple of God, God shall destroy him. For the temple of God is holy, which [temple] you are.
B046C003V018	46	3	18	Let no one deceive himself. If anyone among you seems to be wise in this age, let him become a fool, that he may become wise.
B046C003V019	46	3	19	For the wisdom of this world is foolishness with God. For it is written, "He catches the wise in their craftiness";
B046C003V020	46	3	20	and again, "The LORD knows the thoughts of the wise, that they are useless."
B046C003V021	46	3	21	Therefore let no one boast in men. For all things are yours:
B046C003V022	46	3	22	whether Paul or Apollos or Cephas, or the world or life or death, or things present or things to come-all things[ ]are yours.
B046C003V023	46	3	23	And you are of Christ, and Christ is of God.
B046C004V001	46	4	1	Let a man so consider us, as ministers of Christ and stewards of the mysteries of God.
B046C004V002	46	4	2	Now furthermore what is required among the stewards, is that one be found faithful.
B046C004V003	46	4	3	But to me it is a very small thing that I should be judged by you, or by a human court. Indeed, I do not even judge myself.
B046C004V004	46	4	4	For I am conscious of nothing, but I have not been justified by this; but He who judges me is the Lord.
B046C004V005	46	4	5	So then judge nothing before the time, until the Lord comes, who also will bring to light the hidden things of darkness, and will make clear the purposes of the hearts. Then each one's praise shall come from God.
B046C004V006	46	4	6	Now these things, brothers, I have figuratively applied to myself and Apollos for your sakes, in order that you may learn in us not to think beyond what is written, that none of you may be puffed up on behalf of one against the other.
B046C004V007	46	4	7	For who makes you differ from another? And what do you have that you did not receive? And if you did indeed receive [what you have], why do you boast as though you did not receive it?
B046C004V008	46	4	8	You are already full! You are already rich! You have reigned [as kings] without us; and I wish [that] indeed you did reign, in order that we also might reign with you!
B046C004V009	46	4	9	For I think that God has displayed us, the apostles, last, as men appointed to death; for we became a spectacle to the world, both to angels and to men.
B046C004V010	46	4	10	We are fools for Christ's sake, but you are wise in Christ! We are weak, but you are strong! You are distinguished, but we are despised!
B046C004V011	46	4	11	Even unto this present hour we both hunger and thirst, and we are naked, and beaten, and homeless.
B046C004V012	46	4	12	And we labor, working with our own hands. Being reviled, we bless; being persecuted, we endure;
B046C004V013	46	4	13	being defamed, we encourage; we have become as the sweepings of the world, the offscouring of all things until now.
B046C004V014	46	4	14	I do not write these things to shame you, but as my beloved children I admonish [you].
B046C004V015	46	4	15	For though you might have ten thousand tutors in Christ, yet [you do] not have many fathers; for in Christ Jesus I have begotten you through the gospel.
B046C004V016	46	4	16	Therefore I exhort you, be imitators of me.
B046C004V017	46	4	17	Because of this I sent Timothy to you, who is my beloved and faithful child in the Lord, who will remind you of my ways in Christ, as I teach everywhere in every church.
B046C004V018	46	4	18	Now some have become arrogant, as though I were not coming to you.
B046C004V019	46	4	19	But I will come to you quickly, if the Lord wills, and I will know, not the word of those who are arrogant, but the power.
B046C004V020	46	4	20	For the kingdom of God is not in word, but in power.
B046C004V021	46	4	21	What do you desire? Shall I come to you with a rod, or in love, and a spirit of gentleness?
B046C005V001	46	5	1	It is actually heard that there is fornication among you, and such fornication as is not even named among the Gentiles-that a man has his father's wife!
B046C005V002	46	5	2	And you have become arrogant, and have not rather grieved, so that he who did this deed would be removed from your midst.
B046C005V003	46	5	3	For I indeed, as being absent in body but present in spirit, have already judged (as though I were present) him who has done this deed in this way,
B046C005V004	46	5	4	in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, when you are gathered together, along with my spirit, with the power of our Lord Jesus Christ,
B046C005V005	46	5	5	hand this man over to Satan for the destruction of the flesh, in order that his spirit may be saved in the day of the Lord Jesus.
B046C005V006	46	5	6	Your boasting is not good. Do you not know that a little leaven leavens the whole batch?
B046C005V007	46	5	7	Purge out the old leaven, in order that you may be a new batch of dough, since you are unleavened. For indeed Christ, our Passover, was sacrificed for us.
B046C005V008	46	5	8	So then let us observe the feast, not with old leaven, nor with the leaven of malice and wickedness, but with the unleavened bread of sincerity and truth.
B046C005V009	46	5	9	I wrote to you in my epistle not to associate with fornicators.
B046C005V010	46	5	10	Yet I certainly did not mean with the fornicators of this world, or with the covetous, or swindlers, or idolaters, since then you would need to leave this world!
B046C005V011	46	5	11	But now I have written to you not to associate with anyone named a brother, who is a fornicator, or covetous person, or an idolater, or abusive person, or a drunkard, or a swindler-not even to eat with such a person.
B046C005V012	46	5	12	For what have I to do with judging those also who are outside? Do you not judge those who are inside?
B046C005V013	46	5	13	But those who are outside God will judge. Therefore "put away the evil person from yourselves."
B046C006V001	46	6	1	Does any of you, having a matter against another, dare go to court before the unrighteous, and not before the saints?
B046C006V002	46	6	2	Do you not know that the saints will judge the world? And if the world will be judged by you, are you unworthy to judge the smallest matters?
B046C006V003	46	6	3	Do you not know that we will judge angels? Let alone ordinary [matters]!
B046C006V004	46	6	4	If then you have ordinary lawsuits, do you appoint those who are disdained within the church [to judge?]
B046C006V005	46	6	5	I say [this] to your shame. So is there not among you a wise [man], not even one, who will be able to judge between his brother [and another]?
B046C006V006	46	6	6	But brother goes to court against brother, and that before unbelievers!
B046C006V007	46	6	7	Actually then, it is already a defeat for you that you have lawsuits against one another. Why not rather accept wrong? Why not rather accept being defrauded?
B046C006V008	46	6	8	But you wrong and defraud, and these things [to your] [own ]brothers!
B046C006V009	46	6	9	Or do you not know that the unrighteous will not inherit the kingdom of God? Do not be deceived. Neither fornicators, nor idolaters, nor adulterers, nor homosexuals, nor sodomites,
B046C006V010	46	6	10	nor covetous, nor thieves, nor drunkards, nor abusive people, nor swindlers will inherit the kingdom of God.
B046C006V011	46	6	11	And such were some of you! But you were washed, but you were sanctified, but you were justified in the name of the Lord Jesus and by the Spirit of our God.
B046C006V012	46	6	12	All things are lawful for me, but all things are not profitable. All things are lawful for me, but I will not be mastered by anything.
B046C006V013	46	6	13	Foods for the stomach and the stomach for foods, but God will destroy both this [stomach] and these [foods]. Now the body is not for fornication, but for the Lord, and the Lord for the body.
B046C006V014	46	6	14	Now God has both raised up the Lord, and will also raise us up through His power.
B046C006V015	46	6	15	Do you not know that your bodies are members of Christ? Shall I then take the members of Christ and make [them] members of a harlot? By no means!
B046C006V016	46	6	16	Do you not know that he who is joined to a harlot is one body [with her]? For "the two,"He says, "shall become one flesh."
B046C006V017	46	6	17	But he that is joined with the Lord is one spirit [with Him].
B046C006V018	46	6	18	Flee fornication. Every sin that a man does is outside the body, but he who commits fornication sins against his own body.
B046C006V019	46	6	19	Or do you not know that your body is the temple of the Holy Spirit within you, whom you have from God, and you are not your own?
B046C006V020	46	6	20	For you were bought with a price; therefore glorify God in your body and in your spirit, which are God's.
B046C007V001	46	7	1	Now concerning the[ ]things of which you wrote to me: It is good for a man not to touch a woman.
B046C007V002	46	7	2	Nevertheless, to avoid fornication, let each [man] have his own wife, and let each [woman] have her own husband.
B046C007V003	46	7	3	Let the husband render to his wife the affection due her, and likewise also the wife to her husband.
B046C007V004	46	7	4	The wife does not have authority over her own body, but the husband [does]. And likewise the husband does not have authority over his own body, but the wife [does].
B046C007V005	46	7	5	Do not deprive one another, except by mutual agreement, [and that] for a season, so that you may devote yourselves to fasting and prayer; and come together again, lest Satan tempt you because of your lack of self-control.
B046C007V006	46	7	6	But I say this as a concession, not as a commandment.
B046C007V007	46	7	7	For I wish that all men would be as I myself. But each one has his own gift from God, one in this way and another in that.
B046C007V008	46	7	8	But I say to the unmarried and to the widows: It is good for them if they should remain as I also [remain];
B046C007V009	46	7	9	but if they are not exercising self-control, let them marry. For it is better to marry than to burn [with passion].
B046C007V010	46	7	10	Now to those who have married I command, yet not I, but the Lord: A wife is not to be separated from her husband-
B046C007V011	46	7	11	and even if she does separate, let her remain unmarried or be reconciled to her husband-and a husband is not to divorce his wife.
B046C007V012	46	7	12	But to the rest I, not the Lord, say: If any brother has an unbelieving wife, and she consents to live with him, let him not divorce her.
B046C007V013	46	7	13	And a wife who has an unbelieving husband, if he consents to live with her, let her not divorce him.
B046C007V014	46	7	14	For the unbelieving husband has been sanctified by the wife, and the unbelieving wife has been sanctified by the husband; otherwise your children would be unclean, but now they are holy.
B046C007V015	46	7	15	But if the unbelieving [spouse] separates, let [him or her ]separate; the brother or the sister has not been bound in such cases; but God has called us to peace.
B046C007V016	46	7	16	For how do you know, O wife, whether you will save your husband? Or how do you know, O husband, whether you will save your wife?
B046C007V017	46	7	17	Otherwise as God has distributed to each one, as the Lord has called each one, so let him walk. And so I command in all the churches.
B046C007V018	46	7	18	Was anyone called while circumcised? Let him not become uncircumcised. Was anyone called while uncircumcised? Let him not be circumcised.
B046C007V019	46	7	19	Circumcision is nothing and uncircumcision is nothing, but keeping the commandments of God.
B046C007V020	46	7	20	Let each one remain in the same calling in which he was called.
B046C007V021	46	7	21	Were you called as a slave? Do not be concerned about it; but if you can be made free, rather make use of [it].
B046C007V022	46	7	22	For he who is called in the Lord while a slave is the Lord's free [man]. Likewise he who is called as a free [man] is Christ's slave.
B046C007V023	46	7	23	You were bought with a price; do not become slaves of men.
B046C007V024	46	7	24	Brothers, let each one remain with God in [the state] in which he was called.
B046C007V025	46	7	25	Now concerning virgins, I have no command of the Lord; but I give judgment, as having received mercy by the Lord to be faithful.
B046C007V026	46	7	26	Therefore I consider this to be good because of the present distress, that [it is] good for a man to be as he is:
B046C007V027	46	7	27	Have you been bound to a wife? Do not seek to be released. Have you been released from a wife? Do not seek a wife.
B046C007V028	46	7	28	But even if you should marry, you have not sinned; and if a virgin should marry, she has not sinned. But such will have trouble in the flesh, and I would spare you.
B046C007V029	46	7	29	But this I say, brothers, the time has been shortened; so that from now on even those having wives should be as though they had none,
B046C007V030	46	7	30	and those weeping as though not weeping, and those rejoicing as though not rejoicing, and those buying as though not possessing,
B046C007V031	46	7	31	and those using this world as not using it up. For the form of this world is passing away.
B046C007V032	46	7	32	But I want you to be without anxiety. The unmarried man cares about the things of the Lord-[about ]how he may please the Lord.
B046C007V033	46	7	33	But the [man] having married cares about the things of the world-[about ]how he may please his wife.
B046C007V034	46	7	34	And the wife and the virgin are different. The unmarried woman cares about the things of the Lord, that she may be holy both in body and in spirit. But the woman having married cares about the things of the world-about how she may please her husband.
B046C007V035	46	7	35	And this I say for your own profit, not that I may put a snare upon you, but for that which is proper, and that you may serve the Lord without distraction.
B046C007V036	46	7	36	But if any man thinks he is behaving improperly toward his virgin, if she is past her youth, and thus it must be, let him do what he desires. He does not sin; let them marry.
B046C007V037	46	7	37	But [he] who stands in his heart, not having necessity, but has power over his own desire, and has decided this in his heart that he will keep his virgin, does well.
B046C007V038	46	7	38	So then he who gives her in marriage does well, but he who does not give her in marriage does better.
B046C007V039	46	7	39	A wife has been bound by law as long as her husband lives; but if her husband also dies, she is free to be married to whom she desires, only in the Lord.
B046C007V040	46	7	40	But she is more blessed if she remains as she is, in my opinion-and I think I also have the Spirit of God.
B046C008V001	46	8	1	Now concerning the [things] offered to idols, we know that we all have knowledge. Knowledge puffs up, but love edifies.
B046C008V002	46	8	2	And if anyone thinks that he knows anything, he has come to know nothing yet as he ought to know.
B046C008V003	46	8	3	But if anyone loves God, this one has been known by Him.
B046C008V004	46	8	4	Therefore concerning the eating of the things offered to idols, we know that an idol is nothing in the world, and that there is no other God but one.
B046C008V005	46	8	5	For even if they are being called "gods"whether in heaven or on earth (just as there are many gods and many lords),
B046C008V006	46	8	6	yet for us there is one God, the Father, of whom are all things, and we for Him; and one Lord Jesus Christ, through whom [are] all things, and through whom we [live].
B046C008V007	46	8	7	However, this knowledge is not in all [people]; rather some, with consciousness of the idol, until now eat it as [something] offered to idols; and their conscience, being weak, is defiled.
B046C008V008	46	8	8	But food does not commend us to God; for neither if we eat do we have more, nor if we do not eat do we lack.
B046C008V009	46	8	9	But beware lest somehow this liberty of yours become a stumbling block to those who are weak.
B046C008V010	46	8	10	For if anyone should see you who has knowledge dining in an idol's temple, will not his conscience, being weak, be strengthened so that they eat foods offered to idols?
B046C008V011	46	8	11	And because of your knowledge shall the weak brother perish, for the sake of whom Christ died?
B046C008V012	46	8	12	But when you thus sin against the brothers, and wound their weak conscience, you sin against Christ.
B046C008V013	46	8	13	Wherefore, if food causes my brother to stumble, I will by no means eat meat, lest I cause my brother to stumble.
B046C009V001	46	9	1	Am I not an apostle? Am I not free? Have I not seen Jesus Christ our Lord? Are you not my work in the Lord?
B046C009V002	46	9	2	If I am not an apostle to others, yet indeed I am to you. For you are the seal of my apostleship in the Lord.
B046C009V003	46	9	3	My defense to those who examine me is this:
B046C009V004	46	9	4	Do we not have [the] right to eat and drink?
B046C009V005	46	9	5	Do we not have [the] right to take along a wife [who is] a sister, as do also the other apostles, the brothers of the Lord, and Cephas?
B046C009V006	46	9	6	Or is it only Barnabas and I who must work for a living?
B046C009V007	46	9	7	Who ever serves as a soldier at his own expense? Who plants a vineyard and does not eat of its fruit? Or who tends a flock and does not drink from the milk of the flock?
B046C009V008	46	9	8	Do I say these things as a mere man? Or does not the law say these things also?
B046C009V009	46	9	9	For it is written in the law of Moses, "You shall not muzzle an ox while it threshes."Is it oxen God is concerned about?
B046C009V010	46	9	10	Or does He say [this] altogether for our sakes? For our sakes, no doubt, for it is written, that he that plows should plow in hope, and he that threshes, in hope should partake of his hope.
B046C009V011	46	9	11	If we have sown spiritual things for you, [is it] a great thing if we reap your material things?
B046C009V012	46	9	12	If others partake of this right over you, do not we even more? Nevertheless we did not use this right, but bear all things lest we hinder the gospel of Christ.
B046C009V013	46	9	13	Do you not know that those who minister the holy things eat from the temple, and those who serve at the altar have a share in the altar?
B046C009V014	46	9	14	Thus also the Lord commanded those who proclaim the gospel to live from the gospel.
B046C009V015	46	9	15	But I used none of these things, nor have I written these things that it should become thus for me; for it is better for me rather to die than that anyone should make my boasting void.
B046C009V016	46	9	16	For if I preach the gospel, there is nothing for me to boast about, for necessity is pressed upon me; yes, woe is me if I do not preach the gospel!
B046C009V017	46	9	17	For if I do this willingly, I have a reward; but if unwillingly, I have been entrusted with a commission.
B046C009V018	46	9	18	What then is my reward? That when I preach the gospel, I may present the gospel of Christ free of charge, so as not to exploit my rights in the gospel.
B046C009V019	46	9	19	For being free from all [men], I have made myself a servant to all, in order that I might win the more;
B046C009V020	46	9	20	and to the Jews I became as a Jew, in order that I might win Jews; to those who are under law, as under law, in order that I might win those who are under law;
B046C009V021	46	9	21	to those outside the law, as [one] outside the law (not being outside the law toward God, but subject to [the ]law toward Christ), in order that I might win those outside the law;
B046C009V022	46	9	22	to the weak I became as weak, in order that I might win the weak. I have become all things to all [men], that I might by all means save some.
B046C009V023	46	9	23	Now this I do for the sake of the gospel, in order that I may become a partaker of it [with you].
B046C009V024	46	9	24	Do you not know that those running in a stadium all run, but one receives the prize? So run, in order that you may win.
B046C009V025	46	9	25	And everyone who competes exercises self-control [in] all things. Now they [compete] in order that they may receive a perishable crown, but we [compete] [for ]an imperishable crown.
B046C009V026	46	9	26	Therefore I run thus: not as without a goal, thus I box: not as one beating the air.
B046C009V027	46	9	27	But I treat my body roughly, and I bring it into subjection, lest, having preached to others, I myself should become disqualified.
B046C010V001	46	10	1	Now I do not want you to be ignorant, brothers, that all our fathers were under the cloud, and all passed through the sea,
B046C010V002	46	10	2	and all were baptized into Moses in the cloud and in the sea,
B046C010V003	46	10	3	and all ate the same spiritual food,
B046C010V004	46	10	4	and all drank the same spiritual drink. For they were drinking from that spiritual Rock that followed them, and that Rock was Christ.
B046C010V005	46	10	5	Nevertheless, with the majority of them God was not pleased, for their bodies were scattered in the wilderness.
B046C010V006	46	10	6	Now these things took place as examples for us, in order that we should not lust after evil things, as they also lusted.
B046C010V007	46	10	7	Nor be idolaters, just as some of them; as it is written, "The people sat down to eat and drink, and rose up to play."
B046C010V008	46	10	8	Nor let us commit fornication, just as some of them fornicated, and in one day twenty-three thousand fell;
B046C010V009	46	10	9	nor let us tempt Christ, just as also some of them tempted [Him], and were destroyed by serpents;
B046C010V010	46	10	10	nor murmur, just as also some of them murmured, and were destroyed by the destroyer.
B046C010V011	46	10	11	Now all these things happened to those [people] as examples, and they were written for our instruction, to whom the ends of the ages have come.
B046C010V012	46	10	12	So then, let him who thinks he stands take heed, lest he should fall!
B046C010V013	46	10	13	No temptation has overtaken you except such as is common to man; but God is faithful, who will not permit you to be tempted beyond what you are able, but with the temptation, He will also make the way out, [so as for] you to be able to bear it.
B046C010V014	46	10	14	Therefore, my beloved, flee from idolatry.
B046C010V015	46	10	15	I speak as to wise men; judge for yourselves what I say.
B046C010V016	46	10	16	The cup of blessing which we bless, is it not the communion of the blood of Christ? The bread which we break, is it not the communion of the body of Christ?
B046C010V017	46	10	17	Because we, though many, are one bread and one body; for we all partake from the one bread.
B046C010V018	46	10	18	Look at Israel according to the flesh: are not those who eat of the sacrifices partakers of the altar?
B046C010V019	46	10	19	What am I saying then? That an idol is anything, or what is offered to idols is anything?
B046C010V020	46	10	20	[No], but that the[ ]things which the Gentiles sacrifice, they sacrifice to demons and not to God, and I do not desire that you should have fellowship with demons.
B046C010V021	46	10	21	You cannot drink the cup of the Lord and the cup of demons; you cannot partake of the Lord's table and of the table of demons.
B046C010V022	46	10	22	Or do we provoke the Lord to jealousy? Are we stronger than He?
B046C010V023	46	10	23	All things are lawful for me, but not all things are profitable; all things are lawful for me, but not all things edify.
B046C010V024	46	10	24	Let no one seek his own concerns, but let each [one] seek another's concern.
B046C010V025	46	10	25	Eat everything being sold in the meat market, questioning nothing, for conscience' sake;
B046C010V026	46	10	26	for "The earth is the LORD's, and all its fullness."
B046C010V027	46	10	27	And if any of the unbelievers invites you to dinner, and you desire to go, eat whatever is set before you, questioning nothing, for conscience' sake.
B046C010V028	46	10	28	But if anyone says to you, "This was offered to idols,"do not eat it for the sake of the one who told you, and for his conscience' sake; for "The earth is the LORD's, and all its fullness."
B046C010V029	46	10	29	"Conscience,"I say, not your own, but that of the other. For why is my freedom judged by another man's conscience?
B046C010V030	46	10	30	But if I partake with thanks, why am I defamed for [that] of which I give thanks?
B046C010V031	46	10	31	Therefore, whether you eat or drink, or whatever you do, do all things for the glory of God.
B046C010V032	46	10	32	Be without offense, both toward Jews and toward Greeks, and toward the church of God,
B046C010V033	46	10	33	just as I also please all men in all things, not seeking my own profit, but the [profit] of many, that they may be saved.
B046C011V001	46	11	1	Be imitators of me, just as I also [am] of Christ.
B046C011V002	46	11	2	Now I praise you, brothers, because you remember me in all things, and you hold fast the traditions just as I handed down to you.
B046C011V003	46	11	3	But I want you to know that the head of every man is Christ, the head of woman is man, and the head of Christ is God.
B046C011V004	46	11	4	Every man who prays or who prophesies with his head covered, dishonors his head.
B046C011V005	46	11	5	But every woman who prays or who prophesies with her head uncovered dishonors her own head, for that is one and the same as if her [head] were shaved.
B046C011V006	46	11	6	For if a woman is not covered, let her also have her hair cut. But if it is a shameful [thing ]for a woman to have her hair cut, or to be shaved, let her be covered.
B046C011V007	46	11	7	For a man indeed ought not to cover his head, since he is the image and glory of God; but woman is the glory of man.
B046C011V008	46	11	8	For man did not come from woman, but woman from man.
B046C011V009	46	11	9	Nor was man created for woman, but woman for the man.
B046C011V010	46	11	10	Because of this, the woman ought to have a [symbol] [of] authority on her head, because of the angels.
B046C011V011	46	11	11	Nevertheless, neither is the man apart from the woman, nor the woman apart from the man, in the Lord.
B046C011V012	46	11	12	For as the woman is from the man, even so the man is by the woman; but all things are of God.
B046C011V013	46	11	13	Judge among yourselves. Is it proper for a woman to pray to God uncovered?
B046C011V014	46	11	14	Does not nature itself teach you, that if a man has long hair, it is a dishonor to him?
B046C011V015	46	11	15	But if a woman has long hair, it is a glory for her; because her long hair has been given [to her] in place of a covering.
B046C011V016	46	11	16	But if anyone seems to be contentious, we have no such custom, nor do the churches of God.
B046C011V017	46	11	17	Now in giving these instructions I do not praise you, because you are not coming together for the better, but for the worse.
B046C011V018	46	11	18	For first of all, when you come together in church, I hear that there are divisions among you, and in part I believe it.
B046C011V019	46	11	19	For there must also be sects among you, in order that those who are approved may become recognized among you.
B046C011V020	46	11	20	Therefore when you assemble in the same [place], it is not to eat the Lord's Supper.
B046C011V021	46	11	21	For when you eat, each one takes first his own supper, and one goes hungry and another is drunk!
B046C011V022	46	11	22	What? Do you not have houses to eat and drink in? Or do you despise the church of God, and disgrace those who do not have? What shall I say to you? Shall I praise you in this? I do not praise you!
B046C011V023	46	11	23	For I received from the Lord that which I also delivered unto you: that the Lord Jesus, during the night in which He was betrayed, took bread;
B046C011V024	46	11	24	and having given thanks, He broke it and said, "Take, eat; this is My body which has been broken for you; do this in remembrance of Me."
B046C011V025	46	11	25	Likewise He also took the cup after supper, saying, "This cup is the new covenant in My blood. This do, as often as you drink it, in remembrance of Me."
B046C011V026	46	11	26	For as often as you eat this bread and drink this cup, you proclaim the Lord's death until He comes.
B046C011V027	46	11	27	Therefore whoever eats this bread or drinks this cup of the Lord irreverently will be guilty of the body of the Lord and of the blood of the Lord.
B046C011V028	46	11	28	But let a man examine himself, and in this way let him eat from the bread and drink from the cup.
B046C011V029	46	11	29	For he that eats and drinks irreverently eats and drinks judgment to himself, not judging correctly the body of the Lord.
B046C011V030	46	11	30	Because of this many among you are weak and sick, and many have died.
B046C011V031	46	11	31	For if we judge ourselves correctly, we would not be judged.
B046C011V032	46	11	32	But when we are judged, we are disciplined by the Lord, in order that we may not be condemned along with the world.
B046C011V033	46	11	33	Therefore, my brothers, when you come together to eat, wait for one another.
B046C011V034	46	11	34	But if anyone is hungry, let him eat at home, lest you come together for judgment. And the rest I will put in order when I come.
B046C012V001	46	12	1	Now concerning spiritual [gifts], brothers, I do not want you to be ignorant.
B046C012V002	46	12	2	You know that when you were pagans, how you were led, being carried away to these speechless idols.
B046C012V003	46	12	3	Therefore I make known to you that no one speaking by the Spirit of God says "Jesus be cursed,"and no one can say that Jesus [is] Lord except by the Holy Spirit.
B046C012V004	46	12	4	Now there are varieties of spiritual gifts, but the same Spirit.
B046C012V005	46	12	5	And there are varieties of ministries, but the same Lord.
B046C012V006	46	12	6	And there are varieties of activities, but the same God works all in all.
B046C012V007	46	12	7	But to each [one] the manifestation of the Spirit is given for the profit [of all.]
B046C012V008	46	12	8	For to one is given a word of wisdom through the Spirit, to another a word of knowledge according to the same Spirit,
B046C012V009	46	12	9	and to another faith by the same Spirit, to another gifts of healings by the same Spirit,
B046C012V010	46	12	10	to another the working of miracles, and to another prophecy, and to another discerning of spirits, and to another [different] kinds of tongues, and to another interpretation of tongues.
B046C012V011	46	12	11	But one and the same Spirit works all these things, distributing to each one individually just as He wills.
B046C012V012	46	12	12	For just as the body is one and has many parts, but all the parts of that one body, being many, are one body, so also is Christ.
B046C012V013	46	12	13	For by one Spirit we were all baptized into one body-whether Jews or Greeks, whether slaves or free-and we were all given to drink into one Spirit.
B046C012V014	46	12	14	For in fact the body is not one part but many.
B046C012V015	46	12	15	If the foot should say, "Because I am not a hand, I am not of the body,"is it therefore not of the body?
B046C012V016	46	12	16	And if the ear should say, "Because I am not an eye, I am not of the body,"is it therefore not of the body?
B046C012V017	46	12	17	If the whole body [were] an eye, where [would be] the hearing? If the whole [were] hearing, where [would be] the smelling?
B046C012V018	46	12	18	But now God has set the parts, each one of them, in the body just as He desired.
B046C012V019	46	12	19	And if all [parts ]were one part, where [would be] the body?
B046C012V020	46	12	20	But now indeed there[ are] many parts, but one body.
B046C012V021	46	12	21	And the eye cannot say to the hand, "I have no need of you"; nor again the head to the feet, "I have no need of you."
B046C012V022	46	12	22	But to a greater degree the parts of the body which seem weaker are necessary.
B046C012V023	46	12	23	And [the parts] of the body which we consider to be less honorable, on these we bestow greater honor; and our unpresentable parts have greater propriety.
B046C012V024	46	12	24	But our presentable [parts] have no need. But God united the body, giving greater honor to the [part] being inferior,
B046C012V025	46	12	25	lest there be divisions in the body, but the parts care the same for one another.
B046C012V026	46	12	26	And if one part suffers, all the parts suffer together; or if one part is honored, all the parts rejoice together.
B046C012V027	46	12	27	Now you are the body of Christ, and members individually.
B046C012V028	46	12	28	And [those] whom God has appointed in the church [are]: first apostles, second prophets, third teachers, then miracles, then gifts of healings, helps, administrations, kinds of tongues.
B046C012V029	46	12	29	All [are] not apostles, [are they]? All [are] not prophets, [are they]? Are all teachers? [Are] all [workers of] miracles?
B046C012V030	46	12	30	Do all have gifts of healings? Do all speak with tongues? Do all interpret?
B046C012V031	46	12	31	But strive for the better gifts. And yet I make known a more excellent way.
B046C013V001	46	13	1	Though I speak with the tongues of men and of angels, but have not love, I have become [as] sounding brass or a clashing cymbal.
B046C013V002	46	13	2	And though I have [the gift of] prophecy, and know all mysteries and all knowledge, and though I have all faith, so as to remove mountains, but have not love, I am nothing.
B046C013V003	46	13	3	And though I give away all my possessions to feed [the poor], and though I deliver up my body to be burned, but have not love, it profits me nothing.
B046C013V004	46	13	4	Love is patient, love is kind; love does not envy; love does not boast, is not arrogant;
B046C013V005	46	13	5	does not behave disgracefully, does not seek its own, is not provoked to anger, thinks no evil;
B046C013V006	46	13	6	does not rejoice over unrighteousness, but rejoices with the truth;
B046C013V007	46	13	7	bears all things, believes all things, hopes all things, endures all things.
B046C013V008	46	13	8	Love never fails. But whether there [are] prophecies, they shall pass away; whether there[ are] tongues, they shall cease; whether there[ is] knowledge, it shall pass away.
B046C013V009	46	13	9	Now we know in part, and we prophesy in part.
B046C013V010	46	13	10	But when that which is perfect has come, then that which is partial shall pass away.
B046C013V011	46	13	11	When I was a child, I spoke as a child, I thought as a child, I reasoned as a child; but when I became a man, I put away the things of the child.
B046C013V012	46	13	12	For now we see through a mirror by reflection, but then face to face. Now I know in part, but then I shall know just as I also am known.
B046C013V013	46	13	13	And now abide faith, hope, love, these three; but the greatest of these is love.
B046C014V001	46	14	1	Pursue love, and desire the spiritual [gifts], but especially that you may prophesy.
B046C014V002	46	14	2	For he who speaks in an [unknown] tongue speaks not to men, but to God, for no one understands him; however, in the spirit he speaks mysteries.
B046C014V003	46	14	3	But he who prophesies speaks edification and exhortation and comfort.
B046C014V004	46	14	4	He who speaks in an [unknown] tongue edifies himself, but he who prophesies edifies the church.
B046C014V005	46	14	5	Now I wish you all spoke in tongues, but even more that you should prophesy; for he who prophesies is greater than he who speaks in tongues, unless he interprets, so that the church may be edified.
B046C014V006	46	14	6	But now, brothers, if I come to you speaking in tongues, what shall I profit you unless I speak to you either in a revelation, or in knowledge, or in a prophesy, or in doctrine?
B046C014V007	46	14	7	Likewise the lifeless things, when they make a sound, whether flute or harp, unless they make a distinction in the tones, how will it be known what is being played on the flute, or what is being played on the harp?
B046C014V008	46	14	8	For if the trumpet gives an indistinct sound, who will prepare for battle?
B046C014V009	46	14	9	So also you, [if you] do not give a clear word by the tongue, how will it be known what is being spoken? For you will be speaking into the air.
B046C014V010	46	14	10	There are, perhaps, so many kinds of sounds in the world, and none of them without meaning.
B046C014V011	46	14	11	Therefore, if I do not know the meaning of the sound, I shall be as a foreigner to the [one ]speaking, and the [one] speaking [shall be] as a foreigner to me.
B046C014V012	46	14	12	So also you, since you are zealous of spiritual [gifts], seek that you may abound to the edification of the church.
B046C014V013	46	14	13	Therefore let he that speaks in an [unknown] tongue pray that he may interpret.
B046C014V014	46	14	14	For if I pray in a tongue, my spirit prays, but my understanding is unfruitful.
B046C014V015	46	14	15	What is the conclusion then? I will pray with the spirit, and I will also pray with the mind. I will sing with the spirit, and I will also sing with the mind.
B046C014V016	46	14	16	Otherwise, if you bless with the spirit, how will he who occupies the place of the uninformed say "Amen"when you give thanks, since he does not know what you are saying?
B046C014V017	46	14	17	For you indeed give thanks well, but the other is not edified.
B046C014V018	46	14	18	I thank my God I speak with tongues more than you all;
B046C014V019	46	14	19	but in the church I would rather speak five words with my understanding, in order that I may instruct others, rather than ten thousand words in an [unknown] tongue.
B046C014V020	46	14	20	Brothers, do not be children in your understanding; rather, in malice be children, but in understanding be men.
B046C014V021	46	14	21	In the law it is written: "With men of other tongues and by strange lips I will speak to this people; and yet not even in this way will they hear Me,"says the Lord.
B046C014V022	46	14	22	So then tongues are for a sign, not to those who believe but to unbelievers; but prophesying is not for unbelievers but for those who believe.
B046C014V023	46	14	23	If then the whole church comes together at the same place, and all speak in tongues, and there come in [those that are] unlearned or unbelievers, will they not say that you are mad?
B046C014V024	46	14	24	But if all prophesy, and an unbeliever or an unlearned person comes in, he is reproved by all, he is discerned by all.
B046C014V025	46	14	25	And so the secrets of his heart become clear; and so, falling down on his face, he will worship God, reporting that God is truly among you!
B046C014V026	46	14	26	What is it then, brothers? Whenever you come together, each of you has a song, has a teaching, has a tongue, has a revelation, has an interpretation. Let all things be done for edification.
B046C014V027	46	14	27	If anyone speaks in an [unknown] tongue, [let it be ]by two or at the most three, each in turn, and let one interpret.
B046C014V028	46	14	28	But if there is no interpreter, let him be silent in church, and let him speak to himself and to God.
B046C014V029	46	14	29	Let two or three prophets speak, and let others discriminate.
B046C014V030	46	14	30	But if [something] is revealed to another who sits by, let the first be silent.
B046C014V031	46	14	31	For you can all prophesy [one] by one, that all may learn and all may be encouraged.
B046C014V032	46	14	32	And the spirits of the prophets are subject to the prophets.
B046C014V033	46	14	33	For God is not [the author] of confusion but of peace. As in all the churches of the saints,
B046C014V034	46	14	34	let your women be silent in the churches, for it is not permitted for them to speak, but to be in subjection, just as the law also says.
B046C014V035	46	14	35	And if they desire to learn anything, let them ask their own husbands at home; for it is shameful for women to speak in church.
B046C014V036	46	14	36	Or did the word of God go forth from you? Or did it come to you only?
B046C014V037	46	14	37	If anyone thinks that he is a prophet, or [is] spiritual[,] let him recognize that the things which I am writing to you are the commandments of the Lord.
B046C014V038	46	14	38	But if anyone is ignorant, let him be ignorant.
B046C014V039	46	14	39	Therefore, brothers, seek to prophesy, and do not forbid to speak in tongues.
B046C014V040	46	14	40	Let all things be done properly and according to order.
B046C015V001	46	15	1	Now I made known to you, brothers, the gospel which I preached to you, which also you received, in which you also stand,
B046C015V002	46	15	2	through which also you are saved, if you hold fast that word which I preached to you-unless you believed in vain.
B046C015V003	46	15	3	For I delivered to you first of all that which I also received: that Christ died for our sins according to the Scriptures,
B046C015V004	46	15	4	and that He was buried, and that He was raised on the third day according to the Scriptures,
B046C015V005	46	15	5	and that He appeared to Cephas, then to the Twelve.
B046C015V006	46	15	6	Thereafter He appeared to more than five hundred brothers at one time, of whom the majority remain until now, but some have fallen asleep.
B046C015V007	46	15	7	Thereafter He appeared to James, then to all the apostles.
B046C015V008	46	15	8	And last of all, as of [one] born out of due time, He appeared to me also.
B046C015V009	46	15	9	For I am the least of the apostles, who am not worthy to be called an apostle, because I persecuted the church of God.
B046C015V010	46	15	10	But by the grace of God I am what I am, and His grace toward me was not in vain; but I labored more abundantly than them all, yet not I, but the grace of God which was with me.
B046C015V011	46	15	11	Therefore, whether it was I or they, so we preach and so you believed.
B046C015V012	46	15	12	Now if Christ is preached that He has been raised from the dead, how do some among you say that there is no resurrection of the dead?
B046C015V013	46	15	13	But if there is no resurrection of the dead, then Christ has not been raised.
B046C015V014	46	15	14	And if Christ has not been raised, then our preaching is vain and your faith also is vain!
B046C015V015	46	15	15	And we are found [to be ]false witnesses of God, because we bore witness concerning God, that He raised Christ, whom He did not raise-if in fact the dead are not raised.
B046C015V016	46	15	16	For if the dead are not raised, [then] neither has Christ been raised.
B046C015V017	46	15	17	And if Christ has not been raised, your faith is worthless; you are still in your sins!
B046C015V018	46	15	18	Then also those who have fallen asleep in Christ have perished.
B046C015V019	46	15	19	If in this life only we have hoped in Christ, we are to be pitied above all men.
B046C015V020	46	15	20	But now Christ has been raised from the dead, [and] has become the firstfruits of those who have fallen asleep.
B046C015V021	46	15	21	For since by a man [came] death, also by a Man came the resurrection of the dead.
B046C015V022	46	15	22	For as in Adam all die, even so in Christ all will be made alive.
B046C015V023	46	15	23	But each one in his own order: Christ the firstfruits, then those who belong to Christ at His coming.
B046C015V024	46	15	24	Then [will be] the end, when He hands over the kingdom to God, even the Father, when He abolishes every ruler and every authority and power.
B046C015V025	46	15	25	For He must reign until He puts all His enemies under His feet.
B046C015V026	46	15	26	The last enemy that will be abolished is death.
B046C015V027	46	15	27	For "He has subjected all things under His feet."But when He says that "all things have been subjected,"it is evident that [this is] except for Him who subjected all things to Him.
B046C015V028	46	15	28	Now when all things are made subject to Him, then also the Son Himself will be subjected to Him who subjected all things to Him, in order that God may be all in all.
B046C015V029	46	15	29	Otherwise, what will they do who are being baptized for the dead, if the dead are not raised at all? Why are they also baptized for the dead?
B046C015V030	46	15	30	And why are we also in danger every hour?
B046C015V031	46	15	31	I [affirm], by my boasting in you which I have in Christ Jesus our Lord, I die daily.
B046C015V032	46	15	32	If, in the manner of men, I fought with beasts at Ephesus, what is the benefit to me? If the dead are not raised, "Let us eat and drink, for tomorrow we die!"
B046C015V033	46	15	33	Do not be deceived: "Evil associations corrupt good habits."
B046C015V034	46	15	34	Awake to righteousness, and do not sin! For some have no knowledge of God. I speak this to your shame.
B046C015V035	46	15	35	But someone will say, "How are the dead raised? And with what sort of body do they come?"
B046C015V036	46	15	36	Fool, what you sow is not made alive unless it dies.
B046C015V037	46	15	37	And what you sow, you do not sow that body that will be, but a bare grain-perhaps wheat or some other [grains].
B046C015V038	46	15	38	But God gives to it a body just as He desired, and to each of the seeds its own body.
B046C015V039	46	15	39	All flesh is not the same flesh, but there is a different [kind] [of flesh] for men, and another flesh for beasts, another for fish, and another for birds.
B046C015V040	46	15	40	And there[ are ]heavenly bodies, and earthly bodies; but the glory of the heavenly is one, and the glory of the earthly is another.
B046C015V041	46	15	41	There is one glory of the sun, and another glory of the moon, and another glory of the stars; for one star differs from [another] star in glory.
B046C015V042	46	15	42	So also is the resurrection of the dead. The body is sown in corruption, it is raised in incorruption.
B046C015V043	46	15	43	It is sown in dishonor, it is raised in glory. It is sown in weakness, it is raised in power.
B046C015V044	46	15	44	It is sown a natural body, it is raised a spiritual body. There is a natural body, and there is a spiritual body.
B046C015V045	46	15	45	Thus also it is written, "The first man Adam [became] a living being;"the last Adam [became] a life-giving spirit.
B046C015V046	46	15	46	However, that which is spiritual is not first, but that which is natural, then that which is spiritual.
B046C015V047	46	15	47	The first man [was ]from earth, made of dust; the second Man is the Lord from heaven.
B046C015V048	46	15	48	Like the [man] made of dust, so also [are] those who are made of dust; and as is the heavenly [Man], so also [are ]those [who are ]heavenly.
B046C015V049	46	15	49	And just as we have borne the image of the [man] made of dust, let us also bear the image of the heavenly [Man].
B046C015V050	46	15	50	Now this I say, brothers, that flesh and blood cannot inherit the kingdom of God; nor can corruption inherit incorruption.
B046C015V051	46	15	51	Behold, I tell you a mystery: We shall not all sleep, but we shall all be changed-
B046C015V052	46	15	52	in a moment, in the twinkling of an eye, at the last trumpet. For the trumpet shall sound, and the dead shall be raised incorruptible, and we shall be changed.
B046C015V053	46	15	53	For this corruptible must put on incorruption, and this mortal must put on immortality.
B046C015V054	46	15	54	So when this corruptible should put on incorruption, and this mortal should put on immortality, then will come to pass the word which was written: "Death was swallowed up in victory."
B046C015V055	46	15	55	"O Death, where is your sting? O Hades, where is your victory?"
B046C015V056	46	15	56	Now the sting of death is sin, and the power of sin is the law.
B046C015V057	46	15	57	But thanks be to God, who gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ.
B046C015V058	46	15	58	So then, my beloved brothers, be steadfast, immovable, always abounding in the work of the Lord, knowing that your labor is not in vain in the Lord.
B046C016V001	46	16	1	Now concerning the collection which is for the saints, as I directed to the churches of Galatia, so you must do also:
B046C016V002	46	16	2	On the first day of the week let each one of you put [something] aside, storing up whatever he may prosper, in order that there be no collections when I come.
B046C016V003	46	16	3	But when I arrive, [those] whom ever you approve by letters, these I will send to carry your gracious gift to Jerusalem.
B046C016V004	46	16	4	But if it is fitting that I go also, they will go with me.
B046C016V005	46	16	5	Now I will come to you when I go through Macedonia (for I am coming through Macedonia).
B046C016V006	46	16	6	And perhaps I will remain, or even spend the winter with you, that you may send me on my journey, wherever I may go.
B046C016V007	46	16	7	For I do not wish to see you now in passing; but I hope to spend some time with you, if the Lord permits.
B046C016V008	46	16	8	But I will remain in Ephesus until Pentecost.
B046C016V009	46	16	9	For a great and effective door has been opened to me, and there[ are] many adversaries.
B046C016V010	46	16	10	Now if Timothy comes, see to it that he may be with you without fear; for he does the work of the Lord, as I also [do].
B046C016V011	46	16	11	Therefore let no one despise him. But send him away in peace, that he may come to me; for I am waiting for him with the brothers.
B046C016V012	46	16	12	Now concerning our brother Apollos, I strongly urged him to come to you with the brothers, but it was not his will to come at this time; however, he will come whenever he has an opportunity.
B046C016V013	46	16	13	Watch, stand fast in the faith, be courageous, be strong.
B046C016V014	46	16	14	Let all that you do be done in love.
B046C016V015	46	16	15	I urge you, brothers (you know the household of Stephanas, that it is the firstfruits of Achaia, and that they have devoted themselves to the ministry of the saints)
B046C016V016	46	16	16	that you also subject yourselves to such [people] and to everyone who works and labors with us.
B046C016V017	46	16	17	I rejoice over the coming of Stephanas, Fortunatus, and Achaicus, for what was lacking on your part they have supplied.
B046C016V018	46	16	18	For they refreshed my spirit and yours. Therefore give recognition to such [men].
B046C016V019	46	16	19	The churches of Asia greet you. Aquila and Priscilla greet you heartily in the Lord, together with the church that is in their house.
B046C016V020	46	16	20	All the brothers greet you. Greet one another with a holy kiss.
B046C016V021	46	16	21	The salutation with my own hand-Paul's.
B046C016V022	46	16	22	If anyone does not love the Lord Jesus Christ, let him be Anathema. Marana tha!
B046C016V023	46	16	23	The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with you.
B046C016V024	46	16	24	My love be with you all in Christ Jesus. Amen.
B047C001V001	47	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God, and Timothy our brother, to the church of God which is at Corinth, together with all the saints who are in all Achaia:
B047C001V002	47	1	2	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B047C001V003	47	1	3	Blessed [be] the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father of mercies and God of all comfort,
B047C001V004	47	1	4	who comforts us in all our tribulation, so that we may be able to comfort those who are in any affliction, by means of the comfort with which we ourselves are comforted by God.
B047C001V005	47	1	5	Because just as the sufferings of Christ abound in us, so our consolation also abounds through Christ.
B047C001V006	47	1	6	Now if we are afflicted, it is for your consolation and salvation, which is effective for enduring the same sufferings which we also suffer.
B047C001V007	47	1	7	(And our hope concerning you is steadfast); if we are comforted, it is for your consolation and salvation, knowing that as you are partakers of the sufferings, thus also [you will partake] of the consolation.
B047C001V008	47	1	8	For we do not desire you to be ignorant, brothers, concerning our affliction which happened to us in Asia: that we were burdened beyond measure, beyond our strength, so that we despaired even of life.
B047C001V009	47	1	9	Yes, we have had the sentence of death in ourselves, that we should not trust in ourselves but in God who raises the dead,
B047C001V010	47	1	10	who delivered us from so great a death, and is delivering [us]; in whom we trust that He will still deliver [us],
B047C001V011	47	1	11	you also laboring together for us in prayer, that thanks may be given by many persons on your behalf for the gift [given] to us through many.
B047C001V012	47	1	12	For our boasting is this: the testimony of our conscience, that we have conducted ourselves in the world in simplicity and godly sincerity, not with fleshly wisdom but by the grace of God, and especially toward you.
B047C001V013	47	1	13	For we do not write other things to you except what you read or also understand. And I hope that you will understand, even until the end
B047C001V014	47	1	14	just as also you have understood us in part, that we are your boasting, as indeed you also are ours, in the day of the Lord Jesus.
B047C001V015	47	1	15	And in this confidence I intended to come to you earlier, that you might have a second benefit,
B047C001V016	47	1	16	and through you to pass into Macedonia, and again from Macedonia to come to you, and by you to be sent on to Judea.
B047C001V017	47	1	17	Therefore, when I decided this, did I do it lightly? Or the things I decide, do I decide according to the flesh, that there may be with me "Yes, Yes,"and "No, No?"
B047C001V018	47	1	18	But [as ]God [is] faithful, our word unto you was not "Yes and no."
B047C001V019	47	1	19	For the Son of God, Jesus Christ, who was preached among you by us-by me, Silvanus, and Timothy-was not "Yes and no,"but in Him was "Yes."
B047C001V020	47	1	20	For all the promises of God in Him [are] "Yes,"and in Him "Amen,"to the glory of God through us.
B047C001V021	47	1	21	Now He who establishes us together with you in Christ and who has anointed us is God,
B047C001V022	47	1	22	who also has sealed us, and given us the Spirit in our hearts as a pledge.
B047C001V023	47	1	23	Moreover I call upon God as a witness against my soul, that in order to spare you, I came no more to Corinth.
B047C001V024	47	1	24	Not that we lord it over your faith, but are fellow workers for your joy; for by faith you stand.
B047C002V001	47	2	1	But I determined this within myself, that I would not come again to you in sorrow.
B047C002V002	47	2	2	For if I make you sorrowful, then who is he who makes me glad if not the [one] which is made sorrowful by me?
B047C002V003	47	2	3	And I wrote this very thing to you, lest when I came, I should have sorrow from those from whom I ought to have joy, having confidence in you all that my joy is [the joy] of you all.
B047C002V004	47	2	4	For out of much affliction and distress of heart I wrote to you, through many tears, not that you might be made sorrowful, but that you might know the love which I have more abundantly towards you.
B047C002V005	47	2	5	Now if anyone has caused grief, he has not grieved me, but in part-lest I burden you all.
B047C002V006	47	2	6	Sufficient to such a person is this punishment which was [inflicted] by the majority,
B047C002V007	47	2	7	so that, on the contrary, you ought rather to forgive and comfort him, lest somehow such a person be overwhelmed by excessive sorrow.
B047C002V008	47	2	8	Therefore I appeal to you to reaffirm [your] love towards him.
B047C002V009	47	2	9	For to this end I also wrote, so that I might put you to the test, [to see] if you are obedient in all things.
B047C002V010	47	2	10	And to whom you forgive anything, I also [forgive;] for if indeed I have forgiven anything, [the ]one whom I have forgiven, [I have done so] for your sakes in the presence of Christ,
B047C002V011	47	2	11	lest we be taken advantage of by Satan; for we are not ignorant of his devices.
B047C002V012	47	2	12	Now when I came to Troas for the gospel of Christ, and a door was opened to me by the Lord,
B047C002V013	47	2	13	I had no rest in my spirit, because I did not find Titus my brother; but saying farewell to them, I departed for Macedonia.
B047C002V014	47	2	14	Now thanks be to God, who always leads us in triumph in Christ, and making known through us the fragrance of His knowledge in every place.
B047C002V015	47	2	15	For we are the fragrance of Christ to God among those being saved, and among those perishing.
B047C002V016	47	2	16	To some we are the fragrance of death [leading] to death, but to others the fragrance of life [leading] to life. And who is sufficient for these things?
B047C002V017	47	2	17	For we are not as the rest, corrupting the word of God; but as of sincerity, but as from God, we speak in the sight of God in Christ.
B047C003V001	47	3	1	Do we begin again to commend ourselves? Or do we need, as some do, letters of recommendation to you, or [letters] of recommendation from you?
B047C003V002	47	3	2	You are our letter, having been written in our hearts, being known and being read by all men;
B047C003V003	47	3	3	being made known that you are [the] letter of Christ, which was ministered by us, having been written not with ink but by the Spirit of the living God, not in tablets of stone but in tablets of flesh, [namely] in hearts.
B047C003V004	47	3	4	And we have such trust through Christ toward God.
B047C003V005	47	3	5	Not that we are sufficient in ourselves to consider anything as from ourselves, but our sufficiency is from God,
B047C003V006	47	3	6	who also has made us efficient as ministers of the new covenant, not of [the] letter but of [the] Spirit; for the letter kills, but the Spirit makes alive.
B047C003V007	47	3	7	Now if the ministry of death, having been engraved in letters on stones, came to be with glory, so that the sons of Israel could not look intently into the face of Moses because of the glory of his countenance, the [glory which] [was] passing away,
B047C003V008	47	3	8	how will the ministry of the Spirit not be more glorious?
B047C003V009	47	3	9	For if the ministry of condemnation [had] glory, the ministry of righteousness exceeds much more in glory.
B047C003V010	47	3	10	For even that which has been glorified has not been glorified in this respect, because of the surpassing glory.
B047C003V011	47	3	11	For if that which passes away [was] glorious, then that which remains is much more glorious.
B047C003V012	47	3	12	Therefore, having such hope, we use great boldness of speech-
B047C003V013	47	3	13	and not as Moses, who put a veil over his face so that the sons of Israel could not look intently at the end of what was passing away.
B047C003V014	47	3	14	But their minds were blinded. For until this day the same veil remains unlifted in the reading of the Old Testament, because the veil is removed in Christ.
B047C003V015	47	3	15	But even to this day, when Moses is read, a veil lies on their heart.
B047C003V016	47	3	16	But whenever one turns to the Lord, the veil is taken away.
B047C003V017	47	3	17	Now the Lord is the Spirit; and where the Spirit of the Lord [is], there is freedom.
B047C003V018	47	3	18	But we all, with unveiled face, beholding as in a mirror the glory of the Lord, are being transformed into the same image from glory to glory, just as by the Spirit of the Lord.
B047C004V001	47	4	1	Therefore, since we have this ministry, as we received mercy, we do not despair,
B047C004V002	47	4	2	but we have renounced the hidden things of shame, not walking in craftiness nor falsifying the word of God, but by the disclosure of the truth, commending ourselves to every man's conscience before God.
B047C004V003	47	4	3	But even if our gospel is hidden, it is hidden among those who are perishing,
B047C004V004	47	4	4	among whom the god of this age has blinded the minds of the unbelievers, so that the illumination of the gospel of the glory of Christ, who is the image of God, should not shine on them.
B047C004V005	47	4	5	For we do not preach ourselves, but Christ Jesus the Lord, and ourselves your bondservants for Jesus' sake.
B047C004V006	47	4	6	Because it is God who commanded light to shine out of darkness, who shined in our hearts to give [the] light of the knowledge of the glory of God in [the] face of Jesus Christ.
B047C004V007	47	4	7	But we have this treasure in clay vessels, so that the extraordinary character of the power may be of God and not of us;
B047C004V008	47	4	8	in everything being oppressed, yet not crushed; perplexed, but not in despair;
B047C004V009	47	4	9	persecuted, but not abandoned; cast down, but not destroyed;
B047C004V010	47	4	10	always carrying about in the body the dying of the Lord Jesus, so that also the life of Jesus may be revealed in our body.
B047C004V011	47	4	11	For we who are living are always handed over to death for Jesus' sake, so that the life of Jesus also may be manifest in our body.
B047C004V012	47	4	12	So then death is working in us, but life in you.
B047C004V013	47	4	13	And since we have the same spirit of faith, according to that which is written, "I believed, and therefore I spoke,"we also believe, therefore we also speak,
B047C004V014	47	4	14	knowing that He who raised the Lord Jesus will also raise us through Jesus, and will present us together with you.
B047C004V015	47	4	15	For all things[ are] for your sakes, that grace, having spread through the many, may cause thanksgiving to abound to the glory of God.
B047C004V016	47	4	16	Therefore we do not despair, but even if our outward man is being destroyed, yet the inward man is being renewed day by day.
B047C004V017	47	4	17	For our momentary light affliction is working out for us a far more exceeding and eternal weight of glory,
B047C004V018	47	4	18	while we do not look at the things which are seen, but at the things which are not seen. For the things which are seen are for a season, but the things which are not seen last forever.
B047C005V001	47	5	1	For we know that if our earthly house, this tent, is destroyed, we have a building from God, a house not made by hand, eternal in the heavens.
B047C005V002	47	5	2	For also in this we groan, earnestly desiring to be clothed with our habitation which is from heaven,
B047C005V003	47	5	3	if indeed, having been clothed, we shall not be found naked.
B047C005V004	47	5	4	For we who are in this tent groan, being burdened, inasmuch as we do not desire to be stripped, but to put on [clothing], that that which is mortal may be swallowed up by life.
B047C005V005	47	5	5	Now He who has prepared us for this same thing is God, who also gave to us the down payment of the Spirit.
B047C005V006	47	5	6	Therefore always being confident, and knowing that while we are in the body, we are away from home from the Lord
B047C005V007	47	5	7	(for we walk by faith, not by sight),
B047C005V008	47	5	8	but we are confident and prefer rather to be away from home from the body, and to be at home with the Lord.
B047C005V009	47	5	9	Therefore also we have as our ambition, whether being at home, or being away from home, to be well pleasing to Him.
B047C005V010	47	5	10	For we must all appear before the judgment seat of Christ, that each one may receive the things done in the body, in accordance with the things which he did, whether good or bad.
B047C005V011	47	5	11	Knowing, therefore, the fear of the Lord, we persuade men; but we have been made known to God. And I also hope to have been made known in your consciences.
B047C005V012	47	5	12	For we do not commend ourselves again to you, but give to you an opportunity of boasting on our behalf, so that you may have [an answer] for those who boast in appearance and not in heart.
B047C005V013	47	5	13	For if we were beside ourselves, it [was] for God; or if we are of sound mind, [it is] for you.
B047C005V014	47	5	14	For the love of Christ compels us, having concluded this: that if One died for all, then all died;
B047C005V015	47	5	15	and He died for all, so that they who live should live no longer for themselves, but for the [One] who died for them and rose again.
B047C005V016	47	5	16	Therefore, from now on, we regard no one according to the flesh. Even though we have known Christ according to the flesh, yet now we know [Him thus] no longer.
B047C005V017	47	5	17	Therefore, if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation; the old things passed away; behold, all things have become new.
B047C005V018	47	5	18	And all things are of God, who reconciled us to Himself through Jesus Christ, and who gave to us the ministry of this reconciliation,
B047C005V019	47	5	19	that is, that God was in Christ reconciling the world to Himself, not reckoning their transgressions to them, and committing to us the word of this reconciliation.
B047C005V020	47	5	20	Now then, we serve as ambassadors for Christ, as though God were appealing through us: we implore [you] on Christ's behalf, be reconciled to God.
B047C005V021	47	5	21	For He made Him who knew no sin to be sin for us, so that we might become the righteousness of God in Him.
B047C006V001	47	6	1	And working together [with Him,] we also urge that you not receive the grace of God in vain.
B047C006V002	47	6	2	For He says: "In an acceptable time I have heard you, and in the day of salvation I have helped you."Behold, now is the accepted time; behold, now is the day of salvation.
B047C006V003	47	6	3	We give no occasion for offense in anything, lest the ministry be blamed,
B047C006V004	47	6	4	but in everything commending ourselves as ministers of God: in much endurance, in tribulations, in hardships, in distresses,
B047C006V005	47	6	5	in stripes, in imprisonments, in disturbances, in labors, in sleepless nights, in fastings;
B047C006V006	47	6	6	in purity, in knowledge, in longsuffering, in kindness, in the Holy Spirit, in sincere love,
B047C006V007	47	6	7	through the word of truth, through the power of God, through the weapons of righteousness on the right hand and on the left hand,
B047C006V008	47	6	8	by honor and dishonor, by ill repute and good repute; as deceivers, and yet true;
B047C006V009	47	6	9	as being unknown, and yet well known; as dying, and behold, we live; as being disciplined, and not being put to death;
B047C006V010	47	6	10	as sorrowful, yet always rejoicing; as poor, yet making many rich; as having nothing, and yet possessing all things.
B047C006V011	47	6	11	O Corinthians! We have spoken openly to you, our heart has been opened wide.
B047C006V012	47	6	12	You are not restricted by us, but you are restricted by your own affections.
B047C006V013	47	6	13	Now in return for the same-I speak as to children-you also be opened wide.
B047C006V014	47	6	14	Do not become unequally yoked with unbelievers; for what participation is there for righteousness with lawlessness? And what communion is there for light with darkness?
B047C006V015	47	6	15	And what agreement is there for Christ with Belial? Or what part is there for a believer with an infidel?
B047C006V016	47	6	16	And what union is there for the temple of God with idols? For you are the temple of the living God, just as God has said: "I will dwell in them and walk among them, and I will be their God, and they shall be My people."
B047C006V017	47	6	17	Therefore "Come out from the midst of them and be separated,"says the Lord. "Do not touch what is unclean, and I will receive you."
B047C006V018	47	6	18	"I will be a Father to you, and you will be My sons and daughters, says the LORD Almighty."
B047C007V001	47	7	1	Therefore, having these promises, beloved, let us cleanse ourselves from all filthiness of the flesh and spirit, perfecting holiness in the fear of God.
B047C007V002	47	7	2	Receive us [in your hearts]. We have wronged no one, we have corrupted no one, we have defrauded no one.
B047C007V003	47	7	3	I do not speak to condemn you; for I have said before that you are in our hearts, so that we die together and we live together.
B047C007V004	47	7	4	Great is my confidence toward you, great is my boasting concerning you. I have been filled with comfort. I am exceedingly joyful in all our tribulation.
B047C007V005	47	7	5	For indeed, when we came to Macedonia, our flesh had no rest, but we were afflicted on every side; outside [were] fightings, inside [were] fears.
B047C007V006	47	7	6	Nevertheless God, who comforts the downcast, comforted us by the coming of Titus,
B047C007V007	47	7	7	and not only by his coming, but also by the consolation with which he was comforted over you, as he reported to us your earnest longing, your mourning, your zeal for me, so that I rejoiced even more.
B047C007V008	47	7	8	Because even if I made you sorry in the letter, I do not regret it, even if I did regret it. For I perceive that the same letter made you sorry, though only for a season.
B047C007V009	47	7	9	Now I rejoice, not because you were made sorry, but because your sorrow led to repentance; for you were made sorry in a godly manner, that you might suffer loss from us in nothing.
B047C007V010	47	7	10	For godly sorrow produces repentance leading to salvation, without regret; but worldly sorrow produces death.
B047C007V011	47	7	11	For behold this very thing, that you sorrowed in a godly manner, how much diligence it produced in you, even an eagerness to defend, even indignation, even fear, even longing, even zeal, even vengeance! In all things you demonstrated yourselves to be pure in this matter.
B047C007V012	47	7	12	Therefore, although I wrote to you, it was not for the sake of him who did the wrong, nor for the sake of him who was wronged, but so that your diligence on our behalf might be made known to you before God.
B047C007V013	47	7	13	Because of this we have been comforted. And in your comfort we rejoiced exceedingly more over the joy of Titus, because his spirit has been refreshed by you all.
B047C007V014	47	7	14	Because if in anything I have boasted to him concerning you, I was not put to shame, but as we spoke all things to you in truth, thus also our boasting to Titus became truth.
B047C007V015	47	7	15	And his affections are far greater toward you as he remembers the obedience of you all, how with fear and trembling you received him.
B047C007V016	47	7	16	[Therefore] I rejoice that in everything I am confident in you.
B047C008V001	47	8	1	Now we make known to you brothers, the grace of God which has been given to the churches of Macedonia,
B047C008V002	47	8	2	how that in a great trial of affliction the abundance of their joy and their deep poverty abounded in the riches of their generosity.
B047C008V003	47	8	3	For I bear witness that according to their ability, and beyond their ability, they were freely willing,
B047C008V004	47	8	4	with much appeal, begging us [for ]the grace and the fellowship of the ministry to the saints-
B047C008V005	47	8	5	and not as we hoped, but they first gave their own selves to the Lord, and then to us by the will of God,
B047C008V006	47	8	6	so that we urged Titus, that just as he had begun before, thus he would also finish this grace also in you.
B047C008V007	47	8	7	But as you abound in everything-in faith, in word, in knowledge, in all diligence, and in your love for us-see that you abound in this grace also.
B047C008V008	47	8	8	I speak not by a command, but I am testing the genuineness of your love by means of the diligence of others.
B047C008V009	47	8	9	For you know the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ, that though He was rich, yet on account of you He became poor, that you through His poverty might become rich.
B047C008V010	47	8	10	And I give [my] opinion in this: For this is profitable for you, who not only previously began doing [this], but also desired to, since last year.
B047C008V011	47	8	11	And now also complete doing [it]; that as indeed there[ was ]the readiness to desire [it], thus also there[ may be] the completion from what you have.
B047C008V012	47	8	12	For if there is first a readiness, it is acceptable according to what one has, and not according to what he does not have.
B047C008V013	47	8	13	For I do not [mean] that others should be relieved and you burdened;
B047C008V014	47	8	14	but by way of equality, that now at the present time your abundance [may supply] their need, that their abundance also may supply your need, in order that there may be equality.
B047C008V015	47	8	15	As it is written, "He [who ga]there[d] much did not have too much, and he [who gathered] little had no lack."
B047C008V016	47	8	16	But thanks be to God who puts the same earnest care for you in the heart of Titus.
B047C008V017	47	8	17	Because he accepted my appeal, but being more diligent, he came to you of his own accord.
B047C008V018	47	8	18	And we sent together with him the brother whose praise is in the gospel throughout all the churches,
B047C008V019	47	8	19	and not only that, but who was also chosen by the churches as our traveling companion with this gift, which is ministered by us to the glory of the Lord Himself and [to show] our readiness-
B047C008V020	47	8	20	avoiding this, lest anyone should blame us in this abundance which is ministered by us;
B047C008V021	47	8	21	having regard for honorable things, not only before the Lord, but also before men.
B047C008V022	47	8	22	And we sent together with them our brother whom we often approved in many things, being diligent, but now [being ]much more diligent, by [his] great confidence in you.
B047C008V023	47	8	23	If [anyone inquires ]about Titus, [he is] my partner and fellow worker concerning you; or if our brothers [are inquired about], [they are] messengers of the churches, the glory of Christ.
B047C008V024	47	8	24	Therefore show to them the proof of your love, and of our boasting concerning you, before the churches.
B047C009V001	47	9	1	Now concerning the ministering to the saints, it is unnecessary for me to write to you;
B047C009V002	47	9	2	for I know your readiness, about which I boast concerning you to the Macedonians, that Achaia has been prepared since last year, and your zeal has provoked the majority.
B047C009V003	47	9	3	And I have sent the brothers, lest our boasting about you lose its justification in this matter, that just as I said, you may be prepared,
B047C009V004	47	9	4	lest perhaps if [some] Macedonians come with me and find you unprepared, we (not to mention you!) should be ashamed of this confident boasting.
B047C009V005	47	9	5	Therefore I thought it necessary to urge the brothers, that they should go before [me] to you, and should arrange in advance your generous gift, which you had previously promised, [that] this would be ready, thus as a blessing and not as grudgingly given.
B047C009V006	47	9	6	But this I say: he who sows sparingly will also reap sparingly, and he who sows bountifully will also reap bountifully.
B047C009V007	47	9	7	Let each [one give] just as he decides in his heart, not grudgingly or of necessity; for God loves a cheerful giver.
B047C009V008	47	9	8	And God is able to make all grace abound toward you, that in everything always having all sufficiency, you may abound for every good work,
B047C009V009	47	9	9	just as it is written: "He has dispersed, He has given to the poor; His righteousness endures forever."
B047C009V010	47	9	10	Now may He who supplies seed to the sower, and bread for food, supply and multiply the seed you have sown and increase the fruits of your righteousness;
B047C009V011	47	9	11	in everything being made rich to all generosity, which produces thanksgiving through us to God.
B047C009V012	47	9	12	Because the ministry of this service not only is supplying the needs of the saints, but also is abounding through many thanksgivings to God,
B047C009V013	47	9	13	while through the approved character of this ministry, they glorify God for the obedience of your confession to the gospel of Christ, and [for the] generosity of your sharing toward them and toward all,
B047C009V014	47	9	14	and by their prayer for you, who long for you because of the surpassing grace of God in you.
B047C009V015	47	9	15	Thanks be to God for His indescribable gift!
B047C010V001	47	10	1	Now I, Paul, myself appeal to you by the meekness and gentleness of Christ, I who face to face [am] lowly among you, but when I am away am bold toward you.
B047C010V002	47	10	2	But I beseech [you] that when I am present I may not be bold with the confidence with which I plan to be bold toward some, who consider us as walking according to the flesh.
B047C010V003	47	10	3	For though we walk in the flesh, we do not war according to the flesh.
B047C010V004	47	10	4	For the weapons of our warfare are not carnal, but mighty by God to the pulling down of strongholds,
B047C010V005	47	10	5	casting down imaginations and every high thing that exalts itself against the knowledge of God, and bringing into captivity every thought to the obedience of Christ,
B047C010V006	47	10	6	and being ready to avenge every act of disobedience, whenever your obedience is fulfilled.
B047C010V007	47	10	7	Do you look at things as they appear? If anyone has persuaded himself that he is Christ's, let him again consider this in himself, that just as he is Christ's, even so we are Christ's.
B047C010V008	47	10	8	For even if I should boast somewhat more concerning our authority, which the Lord gave us for edification and not for your destruction, I will not be ashamed,
B047C010V009	47	10	9	lest I seem to terrify you by my letters.
B047C010V010	47	10	10	"For his letters,"they say, "are severe and boisterous, but his bodily presence [is] feeble, and his speech amounts to nothing."
B047C010V011	47	10	11	Let such a person consider this, that of what sort we are in word by letters when we are absent, of such a kind [we will] also [be] in deed when we are present.
B047C010V012	47	10	12	For we dare not to class ourselves or to compare ourselves with those who commend themselves, but they, measuring themselves by themselves, and comparing themselves among themselves, do not understand.
B047C010V013	47	10	13	But we will not boast beyond limits, but according to the measure of the sphere [of influence ]which God assigned us as a measure, to reach even as far as you.
B047C010V014	47	10	14	For we are not overextending ourselves, as though our authority did not reach to you, for it was to you that we came with the gospel of Christ;
B047C010V015	47	10	15	not boasting beyond the limits in the labors of others, but having hope, that as your faith is increased, we shall be greatly enlarged by you according to our sphere [of influence],
B047C010V016	47	10	16	to preach the gospel to the [regions] beyond you, [and] not to boast in the things done in the sphere [of influence] of others.
B047C010V017	47	10	17	But "he who boasts, let him boast in the LORD."
B047C010V018	47	10	18	For not he who commends himself is approved, but he[ ]whom the Lord commends.
B047C011V001	47	11	1	Oh, that you would bear with me a little in my foolishness; but indeed you do bear with me.
B047C011V002	47	11	2	For I am jealous over you with godly jealousy, for I have betrothed you to one husband, to present you as a pure virgin to Christ.
B047C011V003	47	11	3	But I fear, lest perhaps as the serpent deceived Eve by his craftiness, so your minds may be corrupted from the simplicity that is in Christ.
B047C011V004	47	11	4	For if he who comes [to you ]preaches another Jesus whom we did not preach, or if you receive a different spirit which you have not received, or a different gospel which you did not accept, you may well put up with him!
B047C011V005	47	11	5	For I consider [myself] [in] nothing to have been inferior to the most super apostles.
B047C011V006	47	11	6	But even if I [am] unskilled in speech, yet [I am] not [inferior ]in knowledge, but in every [way] I was made known to you in all things.
B047C011V007	47	11	7	Or did I commit sin in humbling myself in order that you might be exalted, because I preached the gospel of God to you free of charge?
B047C011V008	47	11	8	I robbed other churches, taking wages [from them] to minister to you,
B047C011V009	47	11	9	and when I was present with you, and in need, I did not burden anyone; for the brothers who came from Macedonia supplied my need. And in everything I kept myself from being a burden to you, and so I will keep myself.
B047C011V010	47	11	10	As the truth of Christ is in me, that this boasting will not be silenced in me in the regions of Achaia.
B047C011V011	47	11	11	Why? Because I do not love you? God knows!
B047C011V012	47	11	12	But what I am doing, I will also continue to do, that I may cut off the opportunity of those who desire an opportunity, that in what they boast they may be found just as we [are].
B047C011V013	47	11	13	For such are false apostles, deceitful workers, transforming themselves into apostles of Christ.
B047C011V014	47	11	14	And no wonder! For Satan himself transforms himself into an angel of light.
B047C011V015	47	11	15	Therefore it is no great thing if his ministers also transform themselves into ministers of righteousness, whose end will be according to their works.
B047C011V016	47	11	16	Again I say, let no one think me a fool. Otherwise, at least receive me as a fool, that I also may boast a little.
B047C011V017	47	11	17	What I speak, I speak not according to the Lord, but as it were, foolishly, in this confidence of boasting.
B047C011V018	47	11	18	Since many are boasting according to the flesh, I also will boast.
B047C011V019	47	11	19	For you bear with fools gladly, being wise [yourselves]!
B047C011V020	47	11	20	For you put up with it if someone enslaves you, if someone devours you, if someone takes from you, if someone exalts himself, if someone strikes you in the face.
B047C011V021	47	11	21	To our shame, I say that we were too weak [for that]! But in whatever anyone is bold (I speak foolishly) I am bold also.
B047C011V022	47	11	22	Are they Hebrews? So am I. Are they Israelites? So am I. Are they the seed of Abraham? So am I.
B047C011V023	47	11	23	Are they ministers of Christ? (I speak as a fool) I [am] even more: in labors far more, in beatings immeasurably, in imprisonments far more, in deaths often.
B047C011V024	47	11	24	By [the] Jews five times I received forty stripes minus one.
B047C011V025	47	11	25	Three times I was beaten with rods; once I was stoned; three times I was shipwrecked; a night and a day I have spent in the depth [of the sea].
B047C011V026	47	11	26	In journeys often, in dangers of rivers, in dangers of robbers, in dangers from my own race, in dangers from the Gentiles, in dangers in the city, in dangers in the wilderness, in dangers in the sea, in dangers among false brothers;
B047C011V027	47	11	27	in labor and hardship, in sleepless nights often, in hunger and thirst, in fastings often, in cold and nakedness-
B047C011V028	47	11	28	apart from what I leave unmentioned, what comes against me daily: the anxiety for all the churches.
B047C011V029	47	11	29	Who is weak, and I am not weak? Who is caused to stumble, and I do not burn [with indignation]?
B047C011V030	47	11	30	If I must boast, I will boast about the things concerning my weakness.
B047C011V031	47	11	31	The God and Father of the Lord Jesus Christ, who is blessed forever, knows that I am not lying.
B047C011V032	47	11	32	In Damascus the governor, under Aretas the king, was guarding the city of the Damascenes with a garrison, desiring to arrest me;
B047C011V033	47	11	33	but I was let down in a basket through a window in the wall, and escaped from his hands.
B047C012V001	47	12	1	It is indeed not profitable for me to boast. I will come to visions and revelations of the Lord:
B047C012V002	47	12	2	I know a man in Christ who fourteen years ago-whether in the body I do not know, or whether out of the body I do not know, God knows-such a one was caught up to the third heaven.
B047C012V003	47	12	3	And I know such a man-whether in the body or out of the body I do not know, God knows-
B047C012V004	47	12	4	that he was caught up into Paradise and heard unspeakable words, which it is not permitted for a man to utter.
B047C012V005	47	12	5	Concerning such a one I will boast, but concerning myself I will not boast, except in my weaknesses.
B047C012V006	47	12	6	For if I should desire to boast, I will not be foolish; for I will speak [the] truth. But I spare [you], lest anyone consider me to be beyond what he sees me [to be] or hears something from me.
B047C012V007	47	12	7	And lest I exalt myself above measure by the excellence of the revelations, a thorn in the flesh was given to me, an angel of Satan, that it might beat me, lest I exalt myself above measure.
B047C012V008	47	12	8	Concerning this I pleaded with the Lord three times that it might depart from me.
B047C012V009	47	12	9	And He said to me, "My grace is sufficient for you, for My power is perfected in weakness."Therefore most gladly I will rather boast in my weaknesses, in order that the power of Christ may rest upon me.
B047C012V010	47	12	10	Therefore I delight in weaknesses, in insults, in calamities, in persecutions, in distresses, for Christ's sake. For whenever I am weak, then I am strong.
B047C012V011	47	12	11	I have become a fool in boasting; you have compelled me! For I ought to have been commended by you; for in nothing have I been inferior to the super apostles, though I am nothing.
B047C012V012	47	12	12	Truly the signs of an apostle were worked among you with all perseverance, in signs and wonders and miracles.
B047C012V013	47	12	13	For what is it in which you were inferior to other churches, except that I myself did not burden you? Forgive me this wrong!
B047C012V014	47	12	14	Now for the third time I am ready to come to you, and I will not burden you. For I do not seek what is yours, but you. For the children ought not to store up for the parents, but the parents for the children.
B047C012V015	47	12	15	And I gladly will spend and be expended for your souls; although the more abundantly I love you, the less I am loved.
B047C012V016	47	12	16	But be that as it may, I did not burden you. Nevertheless, being crafty, I took you with guile!
B047C012V017	47	12	17	Did I take advantage of you by any of those whom I sent to you?
B047C012V018	47	12	18	I urged Titus, and I sent with him the brother. Did Titus take advantage of you? Did [we] not [walk] in the same Spirit? Did we not walk in the same steps?
B047C012V019	47	12	19	Again, do you think that we are defending ourselves to you? We speak before God in Christ. But we do all things, beloved, for your edification.
B047C012V020	47	12	20	For I am afraid, lest perhaps when I come, I will not find you as I desire, and that I will be found by you as you do not desire; lest perhaps there[ be] contentions, jealousies, outbursts of wrath, disputes, slanders, gossipings, pride, disorders;
B047C012V021	47	12	21	lest, when I come again, my God will humble me before you, and I will mourn for many who have previously sinned and have not repented for the impurity and fornication and lewdness which they practiced.
B047C013V001	47	13	1	This [will be] the third time I am coming to you. "By the mouth of two or three witnesses every word shall be established."
B047C013V002	47	13	2	I have previously said, and I say beforehand, as being present the second [time], and now being absent I write to those who have sinned before, and to all the rest, that if I come again I will not spare [you,]
B047C013V003	47	13	3	since you are seeking proof of Christ speaking in me, who is not weak toward you, but strong in you.
B047C013V004	47	13	4	For although He was crucified in weakness, yet He lives by the power of God. For we are weak in Him, yet we shall live with Him by the power of God toward you.
B047C013V005	47	13	5	Scrutinize yourselves as to whether you are in the faith; prove your own selves. Or do you not know yourselves, that Jesus Christ is in you, unless indeed you are reprobates?
B047C013V006	47	13	6	But I trust that you will know that we are not reprobates.
B047C013V007	47	13	7	Now I pray to God that you do no evil, not that we may appear approved, but that you may do what is honorable, though we may be as reprobates.
B047C013V008	47	13	8	For we can do nothing against the truth, but on behalf of the truth.
B047C013V009	47	13	9	For we rejoice whenever we are weak, but you are strong. And this also we pray, that you may be made complete.
B047C013V010	47	13	10	Because of this I write these things being absent, in order that when I am present I may not deal sharply with you, according to the authority which the Lord gave me for edification and not for destruction.
B047C013V011	47	13	11	Finally brothers, farewell. Restore [yourselves,] comfort [yourselves], be in agreement, be at peace; and the God of love and peace will be with you.
B047C013V012	47	13	12	Greet one another with a holy kiss.
B047C013V013	47	13	13	All the saints greet you.
B047C013V014	47	13	14	The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ, and the love of God, and the fellowship of the Holy Spirit be with you all. Amen.
B048C001V001	48	1	1	Paul, an apostle (not from men nor through man, but through Jesus Christ and God the Father who raised Him from the dead),
B048C001V002	48	1	2	and all the brothers with me, to the churches of Galatia:
B048C001V003	48	1	3	Grace to you and peace from God the Father and our Lord Jesus Christ,
B048C001V004	48	1	4	who gave Himself for our sins, so that He might deliver us from this present evil age, according to the will of our God and Father,
B048C001V005	48	1	5	to whom [be] glory forever and ever. Amen.
B048C001V006	48	1	6	I marvel that you are turning so quickly from Him who called you in the grace of Christ, to a different gospel,
B048C001V007	48	1	7	which is not another; except there are certain people who trouble you and wish to pervert the gospel of Christ.
B048C001V008	48	1	8	But even if we, or an angel from heaven, should preach a gospel to you other than what we preached to you, let him be accursed.
B048C001V009	48	1	9	As we have said before, and I say again just now, if anyone preaches a gospel to you other than what you received, let him be accursed.
B048C001V010	48	1	10	For do I now persuade men, or God? Or do I seek to please men? For if I still pleased men, I would not be a bondservant of Christ.
B048C001V011	48	1	11	But I make known to you, brothers, the gospel preached by me is not according to man.
B048C001V012	48	1	12	For I neither received it from man, nor was I taught it, but through the revelation of Jesus Christ.
B048C001V013	48	1	13	For you have heard of my former conduct at one time in Judaism, that beyond measure I used to persecute the church of God, and I was devastating it.
B048C001V014	48	1	14	And I was advancing in Judaism above many my own age, being far more zealous for the traditions of my forefathers.
B048C001V015	48	1	15	But when it pleased God, who separated me from my mother's womb and called me through His grace,
B048C001V016	48	1	16	to reveal His Son in me, so that I might preach Him among the Gentiles, I did not immediately consult with flesh and blood,
B048C001V017	48	1	17	neither did I go up to Jerusalem to those who were apostles before me; but I went to Arabia, and returned once more to Damascus.
B048C001V018	48	1	18	Then after three years I went up to Jerusalem to visit Peter, and I stayed with him fifteen days.
B048C001V019	48	1	19	But I saw none of the other apostles except James, the Lord's brother.
B048C001V020	48	1	20	Now what I write to you, behold, before God, I do not lie.
B048C001V021	48	1	21	Then I went into the regions of Syria and Cilicia.
B048C001V022	48	1	22	And I was unknown by face to the churches of Judea which are in Christ.
B048C001V023	48	1	23	But they heard only, "He who persecuted us in times past now preaches the faith which at one time he was devastating."
B048C001V024	48	1	24	And they glorified God in me.
B048C002V001	48	2	1	Then after fourteen years I went up again to Jerusalem with Barnabas, also taking Titus along.
B048C002V002	48	2	2	And I went up by revelation, and I set before them that gospel which I preach among the Gentiles, but privately to those with influence, lest somehow I might run, or had run, in vain.
B048C002V003	48	2	3	But not even Titus who was with me, although he was a Greek, was compelled to be circumcised;
B048C002V004	48	2	4	and that was because of false brothers secretly brought in (who slipped in to spy out our freedom which we have in Christ Jesus, so that they might reduce us to slavery),
B048C002V005	48	2	5	to whom not even for an hour did we yield in subjection, that the truth of the gospel might remain with you.
B048C002V006	48	2	6	But from those who seemed to be something-whatever they were, it makes no difference to me; God shows partiality to no man-so to me, those with influence contributed nothing,
B048C002V007	48	2	7	but on the contrary, when they saw that I had been entrusted [with] the gospel for the uncircumcised, just as Peter [was with the gospel ]for the circumcised,
B048C002V008	48	2	8	(for He who worked with Peter in [the] apostleship to the circumcised, worked also with me in [that for] the Gentiles),
B048C002V009	48	2	9	and when James, Cephas, and John, who seemed to be pillars, perceived the grace which was given to me, they gave me and Barnabas the right hand of fellowship, that we [should go] to the Gentiles and they to the circumcised;
B048C002V010	48	2	10	only they desired that we should remember the poor, which indeed I made every effort to do this very thing.
B048C002V011	48	2	11	But when Peter came to Antioch, I opposed him to his face, because he was to be blamed.
B048C002V012	48	2	12	For before certain [men] came from James, he would eat together with the Gentiles; but when they came, he began to draw back and began to separate himself, fearing those of the circumcision party.
B048C002V013	48	2	13	And the rest of the Jews joined him in hypocrisy, so that even Barnabas was carried away with their hypocrisy.
B048C002V014	48	2	14	But when I saw that they did not act rightly with respect to the truth of the gospel, I said to Peter before them all, "If you, being a Jew, live in Gentile fashion and not in Jewish fashion, why do you compel the Gentiles to live as Jews?
B048C002V015	48	2	15	We [who are] Jews by nature, and not sinners of the Gentiles,
B048C002V016	48	2	16	knowing that a man is not justified by the works of the law but by [the ]faith of Jesus Christ, even we have believed in Christ Jesus, so that we might be justified by [the] faith of Christ, and not by [the] works of the law; because no flesh shall be justified by [the] works of the law.
B048C002V017	48	2	17	But if by seeking to be justified in Christ, we ourselves also were found sinners, then is Christ a minister of sin? By no means!
B048C002V018	48	2	18	For if I build again the[ ]things which I destroyed, I make myself a transgressor.
B048C002V019	48	2	19	For I through the law died to the law, that I might live to God.
B048C002V020	48	2	20	I have been crucified with Christ; it is no longer I who live, but Christ lives in me; and the [life] which I now live in the flesh I live by faith in the Son of God, who loved me, and gave Himself for me.
B048C002V021	48	2	21	I do not annul the grace of God; for if righteousness comes through the law, then Christ died for nothing."
B048C003V001	48	3	1	O foolish Galatians! Who has bewitched you, that you should not obey the truth, before whose eyes Jesus Christ was portrayed publicly among you as crucified?
B048C003V002	48	3	2	This only do I wish to learn from you: Did you receive the Spirit by the works of the law, or by the hearing of faith?
B048C003V003	48	3	3	Are you so foolish? Having begun in the Spirit, will you now be made perfect in the flesh?
B048C003V004	48	3	4	Have you suffered so many things in vain-If indeed [they] really [were] in vain?
B048C003V005	48	3	5	Therefore He who supplies the Spirit to you and works miracles among you, does He do it by the works of the law, or by the hearing of faith?-
B048C003V006	48	3	6	Just as Abraham "believed God, and it was credited to him as righteousness."
B048C003V007	48	3	7	Know therefore that those who are of faith, these are sons of Abraham.
B048C003V008	48	3	8	And the Scripture, foreseeing that God would justify the Gentiles by faith, preached the gospel beforehand to Abraham, [saying] that, "In you all the nations shall be blessed."
B048C003V009	48	3	9	Therefore those who are of faith are blessed with believing Abraham.
B048C003V010	48	3	10	For as many as are of the works of the law are under the curse; for it is written, "Cursed is everyone who does not continue in all the things which are written in the book of the law, to do them."
B048C003V011	48	3	11	But that no one is justified by the law before God is evident, for "The just shall live by faith."
B048C003V012	48	3	12	But the law is not of faith, but "the man who does them shall live by them."
B048C003V013	48	3	13	Christ has redeemed us from the curse of the law, having become a curse for us, for it is written, "Cursed is everyone who hangs on a tree,"
B048C003V014	48	3	14	so that the blessing of Abraham might come to the Gentiles in Christ Jesus, that we might receive the promise of the Spirit through faith.
B048C003V015	48	3	15	Brothers, I speak in human fashion: A covenant is of a man, yet having been confirmed, no one annuls or adds to it.
B048C003V016	48	3	16	Now to Abraham and his Seed were the promises spoken. He does not say, "And to seeds,"as of many, but as of one, "And to your Seed,"who is Christ.
B048C003V017	48	3	17	And this I say, that the law, which was four hundred and thirty years later, does not annul the covenant previously confirmed to Christ by God, so that it make the promise of no effect.
B048C003V018	48	3	18	For if the inheritance [comes] by the law, it is no longer of promise; but God has given it to Abraham by promise.
B048C003V019	48	3	19	Why then the law? It was added on account of transgressions, until the Seed should come to whom it had been promised; and it was commanded through angels by the hand of a mediator.
B048C003V020	48	3	20	Now the mediator is not for one person, but God is one.
B048C003V021	48	3	21	Therefore, [is] the law against the promises of God? By no means! For if a law had been given which was able to give life, truly righteousness would have been by the law.
B048C003V022	48	3	22	But the Scripture has confined all under sin, so that the promise by faith in Jesus Christ might be given to those who believe.
B048C003V023	48	3	23	But before faith came, we were kept in custody under the law, having been hemmed in for the faith which was to be revealed.
B048C003V024	48	3	24	Therefore the law has become our custodian, [leading us] to Christ, so that we might be justified by faith.
B048C003V025	48	3	25	But after faith has come, we are no longer under a custodian.
B048C003V026	48	3	26	For you are all sons of God through faith in Christ Jesus.
B048C003V027	48	3	27	For as many of you as were baptized into Christ have put on Christ.
B048C003V028	48	3	28	There is neither Jew nor Greek, neither slave nor free, there is neither male nor female; for you are all one in Christ Jesus.
B048C003V029	48	3	29	And if you are Christ's, then you are Abraham's seed, and heirs according to the promise.
B048C004V001	48	4	1	Now I say, for as much time as the heir is a minor, he does not differ at all from a slave, though he is master of all,
B048C004V002	48	4	2	but is under guardians and stewards until the time appointed by the father.
B048C004V003	48	4	3	Even so we, when we were minors, were enslaved by the elements of the world.
B048C004V004	48	4	4	But when the fullness of the time had come, God sent forth His Son, born of a woman, born under the law,
B048C004V005	48	4	5	so that He might redeem those under the law, so that we might receive the adoption.
B048C004V006	48	4	6	And because you are sons, God has sent forth the Spirit of His Son into your hearts, crying out, "Abba, Father!"
B048C004V007	48	4	7	Therefore you are no longer a slave but a son, and if a son, also an heir of God through Christ.
B048C004V008	48	4	8	But at one time indeed, when you did not know God, you were slaves to those which by nature were not gods.
B048C004V009	48	4	9	But now, having known God, or rather, having been known by God, how is it that you turn again to the weak and beggarly elements, to which once again you wish to be slaves?
B048C004V010	48	4	10	You observe days and months and seasons and years.
B048C004V011	48	4	11	I am afraid for you, lest somehow I have worked hard for you in vain.
B048C004V012	48	4	12	Brothers, I beseech you, become as I am, because I also [am] as you [are]. You have not wronged me at all.
B048C004V013	48	4	13	You know that because of weakness in the flesh I preached the gospel to you the former [time.]
B048C004V014	48	4	14	And my trial which was in my flesh you did not despise nor disdain, but as an angel of God you received me, even as Christ Jesus.
B048C004V015	48	4	15	What then was your blessing? For I bear you witness that, if possible, you would have torn out your own eyes and given them to me!
B048C004V016	48	4	16	Have I therefore become your enemy by speaking the truth to you?
B048C004V017	48	4	17	They are zealous about you in the wrong way; but they wish to shut you out, so that you will be zealous about them.
B048C004V018	48	4	18	But it is good to be zealous in a good thing always, and not only when I am present with you.
B048C004V019	48	4	19	My little children, for whom I labor in birth again until Christ is formed in you!
B048C004V020	48	4	20	And I wanted to be present with you just now and to change my tone; because I am uncertain about you.
B048C004V021	48	4	21	Tell me, you who wish to be under the law, do you not hear the law?
B048C004V022	48	4	22	For it is written that Abraham had two sons: the one by the servant girl, the other by a freewoman.
B048C004V023	48	4	23	But he who was of the servant girl was born according to the flesh, and he of the freewoman through the promise,
B048C004V024	48	4	24	which things are symbolic. For these are two covenants: one in fact from Mount Sinai, bearing children into slavery, which is Hagar-
B048C004V025	48	4	25	for Hagar is Mount Sinai in Arabia, and corresponds to the present Jerusalem, and is in slavery with her children-
B048C004V026	48	4	26	but the Jerusalem above is free, which is the mother of us all.
B048C004V027	48	4	27	For it is written: "Rejoice, O barren, who does not give birth; break forth and shout, who does not have birth pangs; because the children of the desolate are many more than those of her who has a husband."
B048C004V028	48	4	28	But we, brothers, like Isaac, are children of promise.
B048C004V029	48	4	29	But just as then the [one] who was born according to the flesh persecuted the [one born] according to the Spirit, so also it is now.
B048C004V030	48	4	30	But what does the Scripture say? "Cast out the servant girl and her son, for the son of the servant girl shall by no means inherit with the son of the freewoman."
B048C004V031	48	4	31	So then, brothers, we are not children of the servant girl, but of the free[woman].
B048C005V001	48	5	1	Stand fast therefore in the freedom in which Christ has made us free, and do not be loaded down again with a yoke of bondage.
B048C005V002	48	5	2	Indeed I, Paul, say to you that if you become circumcised, Christ will profit you nothing.
B048C005V003	48	5	3	And I testify again to every man who becomes circumcised that he is a obligated to keep the whole law.
B048C005V004	48	5	4	You have become estranged from Christ, you who are justified by law; you have fallen from grace.
B048C005V005	48	5	5	For we by the Spirit eagerly await [for] the hope of righteousness by faith.
B048C005V006	48	5	6	For in Christ Jesus neither circumcision nor uncircumcision means anything, but faith working through love.
B048C005V007	48	5	7	You were running well; who hindered you from obeying the truth?
B048C005V008	48	5	8	This persuasion does not come from Him who calls you.
B048C005V009	48	5	9	A little leaven leavens the whole lump.
B048C005V010	48	5	10	I have confidence in you, in the Lord, that you will be intent on nothing else; but he who troubles you will bear his judgment, whoever he may be.
B048C005V011	48	5	11	And I, brothers, if I still preach circumcision, why am I still persecuted? In that case the offense of the cross has been done away with.
B048C005V012	48	5	12	Oh that those who disturb you would even castrate themselves!
B048C005V013	48	5	13	For you, brothers were called to freedom; only do not use freedom for an opportunity for the flesh, but through love serve one another.
B048C005V014	48	5	14	For all the law is fulfilled in one word, in [this]: "You shall love your neighbor as yourself."
B048C005V015	48	5	15	But if you bite and devour one another, watch out that you are not consumed by one another!
B048C005V016	48	5	16	I say then: Walk in the Spirit, and you shall by no means fulfill the lust of the flesh.
B048C005V017	48	5	17	For the flesh lusts against the Spirit, and the Spirit against the flesh; and these things oppose each other, so that you do not do the things that you wish.
B048C005V018	48	5	18	But if you are led by the Spirit, you are not under the law.
B048C005V019	48	5	19	Now the works of the flesh are manifest, which are: adultery, fornication, immorality, lewdness,
B048C005V020	48	5	20	idolatry, sorcery, hatred, contentions, jealousies, outbursts of wrath, selfish ambitions, dissensions, factions,
B048C005V021	48	5	21	envies, murders, drinking bouts, revelries, and the like; which I tell you beforehand, just as I also told you in time past, that those who practice such things will not inherit the kingdom of God.
B048C005V022	48	5	22	But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, longsuffering, kindness, goodness, faithfulness,
B048C005V023	48	5	23	gentleness, self-control-against such things there is no law.
B048C005V024	48	5	24	And those who are Christ's have crucified the flesh with its passions and lusts.
B048C005V025	48	5	25	If we live by the Spirit, let us also walk by the Spirit.
B048C005V026	48	5	26	Let us not become conceited, provoking one another, envying one another.
B048C006V001	48	6	1	Brothers, if a man is overtaken in any trespass, you who are spiritual restore such a person in a spirit of gentleness, looking out for yourself lest you also be tempted.
B048C006V002	48	6	2	Bear one another's burdens, and thus fulfill the law of Christ.
B048C006V003	48	6	3	For if anyone thinks that he is something, when he is nothing, he deceives himself.
B048C006V004	48	6	4	But let each [person] examine his own work, and then he will have boasting in himself alone, and not in the other.
B048C006V005	48	6	5	For each one shall bear his own load.
B048C006V006	48	6	6	Let him who is taught the word share in all good things with him who teaches.
B048C006V007	48	6	7	Do not be deceived, God is not mocked; for what a man sows, this also he will reap.
B048C006V008	48	6	8	For he who sows to his flesh, from his own flesh will reap corruption, but he who sows to the Spirit, from the Spirit will reap everlasting life.
B048C006V009	48	6	9	And while we do good, let us not lose heart, for in due season we shall reap if we do not become weary.
B048C006V010	48	6	10	So then, as we have opportunity, let us work what is good toward all, but especially toward those who are of the household of faith.
B048C006V011	48	6	11	See with what large letters I have written to you with my own hand!
B048C006V012	48	6	12	As many as wish to make a good showing in the flesh, these compel you to get circumcised, only so that they should not be persecuted for the cross of Christ.
B048C006V013	48	6	13	For not even those who are circumcised keep the law themselves, but they wish you to be circumcised that they may boast in your flesh.
B048C006V014	48	6	14	But God forbid that I should boast except in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, by whom the world has been crucified to me, and I to the world.
B048C006V015	48	6	15	For in Christ Jesus neither circumcision nor uncircumcision means anything, but a new creation.
B048C006V016	48	6	16	And as many as walk according to this rule, peace and mercy be upon them, and upon the Israel of God.
B048C006V017	48	6	17	Finally, let no one cause me trouble, for I bear in my body the marks of the Lord Jesus.
B048C006V018	48	6	18	Brothers, the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit. Amen.
B049C001V001	49	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God, to the saints who are at Ephesus, and faithful in Christ Jesus:
B049C001V002	49	1	2	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B049C001V003	49	1	3	Blessed [be] the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who has blessed us with every spiritual blessing in the heavenlies in Christ,
B049C001V004	49	1	4	just as He chose us in Him before the foundation of the world, that we should be holy and blameless before Him in love,
B049C001V005	49	1	5	having predestined us to adoption as sons by Jesus Christ to Himself, according to the good pleasure of His will,
B049C001V006	49	1	6	to the praise of the glory of His grace, by which He bestowed favor upon us in the Beloved.
B049C001V007	49	1	7	In Him we have redemption through His blood, the forgiveness of sins, according to the riches of His grace
B049C001V008	49	1	8	which He made to abound toward us in all wisdom and insight,
B049C001V009	49	1	9	having made known to us the mystery of His will, according to His good pleasure which He purposed in Himself,
B049C001V010	49	1	10	for an administration of the fullness of the times, [He might ]bring together all things in Christ, those in heaven and those on the earth-in Him.
B049C001V011	49	1	11	In whom also we have obtained an inheritance, being predestined according to the purpose of Him who works all things according to the counsel of His will,
B049C001V012	49	1	12	so that we should be to the praise of His glory, we who first trusted in Christ;
B049C001V013	49	1	13	in whom also you, when you heard the word of truth, the gospel of your salvation; in whom also, having believed, you were sealed with the Holy Spirit of promise,
B049C001V014	49	1	14	who is the guarantee of our inheritance until the redemption of the possession, to the praise of His glory.
B049C001V015	49	1	15	Because of this I also, after I heard of your faith in the Lord Jesus and your love for all the saints,
B049C001V016	49	1	16	do not cease to give thanks concerning you, making mention of you in my prayers:
B049C001V017	49	1	17	that the God of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father of glory, may give to you the spirit of wisdom and revelation in the knowledge of Him,
B049C001V018	49	1	18	the eyes of your heart having been enlightened; that you may know what is the hope of His calling, what are the riches of the glory of His inheritance in the saints,
B049C001V019	49	1	19	and what is the surpassing greatness of His power toward us who believe, according to the working of His mighty power
B049C001V020	49	1	20	which He worked in Christ, having raised Him from the dead, and seated [Him] at His right hand in the heavenlies,
B049C001V021	49	1	21	above every ruler and authority and power and dominion, and every name that is named, not only in this age but also in the coming [age].
B049C001V022	49	1	22	And He subjected all things under His feet, and gave Him to be head over all things to the church,
B049C001V023	49	1	23	which is His body, the fullness of Him filling all things in all.
B049C002V001	49	2	1	And you [He made alive,] being dead in transgressions and sins,
B049C002V002	49	2	2	in which you once walked according to the age of this world, according to the prince of the power of the air, the spirit which is now working in the sons of disobedience,
B049C002V003	49	2	3	among whom also we all once conducted ourselves in the lusts of our flesh, fulfilling the desires of the flesh and of the senses, and were by nature children of wrath, as also the rest.
B049C002V004	49	2	4	But God, being rich in mercy, because of His great love with which He loved us,
B049C002V005	49	2	5	even when we were dead in transgressions, made us alive together with Christ (by grace you have been saved),
B049C002V006	49	2	6	and raised us up together, and seated us together in the heavenlies in Christ Jesus,
B049C002V007	49	2	7	that in the coming ages He might show the surpassing riches of His grace in His kindness toward us in Christ Jesus.
B049C002V008	49	2	8	For by grace you are saved through faith, and that not of yourselves; [it is] the gift of God,
B049C002V009	49	2	9	not of works, lest anyone should boast.
B049C002V010	49	2	10	For we are His handiwork, created in Christ Jesus for good works, which God prepared beforehand that we should walk in them.
B049C002V011	49	2	11	Therefore remember that you, once Gentiles in the flesh-who are called Uncircumcision by what is called the Circumcision made by hands in the flesh-
B049C002V012	49	2	12	that at that time you were apart from Christ, being estranged from the commonwealth of Israel and strangers to the covenants of promise, not having hope and atheists in the world.
B049C002V013	49	2	13	But now in Christ Jesus, you who once were far away have come to be near by the blood of Christ.
B049C002V014	49	2	14	For He Himself is our peace, who has made both one, and who destroyed the dividing wall of separation,
B049C002V015	49	2	15	having abolished in His flesh the enmity, that is, the law of commandments contained in ordinances, that He might create in Himself one new man [from] the two, [thus] making peace,
B049C002V016	49	2	16	and that He might reconcile them both to God in one body through the cross, putting to death the enmity in Himself.
B049C002V017	49	2	17	And having come, He preached peace to you who were far away and to those near.
B049C002V018	49	2	18	Because through Him we both have access by one Spirit to the Father.
B049C002V019	49	2	19	So then, you are no longer strangers and aliens, but fellow citizens with the saints and members of the household of God,
B049C002V020	49	2	20	being built upon the foundation of the apostles and prophets, Jesus Christ Himself being the chief cornerstone,
B049C002V021	49	2	21	in whom the whole building, being joined together, grows into a holy temple in the Lord,
B049C002V022	49	2	22	in whom you also are being built together for a habitation of God in the Spirit.
B049C003V001	49	3	1	For this reason I, Paul, the prisoner of Christ Jesus in behalf of you Gentiles-
B049C003V002	49	3	2	if indeed you have heard of the dispensation of the grace of God which was given to me for you,
B049C003V003	49	3	3	how that by revelation He made known to me the mystery, just as I wrote before briefly,
B049C003V004	49	3	4	with reference to which, when you read, you can understand my insight in the mystery of Christ,
B049C003V005	49	3	5	which in other generations was not made known to the sons of men, as it has now been revealed by the Spirit to His holy apostles and prophets:
B049C003V006	49	3	6	that the Gentiles should be joint-heirs, and of the same body, and joint-partakers in His promise in Christ by the gospel,
B049C003V007	49	3	7	of which I became a minister according to the free gift of the grace of God which was given to me according to the working of His power.
B049C003V008	49	3	8	To me, the very least of all the saints, this grace was given, to preach among the Gentiles the unsearchable riches of Christ,
B049C003V009	49	3	9	and to enlighten all [as to] what is the administration of the mystery, which had been hidden from the ages in God, who created all things through Jesus Christ;
B049C003V010	49	3	10	that the manifold wisdom of God might be made known by the church to the rulers and authorities in the heavenlies,
B049C003V011	49	3	11	according to the eternal purpose which He made in Christ Jesus our Lord,
B049C003V012	49	3	12	in whom we have the boldness and the access with confidence through faith in Him.
B049C003V013	49	3	13	Therefore I beseech [you] not to lose heart at my tribulations on your behalf, which is your glory.
B049C003V014	49	3	14	For this reason I bow my knees to the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ,
B049C003V015	49	3	15	from whom every family in heaven and upon earth takes its name,
B049C003V016	49	3	16	that He would grant you, according to the riches of His glory, to be strengthened with power by His Spirit in the inner man,
B049C003V017	49	3	17	that Christ may dwell in your hearts through faith; being rooted and founded in love,
B049C003V018	49	3	18	that you may be able to comprehend with all the saints what is the breadth and length and depth and height-
B049C003V019	49	3	19	and to know the love of Christ which surpasses knowledge; that you may be filled with all the fullness of God.
B049C003V020	49	3	20	Now to Him who is able to do exceedingly abundantly above all that we ask or think, according to the power that works in us,
B049C003V021	49	3	21	to Him [be] glory in the church by Christ Jesus to all generations, forever and ever. Amen.
B049C004V001	49	4	1	Therefore I, the prisoner of the Lord, urge you to walk worthy of the calling with which you were called,
B049C004V002	49	4	2	with all humility and meekness, with longsuffering, bearing with one another in love,
B049C004V003	49	4	3	being diligent to keep the unity of the Spirit in the bond of peace.
B049C004V004	49	4	4	There is one body and one Spirit, just as also you were called in one hope of your calling;
B049C004V005	49	4	5	one Lord, one faith, one baptism;
B049C004V006	49	4	6	one God and Father of all, who is over all, and through all, and in us all.
B049C004V007	49	4	7	But to each one of us grace was given according to the measure of the free gift of Christ.
B049C004V008	49	4	8	Therefore He says: "When He ascended on high, He led captivity captive, and gave gifts to men."
B049C004V009	49	4	9	But that "He ascended"-what is it but that He also first descended into the lower parts of the earth?
B049C004V010	49	4	10	He that descended, He is also the [One] who ascended far above all the heavens, that He might fill all things.
B049C004V011	49	4	11	And He gave some as apostles, and some as prophets, and some as evangelists, and some as pastors and teachers,
B049C004V012	49	4	12	for the perfecting of the saints for the work of ministry, for the building up of the body of Christ,
B049C004V013	49	4	13	until we all arrive to the unity of the faith and of the knowledge of the Son of God, to a mature man, to [the] measure of [the] stature of the fullness of Christ;
B049C004V014	49	4	14	that we may no longer be infants, being tossed as by waves, and being carried about by every wind of doctrine, by the trickery of men, by craftiness in regard to deceitful scheming,
B049C004V015	49	4	15	but speaking the truth in love, we may grow up in all things into Him who is the head-Christ;
B049C004V016	49	4	16	from whom the whole body, being fitted and held together by what every joint supplies, according to the working of the measure of each individual part, causes the growth of the body for the edification of itself in love.
B049C004V017	49	4	17	This I say, therefore, and testify in the Lord, that you should no longer walk as the rest of the Gentiles walk, in the vanity of their mind,
B049C004V018	49	4	18	having been darkened in understanding, being estranged from the life of God, because of the ignorance which is in them, because of the hardness of their heart;
B049C004V019	49	4	19	who, having become callous, gave themselves over to debauchery, for the working of uncleanness with utmost greediness.
B049C004V020	49	4	20	But you did not thus learn Christ,
B049C004V021	49	4	21	if indeed you have heard Him and were instructed by Him, just as the truth is in Jesus:
B049C004V022	49	4	22	that you put off, concerning your former way of life, the old man which is being corrupted according to the deceitful lusts,
B049C004V023	49	4	23	and that you be renewed in the spirit of your mind,
B049C004V024	49	4	24	and that you put on the new man which was created in the likeness of God, in true righteousness and holiness.
B049C004V025	49	4	25	Therefore, having put off falsehood, "Let each one speak truth with his neighbor,"for we are members of one another.
B049C004V026	49	4	26	"Be angry, and do not sin": do not let the sun set on your anger,
B049C004V027	49	4	27	nor give opportunity to the devil.
B049C004V028	49	4	28	Let him who stole steal no longer, but rather let him labor, working that which is good with his hands, in order that he may have something to share with him who has need.
B049C004V029	49	4	29	Let no corrupt word proceed from your mouth, but only what is good for edification, that it may give grace to them that hear.
B049C004V030	49	4	30	And do not grieve the Holy Spirit of God, by whom you were sealed for the day of redemption.
B049C004V031	49	4	31	Let all bitterness, wrath, anger, clamor, and blasphemy be removed from you, with all malice.
B049C004V032	49	4	32	And be kind to one another, tenderhearted, forgiving one another, just as also God in Christ forgave us.
B049C005V001	49	5	1	Therefore be imitators of God as beloved children.
B049C005V002	49	5	2	And walk in love, just as Christ also loved us and gave Himself for us, an offering and a sacrifice to God for a fragrant aroma.
B049C005V003	49	5	3	But fornication and all uncleanness or covetousness, let it not even be named among you, as is fitting for saints;
B049C005V004	49	5	4	neither wickedness, nor foolish talk or coarse jesting, which are not proper, but rather thanksgiving.
B049C005V005	49	5	5	For this you know, that no fornicator, or unclean person, nor covetous person, who is an idolater, has any inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and God.
B049C005V006	49	5	6	Let no one deceive you with empty words, for because of these things the wrath of God comes upon the sons of disobedience.
B049C005V007	49	5	7	Therefore do not be participants with them.
B049C005V008	49	5	8	For you were once darkness, but now you are light in the Lord. Walk as children of light-
B049C005V009	49	5	9	for the fruit of the Spirit is in all goodness, righteousness, and truth,
B049C005V010	49	5	10	proving what is well-pleasing to the Lord.
B049C005V011	49	5	11	And have no partnership with the unfruitful works of darkness, but rather expose [them].
B049C005V012	49	5	12	For it is shameful even to speak of those things being done by them in secret.
B049C005V013	49	5	13	But all things that are exposed are made manifest by the light, for whatever makes manifest is light.
B049C005V014	49	5	14	Therefore He says: "Awake, you who are sleeping, and arise from the dead, and Christ will shine on you."
B049C005V015	49	5	15	See then that you walk carefully, not as unwise, but as wise,
B049C005V016	49	5	16	redeeming the time, because the days are evil.
B049C005V017	49	5	17	Therefore do not be foolish, but understand what the will of the Lord [is].
B049C005V018	49	5	18	And do not get drunk with wine, in which is dissipation; but be filled with the Spirit,
B049C005V019	49	5	19	speaking to one another in psalms and hymns and spiritual songs, singing and making melody in your heart to the Lord,
B049C005V020	49	5	20	giving thanks always concerning all things to God the Father in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ,
B049C005V021	49	5	21	subjecting yourselves to one another in the fear of God.
B049C005V022	49	5	22	Wives, subject yourselves to your own husbands, as to the Lord,
B049C005V023	49	5	23	because the husband is head of the wife, as also Christ is head of the church; and He is the Savior of the body.
B049C005V024	49	5	24	But just as the church is subject to Christ, so also the wives be to their own husbands in everything.
B049C005V025	49	5	25	Husbands, love your own wives, just as Christ also loved the church and gave Himself for her,
B049C005V026	49	5	26	in order that He might sanctify her, cleansing her by the washing of water by the word,
B049C005V027	49	5	27	that He might present her to Himself a glorious church, not having spot or wrinkle or any such thing, but that she should be holy and blameless.
B049C005V028	49	5	28	So husbands ought to love their own wives as their own bodies; he that loves his own wife loves himself.
B049C005V029	49	5	29	For no one ever hated his own flesh, but nourishes and cherishes it, just as also the Lord does the church.
B049C005V030	49	5	30	For we are members of His body, of His flesh and of His bones.
B049C005V031	49	5	31	"For this reason a man shall leave his father and mother and be joined to his wife, and the two shall become one flesh."
B049C005V032	49	5	32	This is a great mystery, but I speak in reference to Christ and to the church.
B049C005V033	49	5	33	Nevertheless you also individually, let each one love his own wife as himself, and let the wife see that she respect her husband.
B049C006V001	49	6	1	Children, obey your parents in the Lord, for this is right.
B049C006V002	49	6	2	"Honor your father and mother,"which is the first commandment with a promise:
B049C006V003	49	6	3	"that it may be well with you, and you may live long on the earth."
B049C006V004	49	6	4	And fathers, do not provoke your children to anger, but bring them up in the discipline and admonition of the Lord.
B049C006V005	49	6	5	Slaves, obey your masters according to the flesh with fear and trembling, in simplicity of heart, as to Christ;
B049C006V006	49	6	6	not with eyeservice, as men-pleasers, but as slaves of Christ, doing the will of God wholeheartedly,
B049C006V007	49	6	7	with good will doing service, as to the Lord, and not to men,
B049C006V008	49	6	8	knowing that whatever good thing anyone does, the same he shall receive back from the Lord, whether slave or free.
B049C006V009	49	6	9	And masters, do the same things towards them, giving up threatening, knowing that your own Master is in heaven, and there is no partiality with Him.
B049C006V010	49	6	10	Finally, my brothers, be strong in the Lord and in the power of His might.
B049C006V011	49	6	11	Put on the full armor of God, so that you may be able to stand against the stratagems of the devil.
B049C006V012	49	6	12	For we wrestle not against flesh and blood, but against principalities, against powers, against the rulers of the darkness of this age, against spiritual [forces] of evil in the heavenlies.
B049C006V013	49	6	13	Because of this, take up the whole armor of God, that you may be able to withstand in the evil day, and having accomplished all things, to stand.
B049C006V014	49	6	14	Stand therefore, having girded your waist with truth, having put on the breastplate of righteousness,
B049C006V015	49	6	15	and having shod your feet with the preparation of the gospel of peace;
B049C006V016	49	6	16	above all, taking up the shield of faith, with which you will be able to quench all the flaming arrows of the evil one.
B049C006V017	49	6	17	And take the helmet of salvation, and the sword of the Spirit, which is the word of God;
B049C006V018	49	6	18	through every prayer and petition, praying in every season in the Spirit, being watchful to this same thing with all perseverance and petition concerning all the saints-
B049C006V019	49	6	19	and for me, that utterance may be given to me in the opening of my mouth, to make known with boldness the mystery of the gospel,
B049C006V020	49	6	20	for the sake of which I serve as an ambassador in chains; that in it I may speak boldly, as I must speak.
B049C006V021	49	6	21	But that you also may know my circumstances, and how I am doing, Tychicus, a beloved brother and faithful servant in the Lord, will make all things known to you;
B049C006V022	49	6	22	whom I have sent to you for this very purpose, that you may know our situation, and that he may comfort your hearts.
B049C006V023	49	6	23	Peace to the brothers, and love with faith, from God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B049C006V024	49	6	24	Grace be with all those who love our Lord Jesus Christ in sincerity. Amen.
B050C001V001	50	1	1	Paul and Timothy, bondservants of Jesus Christ, to all the saints in Christ Jesus who are at Philippi, together with the overseers and ministers:
B050C001V002	50	1	2	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and [the] Lord Jesus Christ.
B050C001V003	50	1	3	I thank my God upon every remembrance of you,
B050C001V004	50	1	4	always in every prayer of mine in behalf of you all, with joy,
B050C001V005	50	1	5	for your fellowship in the gospel from the first day until now,
B050C001V006	50	1	6	having been persuaded of this very thing, that He who began a good work in you will complete it until the day of Christ Jesus;
B050C001V007	50	1	7	just as it is right for me to think this concerning you all, because I have you in my heart, both in my chains and in the defense and confirmation of the gospel, you all are partakers with me of grace.
B050C001V008	50	1	8	For God is my witness, how greatly I long for you all with the affection of Jesus Christ.
B050C001V009	50	1	9	And this I pray, that your love may abound yet more and more in knowledge and all perception,
B050C001V010	50	1	10	that you may approve the things that are excellent, in order that you may be sincere and without offense till the day of Christ,
B050C001V011	50	1	11	having been filled with the fruits of righteousness which are by Jesus Christ, to the glory and praise of God.
B050C001V012	50	1	12	But I want you to know, brothers, that the things [which happened ]to me have come about for the advancement of the gospel,
B050C001V013	50	1	13	so that it has become evident to the whole palace guard, and to all the rest, that my chains are in Christ;
B050C001V014	50	1	14	and most of the brothers in the Lord, having been persuaded by my chains, are much more bold to speak the word fearlessly.
B050C001V015	50	1	15	Some indeed are preaching Christ even from envy and strife, but some also from good will:
B050C001V016	50	1	16	The [former ]proclaim Christ out of selfish ambition, not sincerely, supposing to add affliction to my chains;
B050C001V017	50	1	17	but the latter out of love, knowing that I am appointed for the defense of the gospel.
B050C001V018	50	1	18	What then? Nevertheless in every way, whether in pretense or in truth, Christ is proclaimed; and in this I rejoice; yes, and I will rejoice.
B050C001V019	50	1	19	For I know that this will turn out for my deliverance through your prayer and the supply of the Spirit of Jesus Christ,
B050C001V020	50	1	20	according to my earnest expectation and hope that in nothing I will be ashamed, but with utmost boldness, as always, now also Christ will be magnified in my body, whether by life or by death.
B050C001V021	50	1	21	For to me, to live [is] Christ, and to die [is] gain.
B050C001V022	50	1	22	But if I am to live on in the flesh, this to me will mean fruit from my labor; and what I shall choose I do not know.
B050C001V023	50	1	23	For I am hard pressed by the two, having a desire to depart and to be with Christ, [which is] far better.
B050C001V024	50	1	24	But to remain in the flesh is more needful for your sake.
B050C001V025	50	1	25	And having been persuaded of this, I know that I shall remain and continue with you all for your progress and joy in the faith,
B050C001V026	50	1	26	that your boasting may abound in Christ Jesus in me through my coming again to you.
B050C001V027	50	1	27	Only conduct yourselves worthy of the gospel of Christ, so that whether I come and see you or am absent, I may hear of your affairs, that you stand fast in one spirit, with one soul striving together for the faith of the gospel,
B050C001V028	50	1	28	and not being terrified in anything by your enemies, which is to them a proof of destruction, but to you of salvation, and this from God.
B050C001V029	50	1	29	For to you it has been granted for the sake of Christ, not only to believe in Him, but also to suffer for His sake,
B050C001V030	50	1	30	having the same struggle which you saw in me and now you hear is in me.
B050C002V001	50	2	1	Therefore if there is any consolation in Christ, if any comfort of love, if any fellowship of the Spirit, if any affection and acts of compassion,
B050C002V002	50	2	2	fulfill my joy by being like-minded, having the same love, being united in spirit, intending the same purpose,
B050C002V003	50	2	3	doing nothing according to selfish ambition or conceit, but with humility, regarding one another as being better than yourselves.
B050C002V004	50	2	4	Let each of you look out not only for his own concerns, but also for the concerns of others.
B050C002V005	50	2	5	Let this mind be in you which was also in Christ Jesus,
B050C002V006	50	2	6	who, existing in the form of God, did not consider it robbery to be equal with God,
B050C002V007	50	2	7	but made Himself of no reputation, taking the form of a bondservant, and coming to be in the likeness of men.
B050C002V008	50	2	8	And being found in appearance as a man, He humbled Himself, becoming obedient unto death, even the death of the cross.
B050C002V009	50	2	9	Therefore God also has highly exalted Him, and has graciously given Him a name which is above every name,
B050C002V010	50	2	10	that at the name of Jesus every knee may bow, of those in heaven, and of those on earth, and of those under the earth,
B050C002V011	50	2	11	and [that ]every tongue may confess that Jesus Christ is Lord, to the glory of God the Father.
B050C002V012	50	2	12	So then, my beloved, just as you have always obeyed, not as in my presence only, but now much more in my absence, work out your own salvation with fear and trembling;
B050C002V013	50	2	13	for it is God who is working in you, both to will and to do for His good pleasure.
B050C002V014	50	2	14	Do all things without grumbling and disputing,
B050C002V015	50	2	15	in order that you may become blameless and harmless, children of God without fault in the midst of a crooked and perverted generation, among whom you shine as light bearers in the world,
B050C002V016	50	2	16	holding fast the word of life, so that I may rejoice in the day of Christ, that I have not run in vain or labored in vain.
B050C002V017	50	2	17	But even if I am being poured upon the sacrifice and service of your faith, I rejoice; [yea,] and I rejoice with you all.
B050C002V018	50	2	18	For the same reason you also rejoice and rejoice together with me.
B050C002V019	50	2	19	Now I hope in the Lord Jesus to send Timothy to you shortly, that I also may be encouraged when I learn of your circumstances.
B050C002V020	50	2	20	For I have no one like-minded, who will be genuinely concerned about your circumstances.
B050C002V021	50	2	21	For all seek their own interests, not the things of Christ Jesus.
B050C002V022	50	2	22	And you know his approved character, that as a child with his father he served as a slave for the gospel.
B050C002V023	50	2	23	Therefore I hope to send him at once, as soon as I may see how my circumstances go.
B050C002V024	50	2	24	But I have been persuaded in the Lord that I myself will also come shortly.
B050C002V025	50	2	25	Yet I considered it necessary to send to you Epaphroditus, my brother, fellow worker, and fellow soldier, and your messenger and minister to my needs;
B050C002V026	50	2	26	since he was longing for you all, and was distressed because you had heard that he was sick.
B050C002V027	50	2	27	For indeed he was sick, [and ]near death; but God showed mercy [on] him, and not only on him but on me also, lest I should have sorrow upon sorrow.
B050C002V028	50	2	28	Therefore I sent him more eagerly, in order that when you see him again you may have joy, and I may be less anxious.
B050C002V029	50	2	29	Receive him therefore in the Lord with the utmost joy, and hold such [ones] in honor;
B050C002V030	50	2	30	because for the work of Christ he drew near unto death, being careless with his life, in order that he might fill up that which was lacking in your service to me.
B050C003V001	50	3	1	Finally, my brothers, rejoice in the Lord. For me to write the same things to you is not troublesome, but for you it is safe.
B050C003V002	50	3	2	Beware of the dogs, beware of the evil workers, beware of the [false] circumcision!
B050C003V003	50	3	3	For we are the [true] circumcision, worshipping by the Spirit of God, rejoicing in Christ Jesus, and having no confidence in the flesh,
B050C003V004	50	3	4	although I also [am] having confidence in the flesh. If any other [person] thinks to have confidence in the flesh, I even more:
B050C003V005	50	3	5	circumcised the eighth day, of the nation of Israel, of the tribe of Benjamin, a Hebrew of Hebrews; with respect to the law, a Pharisee;
B050C003V006	50	3	6	with respect to zeal, persecuting the church; with respect to righteousness which is in the law, blameless.
B050C003V007	50	3	7	But such things as were gain to me, these I have considered loss for the sake of Christ.
B050C003V008	50	3	8	More than that I also consider all things to be loss for the excellence of the knowledge of Christ Jesus my Lord, for whom I have sustained the loss of all things, and I consider them to be rubbish, in order that I may gain Christ
B050C003V009	50	3	9	and be found in Him, not having my own righteousness, which is of the law, but that which is through [the] faith of Christ, the righteousness [which is] of God by faith;
B050C003V010	50	3	10	[so as] to know Him and the power of His resurrection, and the fellowship of His sufferings, being conformed to His death,
B050C003V011	50	3	11	if in some way I may attain to the resurrection from the dead.
B050C003V012	50	3	12	Not that I have already obtained, or have already been made perfect; but I press on, if also I may lay hold of that for which I was laid hold of by Christ Jesus.
B050C003V013	50	3	13	Brothers, I do not count myself to have laid hold; but one thing[ I do], forgetting those things which are behind, and reaching forward to those things which are ahead,
B050C003V014	50	3	14	I press toward the goal for the prize of the high calling of God in Christ Jesus.
B050C003V015	50	3	15	Therefore, as many as are mature, let us think this way; and if in anything you think otherwise, even this God will reveal to you.
B050C003V016	50	3	16	Nevertheless, to what we have attained, let us walk by the same rule, [being] of the same mind.
B050C003V017	50	3	17	Be fellow imitators of me, brothers, and look out for those walking this way, just as you have us for a pattern.
B050C003V018	50	3	18	For many walk, of whom often I was speaking to you, and now even weeping I tell you, [that they are] the enemies of the cross of Christ:
B050C003V019	50	3	19	whose end is destruction, whose god is their belly, and whose glory is in their shame-who are mindful of earthly things.
B050C003V020	50	3	20	For our citizenship exists in heaven, from which also we eagerly await for the Savior, the Lord Jesus Christ,
B050C003V021	50	3	21	who will transform our lowly body, that it may be conformed to His glorious body, according to the working by which He is able even to subject all things to Himself.
B050C004V001	50	4	1	Therefore, my beloved and longed for brothers, my joy and crown, in this way stand fast in the Lord, beloved.
B050C004V002	50	4	2	I implore Euodia and I implore Syntyche to be of the same mind in the Lord.
B050C004V003	50	4	3	Yes, I ask you also, true companion, help these women who labored together with me in the gospel, and with Clement also, and the rest of my fellow workers, whose names are in the Book of Life.
B050C004V004	50	4	4	Rejoice in the Lord always. Again I will say, rejoice!
B050C004V005	50	4	5	Let your gentleness be known to all men. The Lord is at hand.
B050C004V006	50	4	6	Be anxious for nothing, but in everything by prayer and petition, along with thanksgiving, let your requests be made known to God;
B050C004V007	50	4	7	and the peace of God, which surpasses all understanding, shall guard your hearts and your thoughts in Christ Jesus.
B050C004V008	50	4	8	Finally, brothers, as many things as are true, as many as are honorable, as many as are just, as many as are pure, as many as are lovely-if there is any virtue and if there is any praise-meditate on these things.
B050C004V009	50	4	9	The things which you learned and received and heard and saw in me, practice these things; and the God of peace shall be with you.
B050C004V010	50	4	10	But I rejoiced in the Lord greatly that now once [again] you have revived your mindfulness on my behalf, inasmuch as indeed you were mindful, but you lacked opportunity.
B050C004V011	50	4	11	Not that I am speaking with respect to need, for I have learned to be content in whatever state I am.
B050C004V012	50	4	12	I know how to be abased, and I know how to abound. In every place and in all [circumstances] I have learned both to be full and to be hungry, both to abound and to be in need.
B050C004V013	50	4	13	I can do all things through Christ who strengthens me.
B050C004V014	50	4	14	Nevertheless you have done well that you shared in my affliction.
B050C004V015	50	4	15	Now you Philippians also know that in the beginning of the gospel, when I went out from Macedonia, no church shared with me in an accounting of giving and receiving except you only.
B050C004V016	50	4	16	Because even in Thessalonica, both once and again you sent for my need.
B050C004V017	50	4	17	Not that I seek the gift, but I seek the fruit which is increasing to your account.
B050C004V018	50	4	18	And I have all things and abound. I have been made full, having received from Epaphroditus the things [sent] from you, a fragrant aroma, an acceptable sacrifice, well pleasing to God.
B050C004V019	50	4	19	And my God will supply all your need according to His riches in glory in Christ Jesus.
B050C004V020	50	4	20	Now to our God and Father be glory forever and ever. Amen.
B050C004V021	50	4	21	Greet every saint in Christ Jesus. The brothers who are with me greet you.
B050C004V022	50	4	22	All the saints greet you, but especially those of the household of Caesar.
B050C004V023	50	4	23	The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with you all. Amen.
B051C001V001	51	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ by [the] will of God, and Timothy our brother,
B051C001V002	51	1	2	To the saints and faithful brothers in Christ in Colosse: Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B051C001V003	51	1	3	We give thanks to the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, praying always for you,
B051C001V004	51	1	4	when we heard of your faith in Christ Jesus and your love which is towards all the saints;
B051C001V005	51	1	5	because of the hope being laid up for you in [the] heavens, in which you heard before in the word of the truth of the gospel,
B051C001V006	51	1	6	which has come to you, just as also in all the world, and is bearing fruit and growing, just as also among you, from the day which you heard and fully knew the grace of God in truth;
B051C001V007	51	1	7	just as also you learned from Epaphras, our beloved fellow servant, who is a faithful minister of Christ for you,
B051C001V008	51	1	8	who also told us of your love in the Spirit.
B051C001V009	51	1	9	On account of this we also, since the day we heard, do not cease praying for you, and asking that you may be filled with the full knowledge of His will in all wisdom and spiritual understanding;
B051C001V010	51	1	10	that you should walk worthy of the Lord, to please Him in all respects, bearing fruit and increasing in the full knowledge of God;
B051C001V011	51	1	11	being strengthened with all power, according to the might of His glory, for all endurance and longsuffering with joy;
B051C001V012	51	1	12	giving thanks to the Father who has qualified us to share in the inheritance of the saints in the light.
B051C001V013	51	1	13	He has delivered us from the dominion of darkness and transferred us into the kingdom of the Son of His love,
B051C001V014	51	1	14	in whom we have redemption, the forgiveness of sins.
B051C001V015	51	1	15	He is the image of the invisible God, the firstborn over all creation,
B051C001V016	51	1	16	because by Him all things were created, those in the heavens and those on earth, visible and invisible, whether thrones or dominions or rulers or authorities; all things have been created through Him and for Him.
B051C001V017	51	1	17	And He is before all things, and in Him all things are held together.
B051C001V018	51	1	18	And He is the head of the body, the church, who is the beginning, the firstborn from the dead, so that in all things He may have the preeminence;
B051C001V019	51	1	19	for it pleased [the Father that] in Him all the fullness should dwell,
B051C001V020	51	1	20	and through Him to reconcile all things to Himself, by Him, whether things on the earth or things in the heavens, having made peace through the blood of His cross.
B051C001V021	51	1	21	And you, who once were alienated and enemies in your mind by wicked works, yet now He has reconciled
B051C001V022	51	1	22	in the body of His flesh through death, to present you holy, and blameless, and above reproach before Him-
B051C001V023	51	1	23	if indeed you continue in the faith, having been founded and firm and not drifting away from the hope of the gospel which you heard, which was proclaimed to all creation under heaven, of which I, Paul, became a minister.
B051C001V024	51	1	24	I now rejoice in my sufferings for you, and fill up in my flesh what is lacking in the afflictions of Christ, for His body, which is the church,
B051C001V025	51	1	25	of which I became a minister according to the stewardship of God which was given to me for you, to fulfill the word of God,
B051C001V026	51	1	26	the mystery which has been hidden from the ages and from generations, but now was revealed to His saints.
B051C001V027	51	1	27	To whom God willed to make known what are the riches of the glory of this mystery among the nations, which is Christ in you, the hope of glory;
B051C001V028	51	1	28	whom we proclaim, warning every man and teaching every man in all wisdom, that we may present every man perfect in Christ Jesus;
B051C001V029	51	1	29	for which I also labor, striving according to His working which is working in me with power.
B051C002V001	51	2	1	For I want you to know how great a struggle I have concerning you and those in Laodicea, and for as many as have not seen my face in the flesh,
B051C002V002	51	2	2	that their hearts may be encouraged, being joined together in love, and to all riches of the full assurance of understanding, to a full knowledge of the mystery of God, both of the Father and of Christ,
B051C002V003	51	2	3	in whom are hidden all the treasures of wisdom and knowledge.
B051C002V004	51	2	4	Now this I say lest anyone may deceive you with persuasive words.
B051C002V005	51	2	5	For though indeed I am absent in the flesh, yet I am with you in spirit, rejoicing to see your orderliness and the steadfastness of your faith in Christ.
B051C002V006	51	2	6	Therefore as you have received Christ Jesus the Lord, so walk in Him,
B051C002V007	51	2	7	having been rooted and built up in Him and being established in the faith, just as you were taught, abounding in it with thanksgiving.
B051C002V008	51	2	8	Beware lest anyone captures you through philosophy and empty deceit, according to the tradition of men, according to the basic principles of the world, and not according to Christ.
B051C002V009	51	2	9	For in Him dwells all the fullness of the Godhead bodily;
B051C002V010	51	2	10	and you are completed in Him, who is the head of all principality and power.
B051C002V011	51	2	11	In whom you were also circumcised with the circumcision made without hands, by the putting off the body of the sins of the flesh, by the circumcision of Christ,
B051C002V012	51	2	12	having been buried together with Him in baptism, in which also you were raised together through faith in the working of God, who raised Him from the dead.
B051C002V013	51	2	13	And you, being dead in your trespasses and the uncircumcision of your flesh, He made you alive together with Him, having forgiven us all our trespasses,
B051C002V014	51	2	14	having blotted out the handwriting of ordinances that was against us, which was contrary to us, and He has taken it out of the midst, nailing it to the cross.
B051C002V015	51	2	15	[And h]aving disarmed principalities and powers, He mocked them in public, triumphing over them in it.
B051C002V016	51	2	16	Therefore do not let anyone judge you in food or in drink, or regarding a festival or of a new moon or of sabbaths,
B051C002V017	51	2	17	which are a shadow of things to come, but the body is of Christ.
B051C002V018	51	2	18	Let no one rule against you, desiring [to do so] in [false] humility and in worship of the angels, intruding into those things which he has not seen, in vain being puffed up by his carnal mind,
B051C002V019	51	2	19	and not holding fast to the Head, from whom all the body, supported and joined together by joints and ligaments, grows with the growth of God.
B051C002V020	51	2	20	If you died with Christ from the basic principles of the world, why, as though living in the world, do you submit to regulations-
B051C002V021	51	2	21	"Do not handle, nor taste, nor touch,"
B051C002V022	51	2	22	which things are all for corruption with the using, according to the commands and teaching of men?
B051C002V023	51	2	23	These things indeed have a reputation of wisdom in self-imposed religion, false humility, and severity [on the] body, but [are] not of any value against the indulgence of the flesh.
B051C003V001	51	3	1	If then you were raised with Christ, seek those things which are above, where Christ is, sitting at [the] right [hand] of God.
B051C003V002	51	3	2	Set your mind on things above, not on things on the earth.
B051C003V003	51	3	3	For you died, and your life has been hidden with Christ in God.
B051C003V004	51	3	4	Whenever Christ [who is] our life appears, then you also will appear with Him in glory.
B051C003V005	51	3	5	Therefore put to death your members on the earth: fornication, uncleanness, passion, evil desire, and greed, which is idolatry.
B051C003V006	51	3	6	Because of which things the wrath of God is coming on the sons of disobedience,
B051C003V007	51	3	7	in which you yourselves once walked when you lived in them.
B051C003V008	51	3	8	But now you yourselves are to put off all [these]: wrath, anger, malice, blasphemy, filthy language out of your mouth.
B051C003V009	51	3	9	Do not lie to one another, since you have stripped off the old man with his practices,
B051C003V010	51	3	10	and have put on the new man who is renewed in full knowledge according to the image of Him who created it,
B051C003V011	51	3	11	where there is not Greek nor Jew, circumcised nor uncircumcised, barbarian, Scythian, slave nor free, but Christ is all and in all.
B051C003V012	51	3	12	Therefore, as the elect of God, holy and beloved, put on hearts of compassion, kindness, humility, meekness, patience;
B051C003V013	51	3	13	forbearing one another and forgiving yourselves, if anyone should have a complaint against any; just as Christ forgave you, so you also [do].
B051C003V014	51	3	14	But above all these things put on love, which is the bond of perfection.
B051C003V015	51	3	15	And let the peace of God rule in your hearts, to which also you were called in one body; and be thankful.
B051C003V016	51	3	16	Let the word of Christ dwell in you richly in all wisdom, teaching and admonishing one another in psalms and hymns and spiritual songs, singing with grace in your hearts to the Lord.
B051C003V017	51	3	17	And whatever you may do in word or deed, do all things in the name of the Lord Jesus, giving thanks to God the Father through Him.
B051C003V018	51	3	18	Wives, subject yourselves to your own husbands, as is fitting in the Lord.
B051C003V019	51	3	19	Husbands, love your wives and do not be bitter toward them.
B051C003V020	51	3	20	Children, obey your parents in all things, for this is well pleasing in the Lord.
B051C003V021	51	3	21	Fathers, do not provoke your children, lest they become discouraged.
B051C003V022	51	3	22	Bondservants, obey your masters according to the flesh in all things, not with eyeservice, as men-pleasers, but in sincerity of heart, fearing God.
B051C003V023	51	3	23	And whatever you may do, work [it] from your soul, as to the Lord and not to men,
B051C003V024	51	3	24	knowing that from the Lord you will receive the reward of the inheritance. For you serve the Lord Christ.
B051C003V025	51	3	25	But the [one] doing wrong will be repaid for what he has done, and there is not partiality.
B051C004V001	51	4	1	Masters, provide to your bondservants what is just and fair, knowing that you also have a Master in [the] heavens.
B051C004V002	51	4	2	Continue earnestly in prayer, being vigilant in it with thanksgiving;
B051C004V003	51	4	3	praying at the same time also for us, that God would open a door for the word, to speak the mystery of Christ, because of which I am also in chains,
B051C004V004	51	4	4	that I may make it manifest, as I ought to speak.
B051C004V005	51	4	5	Walk in wisdom toward outsiders, redeeming the time.
B051C004V006	51	4	6	Let your word always be with grace, having been seasoned with salt, to know how you ought to answer each [one].
B051C004V007	51	4	7	Tychicus, the beloved brother and faithful minister, and fellow servant in the Lord, will tell you all things about me.
B051C004V008	51	4	8	I am sending him to you for this very thing, that he may know your circumstances, and he may encourage your hearts,
B051C004V009	51	4	9	with Onesimus, the faithful and beloved brother, who is one of you. They will make known to you all the things[ happening] here.
B051C004V010	51	4	10	Aristarchus my fellow prisoner greets you, with Mark the cousin of Barnabas (about whom you received instructions: if he comes to you, receive him),
B051C004V011	51	4	11	and Jesus who is called Justus. These alone are my fellow workers for the kingdom of God who are of the circumcision; they have proved to be a comfort to me.
B051C004V012	51	4	12	Epaphras greets you, who is one of you, a bondservant of Christ, always struggling for you in his prayers, that you may stand mature and complete in all the will of God.
B051C004V013	51	4	13	For I bear him witness that he has much zeal for you, and those in Laodicea, and those in Hierapolis.
B051C004V014	51	4	14	Luke the beloved physician greets you, also Demas.
B051C004V015	51	4	15	Greet the brothers who are in Laodicea, and Nymphas and the church in his house.
B051C004V016	51	4	16	And whenever this letter is read before you, see that it is also read in the church of the Laodiceans, and that you also read the [one] from Laodicea.
B051C004V017	51	4	17	And say to Archippus, "Take heed to the ministry which you received in the Lord, that you fulfill it."
B051C004V018	51	4	18	This greeting [is] by my [own] hand-Paul. Remember my chains. Grace be with you. Amen.
B052C001V001	52	1	1	Paul, Silvanus, and Timothy, To the church of the Thessalonians in God [the] Father and [the] Lord Jesus Christ: Grace to you and peace from God our Father and [the] Lord Jesus Christ.
B052C001V002	52	1	2	We give thanks to God always concerning you all, making mention of you in our prayers,
B052C001V003	52	1	3	constantly remembering your work of faith, labor of love, and perseverance of hope in our Lord Jesus Christ in the presence of our God and Father,
B052C001V004	52	1	4	knowing, beloved brothers, your election by God.
B052C001V005	52	1	5	For our gospel did not come to you in word only, but also in power, and in the Holy Spirit and in much assurance, just as you know what kind [of men ]we were among you for your sake.
B052C001V006	52	1	6	And you became imitators of us and of the Lord, in that you received the word in much tribulation, with joy of the Holy Spirit,
B052C001V007	52	1	7	so that you became patterns to all those who believe in Macedonia and Achaia.
B052C001V008	52	1	8	For from you the word of the Lord has resounded, not only in Macedonia and in Achaia, but also in every place. Your faith toward God has gone forth, so that we have no need to say anything.
B052C001V009	52	1	9	For they themselves report about us what kind of entrance we had to you, and how you turned to God from idols to serve the living and true God,
B052C001V010	52	1	10	and to wait for His Son from heaven, whom He raised from the dead, Jesus, who delivers us from the coming wrath.
B052C002V001	52	2	1	For you yourselves know, brothers, [regarding] our coming to you, that it was not in vain.
B052C002V002	52	2	2	But suffering before and being spitefully treated at Philippi, just as you know, we were bold in our God to speak to you the gospel of God with much conflict.
B052C002V003	52	2	3	For our exhortation [was ]not from error nor from uncleanness, nor in trickery,
B052C002V004	52	2	4	but just as we have been approved by God to be entrusted with the gospel, even so we speak, not as pleasing men, but God who is testing our hearts.
B052C002V005	52	2	5	For neither were we using flattering speech, as you know, nor covering up greed, God is [our ]witness.
B052C002V006	52	2	6	Nor seeking glory from men, neither from you, nor from others, even though we were able to carry weight as apostles of Christ.
B052C002V007	52	2	7	But we proved to be gentle in your midst, as a nursing [mother] cherishes her own children.
B052C002V008	52	2	8	In this way longing for you, we were well pleased to impart to you not only the gospel of God, but also our own lives, because you had become dear to us.
B052C002V009	52	2	9	For you remember, brothers, our labor and toil; for laboring night and day, that we might not be a burden to any of you, we proclaimed to you the gospel of God.
B052C002V010	52	2	10	You are witnesses, and [so is ]God, how devoutly and justly and blamelessly we were among you that believe;
B052C002V011	52	2	11	as indeed you know how each one of you, as a father [to] his own children, we exhorted, and comforted [you], and imploring you,
B052C002V012	52	2	12	that you would walk worthy of God who calls you into His own kingdom and glory.
B052C002V013	52	2	13	Because of this we also give thanks to God unceasingly, so that when you received the word of God which you heard from us, you received not the word of men, but just as it truly is, the word of God, which also is at work in you that believe.
B052C002V014	52	2	14	For you, brothers, became imitators of the churches of God which are in Judea in Christ Jesus, because you suffered the same things from your fellow countrymen, just as also they [did] by the Jews,
B052C002V015	52	2	15	who killed both the Lord Jesus and their own prophets, and have persecuted us; and they do not please God and [are] against all men,
B052C002V016	52	2	16	forbidding us from speaking to the Gentiles so that they may be saved, so as always to fill up [the measure of] their sins; but the wrath [of God ]has come upon them to the uttermost.
B052C002V017	52	2	17	But we, brothers, being unwillingly separated from you for a short season, in presence, not in heart, were all the more eager to see your face with much desire.
B052C002V018	52	2	18	Therefore we desired to come to you-I, Paul, time and again, but Satan hindered us.
B052C002V019	52	2	19	For what is our hope, or joy, or crown of boasting? [Is] it not even you, in the presence of our Lord Jesus at His coming?
B052C002V020	52	2	20	For you are our glory and joy.
B052C003V001	52	3	1	Therefore, when we could no longer endure it, we were well pleased to be left behind in Athens alone,
B052C003V002	52	3	2	and sent Timothy, our brother and minister of God, and our fellow worker in the gospel of Christ, in order to establish you and encourage you concerning your faith,
B052C003V003	52	3	3	that no one should be disturbed by these afflictions; for you yourselves know that we are appointed unto this.
B052C003V004	52	3	4	For even when we were with you, we were telling you in advance that we were going to be afflicted, just as it also happened, and you know.
B052C003V005	52	3	5	Because of this, when I could no longer endure [it], I sent to learn about your faith, lest somehow the tempter had tempted you, and our labor be in vain.
B052C003V006	52	3	6	But now when Timothy came to us from you, and brought good news to us of your faith and your love, and that you have good remembrance of us always, longing to see us, as we also [long to see] you-
B052C003V007	52	3	7	because of this we were encouraged, brothers, in regard to you in all our affliction and distress by your faith.
B052C003V008	52	3	8	Because now we live, if you stand firm in the Lord.
B052C003V009	52	3	9	For whatever thanksgiving can we render to God for you, for all the joy with which we are rejoicing because of you in the presence of our God,
B052C003V010	52	3	10	night and day praying exceedingly that we may see your face and to perfect what is lacking in your faith?
B052C003V011	52	3	11	Now may our God and Father Himself, and our Lord Jesus Christ, lead us directly to you.
B052C003V012	52	3	12	And may the Lord make you to increase and abound in love toward one another and toward all [men], as indeed we also do toward you,
B052C003V013	52	3	13	so that He may establish your hearts blameless in holiness before our God and Father at the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ with all His saints.
B052C004V001	52	4	1	Finally then, brothers, we request of you and exhort [you] in the Lord Jesus, just as you received from us how you ought to walk and to please God, that you should abound more.
B052C004V002	52	4	2	For you know what commandments we gave you through the Lord Jesus.
B052C004V003	52	4	3	For this is [the] will of God, your sanctification: that you should abstain from fornication,
B052C004V004	52	4	4	that each of you should know how to possess his own vessel in sanctification and honor,
B052C004V005	52	4	5	not in lustful passion, like the Gentiles who do not know God,
B052C004V006	52	4	6	that no one should transgress against and to defraud his brother in this matter, because the Lord is the avenger concerning all, just as we told you before and solemnly testified.
B052C004V007	52	4	7	For God did not call us to uncleanness, but in sanctification.
B052C004V008	52	4	8	Therefore he who rejects [this] does not reject man, but God, who has given His Holy Spirit to you.
B052C004V009	52	4	9	Now concerning brotherly love you have no need [for me] to write to you, for you yourselves are taught by God to love one another.
B052C004V010	52	4	10	For indeed you do so toward all the brothers in all Macedonia. But we exhort you, brothers, that you increase more and more,
B052C004V011	52	4	11	and that you aspire to be quiet, and to mind your own business, and to work with your own hands, just as we commanded you,
B052C004V012	52	4	12	in order that you may walk decently toward those that are outside, and may have need of nothing.
B052C004V013	52	4	13	Now we do not want you to be uninformed, brothers, concerning those who have fallen asleep, lest you be sorrowful as those who have no hope.
B052C004V014	52	4	14	For if we believe that Jesus died and rose [again], thus also God will bring with Him those who sleep in Jesus.
B052C004V015	52	4	15	For this we say to you by the word of the Lord, that we who are alive and remain until the coming of the Lord shall by no means precede those who are asleep.
B052C004V016	52	4	16	Because the Lord Himself shall descend from heaven with a word of command, with [the] voice of an archangel, and with [the] trumpet of God, and the dead in Christ shall rise first.
B052C004V017	52	4	17	Then we who are alive [and] remain shall be caught up together with them in the clouds to meet the Lord in the air. And thus we shall always be with the Lord.
B052C004V018	52	4	18	So then comfort one another with these words.
B052C005V001	52	5	1	But concerning the times and the seasons, brothers, you have no need that I should write to you.
B052C005V002	52	5	2	For you yourselves know accurately that the day of the Lord so comes as a thief in the night.
B052C005V003	52	5	3	For when they say, "Peace and safety!"then sudden destruction comes upon them, just as labor pains upon the woman that is pregnant, and they shall by no means escape.
B052C005V004	52	5	4	But you, brothers, are not in darkness, so that this Day should overtake you as a thief.
B052C005V005	52	5	5	You are all sons of light and sons of the day. We are not of the night nor of darkness.
B052C005V006	52	5	6	Therefore let us not sleep, as others do, but let us watch and be sober.
B052C005V007	52	5	7	For those who sleep, sleep at night, and those[ ]getting drunk, are drunk at night.
B052C005V008	52	5	8	But we, since we are of the day, let us be sober, putting on a breastplate of faith and love, and as a helmet, the hope of salvation.
B052C005V009	52	5	9	For God did not appoint us to wrath, but to [the] obtaining of salvation through our Lord Jesus Christ,
B052C005V010	52	5	10	who died for us, in order that whether we are awake or asleep, we may live together with Him.
B052C005V011	52	5	11	Therefore comfort each other and edify one another, just as you also are doing.
B052C005V012	52	5	12	And we request of you, brothers, to recognize those who labor among you, and are over you in the Lord and instruct you,
B052C005V013	52	5	13	and to regard them beyond all measure in love, because of their work. Be at peace among yourselves.
B052C005V014	52	5	14	Now we exhort you, brothers, admonish the disorderly, encourage the discouraged, be supportive of the weak, be patient toward all.
B052C005V015	52	5	15	See that no one pays back evil for evil to anyone, but always pursue that which is good, both for one another and for all.
B052C005V016	52	5	16	Rejoice always!
B052C005V017	52	5	17	Pray without ceasing!
B052C005V018	52	5	18	In everything give thanks; for this is the will of God in Christ Jesus for you.
B052C005V019	52	5	19	Do not quench the Spirit.
B052C005V020	52	5	20	Do not despise prophecies.
B052C005V021	52	5	21	But test all things; hold fast that which is good.
B052C005V022	52	5	22	Abstain from every form of evil.
B052C005V023	52	5	23	Now [may] the God of peace Himself sanctify you completely; and may your whole spirit, soul, and body be kept blameless at the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B052C005V024	52	5	24	He who calls you is faithful, who also will do [this].
B052C005V025	52	5	25	Brothers, pray for us.
B052C005V026	52	5	26	Greet all the brothers with a holy kiss.
B052C005V027	52	5	27	I adjure you by the Lord [for] this letter to be read to all the holy brothers.
B052C005V028	52	5	28	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you. Amen.
B053C001V001	53	1	1	Paul, Silvanus, and Timothy, To the church of the Thessalonians in God our Father and [the] Lord Jesus Christ:
B053C001V002	53	1	2	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and [the] Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C001V003	53	1	3	We are obligated to give thanks to God always for you, brothers, [and ]rightfully so, because your faith grows exceedingly, and the love of every one of you all increases towards one another,
B053C001V004	53	1	4	so that we ourselves are boasting in you among the churches of God about your patience and faith in all your persecutions and tribulations that you endure,
B053C001V005	53	1	5	[which is] evidence of the righteous judgment of God, so that you may be counted worthy of the kingdom of God, on behalf of which you also suffer;
B053C001V006	53	1	6	since it is a righteous thing with God to repay with affliction those who afflict you,
B053C001V007	53	1	7	and to give you who are being afflicted rest along with us at the revelation of the Lord Jesus from heaven with His mighty angels,
B053C001V008	53	1	8	in flaming fire, inflicting vengeance on those who do not know God, and on those who do not obey the gospel of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C001V009	53	1	9	These shall pay a penalty-eternal destruction from the presence of the Lord and from the glory of His might,
B053C001V010	53	1	10	whenever He comes, in that Day, to be glorified among His saints and to be marveled among all those having believed, because our testimony among you was believed.
B053C001V011	53	1	11	Therefore we also pray always concerning you that our God may count you worthy of [this] calling, and may fulfill all the good pleasure of His goodness and the work of faith with power,
B053C001V012	53	1	12	in order that the name of our Lord Jesus Christ may be glorified in you, and you in Him, according to the grace of our God and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C002V001	53	2	1	Now, brothers, concerning the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ and our gathering together to Him, we beseech you,
B053C002V002	53	2	2	not to be quickly shaken from your mind, nor be disturbed, neither by spirit nor by word nor by letter, as if from us, [as though] the day of Christ has come.
B053C002V003	53	2	3	Let no one deceive you by any means; for [that day will not come] unless the falling away comes first, and the man of sin is unveiled, the son of perdition,
B053C002V004	53	2	4	who opposes and exalts himself above all that is called God, or [every] object of worship, so that he sits as God in the temple of God, showing himself that he is God.
B053C002V005	53	2	5	Do you not remember that while I was still with you, I was telling you these things?
B053C002V006	53	2	6	And now you know that which is restraining, that he may be revealed in his own time.
B053C002V007	53	2	7	For the mystery of lawlessness is already at work; only He who now restrains [will continue ]until one arises from out of [the] midst.
B053C002V008	53	2	8	And then the lawless one will be unveiled, whom the Lord will consume with the breath of His mouth, and will destroy by the brightness of His coming,
B053C002V009	53	2	9	whose coming is according to the working of Satan, with all power, signs, and lying wonders,
B053C002V010	53	2	10	and in all deception of unrighteousness among those who perish, because they did not receive the love of the truth, that they might be saved.
B053C002V011	53	2	11	And because of this, God will send them strong delusion, in order for them to believe the lie,
B053C002V012	53	2	12	so that they all might be damned who did not believe the truth, but delighted in unrighteousness.
B053C002V013	53	2	13	But we are obligated to give thanks to God always for you, brothers beloved by the Lord, because God chose you from the beginning for salvation, through sanctification of the Spirit and belief in the truth,
B053C002V014	53	2	14	to which He called you through our gospel, for the obtaining of the glory of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C002V015	53	2	15	So then, brothers, stand fast and hold to the traditions which you were taught, whether by word or our letter.
B053C002V016	53	2	16	Now may our Lord Jesus Christ Himself, and our God and Father, who loved us and gave us eternal comfort and a good hope by grace,
B053C002V017	53	2	17	comfort your hearts and establish you in every good word and work.
B053C003V001	53	3	1	Finally, brothers, pray for us, that the word of the Lord may run and be glorified, just as [it is ]with you,
B053C003V002	53	3	2	and that we may be delivered from evil and wicked men; for not all have faith.
B053C003V003	53	3	3	But the Lord is faithful, who will establish you and will guard you from the evil one.
B053C003V004	53	3	4	And we trust in the Lord concerning you, that the[ ]things which we command to you, you are both doing, and will do [them.]
B053C003V005	53	3	5	Now may the Lord direct your hearts into the love of God and into the patience of Christ.
B053C003V006	53	3	6	But we command you, brothers, in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, that you keep away from every brother living in idleness, and not according to the tradition which they received from us.
B053C003V007	53	3	7	For you yourselves know how you ought to follow us, for we were not disorderly among you;
B053C003V008	53	3	8	nor did we eat bread from anyone without paying, but in labor and hardship, working night and day, so as not to be a burden to any of you,
B053C003V009	53	3	9	not because we do not have authority, but in order that we may give ourselves as a pattern to you, so that you might follow us.
B053C003V010	53	3	10	For even when we were with you, we commanded you this: If anyone is not willing to work, neither let him eat!
B053C003V011	53	3	11	For we hear [that] some are walking among you in a disorderly way, not working at all, but being busybodies.
B053C003V012	53	3	12	And to such [people] we command and urge by our Lord Jesus Christ that they work in quietness and eat their own bread.
B053C003V013	53	3	13	But as for you, brothers, do not lose heart [in] doing good.
B053C003V014	53	3	14	Now if anyone does not obey our word in this letter, take note of him, and do not associate with him, that he may be ashamed.
B053C003V015	53	3	15	Yet do not consider him as an enemy, but admonish [him] as a brother.
B053C003V016	53	3	16	Now may the Lord of peace Himself give you peace always in every way. The Lord be with you all.
B053C003V017	53	3	17	The greeting of Paul by my own hand, which is a sign in every letter; so I write.
B053C003V018	53	3	18	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you all. Amen.
B054C001V001	54	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ, according to [the] commandment of God our Savior and [the] Lord Jesus Christ, our hope,
B054C001V002	54	1	2	To Timothy, [my ]own son in the faith: Grace, mercy, and peace from God our Father and Christ Jesus our Lord.
B054C001V003	54	1	3	Just as I urged you to remain in Ephesus as I traveled into Macedonia, that you should command certain [people] not to teach differently,
B054C001V004	54	1	4	nor to pay attention to myths and endless genealogies, which cause disputes rather than godly edification which is in faith.
B054C001V005	54	1	5	Now the goal of the commandment is love out of a pure heart, from a good conscience, and from sincere faith,
B054C001V006	54	1	6	from which some, having strayed, have turned aside to futile talk,
B054C001V007	54	1	7	desiring to be teachers of the law, not understanding either what they say or what they affirm.
B054C001V008	54	1	8	But we know that the law is good if one uses it lawfully,
B054C001V009	54	1	9	knowing this: that the law is not laid down for the righteous, but for the lawless and insubordinate, for the ungodly and for sinners, for unholy and profane, for killers of fathers and killers of mothers, for murderers,
B054C001V010	54	1	10	for fornicators, for sodomites, for kidnappers, for liars, for perjurers, and if there is any other thing that is opposed to sound doctrine,
B054C001V011	54	1	11	according to the gospel of the glory of the blessed God, [with] which I was entrusted.
B054C001V012	54	1	12	And I give thanks to the [One] who empowers me, Christ Jesus our Lord, because He considered me faithful, putting me into the ministry,
B054C001V013	54	1	13	I, who was formerly a blasphemer, a persecutor, and an insolent man; but I was shown mercy, because, being ignorant, I did it in unbelief,
B054C001V014	54	1	14	and the grace of our Lord superabounded with faith and love which is in Christ Jesus.
B054C001V015	54	1	15	Faithful is this word, and worthy of all acceptance, that Christ Jesus came into the world to save sinners, of whom I am chief.
B054C001V016	54	1	16	However, because of this I was shown mercy, so that in me first Jesus Christ might show forth all longsuffering, as a pattern for those who are going to believe on Him for everlasting life.
B054C001V017	54	1	17	Now to the King of the Ages, immortal, invisible, [the] only wise God, [be] honor and glory forever and ever. Amen.
B054C001V018	54	1	18	This charge I commit to you, [my] son Timothy, according to the prophecies previously made concerning you, that you may war by them the good warfare,
B054C001V019	54	1	19	having faith and a good conscience, which some having rejected, concerning the faith have suffered shipwreck,
B054C001V020	54	1	20	of whom are Hymenaeus and Alexander, whom I handed over to Satan so that they may be taught not to blaspheme.
B054C002V001	54	2	1	Therefore I exhort first of all that supplications, prayers, intercessions, and thanksgivings be made on behalf of all men,
B054C002V002	54	2	2	on behalf of kings and all those who are in authority, that we may lead a tranquil and quiet life in all godliness and dignity.
B054C002V003	54	2	3	For this is good and acceptable before God our Savior,
B054C002V004	54	2	4	who desires all men to be saved and to come to the full knowledge of the truth.
B054C002V005	54	2	5	For there is one God and one Mediator between God and men, the Man Christ Jesus,
B054C002V006	54	2	6	who gave Himself a ransom for all, the testimony in due time;
B054C002V007	54	2	7	for which I was appointed a herald and apostle-I speak the truth in Christ, I do not lie-a teacher of Gentiles in faith and truth.
B054C002V008	54	2	8	I desire therefore that men pray in every place, lifting up holy hands, without wrath and doubting.
B054C002V009	54	2	9	Likewise also that the women adorn themselves in modest apparel, with propriety and discretion, not with braids or gold or pearls or expensive clothing,
B054C002V010	54	2	10	but which is fitting for women professing godliness, by means of good works.
B054C002V011	54	2	11	Let a woman learn in silence with all submission.
B054C002V012	54	2	12	And I do not permit a woman to teach, nor to have authority over a man, but to be in silence.
B054C002V013	54	2	13	For Adam first was formed, then Eve.
B054C002V014	54	2	14	And Adam was not deceived, but the woman being deceived, has come to be in transgression.
B054C002V015	54	2	15	Nevertheless she shall be saved through childbirth, if they remain in faith and love, and sanctification, with self-control.
B054C003V001	54	3	1	Faithful is this word: If anyone aspires to the position of a bishop, he desires a good work.
B054C003V002	54	3	2	It is necessary, therefore, for a bishop to be irreproachable, the husband of one wife, temperate, sober-minded, well-behaved, hospitable, skillful at teaching;
B054C003V003	54	3	3	not given to wine, not a bully, not greedy for money, but gentle, not quarrelsome, not loving money;
B054C003V004	54	3	4	one ruling his own house well, having [his] children in submission with all reverence;
B054C003V005	54	3	5	(for if one does not know how to rule his own house, how will he take care of the church of God?);
B054C003V006	54	3	6	not a new convert, lest being puffed up [with pride] he fall into the [same] condemnation as the devil.
B054C003V007	54	3	7	Moreover he must have a good testimony among those outside, lest he fall into reproach and the snare of the devil.
B054C003V008	54	3	8	Likewise deacons must be reverent, not double-tongued, not being given to much wine, not greedy for money,
B054C003V009	54	3	9	holding the mystery of the faith with a pure conscience.
B054C003V010	54	3	10	But let these also first be tested; then let them serve as deacons, being irreproachable.
B054C003V011	54	3	11	Likewise their wives must be reverent, not slanderers, temperate, faithful in all things.
B054C003V012	54	3	12	Let deacons be the husbands of one wife, ruling their children well, and their own houses.
B054C003V013	54	3	13	For those who have served well as deacons obtain a standing for themselves and much boldness in the faith which is in Christ Jesus.
B054C003V014	54	3	14	These things I write to you, hoping to come to you shortly;
B054C003V015	54	3	15	but if I am delayed, [I write] so that you may know how it is necessary to conduct oneself in the house of God, which is the church of the living God, the pillar and bulwark of the truth.
B054C003V016	54	3	16	And confessedly, great is the mystery of godliness: God was manifested in the flesh, justified in the Spirit, seen by angels, proclaimed among [the ]Gentiles, believed on in the world, [and ]was received up in glory.
B054C004V001	54	4	1	But the Spirit explicitly says, that in latter times some shall fall away from the faith, giving heed to deceiving spirits and doctrines of demons,
B054C004V002	54	4	2	speaking lies in hypocrisy, having been seared with a hot iron [as to ]their own conscience,
B054C004V003	54	4	3	forbidding to marry, [commanding] to abstain from foods which God created to be received with thanksgiving by those who are believers and have come to know the truth.
B054C004V004	54	4	4	Because every creature of God is good, and not one is to be rejected, being received with thanksgiving,
B054C004V005	54	4	5	for it is sanctified through the word of God and prayer.
B054C004V006	54	4	6	Instructing the brothers in these things, you will be a good minister of Jesus Christ, being nourished by the words of faith and of the good doctrine which you have carefully followed.
B054C004V007	54	4	7	But reject profane and old wives' tales, and exercise yourself unto godliness.
B054C004V008	54	4	8	For bodily exercise is profitable a little, but godliness is profitable for all things, having promise of the present life and of the coming life.
B054C004V009	54	4	9	Trustworthy is this word and worthy of all acceptance.
B054C004V010	54	4	10	For to this end we both labor and suffer reproach, because we trust in the living God, who is the Savior of all men, especially of believers.
B054C004V011	54	4	11	These things command and teach.
B054C004V012	54	4	12	Let no one look down on your youthfulness, but [rather ]become a pattern for the believers in word, in conduct, in love, in spirit, in faith, in purity.
B054C004V013	54	4	13	Until I come, give attention to [public] reading, to exhortation, to doctrine.
B054C004V014	54	4	14	Do not neglect the gift that is in you, which was given to you through prophecy with the laying on of the hands of the eldership.
B054C004V015	54	4	15	Meditate on these things; be in these things[, ]so that your progress may be evident to all.
B054C004V016	54	4	16	Take heed to yourself and to the doctrine. Continue in them, for by doing this you will save both yourself and those who hear you.
B054C005V001	54	5	1	Do not sharply rebuke an older man, but [rather ]exhort him as a father, younger men as brothers,
B054C005V002	54	5	2	older women as mothers, younger women as sisters, with all purity.
B054C005V003	54	5	3	Honor widows who are really widows.
B054C005V004	54	5	4	But if a certain widow has children or grandchildren, let them first learn to show piety to their own household and to make repayment to their parents; for this is acceptable before God.
B054C005V005	54	5	5	Now she who is really a widow and having been left alone, has set her hope on God, and continues in supplications and prayers night and day.
B054C005V006	54	5	6	But she who is living for pleasure is dead while she lives.
B054C005V007	54	5	7	And these things command, so that they may be blameless.
B054C005V008	54	5	8	But if anyone does not provide for his own, and especially for those of his [own] house, he has denied the faith and is worse than an unbeliever.
B054C005V009	54	5	9	Let a widow be enrolled having become not less than sixty years, [the] wife of one man,
B054C005V010	54	5	10	having a reputation for good works, if she has brought up children, if she has lodged strangers, if she has washed the saints' feet, if she has relieved the afflicted, if she has diligently followed every good work.
B054C005V011	54	5	11	But refuse [to enroll] the younger widows; for whenever they grow lustful against Christ, they desire to marry,
B054C005V012	54	5	12	having condemnation because they have set aside their first faith.
B054C005V013	54	5	13	And besides they learn to be idle, going around from house to house, and not only idle but also gossipy and busybodies, speaking things [which are] not proper.
B054C005V014	54	5	14	Therefore I desire that the younger widows to marry, to bear children, to manage the house, to give no opportunity to the adversary because of reproach.
B054C005V015	54	5	15	For already some have turned aside after Satan.
B054C005V016	54	5	16	If any believing man or believing woman has widows, let [that one] relieve them, and do not let the church be burdened, that it may relieve those who are really widows.
B054C005V017	54	5	17	Let the elders having ruled well be counted worthy of double honor, especially those who labor in the word and doctrine.
B054C005V018	54	5	18	For the Scripture says, "You shall not muzzle an ox threshing [grain],"and, "The worker is worthy of his wages."
B054C005V019	54	5	19	Do not receive an accusation against an elder unless on [the basis of] two or three witnesses.
B054C005V020	54	5	20	Those who are sinning rebuke before all, that the rest also may have fear.
B054C005V021	54	5	21	I charge you before God and the Lord Jesus Christ and the elect angels that you observe these things without prejudice, doing nothing according to partiality.
B054C005V022	54	5	22	Lay hands on no one hastily, nor share in [the] sins of others; keep yourself pure.
B054C005V023	54	5	23	No longer drink water [only], but use a little wine on account of your stomach, and your frequent illnesses.
B054C005V024	54	5	24	The sins of some men are evident beforehand, preceding them to judgment, but some also follow after.
B054C005V025	54	5	25	Likewise also the good works [of some] are evident beforehand, and those which are otherwise cannot be hidden.
B054C006V001	54	6	1	Let as many as are slaves under a yoke count their own masters worthy of all honor, so that the name of God and His doctrine may not be blasphemed.
B054C006V002	54	6	2	And those having believing masters, let them not despise them because they are brothers, but rather let them serve as slaves, because those receiving the good service are believing and beloved. Teach and exhort these things.
B054C006V003	54	6	3	If anyone teaches differently and does not consent to sound words, even those of our Lord Jesus Christ, and to the doctrine which accords with godliness,
B054C006V004	54	6	4	he is puffed up, understanding nothing, but [is] morbidly concerned with disputes and word battles, from which come envy, strife, slanders, evil suspicions,
B054C006V005	54	6	5	constant wranglings of men of corrupt minds and having been deprived of the truth, supposing that godliness is a means of profit. Withdraw from such [people].
B054C006V006	54	6	6	But godliness with contentment is great gain.
B054C006V007	54	6	7	For we brought nothing into this world, and it is certain that neither can we carry anything out!
B054C006V008	54	6	8	But having food and clothing, with these things we shall be content.
B054C006V009	54	6	9	But those desiring to be rich fall into temptation and a snare, and many senseless and harmful lusts which sink men into destruction and perdition.
B054C006V010	54	6	10	For the love of money is[ the] root of all evil, of which some [by] aspiring have strayed away from the faith in their greediness, and pierced themselves through with many sorrows.
B054C006V011	54	6	11	You however, O man of God, flee these things. But pursue righteousness, godliness, faith, love, endurance, gentleness.
B054C006V012	54	6	12	Fight the good fight of faith, lay hold of eternal life, to which you were called and have confessed the good confession before many witnesses.
B054C006V013	54	6	13	I charge you before God who gives life to all things, and before Christ Jesus who witnessed the good confession before Pontius Pilate,
B054C006V014	54	6	14	that you keep this commandment without spot, blameless until the appearing of our Lord Jesus Christ,
B054C006V015	54	6	15	which He will show in His own time, He who is the blessed and only Sovereign, the King of kings and Lord of lords,
B054C006V016	54	6	16	who alone has immortality, dwelling in unapproachable light, whom no man has seen or is able to see, to whom be honor and everlasting power. Amen.
B054C006V017	54	6	17	Command those who are rich in this present age not to be haughty, nor to put their hope on the uncertainty of riches, but in the living God, who provides all things richly for us to enjoy,
B054C006V018	54	6	18	to do good, to be rich in good works, to be generous, sharing,
B054C006V019	54	6	19	storing up for yourselves a good foundation for the future, that they may lay hold of eternal life.
B054C006V020	54	6	20	O Timothy! Guard that which was committed to your trust, turning away from the profane and empty babblings and opposing views of what is falsely called "knowledge,"
B054C006V021	54	6	21	which some, by professing [expertise,] missed the mark concerning the faith. Grace be with you. Amen.
B055C001V001	55	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the will of God, according to the promise of life which [is] in Christ Jesus,
B055C001V002	55	1	2	To Timothy, [my ]beloved son: Grace, mercy, and peace from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Lord.
B055C001V003	55	1	3	I give thanks to God, whom I serve with a pure conscience, as my forefathers did, how unceasingly I have remembrance of you in my prayers night and day,
B055C001V004	55	1	4	longing to see you, having recalled your tears, that I may be filled with joy,
B055C001V005	55	1	5	taking recollection of the genuine faith [that is] in you, which dwelt first in your grandmother Lois and in your mother Eunice, and I am persuaded is in you also.
B055C001V006	55	1	6	For which cause I remind you to stir up the gift of God which is in you through the laying on of my hands.
B055C001V007	55	1	7	For God has not given us a spirit of fear, but of power and of love and of a sound mind.
B055C001V008	55	1	8	Therefore do not be ashamed of the testimony of our Lord, nor of me His prisoner, but endure hardship with the gospel according to the power of God,
B055C001V009	55	1	9	who having saved us, and having called us with a holy calling, not according to our works, but according to His own purpose and grace which was given to us in Christ Jesus before time [itself],
B055C001V010	55	1	10	but has now been revealed through the appearance of our Savior Jesus Christ, having abolished death on the one hand, [and] having brought to life immortality through the gospel on the other,
B055C001V011	55	1	11	to which I was appointed a herald and apostle, and a teacher of the Gentiles.
B055C001V012	55	1	12	For which cause I also suffer these things; but I am not ashamed, for I know whom I have believed, and I have been persuaded that He is able to guard that which I have committed to Him until that Day.
B055C001V013	55	1	13	Hold to the pattern of sound words which you have heard from me, in faith and love which are in Christ Jesus.
B055C001V014	55	1	14	That good thing which was committed to you, guard by the Holy Spirit who dwells in us.
B055C001V015	55	1	15	This you know, that all those in Asia have turned away from me, of whom are Phygellus and Hermogenes.
B055C001V016	55	1	16	May the Lord grant mercy to the household of Onesiphorus, because he often refreshed me, and he was not ashamed of my chain;
B055C001V017	55	1	17	but when he arrived in Rome, he more diligently sought me out and found [me].
B055C001V018	55	1	18	May the Lord grant to him to find mercy from the Lord in that Day-and you very well know how many ways he served in Ephesus.
B055C002V001	55	2	1	You therefore, my child, be empowered by the grace which is in Christ Jesus.
B055C002V002	55	2	2	And the things which you have heard from me through many witnesses, commit these to faithful men who will be competent to teach others also.
B055C002V003	55	2	3	You therefore endure hardship as a good soldier of Jesus Christ.
B055C002V004	55	2	4	No one serving as a soldier entangles [himself] in the affairs of [civilian] life, in order that he may please the [one] having enlisted him.
B055C002V005	55	2	5	And also if anyone competes in athletics, he is not crowned unless he competes according to the rules.
B055C002V006	55	2	6	It is necessary for the hard-working farmer [to be] first to receive of the fruits.
B055C002V007	55	2	7	Consider the things I say, and may the Lord give you understanding in all things.
B055C002V008	55	2	8	Remember that Jesus Christ, of the seed of David, was raised from the dead according to my gospel,
B055C002V009	55	2	9	in which I endure hardship unto chains as an evildoer; but the word of God is not chained.
B055C002V010	55	2	10	Because of this, I endure all things for the sake of the elect, that they also may obtain the salvation which is in Christ Jesus with eternal glory.
B055C002V011	55	2	11	Faithful is this word: For if we died with [Him], we shall also live with [Him].
B055C002V012	55	2	12	If we endure, we shall also reign with [Him]. If we deny [Him], He also will deny us.
B055C002V013	55	2	13	If we are faithless, He remains faithful; He cannot deny Himself.
B055C002V014	55	2	14	Remind them of these things, charging them before the Lord not to dispute about words, useful for nothing, for the ruin of the hearers.
B055C002V015	55	2	15	Be diligent to show yourself approved unto God, a worker unashamed, rightly dividing the word of truth.
B055C002V016	55	2	16	But shun profane and empty babblings; for they will advance to more ungodliness.
B055C002V017	55	2	17	And their word will spread like gangrene; of whom are Hymenaeus and Philetus,
B055C002V018	55	2	18	who have strayed concerning the truth, asserting that the resurrection has already occurred; and they overturn the faith of some.
B055C002V019	55	2	19	Nevertheless the firm foundation of God stands, having this seal: "The Lord knows those that are His,"and, "Let everyone naming the name of the Lord depart from unrighteousness."
B055C002V020	55	2	20	Now in a great house there are not only vessels of gold and silver, but also of wood and clay, some for honor and some for dishonor.
B055C002V021	55	2	21	Therefore if anyone cleanses himself from the [latter], he will be a vessel for honor, having been consecrated and useful to the Master, having been prepared for every good work.
B055C002V022	55	2	22	Flee youthful lusts; but pursue righteousness, faith, love, peace with those who call on the Lord out of a pure heart.
B055C002V023	55	2	23	But reject foolish and ignorant disputes, knowing that they bring forth fights.
B055C002V024	55	2	24	And a servant of the Lord ought not to fight, but to be gentle to all, skillful at teaching, forbearing,
B055C002V025	55	2	25	in meekness instructing those that oppose, if God perhaps may give them repentance, to a full knowledge of the truth,
B055C002V026	55	2	26	and they regain their senses [and escape] out of the snare of the devil, having been captured alive by him to do his will.
B055C003V001	55	3	1	But know this, that in the last days perilous times shall come.
B055C003V002	55	3	2	For men will be lovers of themselves, lovers of money, boasters, proud, blasphemers, disobedient to parents, unthankful, unholy,
B055C003V003	55	3	3	unloving, unforgiving, slanderers, without self-control, brutal, not loving what is good,
B055C003V004	55	3	4	traitors, headstrong, having been puffed up, lovers of pleasure rather than lovers of God,
B055C003V005	55	3	5	having a form of godliness but denying its power. And from these people turn away!
B055C003V006	55	3	6	For of these are those [who] creep into houses and captivate gullible women having been loaded down with sins, who are led by various lusts,
B055C003V007	55	3	7	always learning and never being able to come to a full knowledge of the truth.
B055C003V008	55	3	8	And in just the way Jannes and Jambres resisted Moses, thus also these resist the truth: men corrupted in mind, disapproved regarding the faith.
B055C003V009	55	3	9	But they shall not advance further, for their folly shall be manifest to all, as also theirs became.
B055C003V010	55	3	10	You however have carefully followed my doctrine, lifestyle, purpose, faith, patience, love, endurance,
B055C003V011	55	3	11	persecutions, [and ]afflictions, which happened to me at Antioch, in Iconium, at Lystra-what persecutions I endured. And out of them all the Lord delivered me.
B055C003V012	55	3	12	Yes, and all who desire to live godly in Christ Jesus will be persecuted.
B055C003V013	55	3	13	But evil men and impostors shall advance worse and worse, deceiving and being deceived.
B055C003V014	55	3	14	But you must continue in the things which you have learned and been assured of, knowing from whom you learned them,
B055C003V015	55	3	15	and that from childhood you have known the Holy Scriptures, which are able to make you wise to salvation through faith which is in Christ Jesus.
B055C003V016	55	3	16	All Scripture is given by inspiration of God, and is profitable for doctrine, for reproof, for correction, for instruction in righteousness,
B055C003V017	55	3	17	that the man of God may be proficient, having been thoroughly equipped for every good work.
B055C004V001	55	4	1	I charge you therefore before God and the Lord Jesus Christ, who is going to judge the living and the dead in accordance with His appearing and His kingdom:
B055C004V002	55	4	2	preach the word! Be ready in season and out of season. Reprove, rebuke, exhort, with all patience and teaching.
B055C004V003	55	4	3	For there will be a time when they will not put up with sound doctrine, but according to their own lusts, they will heap up for themselves teachers, tickling their ears,
B055C004V004	55	4	4	and they will turn their ears away from the truth, and be turned aside to myths.
B055C004V005	55	4	5	You however be watchful in all things, endure hardship, do the work of an evangelist, fulfill your ministry.
B055C004V006	55	4	6	For I am already being poured out [as a drink offering], and the time of my departure has arrived.
B055C004V007	55	4	7	I have fought the good fight. I have finished the race, I have kept the faith.
B055C004V008	55	4	8	Finally, there is laid up for me the crown of righteousness, which the Lord, the righteous Judge, will give to me on that Day, and not only to me, but also to all those who have loved His appearing.
B055C004V009	55	4	9	Be diligent to come to me quickly.
B055C004V010	55	4	10	For Demas has forsaken me, having loved this present world, and traveled to Thessalonica-Crescens to Galatia, Titus to Dalmatia.
B055C004V011	55	4	11	Luke alone is with me. Take Mark, and bring him with you, for he is useful to me for ministry.
B055C004V012	55	4	12	And Tychicus I have sent to Ephesus.
B055C004V013	55	4	13	Bring the cloak which I left with Carpus at Troas when you come-and the books, especially the parchments.
B055C004V014	55	4	14	Alexander the coppersmith did me much harm. May the Lord repay him according to his works;
B055C004V015	55	4	15	whom you also should guard against, for he has greatly resisted our words.
B055C004V016	55	4	16	At my first defense no one stood with me, but all forsook me. May it not be reckoned to them.
B055C004V017	55	4	17	But the Lord stood by me and strengthened me, so that through me the proclamation might be fulfilled, and all the Gentiles might hear, and I was delivered out of the mouth of the lion.
B055C004V018	55	4	18	And the Lord shall deliver me from every evil work and preserve me for His heavenly kingdom. To Him [be] glory forever and ever. Amen!
B055C004V019	55	4	19	Greet Prisca and Aquila, and the household of Onesiphorus.
B055C004V020	55	4	20	Erastus stayed in Corinth, but Trophimus I have left in Miletus sick.
B055C004V021	55	4	21	Be diligent to come before winter. Eubulus greets you, as well as Pudens, Linus, Claudia, and all the brothers.
B055C004V022	55	4	22	The Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit. Grace be with you. Amen.
B056C001V001	56	1	1	Paul, a bondservant of God and an apostle of Jesus Christ, according to [the] faith of the elect of God and [the] full knowledge of [the] truth which is according to godliness,
B056C001V002	56	1	2	in hope of eternal life which God, who cannot lie, promised before time [itself],
B056C001V003	56	1	3	but has in due time manifested His word in a proclamation, [with ]which I was entrusted according to the command of God our Savior;
B056C001V004	56	1	4	To Titus, [my ]own son according to [our] common faith: Grace, mercy, and peace from God [the] Father and [the] Lord Jesus Christ our Savior.
B056C001V005	56	1	5	For this reason I left you behind in Crete, so that you should set in order the things[ ]that are lacking, and you should appoint elders in every city as I commanded you:
B056C001V006	56	1	6	if a man is unimpeachable, the husband of one wife, having faithful children not accused of dissipation or [who are ]insubordinate.
B056C001V007	56	1	7	For a bishop must be unimpeachable, as God's steward, not self-willed, not quick-tempered, not given to wine, not violent, not greedy for money,
B056C001V008	56	1	8	but hospitable, loving good, prudent, just, holy, temperate,
B056C001V009	56	1	9	holding fast to the faithful word as he was taught, that he may be able to exhort by sound doctrine, and to convince those who oppose it.
B056C001V010	56	1	10	For there are also many insubordinate, both idle talkers and deceivers, especially those of the circumcision,
B056C001V011	56	1	11	whom it is necessary to shut [their] mouths, who overturn whole households, teaching things which they ought not, for the sake of dishonest gain.
B056C001V012	56	1	12	There said a certain one of them, a prophet of their own, "Cretans are always liars, evil beasts, idle gluttons."
B056C001V013	56	1	13	This testimony is true; for which cause rebuke them sharply, that they may be sound in the faith,
B056C001V014	56	1	14	not giving heed to Jewish myths and to commands of men turning away from the truth.
B056C001V015	56	1	15	All things indeed are pure to the pure; but to those who are defiled and unbelieving nothing is pure; but even their mind and conscience have been defiled.
B056C001V016	56	1	16	They profess to know God, but in their works they deny Him, being abominable, disobedient, and disqualified for every good work.
B056C002V001	56	2	1	But you speak the[ ]things which suit sound doctrine.
B056C002V002	56	2	2	Older men are to be sober, serious, temperate, sound in the faith, in love, in endurance.
B056C002V003	56	2	3	Older women likewise are to be reverent in demeanor, not slanderers, not given to much wine, teaching what is good,
B056C002V004	56	2	4	so that they may urge the young women to be lovers of their husbands, lovers of their children,
B056C002V005	56	2	5	temperate, pure, homemakers, good, submitting to their own husbands, lest the word of God be blasphemed.
B056C002V006	56	2	6	Likewise exhort the young men to be sensible,
B056C002V007	56	2	7	in all respects showing yourself to be a pattern of good works; in doctrine showing integrity, dignity, incorruptibility,
B056C002V008	56	2	8	sound speech that cannot be condemned, in order that the [one] who is an opponent may be put to shame, having nothing bad to say about us.
B056C002V009	56	2	9	[Exhort] bondservants to be subject to their own masters, to be well pleasing in all things, not talking back,
B056C002V010	56	2	10	not embezzling, but showing good faith, so that they may adorn the doctrine of God our Savior in all things.
B056C002V011	56	2	11	For the saving grace of God has appeared to all men,
B056C002V012	56	2	12	teaching us that, denying ungodliness and worldly lusts, we should live soberly, righteously, and godly in the present age,
B056C002V013	56	2	13	looking for the blessed hope and glorious appearing of our great God and Savior Jesus Christ,
B056C002V014	56	2	14	who gave Himself for us, that He might redeem us from every lawless deed and purify for Himself a people as [His] own possession, zealous for good works.
B056C002V015	56	2	15	Speak these things, exhort and rebuke with all authority. Let no one despise you.
B056C003V001	56	3	1	Remind them to be subject to rulers and authorities, to be obedient, to be ready for every good work,
B056C003V002	56	3	2	to slander no one, to be peaceable, gentle, demonstrating all meekness to all men.
B056C003V003	56	3	3	For we ourselves were also once foolish, disobedient, being deceived, being enslaved to various lusts and pleasures, living in malice and envy, hateful, and hating one another.
B056C003V004	56	3	4	But when the kindness and the love of God our Savior toward man appeared,
B056C003V005	56	3	5	not by works of righteousness which we did, but according to His mercy He saved us, through the washing of regeneration and renewing of the Holy Spirit,
B056C003V006	56	3	6	whom He poured out on us richly through Jesus Christ our Savior,
B056C003V007	56	3	7	that having been justified by His grace we might become heirs according to the hope of eternal life.
B056C003V008	56	3	8	Faithful is this word, and concerning these things I want you to strongly affirm, so that those who have believed in God may take thought to maintain good works. These things are good and profitable to men.
B056C003V009	56	3	9	But avoid foolish disputes and genealogies, and strifes and legal fights; for they are unprofitable and futile.
B056C003V010	56	3	10	Reject a divisive man after the first and second admonition,
B056C003V011	56	3	11	knowing that such a person has been perverted and is sinning, being self-condemned.
B056C003V012	56	3	12	Whenever I shall send Artemas to you, or Tychicus, hasten to come to me at Nicopolis, for I have decided to spend the winter there.
B056C003V013	56	3	13	Speedily send forward Zenas the lawyer and Apollos, in order that they may lack nothing.
B056C003V014	56	3	14	And let our [people] also learn to maintain good works, to meet urgent needs, lest they be unfruitful.
B056C003V015	56	3	15	All[ ]who [are] with me greet you. Greet those who love us in the faith. Grace be with you all. Amen.
B057C001V001	57	1	1	Paul, a prisoner of Christ Jesus, and Timothy our brother, to Philemon our beloved and fellow worker,
B057C001V002	57	1	2	to Apphia the beloved, and to Archippus our fellow soldier, and to the church at your house:
B057C001V003	57	1	3	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B057C001V004	57	1	4	I thank my God, always making mention of you in my prayers,
B057C001V005	57	1	5	hearing of your love and faith which you have toward the Lord Jesus and toward all the saints,
B057C001V006	57	1	6	that the sharing of your faith may become effective in full knowledge of every good thing which is in us in Christ Jesus.
B057C001V007	57	1	7	For we have much thanksgiving and encouragement over your love, because the affections of the saints have been refreshed through you, brother.
B057C001V008	57	1	8	Therefore, having much boldness in Christ to command you what is fitting,
B057C001V009	57	1	9	rather on account of love I appeal to you-being such a one as Paul, the elder, and now also a prisoner of Jesus Christ-
B057C001V010	57	1	10	I appeal to you for my son Onesimus, whose father I became in my imprisonment,
B057C001V011	57	1	11	who formerly was unprofitable to you, but now is profitable both to you and to me,
B057C001V012	57	1	12	whom I am sending back. You therefore receive him, that is, my very heart;
B057C001V013	57	1	13	whom I wished to keep with myself, in order that on your behalf he might serve me in the bonds of the gospel.
B057C001V014	57	1	14	But I wished to do nothing without your consent, in order that your good might not be by necessity, but by [being] voluntary.
B057C001V015	57	1	15	For perhaps he was taken away for a time on account of this, in order that you might keep him eternally,
B057C001V016	57	1	16	no longer as a slave but more than a slave-a beloved brother, especially to me but how much more to you, both in the flesh and in the Lord.
B057C001V017	57	1	17	If then you count me as a partner, receive him as [you would ]me.
B057C001V018	57	1	18	But if he has wronged you or owes [anything], charge this to me.
B057C001V019	57	1	19	I, Paul, am writing with my own hand. I will repay-lest I say to you that even yourself you owe to me!
B057C001V020	57	1	20	Yes, brother, may I have profit from you in the Lord; refresh my heart in the Lord.
B057C001V021	57	1	21	Having been persuaded of your obedience, I am writing to you, knowing that you will do even beyond what I say.
B057C001V022	57	1	22	But meanwhile, also prepare for me a guestroom, for I hope that through your prayers I will be graciously given to you.
B057C001V023	57	1	23	Epaphras, my fellow captive in Christ Jesus, greets you,
B057C001V024	57	1	24	[ as do] Mark, Aristarchus, Demas, Luke, my fellow workers.
B057C001V025	57	1	25	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit. Amen.
B058C001V001	58	1	1	God, who at various times and in various ways spoke in time past to the fathers by the prophets,
B058C001V002	58	1	2	has in these last days spoken to us by [His] Son, whom He has appointed heir [of] all things, through whom also He made the worlds;
B058C001V003	58	1	3	who being the radiance of His glory and the exact expression of His substance, and upholding all things by the word of His power, when He had by Himself purged our sins, sat down at the right hand of the Majesty on high,
B058C001V004	58	1	4	having become so much better than the angels, as He has inherited a more excellent name than they.
B058C001V005	58	1	5	For to which of the angels did He ever say: "You are My Son, today I have begotten You"? And again: "I will be a Father to Him, and He shall be a Son to Me"?
B058C001V006	58	1	6	But when He again brings the firstborn into the world, He says: "Let all the angels of God worship Him."
B058C001V007	58	1	7	And of the angels He says, "He who makes His angels spirits and His ministers flames of fire."
B058C001V008	58	1	8	But of the Son [He says]: "Your throne, O God, is forever and ever; the scepter of righteousness is the scepter of Your Kingdom.
B058C001V009	58	1	9	You have loved righteousness and hated lawlessness; therefore God, Your God, has anointed You with the oil of gladness above Your companions."
B058C001V010	58	1	10	And: "You, LORD, in the beginning laid the foundation of the earth, and the heavens are the work of Your hands.
B058C001V011	58	1	11	They shall perish, but You continue; and they all shall grow old like a garment;
B058C001V012	58	1	12	and like a cloak You will roll them up, and they shall be changed. But You are the same, and Your years shall not fail."
B058C001V013	58	1	13	But to which of the angels has He ever said: "Sit at My right hand, till I make Your enemies a footstool for Your feet"?
B058C001V014	58	1	14	Are they not all ministering spirits being sent out to minister for the sake of those who shall be heirs of salvation?
B058C002V001	58	2	1	On account of this we must give the more earnest heed to the things we have heard, lest we drift away.
B058C002V002	58	2	2	For if the word which was spoken through angels was confirmed, and every transgression and disobedience received a just retribution,
B058C002V003	58	2	3	how shall we escape if we neglect so great a salvation, which in the beginning was spoken by the Lord, and was confirmed to us by those who heard,
B058C002V004	58	2	4	God also bearing witness both with signs and wonders, with various miracles, and gifts of the Holy Spirit, according to His own will?
B058C002V005	58	2	5	For He did not subject the world which is to come, concerning which we speak, to angels.
B058C002V006	58	2	6	But someone somewhere testified, saying: "What is man that You are mindful of him, or the son of man that You visit him?
B058C002V007	58	2	7	You made him a little lower than the angels, You crowned him with glory and honor,
B058C002V008	58	2	8	You have subjected all things under his feet."For in subjecting to him all things[, ]He left nothing not subjected to him. But now we do not yet see all things having been subjected to him.
B058C002V009	58	2	9	But we see Jesus, who was made a little lower than the angels, through the suffering of death, having been crowned with glory and honor, so that by the grace of God, He might taste death for everyone.
B058C002V010	58	2	10	For it was fitting for Him, on account of whom [are] all things and through whom [are] all things, in bringing many sons to glory, to perfect the Author of their salvation through sufferings.
B058C002V011	58	2	11	For both He who sanctifies and those who are being sanctified are all of one; for which reason He is not ashamed to call them brothers,
B058C002V012	58	2	12	saying: "I will declare Your name to My brothers; in the midst of the congregation I will sing praise to You."
B058C002V013	58	2	13	And again: "I will put My trust in Him."And again: "Behold I and the children to whom God has given Me."
B058C002V014	58	2	14	Therefore since the children have partaken of flesh and blood, He Himself likewise shared in the same things, in order that through death He might destroy the [one] having the power of death, that is, the devil,
B058C002V015	58	2	15	and that He might set free these, as many as by fear of death through all of their lives, were subject to bondage.
B058C002V016	58	2	16	For indeed He does not take hold of angels, but He does take hold of the seed of Abraham.
B058C002V017	58	2	17	Therefore He was obligated to become like His brothers in all [respects], in order that He might become a merciful and faithful High Priest in things [pertaining] to God, in order that He might make propitiation for the sins of the people.
B058C002V018	58	2	18	For in that which He Himself has suffered, being tempted, He is able to help those who are tempted.
B058C003V001	58	3	1	Therefore, holy brothers, partakers of the heavenly calling, consider the Apostle and High Priest of our confession, Jesus Christ,
B058C003V002	58	3	2	who is faithful to Him who appointed Him, as Moses also was faithful in all His house.
B058C003V003	58	3	3	For He has been counted worthy of more honor than Moses, inasmuch as He who built the house has more honor than the house.
B058C003V004	58	3	4	For every house is built by someone, but He[ ]who built all things is God.
B058C003V005	58	3	5	And Moses indeed was faithful in all His house as a servant, for a testimony of the things which would be spoken,
B058C003V006	58	3	6	but Christ [was faithful ]as a Son over His own house, whose house we are if we hold fast the confidence and the boast of hope firm until [the] end.
B058C003V007	58	3	7	Therefore, just as the Holy Spirit says: "Today, if you will hear His voice,
B058C003V008	58	3	8	Do not harden your hearts as in the rebellion, in the day of trial in the wilderness,
B058C003V009	58	3	9	Where your fathers tested Me, they tried Me, and saw My works forty years.
B058C003V010	58	3	10	Therefore I was indignant with that generation, and said, 'They go astray in their heart; and they did not know My ways.'
B058C003V011	58	3	11	So I swore in My wrath, 'They shall not enter My rest.'
B058C003V012	58	3	12	Take heed, brothers, lest there be in any one of you a wicked heart of unbelief in departing from the living God;
B058C003V013	58	3	13	but encourage yourselves every day, while it is called "Today,"lest any of you be hardened through the deceitfulness of sin.
B058C003V014	58	3	14	For we have become partakers of Christ, if indeed we hold fast the beginning of the assurance firm until the end,
B058C003V015	58	3	15	while it is said: "Today, if you hear His voice, do not harden your hearts as in the rebellion."
B058C003V016	58	3	16	For some, having heard, did provoke: but not all who came out of Egypt through Moses.
B058C003V017	58	3	17	And with whom was He indignant forty years? Was it not with those who sinned, whose carcasses fell in the wilderness?
B058C003V018	58	3	18	And to whom did He swear that they would not enter into His rest, except to those who disobeyed?
B058C003V019	58	3	19	And we see that they were not able to enter on account of unbelief.
B058C004V001	58	4	1	Therefore let us fear, lest while the promise remains to enter into His rest, any one of you seems to have fallen short.
B058C004V002	58	4	2	For indeed we have had the gospel preached [to us] just as those also; but the word which they heard did not profit those, not having been mixed with faith in those having heard it.
B058C004V003	58	4	3	For we who have believed enter that rest, as He has said: "So I swore in My wrath, they shall not enter My rest,"although His works were finished from the foundation of the world.
B058C004V004	58	4	4	For He has said somewhere concerning the seventh day thus, "And God rested on the seventh day from all His works;"
B058C004V005	58	4	5	and again in this place: "They shall not enter My rest."
B058C004V006	58	4	6	Therefore since it remains [for] some to enter into it, and those formerly having the gospel preached [to them] did not enter on account of disobedience,
B058C004V007	58	4	7	again He appoints a certain day, saying in David, "Today,"after such a time, just as it has been said: "Today, if you will hear His voice, do not harden your hearts."
B058C004V008	58	4	8	For if Joshua had given them rest, then He would not have spoken afterward of another day.
B058C004V009	58	4	9	Then there remains a Sabbath rest for the people of God.
B058C004V010	58	4	10	For he who has entered into His rest also rested himself from his works, as God [did] from His own.
B058C004V011	58	4	11	Therefore let us be diligent to enter into that rest, lest anyone falls in the same example of disobedience.
B058C004V012	58	4	12	For the word of God is living and active, and sharper than any two-edged sword, piercing even to the division of soul and spirit, and of joints and marrow, and is a discerner of the thoughts and intentions of the heart.
B058C004V013	58	4	13	And there is no creature hidden before Him, but all things are naked and open to His eyes, to whom we must give an account.
B058C004V014	58	4	14	Therefore having a great High Priest who has passed through the heavens, Jesus the Son of God, let us hold fast the confession.
B058C004V015	58	4	15	For we do not have a High Priest who cannot sympathize with our weaknesses, but having been tempted in all [respects] in quite the same way as [we are], yet without sin.
B058C004V016	58	4	16	Therefore let us come boldly to the throne of grace, so that we may receive mercy and find grace to help in time of need.
B058C005V001	58	5	1	For every high priest taken from among men is appointed for men in the things pertaining to God, that he may offer both gifts and sacrifices for sins,
B058C005V002	58	5	2	being able to deal gently with those who sin in ignorance and go astray, since he himself is also subject to weakness.
B058C005V003	58	5	3	On account of this he is obligated to offer [sacrifices ]for sins, just as concerning the people, so also concerning himself.
B058C005V004	58	5	4	And no man takes this honor for himself, but he that is called by God, just as Aaron also [was].
B058C005V005	58	5	5	So also Christ did not glorify Himself to become High Priest, but it was He who said to Him: "You are My Son, Today I have begotten You."
B058C005V006	58	5	6	Just as He also says in another place: "You are a priest forever according to the order of Melchizedek";
B058C005V007	58	5	7	who, in the days of His flesh, when He had offered up both prayers and supplications, with strong crying and tears to the [One] who was able to save Him from death, and was heard because of His fear of God,
B058C005V008	58	5	8	though He was a Son, He learned obedience by the things which He suffered.
B058C005V009	58	5	9	And having been perfected, He became the author of eternal salvation to all who obey Him,
B058C005V010	58	5	10	having been designated by God a High Priest "according to the order of Melchizedek,"
B058C005V011	58	5	11	concerning whom we have much to say, and it is hard to explain, since you have become sluggish in hearing.
B058C005V012	58	5	12	For indeed, although you ought to be teachers by this time, again you have need [for someone ]to teach you what are the elements of the beginning of the oracles of God; and you have come to need milk and not solid food.
B058C005V013	58	5	13	For everyone who partakes [only ]of milk is unacquainted with the word of righteousness, for he is an infant.
B058C005V014	58	5	14	But solid food is for the mature, for those because of their practice have their senses trained for the distinguishing of both good and evil.
B058C006V001	58	6	1	Therefore, leaving the subject of the beginning of Christ, let us be moved to perfection, not again laying down a foundation of repentance from dead works and of faith toward God,
B058C006V002	58	6	2	of the doctrine of baptisms, of laying on of hands, and of resurrection of the dead, and of eternal judgment.
B058C006V003	58	6	3	And let us do this if indeed God permits.
B058C006V004	58	6	4	For it is impossible for those who were once enlightened, and have tasted of the heavenly gift, and became partakers of the Holy Spirit,
B058C006V005	58	6	5	and have tasted the good word of God and [the] powerful deeds of the age to come,
B058C006V006	58	6	6	and having fallen away, to renew [them] again to repentance, since they crucify again for themselves the Son of God, and hold Him up to contempt.
B058C006V007	58	6	7	For the earth which drinks the rain often coming upon it, and bears suitable vegetation for those on account of whom it is cultivated, receives a blessing from God;
B058C006V008	58	6	8	but if it bears thorns and thistles, it is worthless and near to being cursed, of which the end [is] for burning.
B058C006V009	58	6	9	But we are persuaded concerning you, beloved, of better things and those pertaining to salvation, even though we speak in this manner.
B058C006V010	58	6	10	For God is not unjust to forget your work and labor of love which you have shown toward His name, in that you have ministered to the saints, and do minister.
B058C006V011	58	6	11	But we desire that each one of you show the same diligence to the full assurance of hope until [the] end,
B058C006V012	58	6	12	lest you become dull, but [become] imitators of those who through faith and patience inherit the promises.
B058C006V013	58	6	13	For when God made a promise to Abraham, since He could swear by no one greater, He swore by Himself,
B058C006V014	58	6	14	saying, "Surely blessing I will bless you, and multiplying I will multiply you."
B058C006V015	58	6	15	And so, after he had been patient, he obtained the promise.
B058C006V016	58	6	16	For men indeed swear by the greater, and the oath for confirmation [is] an end of every dispute to them.
B058C006V017	58	6	17	Thus God, wanting to show even more clearly to the heirs of the promise the unchangeableness of His counsel, guaranteed it by an oath,
B058C006V018	58	6	18	in order that through two unchangeable things, in which it is impossible for God to lie, we might have strong encouragement, who have fled to take hold of the hope being set before [us];
B058C006V019	58	6	19	which [hope] we have as an anchor of the soul, both sure and secure, and which enters into the inner [side] of the veil,
B058C006V020	58	6	20	where the Forerunner has entered on our behalf, [even] Jesus, having become a High Priest forever according to the order of Melchizedek.
B058C007V001	58	7	1	For this Melchizedek, king of Salem, priest of the Most High God, who met Abraham returning from the slaughter of the kings and blessed him,
B058C007V002	58	7	2	to whom also Abraham divided a tenth from all, first being interpreted "king of righteousness,"and then also king of Salem, which is "king of peace,"
B058C007V003	58	7	3	without father, without mother, without genealogy, having neither beginning of days nor end of life, but having been made like the Son of God, remains a priest continually.
B058C007V004	58	7	4	But observe how great this [man was], to whom even the patriarch Abraham gave a tenth of the spoils.
B058C007V005	58	7	5	And indeed those who are of the sons of Levi, who receive the priesthood, have a commandment to collect tithes from the people according to the law, that is, from their brothers, though they have come from the loins of Abraham;
B058C007V006	58	7	6	but the [one] not tracing his descent from them has received tithes from Abraham, and he has blessed the [one] having the promises.
B058C007V007	58	7	7	Now without any contradiction the lesser is blessed by the better.
B058C007V008	58	7	8	And here on the one hand mortal men receive tithes, but there on the other he[ receives them], of whom[ ]it is witnessed that he lives.
B058C007V009	58	7	9	Even Levi, the [one] receiving tithes, has paid tithes through Abraham, so to speak,
B058C007V010	58	7	10	for he was still in the loins of his father when Melchizedek met him.
B058C007V011	58	7	11	Therefore, if perfection was through the Levitical priesthood (for under it the people have received the law), why is there yet a need [for] another priest to rise, according to the order of Melchizedek, and not to be called according to the order of Aaron?
B058C007V012	58	7	12	For the priesthood being changed, of necessity there occurs a change of law also.
B058C007V013	58	7	13	For He concerning whom these things are spoken belongs to another tribe, from which no one has officiated at the altar.
B058C007V014	58	7	14	For it is evident that our Lord has risen out of Judah, regarding which tribe Moses spoke nothing concerning priesthood.
B058C007V015	58	7	15	And it is yet even more clearer, if according to the likeness of Melchizedek, there arises another priest
B058C007V016	58	7	16	who has come, not according to the law of a fleshly commandment, but according to the power of an endless life.
B058C007V017	58	7	17	For He testifies: "You are a priest forever according to the order of Melchizedek."
B058C007V018	58	7	18	For on the one hand an annulment comes about of the preceding commandment on account of its weakness and uselessness.
B058C007V019	58	7	19	For the law made nothing perfect; but there[ is] the bringing in of a better hope, through which we draw near to God.
B058C007V020	58	7	20	And inasmuch as [it was] not without an oath,
B058C007V021	58	7	21	for they have become priests without an oath, but He with an oath by Him that said to Him: "The LORD has sworn and will not relent, 'You are a priest forever according to the order of Melchizedek' ",
B058C007V022	58	7	22	by so much more Jesus has become the guarantee of a better covenant.
B058C007V023	58	7	23	Also there were many priests, because they were prevented by death from continuing.
B058C007V024	58	7	24	But He, because He remains forever, has an unchangeable priesthood.
B058C007V025	58	7	25	Therefore He is also able to save to the uttermost those coming to God through Him, since He always lives to make intercession for them.
B058C007V026	58	7	26	For such a High Priest was fitting for us, who is holy, innocent, undefiled, having been separated from sinners, and has become higher than the heavens;
B058C007V027	58	7	27	who does not need daily, as those high priests, to offer up sacrifices beforehand, on behalf of His own sins and then for the people's, for this He did once for all when He offered up Himself.
B058C007V028	58	7	28	For the law appoints men as high priests who have weakness, but the word of the oath, which came after the law, [appoints] a Son who has been perfected forever.
B058C008V001	58	8	1	Now this is the main point of the things being said: We have such a High Priest, who is seated at the right hand of the throne of the Majesty in the heavens,
B058C008V002	58	8	2	a Minister of the sanctuary and of the true tabernacle which the Lord set up, and not man.
B058C008V003	58	8	3	For every high priest is appointed to offer both gifts and sacrifices; therefore it is necessary that this [high priest] also have something to offer.
B058C008V004	58	8	4	For if He were on earth, He would not be a priest, since there are priests who offer the gifts according to the law;
B058C008V005	58	8	5	who serve a copy and shadow of the heavenly things, just as Moses had been warned when he was about to complete the tabernacle, for He says, "See, you shall make all things according to the pattern shown to you on the mountain."
B058C008V006	58	8	6	But now He has obtained a more excellent ministry, inasmuch as He is also Mediator of a better covenant, which has been enacted upon better promises.
B058C008V007	58	8	7	For if that first [covenant] had been faultless, then no place would have been sought for a second.
B058C008V008	58	8	8	For finding fault [with] them, He says: "Behold, the days are coming, says the LORD, when I will establish a new covenant with the house of Israel and with the house of Judah,
B058C008V009	58	8	9	not according to the covenant which I made with their fathers, in the day when I took their hand to lead them out of the land of Egypt. Because they did not persevere in My covenant, and I disregarded them, says the LORD.
B058C008V010	58	8	10	For this is the covenant that I will make with the house of Israel after those days, says the LORD: I will put My laws in their mind, and I will inscribe them upon their hearts; and I will be their God, and they shall be My people.
B058C008V011	58	8	11	And by no means will they teach each [one ]his fellow citizen, and each [one] his brother, saying, 'Know the LORD,' for all shall know Me, from the least of them to the greatest of them.
B058C008V012	58	8	12	For I will be merciful to their iniquities, and their sins and their lawless deeds I shall by no means remember anymore."
B058C008V013	58	8	13	In that He says, "A new [covenant],"He has made the first obsolete. And whatever is becoming obsolete and growing old is ready to vanish.
B058C009V001	58	9	1	Now even the first [covenant] had ordinances of [divine] service and the earthly sanctuary.
B058C009V002	58	9	2	For a tabernacle was prepared: the first [part], in which [were] both the lampstand and the table and the showbread, which is called the holy place;
B058C009V003	58	9	3	and after the second veil, the part of the tabernacle which is called the Holy of Holies,
B058C009V004	58	9	4	having a golden altar, and the ark of the covenant having been overlaid on all sides with gold, in which [was] a golden jar holding the manna, and the rod of Aaron which budded, and the tablets of the covenant;
B058C009V005	58	9	5	and above it [were] cherubim of glory overshadowing the mercy seat; concerning these things we cannot now speak in detail.
B058C009V006	58	9	6	Now when these things had been thus prepared, the priests always went into the first tabernacle, accomplishing the services,
B058C009V007	58	9	7	but into the second [part] the high priest [goes] alone once during the year, not without blood, which he offers for himself and for the people's sins committed in ignorance;
B058C009V008	58	9	8	the Holy Spirit signifying this, that the way into the Holiest of All was not yet revealed while the first tabernacle was still standing,
B058C009V009	58	9	9	which [was] symbolic for the present time, according to which both gifts and sacrifices are being offered, which are not able, in respect to conscience, to make perfect the [one] performing the service,
B058C009V010	58	9	10	[concerned] only with foods and drinks, various washings, and fleshly ordinances which are imposed until a time of reformation.
B058C009V011	58	9	11	But Christ came [as] a High Priest of the good things to come, through the greater and more perfect tabernacle not made with hands, that is, not of this creation.
B058C009V012	58	9	12	Not through the blood of goats and calves, but through His own blood, He entered once for all into the Holies, having obtained eternal redemption.
B058C009V013	58	9	13	For if the blood of bulls and goats and the ashes of a heifer, sprinkling those having been defiled, sanctifies for the purity of the flesh,
B058C009V014	58	9	14	by how much more shall the blood of Christ, who through the eternal Spirit offered Himself without spot to God, will cleanse your conscience from dead works in order that we might serve the living God?
B058C009V015	58	9	15	And on account of this He is the Mediator of the new covenant, so that, since a death has occurred for redemption of the transgressions at the time of the first covenant, that those having been called may receive the promise of the eternal inheritance.
B058C009V016	58	9	16	For where there [is] a testament, there is necessity for death to be offered of the [one] making the testament.
B058C009V017	58	9	17	For a testament is valid over dead [people], since it is never valid when the [one] making the testament lives.
B058C009V018	58	9	18	Therefore not even the first [covenant] has been dedicated without blood.
B058C009V019	58	9	19	For when every commandment had been spoken by Moses according to law to all the people, he took the blood of calves and goats, with water, scarlet wool, and hyssop, and sprinkled both the book itself and all the people,
B058C009V020	58	9	20	saying, "This is the blood of the covenant which God has commanded you."
B058C009V021	58	9	21	And likewise he sprinkled both the tabernacle and all the vessels of the service with the blood.
B058C009V022	58	9	22	And according to the law almost all things are purified with blood, and without shedding of blood there is no remission.
B058C009V023	58	9	23	Therefore it [was] necessary that the copies of the things in the heavens to be continually purified with these, but the heavenly things themselves by better sacrifices than these.
B058C009V024	58	9	24	For Christ did not enter into [the] holies made by hands, which are copies of the true, but into heaven itself, now to appear in the presence of God on our behalf;
B058C009V025	58	9	25	not that He should offer Himself often, as the high priest enters into the Holies every year with another's blood-
B058C009V026	58	9	26	since it would have been necessary [for] Him to suffer often from the foundation of the world; but now, once at the consummation of the ages, He has appeared to put away sin through the sacrifice of Himself.
B058C009V027	58	9	27	And inasmuch as it is appointed for men once to die and after this judgment,
B058C009V028	58	9	28	so also Christ, having been offered once to bear the sins of many, will appear a second time apart from sin unto salvation, to those who eagerly await Him.
B058C010V001	58	10	1	For the law, having a shadow of the good things to come, and not the image itself of the things, can never with the same sacrifices, which they offer continually every year, make those approaching perfect.
B058C010V002	58	10	2	Otherwise they would not have ceased to be offered, because the worshippers, once purified, would have had no more consciousness of sins.
B058C010V003	58	10	3	But in them there is a reminder of sins every year.
B058C010V004	58	10	4	For it is not possible for [the] blood of bulls and goats to take away sins.
B058C010V005	58	10	5	Therefore, when He entered into the world, He said: "Sacrifice and offering You did not desire, but a body You have prepared for Me.
B058C010V006	58	10	6	In burnt offerings and [sacrifices] for sin You had no pleasure.
B058C010V007	58	10	7	Then I said, 'Behold, I have come-In the volume of the book it is written of Me- To do Your will, O God.' "
B058C010V008	58	10	8	Earlier saying, "Sacrifice and offering, burnt offerings, and [sacrifices] for sin You did not desire, nor had pleasure in them"(which are offered according to the law),
B058C010V009	58	10	9	then He has said, "Behold, I have come to do Your will, O God."He takes away the first in order that He may establish the second.
B058C010V010	58	10	10	By which will we are sanctified through the offering of the body of Jesus Christ once for all.
B058C010V011	58	10	11	And every priest stands ministering daily and offering repeatedly the same sacrifices, which are never able to take away sins.
B058C010V012	58	10	12	But He Himself, having offered one sacrifice for sins forever, He sat down at the right hand of God,
B058C010V013	58	10	13	from that time waiting till His enemies are placed as a footstool for His feet.
B058C010V014	58	10	14	For by one offering He has perfected forever those who are being sanctified.
B058C010V015	58	10	15	But the Holy Spirit also witnesses to us; for after He had said before,
B058C010V016	58	10	16	"This is the covenant that I will make with them after those days, says the LORD: I will put My laws on their hearts, and I will inscribe them on their minds,
B058C010V017	58	10	17	and their sins and their lawless deeds I shall by no means remember any longer."
B058C010V018	58	10	18	Now where there is remission of these, there is no longer an offering for sin.
B058C010V019	58	10	19	Therefore, brothers, having boldness to enter the Holiest by the blood of Jesus,
B058C010V020	58	10	20	by a new and living way which He inaugurated for us, through the veil, that is, His flesh,
B058C010V021	58	10	21	and [having] a High Priest over the house of God,
B058C010V022	58	10	22	let us approach with a true heart in full assurance of faith, having our hearts sprinkled from an evil conscience, and our bodies having been washed with clean water.
B058C010V023	58	10	23	Let us hold fast the confession of our hope without wavering, for He who promised is faithful.
B058C010V024	58	10	24	And let us consider one another for the stirring up of love and of good works,
B058C010V025	58	10	25	not forsaking the assembling of ourselves, just as is the custom for some, but exhorting [one another], and all the more as you see the Day drawing near.
B058C010V026	58	10	26	For if we sin willfully after receiving the knowledge of the truth, there no longer remains a sacrifice for sins,
B058C010V027	58	10	27	but a certain fearful expectation of judgment, and fiery zeal being about to devour the adversaries.
B058C010V028	58	10	28	Anyone disregarding the law of Moses dies without compassions on [the testimony of] two or three witnesses.
B058C010V029	58	10	29	By how much worse punishment, do you think, will he be deemed worthy who has trampled the Son of God underfoot, and has regarded as common the blood of the covenant, by which he was sanctified, and has insulted the Spirit of grace?
B058C010V030	58	10	30	For we know Him who said, "Vengeance is Mine; I will repay,"says the Lord. And again, "The LORD will judge His people."
B058C010V031	58	10	31	It is a fearful [thing] to fall into the hands of the living God!
B058C010V032	58	10	32	But remember the former days, in which after you were enlightened, you endured a great struggle of sufferings,
B058C010V033	58	10	33	in part being exposed publicly, both to reproaches and to afflictions, and in part having become partners of those treated in this way.
B058C010V034	58	10	34	For you sympathized with me in my chains, and you received the plunder of your possessions with joy, knowing that you have for yourselves a better and enduring possession in heaven.
B058C010V035	58	10	35	Therefore do not cast away your confidence, which has a great recompense.
B058C010V036	58	10	36	For you have need of endurance, so that having done the will of God, you may receive the promise:
B058C010V037	58	10	37	"For yet a little while, and He who is coming will come and will not delay.
B058C010V038	58	10	38	But the just shall live by faith, and if he withdraws, My soul has no pleasure in him."
B058C010V039	58	10	39	But we are not of [those] shrinking back to destruction, but of faith, to the saving of the soul.
B058C011V001	58	11	1	Now faith is the substance of things hoped for, the evidence of things not seen.
B058C011V002	58	11	2	For by it the elders obtained witness.
B058C011V003	58	11	3	By faith we understand that time [itself] was framed by a command of God, so that the things which are seen were not made of things which are visible.
B058C011V004	58	11	4	By faith Abel offered to God a more excellent sacrifice than Cain, through which he obtained witness that he was righteous, God testifying concerning his gifts; and through it, although he died, he still speaks.
B058C011V005	58	11	5	By faith Enoch was translated [so as] not to see death, "and he was not found, because God translated him"; for before his translation he had obtained witness that he was pleasing to God.
B058C011V006	58	11	6	But without faith it is impossible to please [God], for it is necessary [for] the [one] approaching God to believe that He is, and that He becomes a rewarder of those who diligently seek Him.
B058C011V007	58	11	7	By faith Noah, having being warned [by God] concerning the things[ ]not yet seen, being reverent, prepared an ark for the salvation of his household, through which he condemned the world and became an heir of the righteousness which is according to faith.
B058C011V008	58	11	8	By faith Abraham obeyed when he was called to go forth to the place which he was about to receive as an inheritance. And he went out, not knowing where he was going.
B058C011V009	58	11	9	By faith he migrated into a land of promise as [in] a foreign [land], dwelling in tents with Isaac and Jacob, the fellow heirs of the same promise;
B058C011V010	58	11	10	for he waited for the city having foundations, whose builder and maker is God.
B058C011V011	58	11	11	By faith Sarah herself also received power for conception of seed, and she bore a child past the normal age, because she regarded [Him] faithful who had promised.
B058C011V012	58	11	12	Therefore even from one [man ]they were begotten, and him as good as dead, just as the stars of the sky in multitude, and innumerable as the sand by the seashore.
B058C011V013	58	11	13	These all died according to faith, not having received the promises, but having seen them afar off and welcoming [them], and confessing that they were strangers and pilgrims on the earth.
B058C011V014	58	11	14	For those saying such things make evident that they seek a fatherland.
B058C011V015	58	11	15	And indeed if they had remembered that land from which they went out, they would have had opportunity to turn back.
B058C011V016	58	11	16	But now they desire a better [land], that is, a heavenly [one]. Therefore God is not ashamed to be called their God, for He has prepared a city for them.
B058C011V017	58	11	17	By faith Abraham, when he was tested, had offered up Isaac, and he that received the promises offered up his only begotten [son],
B058C011V018	58	11	18	of whom it was spoken, "In Isaac your seed shall be called,"
B058C011V019	58	11	19	considering that even from the dead, God [was] able to raise [him up], from which he also received him in a figurative sense.
B058C011V020	58	11	20	By faith Isaac blessed Jacob and Esau concerning things to come.
B058C011V021	58	11	21	By faith Jacob, when he was dying, blessed each of the sons of Joseph, and worshipped, [leaning] on the top of his staff.
B058C011V022	58	11	22	By faith Joseph, when he was dying, remembered concerning the exodus of the sons of Israel, and gave orders concerning his bones.
B058C011V023	58	11	23	By faith Moses, when he was born, was hidden three months by his parents, because they saw a beautiful child; and they did not fear the edict of the king.
B058C011V024	58	11	24	By faith Moses, when he was grown up, refused to be called a son of Pharaoh's daughter,
B058C011V025	58	11	25	choosing rather to suffer affliction with the people of God, than to have the temporary pleasure of sin,
B058C011V026	58	11	26	regarding the reproach of Christ greater riches than the treasures of Egypt; for he was looking to the reward.
B058C011V027	58	11	27	By faith he left Egypt, not fearing the anger of the king; for he endured as seeing the Unseen [One].
B058C011V028	58	11	28	By faith he kept the Passover and the sprinkling of the blood, lest he who destroyed the firstborn should touch them.
B058C011V029	58	11	29	By faith they passed through the Red Sea as through dry land, whereas the Egyptians, attempting to do so, were drowned.
B058C011V030	58	11	30	By faith the walls of Jericho fell, having been encircled for seven days.
B058C011V031	58	11	31	By faith the prositute Rahab did not perish with those who did not believe, when she had received the spies with peace.
B058C011V032	58	11	32	And what more should I say? For the time would fail me to tell of Gideon, both Barak and Samson and Jephthah, both David and Samuel and the prophets:
B058C011V033	58	11	33	who through faith overcame kingdoms, worked righteousness, obtained promises, stopped the mouths of lions,
B058C011V034	58	11	34	quenched the power of fire, escaped the edge of the sword, out of weakness were made strong, became mighty in battle, turned to flight the armies of foreigners.
B058C011V035	58	11	35	Women received their dead [back] by resurrection. And others were tortured, not accepting deliverance, in order that they might obtain a better resurrection.
B058C011V036	58	11	36	Still others took a trial of mockings and scourgings, yes, and of chains and of prison.
B058C011V037	58	11	37	They were stoned, they were sawn in two, they were tried, they were slain, being murdered with the sword. They went about in sheepskins and goatskins, being in want, being afflicted, being ill treated,
B058C011V038	58	11	38	of whom the world was not worthy, wandering in deserts and mountains and caves, and the holes of the earth.
B058C011V039	58	11	39	And all these, having obtained witness through their faith, did not receive the promise,
B058C011V040	58	11	40	God having provided something better for us, that they should not be made perfect apart from us.
B058C012V001	58	12	1	So therefore we also, since we are surrounded by so great a cloud of witnesses, let us lay aside every impediment, and the sin which so easily ensnares us, and let us run with endurance the race that is set before us,
B058C012V002	58	12	2	looking unto Jesus, the author and perfecter of our faith, who for the joy that was set before Him endured [the] cross, despising the shame, and has sat down at the right hand of the throne of God.
B058C012V003	58	12	3	For consider Him who endured such hostility from sinners against Himself, lest you be weary and discouraged in your souls.
B058C012V004	58	12	4	You have not yet resisted to the point of bloodshed, struggling against sin.
B058C012V005	58	12	5	And you have forgotten the exhortation which speaks to you as sons: "My son, do not despise the discipline of the LORD, nor be discouraged when you are reproved;
B058C012V006	58	12	6	For whom the LORD loves He disciplines, and scourges every son whom He receives."
B058C012V007	58	12	7	It is for discipline [that] you endure; God deals with you as with sons. For what son is there whom a father does not discipline?
B058C012V008	58	12	8	But if you are without discipline, of which all have become partakers, then you are illegitimate and not sons.
B058C012V009	58	12	9	Furthermore, we have had human fathers who corrected us, and we respected [them.] Shall we not much more readily be in subjection to the Father of spirits and live?
B058C012V010	58	12	10	For they indeed disciplined us for a few days, as seemed best to them, but He [disciplines us ]for [our] good, so that we may partake of His holiness.
B058C012V011	58	12	11	Now no discipline seems to be joyful for the present, but painful; nevertheless, later it yields the peaceable fruit of righteousness to those having been trained by it.
B058C012V012	58	12	12	Therefore strengthen the hands which are weakened, and the feeble knees,
B058C012V013	58	12	13	and make straight paths for your feet, so that the lame may not be turned aside, but rather be healed.
B058C012V014	58	12	14	Pursue peace and holiness with all [people], without which no one shall see the Lord:
B058C012V015	58	12	15	looking diligently lest anyone fall from the grace of God; lest any root of bitterness growing up cause trouble, and through this many be defiled;
B058C012V016	58	12	16	lest there be any fornicator or profane [person] like Esau, who in exchange for one meal gave up his birthright.
B058C012V017	58	12	17	For you know that indeed afterward, wishing to inherit the blessing, he was rejected, for he found no place for repentance, having sought it out diligently with tears.
B058C012V018	58	12	18	For you have not come to the mountain that may be touched and that burned with fire, and to blackness and darkness and to a whirlwind,
B058C012V019	58	12	19	and to a sound of a trumpet and to a voice of words, which those who heard begged that no further word be spoken to them.
B058C012V020	58	12	20	For they could not bear that [which] was commanded: "And if so much as a beast touches the mountain, it shall be stoned."
B058C012V021	58	12	21	And so fearful was the spectacle, [that] Moses said, "I am greatly afraid and trembling."
B058C012V022	58	12	22	But you have come to Zion, to the Mountain and city of the living God, the heavenly Jerusalem, and to myriads of angels,
B058C012V023	58	12	23	to the general assembly and church of the firstborn having been enrolled in [the] heavens, to God the Judge of all, and to spirits of just men made perfect,
B058C012V024	58	12	24	and to Jesus, the mediator of a new covenant, and to the blood of sprinkling which speaks better things than the [blood] of Abel.
B058C012V025	58	12	25	See that you do not refuse Him who speaks. For if they did not escape, having refused Him who warned [them], how much more [shall we not escape] if we turn away from Him who warns from heaven;
B058C012V026	58	12	26	whose voice then shook the earth; but now He has promised, saying, "Yet once more I shake not only the earth, but also the heaven."
B058C012V027	58	12	27	Now the [phrase], "Yet once more,"signifies the removal of the things being shaken, as having been made, so that the things which cannot be shaken may remain.
B058C012V028	58	12	28	Therefore, since we are receiving an unshakable kingdom, let us have grace, through which we serve God acceptably with reverence and godly fear.
B058C012V029	58	12	29	For our God is a consuming fire.
B058C013V001	58	13	1	Let brotherly love remain.
B058C013V002	58	13	2	Do not forget hospitality, for by this some have entertained angels without knowing it.
B058C013V003	58	13	3	Remember the prisoners as if having been bound with them, those who are ill treated, as you yourselves are in the body also.
B058C013V004	58	13	4	Marriage is honorable among all, and the bed undefiled; but fornicators and adulterers God will judge.
B058C013V005	58	13	5	Let [your] way of life [be] without loving money, being satisfied with what you have. For He Himself has said, "By no means shall I desert you, nor in any way shall I forsake you;"
B058C013V006	58	13	6	so that being confident, we may say: "The LORD is my helper; I will not fear. What can man do to me?"
B058C013V007	58	13	7	Remember your leaders, who spoke the word of God to you, of whom considering the result of their conduct, imitate their faith.
B058C013V008	58	13	8	Jesus Christ is the same yesterday, today, and forever.
B058C013V009	58	13	9	Do not be carried away with various and strange doctrines. For it is good [for] the heart to be established by grace, not by foods, by which those having walked were not profited.
B058C013V010	58	13	10	We have an altar from which those who serve the tabernacle have no right to eat.
B058C013V011	58	13	11	For of the animals, [whose ]blood is brought into the Holies by the high priest [as an offering ]for sin, the bodies [of these animals] are burned outside the camp.
B058C013V012	58	13	12	Therefore Jesus also, so that He might sanctify the people through His own blood, suffered outside the gate.
B058C013V013	58	13	13	Therefore let us go out to Him, outside the camp, bearing His reproach.
B058C013V014	58	13	14	For we have no permanent city, but we seek the [city ]which is to come.
B058C013V015	58	13	15	Therefore through Him let us continually offer up a sacrifice of praise to God, that is, the fruit of our lips, confessing to His name.
B058C013V016	58	13	16	But do not forget the doing of good and generosity, for with such sacrifices God is well pleased.
B058C013V017	58	13	17	Obey your leaders, and submit to [them], for they keep watch over your souls, as giving an account, in order that they may do this with joy and not groaning, for this [would be] unprofitable for you.
B058C013V018	58	13	18	Pray for us; for we are persuaded that we have a good conscience, in all things desiring to live commendably.
B058C013V019	58	13	19	But I especially urge [you] to do this, in order that I may be restored to you more quickly.
B058C013V020	58	13	20	Now may the God of peace, who brought up our Lord Jesus from the dead, that great Shepherd of the sheep, by the blood of the everlasting covenant,
B058C013V021	58	13	21	make you complete in every good work to do His will, working in you what is well pleasing before Him, through Jesus Christ, to whom [be] glory forever and ever. Amen.
B058C013V022	58	13	22	And I appeal to you, brothers, bear with this word of exhortation, for I have written to you briefly.
B058C013V023	58	13	23	Know [that] our brother Timothy has been released, with whom I shall see you, if he comes quickly.
B058C013V024	58	13	24	Greet all your leaders, and all the saints. Those from Italy greet you.
B058C013V025	58	13	25	Grace be with you all. Amen.
B059C001V001	59	1	1	James, a bondservant of God and of the Lord Jesus Christ, to the twelve tribes which are scattered abroad: Greetings.
B059C001V002	59	1	2	Count it all joy, my brothers, when you fall into various trials,
B059C001V003	59	1	3	knowing that the testing of your faith produces endurance.
B059C001V004	59	1	4	But let endurance have its perfect work, that you may be mature and complete, lacking nothing.
B059C001V005	59	1	5	If any of you lacks wisdom, let him ask of God, who gives to all generously and without reproach, and it shall be given to him.
B059C001V006	59	1	6	But let him ask in faith, doubting nothing, for he that doubts is like a wave of the sea driven and tossed by the wind.
B059C001V007	59	1	7	For let not that man suppose that he shall receive anything from the Lord;
B059C001V008	59	1	8	he is a double-minded man, unstable in all his ways.
B059C001V009	59	1	9	Let the lowly brother rejoice in his exaltation,
B059C001V010	59	1	10	but the rich [man ]in his humiliation, because as a flower of the field he will pass away.
B059C001V011	59	1	11	For the sun arose with burning heat and withered the grass, and its flower fell off, and its beautiful appearance perished. So the rich man also shall fade away in his pursuits.
B059C001V012	59	1	12	Blessed is the man who endures temptation; because when he is approved, he shall receive the crown of life which the Lord promised to those who love Him.
B059C001V013	59	1	13	Let no one say when he is tempted, "I am tempted by God"; for God cannot be tempted by evil, nor does He Himself tempt anyone.
B059C001V014	59	1	14	But each [one] is tempted by his own lusts, being drawn away and being seduced [by them].
B059C001V015	59	1	15	Then lust, when it conceives, gives birth to sin; and sin, when it is full-grown, brings forth death.
B059C001V016	59	1	16	Do not be deceived, my beloved brothers.
B059C001V017	59	1	17	Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, and comes down from the Father of lights, with whom there is no variation or shadow of turning.
B059C001V018	59	1	18	Exercising His will He begat us by the word of truth, that we might be a kind of firstfruits of His creatures.
B059C001V019	59	1	19	So then, my beloved brothers, let every man be quick to hear, slow to speak, slow to anger;
B059C001V020	59	1	20	for the wrath of man does not produce the righteousness of God.
B059C001V021	59	1	21	Therefore laying aside all filthiness and abundance of evil, in meekness receive the implanted word, which is able to save your souls.
B059C001V022	59	1	22	But become doers of the word, and not hearers only, deceiving yourselves.
B059C001V023	59	1	23	Because if anyone is a hearer of the word and not a doer, this [one] is like a man observing his natural face in a mirror;
B059C001V024	59	1	24	for he observed himself and has gone away, and immediately forgot what sort of [man] he was.
B059C001V025	59	1	25	But the [one] who looks into the perfect law of liberty and continues [in it], and is not a forgetful hearer but a doer of the work, this one shall be blessed in what he does.
B059C001V026	59	1	26	If anyone among you thinks he is religious, and does not bridle his tongue but deceiving his heart, the religion of this [man ]is useless.
B059C001V027	59	1	27	Pure and undefiled religion before God and [the] Father is this: to care for orphans and widows in their affliction, and to keep oneself unspotted from the world.
B059C002V001	59	2	1	My brothers, do not hold the faith of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Lord of glory, with partiality.
B059C002V002	59	2	2	For if a man enters into your assembly with a gold ring, in fine clothes, and there should also come in a poor [man] in dirty clothes,
B059C002V003	59	2	3	and you have respect for him that wears the fine clothes and you say to him, "You sit here in a good seat,"and say to the poor man, "You stand there,"or, "Sit here under my footstool,"
B059C002V004	59	2	4	and so did you not differentiate among yourselves, and become judges with evil thoughts?
B059C002V005	59	2	5	Listen, my beloved brothers. Did God not choose the poor of the world [to be] rich in faith, and heirs of the kingdom which He promised to those that love Him?
B059C002V006	59	2	6	But you have dishonored the poor. Do not the rich oppress you and drag you into court?
B059C002V007	59	2	7	Do they not blaspheme the noble name by which you are called?
B059C002V008	59	2	8	If you really fulfill the royal law according to the Scripture, "You shall love your neighbor as yourself,"you do well;
B059C002V009	59	2	9	but if you show partiality, you commit sin, and are convicted by the law as transgressors.
B059C002V010	59	2	10	For whoever shall keep the whole law, and yet stumble in one [point], he has become guilty of all.
B059C002V011	59	2	11	For He who said, "Do not commit adultery,"also said, "You shall not murder."Now if you do not commit adultery, but [yet ]you murder, [then ]you have become a transgressor of the law.
B059C002V012	59	2	12	So speak and so do as those who will be judged by the law of liberty.
B059C002V013	59	2	13	For judgment is without mercy to the one who does not show mercy. Mercy triumphs over judgment.
B059C002V014	59	2	14	What does it profit, my brothers, if someone says he has faith but does not have works? Is that [kind of] faith able to save him?
B059C002V015	59	2	15	If a brother or sister is naked and destitute of daily food,
B059C002V016	59	2	16	and one of you says to them, "Go in peace, be warmed and filled,"but you do not give them the necessary things of the body, what [is] the benefit?
B059C002V017	59	2	17	Thus also that faith, if it does not have works, is dead, [being] by itself.
B059C002V018	59	2	18	But someone will say, "You have faith, and I have works."Show me your faith [apart] from your works, and I will show you my faith by means of my works.
B059C002V019	59	2	19	You believe God is one. You do well. Even the demons believe-and they shudder!
B059C002V020	59	2	20	But do you want to know, O foolish man, that faith without works is dead?
B059C002V021	59	2	21	Was not Abraham our father justified by works when he offered Isaac his son on the altar?
B059C002V022	59	2	22	Do you see that faith was working together with his works, and by means of his works faith was made perfect?
B059C002V023	59	2	23	And the Scripture was fulfilled which says, "Abraham believed God, and it was accounted to him for righteousness."And he was called a friend of God.
B059C002V024	59	2	24	You see then that a man is justified by works, and not by faith only.
B059C002V025	59	2	25	Likewise, was not Rahab the harlot also justified by means of works, when she received the messengers and sent [them] out another way?
B059C002V026	59	2	26	For as the body without the spirit is dead, so faith without works is dead also.
B059C003V001	59	3	1	My brothers, let not many become teachers, knowing that we shall receive greater judgment.
B059C003V002	59	3	2	For we all stumble in many [ways]. If anyone does not stumble in word, he is a mature man, able also to bridle the whole body.
B059C003V003	59	3	3	Consider that we put bits in horses' mouths that they may obey us, and we guide their whole body.
B059C003V004	59	3	4	Consider also the ships: although they are so large and are driven by fierce winds, they are guided by a very small rudder wherever the impulse of the pilot desires.
B059C003V005	59	3	5	Even so the tongue is a small member and it boasts great things. See how great a forest a little fire kindles!
B059C003V006	59	3	6	And the tongue is a fire, a world of iniquity. Thus the tongue is set among our members, as that which defiles the whole body, and sets on fire the course of nature; and it is set on fire by hell.
B059C003V007	59	3	7	For every kind of both beasts and birds, of both reptiles and sea creatures, is tamed and has been tamed by mankind.
B059C003V008	59	3	8	But no man can tame the tongue. [It] is an unrestrainable evil, full of deadly poison.
B059C003V009	59	3	9	With it we bless our God and Father, and with it we curse men, who are created according to [the] likeness of God.
B059C003V010	59	3	10	Out of the same mouth come blessings and curses. My brothers, these things ought not to be so.
B059C003V011	59	3	11	The spring does not pour forth from the same opening [both ]the sweet and the bitter [water, does it]?
B059C003V012	59	3	12	It is not possible, my brothers, [for] a fig tree to make olives, or a vine [to make ]figs, [is it]? Thus no spring is able to produce [both] salt and sweet water.
B059C003V013	59	3	13	Is there anyone wise and understanding among you? Let him show by his good conduct [that] his works [are] in meekness of wisdom.
B059C003V014	59	3	14	But if you have bitter jealousy and strife in your heart, do not boast and lie against the truth.
B059C003V015	59	3	15	This wisdom is not that which comes down from above, but is earthly, sensual, demonic.
B059C003V016	59	3	16	For where jealousy and strife [exist], there unrest and every evil deed [are].
B059C003V017	59	3	17	But the wisdom from above is first pure, then peaceable, gentle, willing to yield, full of mercy and good fruits, without partiality and without hypocrisy.
B059C003V018	59	3	18	Now the fruit of righteousness is sown in peace by those making peace.
B059C004V001	59	4	1	From where [come] wars and disputes among you? Is it not from here, from your lusts, which war in your members?
B059C004V002	59	4	2	You lust and you do not have. You murder and are jealous and you cannot obtain. You fight and make war. You do not have because you do not ask.
B059C004V003	59	4	3	You ask and do not receive, because you ask with wrong motives, that you may spend [it] in [gratifying] your lusts.
B059C004V004	59	4	4	Adulterers and adulteresses! Do you not know that friendship with the world is enmity with God? Whoever therefore wants to be a friend of the world is constituted an enemy of God.
B059C004V005	59	4	5	Or do you think that the Scripture says in vain, "The Spirit who dwells in us yearns jealously"?
B059C004V006	59	4	6	But He gives more grace. Therefore He says: "God resists the proud, but gives grace to the humble."
B059C004V007	59	4	7	Therefore submit to God. Resist the devil and he will flee from you.
B059C004V008	59	4	8	Draw near to God and He will draw near to you. Cleanse [your] hands, [you] sinners; and purify [your] hearts, [you] double-minded.
B059C004V009	59	4	9	Lament and mourn and weep! Let your laughter change into mourning and your joy into dejection.
B059C004V010	59	4	10	Be humbled before the Lord, and He will exalt you.
B059C004V011	59	4	11	Do not speak evil of one another, brothers. He who speaks evil against a brother and judges his brother speaks against the law and judges the law. And if you judge the law, you are not a doer of the law but a judge.
B059C004V012	59	4	12	There is one Lawgiver, who is able to save and to destroy. But who are you who judges the other?
B059C004V013	59	4	13	Come now, you who say, "Today and tomorrow let us travel to this city, and let us spend a year there, and let us trade and make a profit"-
B059C004V014	59	4	14	[you] who do not know [what will] happen tomorrow. For what is your life? For it will be a vapor that appears for a little [time], but then also disappears.
B059C004V015	59	4	15	Instead you ought to say, "If the Lord wills, we shall live and do this or that."
B059C004V016	59	4	16	But now you boast in your arrogance. All such boasting is evil.
B059C004V017	59	4	17	Therefore, to him who knows to do good and does not do [it], to him it is sin.
B059C005V001	59	5	1	Listen now, you rich, weep and howl at your miseries which are coming upon you!
B059C005V002	59	5	2	Your riches have decayed, and your garments have become moth-eaten.
B059C005V003	59	5	3	Your gold and silver have become corroded, and their poison will be a witness against you and will eat your flesh like fire. You stored up treasure in the last days.
B059C005V004	59	5	4	Indeed, the wages of the laborers who reaped your fields, which were kept back by you, cry out, and the cries of the reapers have entered into the ears of the Lord of Hosts.
B059C005V005	59	5	5	You lived luxuriously upon the earth and you lived riotously, you nourished your hearts as in a day of slaughter.
B059C005V006	59	5	6	You have condemned; you have murdered the just[. ]He does not resist you.
B059C005V007	59	5	7	Therefore be patient, brothers, until the coming of the Lord. See how the farmer awaits for the precious fruit of the earth, being patient for it, until it receives the early and late rain.
B059C005V008	59	5	8	You also be patient. Establish your hearts, because the coming of the Lord has drawn near.
B059C005V009	59	5	9	Do not murmur against one another, brothers, lest you be judged. Behold, the Judge stands before the doors!
B059C005V010	59	5	10	My brothers, take the prophets, who spoke in the name of the Lord, as an example of evil suffering and of longsuffering.
B059C005V011	59	5	11	Indeed we count those blessed who endure. You have heard of the patience of Job, and you saw the end of the Lord-that He is compassionate and He is merciful.
B059C005V012	59	5	12	But above all, my brothers, do not swear, neither by heaven nor the earth, nor any other oath. But let your "Yes"be "Yes,"and [your] "No,""No,"so that you may not fall into hypocrisy.
B059C005V013	59	5	13	Does anyone among you suffer misfortune? Let him pray. Is anyone cheerful? Let him sing praises.
B059C005V014	59	5	14	Is anyone among you sick? Let him call on the elders of the church, and let them pray over him, anointing him with oil in the name of the Lord.
B059C005V015	59	5	15	And the prayer of faith will save the [one ]who is sick, and the Lord will raise him up. And if he has committed sins, it will be forgiven him.
B059C005V016	59	5	16	Confess your transgressions to one another, and pray for one another, so that you may be healed. The effective prayer of the righteous is very powerful.
B059C005V017	59	5	17	Elijah was a man of similar nature to us, and with a prayer, he prayed earnestly for it not to rain, and it did not rain upon the land for three years and six months.
B059C005V018	59	5	18	And again he prayed, and the heaven gave rain, and the earth produced its fruit.
B059C005V019	59	5	19	Brothers, if anyone among you wanders away from the truth, and anyone turns him back,
B059C005V020	59	5	20	let him know that he who turns a sinner back from the error of his way will save a soul from death and will cover a multitude of sins.
B060C001V001	60	1	1	Peter, an apostle of Jesus Christ, to the elect sojourners of the Dispersion of Pontus, Galatia, Cappadocia, Asia, and Bithynia,
B060C001V002	60	1	2	according to the foreknowledge of God the Father, in sanctification of the Spirit, for obedience and sprinkling of the blood of Jesus Christ: Grace to you and peace be multiplied.
B060C001V003	60	1	3	Blessed [be] the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who according to His great mercy has begotten us again to a living hope through the resurrection of Jesus Christ from the dead,
B060C001V004	60	1	4	into an inheritance incorruptible and undefiled and unfading, reserved in the heavens for you,
B060C001V005	60	1	5	who by the power of God [are] being guarded through faith for the salvation ready to be revealed in the last time.
B060C001V006	60	1	6	In which you greatly rejoice, [though for] a little while now, if need be, you have been distressed by various trials,
B060C001V007	60	1	7	so that the genuineness of your faith, which is more precious than gold that perishes, though being tested with fire, may be found to praise, honor, and glory at the revelation of Jesus Christ.
B060C001V008	60	1	8	Whom not having seen, you love, in whom now not seeing, but believing, you rejoice with inexpressible joy and glorified,
B060C001V009	60	1	9	obtaining for yourselves the outcome your faith-the salvation [of your] souls.
B060C001V010	60	1	10	Concerning this salvation the prophets have sought out and inquired carefully, having prophesied of the grace [that would come] to you,
B060C001V011	60	1	11	searching for who or what kind of time the Spirit of Christ in them was revealing when He testified beforehand the sufferings of Christ and the glories which were to follow.
B060C001V012	60	1	12	To them it was revealed that, not to themselves, but to you they were ministering these things, which things were now announced to you by those who proclaimed the gospel to you by the Holy Spirit sent from heaven-things which angels desire to look into.
B060C001V013	60	1	13	Therefore gird up the loins of your mind, stay sober, put your hope fully in the grace brought to you at the revelation of Jesus Christ;
B060C001V014	60	1	14	as obedient children, not fashioning yourselves [after] the former lusts, [as you did in ]your ignorance;
B060C001V015	60	1	15	but as He[ ]who called you is holy, you also be holy in all manner of life,
B060C001V016	60	1	16	because it is written, "Be holy, for I am holy."
B060C001V017	60	1	17	And if you call on the Father, who without partiality judges according to each one's work, pass the time of your sojourning [here] in fear;
B060C001V018	60	1	18	knowing that you were not redeemed with corruptible things, like silver or gold, from your futile way of life handed down from your forefathers,
B060C001V019	60	1	19	but with the precious blood of Christ, as of a lamb blameless and spotless,
B060C001V020	60	1	20	having been foreknown indeed before the foundation of the world, He was made manifest in these last times for you,
B060C001V021	60	1	21	who through Him believe in God, who raised Him from the dead and gave Him glory, so that your faith and hope are in God.
B060C001V022	60	1	22	Since you have purified your souls by obedience to the truth through the Spirit in sincere love for the brothers, love one another fervently from a pure heart,
B060C001V023	60	1	23	having been born again, not of corruptible seed, but of incorruptible, through the word of God which lives and abides forever.
B060C001V024	60	1	24	For "All flesh is as grass, and all the glory of man is as the flower of [the] grass. The grass withers, and its flower falls away,
B060C001V025	60	1	25	but the word of the LORD endures forever."Now this is the word which was proclaimed to you.
B060C002V001	60	2	1	Therefore having put away all malice, all guile, hypocrisy, envy, and all slanders,
B060C002V002	60	2	2	as newborn babes, desire the genuine milk of the word, that by it you may grow,
B060C002V003	60	2	3	if indeed you tasted that the Lord is good.
B060C002V004	60	2	4	Coming to Him as to a living stone, having been rejected indeed by men, but chosen by God and precious,
B060C002V005	60	2	5	you also, as living stones, are being built [into] a spiritual house, a holy priesthood, to offer up spiritual sacrifices acceptable to God through Jesus Christ.
B060C002V006	60	2	6	For it is also contained in the Scripture, "Behold, I place in Zion a chief cornerstone, chosen, precious, and he who believes on Him shall by no means be put to shame."
B060C002V007	60	2	7	Therefore, to you who believe, [He] is precious; but to those who are disobedient, "The stone which the builders rejected has become the chief cornerstone,"
B060C002V008	60	2	8	and "a stone of stumbling and a rock of offense."They stumble, being disobedient to the word, to which they also were appointed.
B060C002V009	60	2	9	But you are a chosen race, a royal priesthood, a holy nation, a people for God's [own] possession, that you may proclaim the excellent virtues of Him who called you out of darkness into His marvelous light;
B060C002V010	60	2	10	who formerly [were] not a people but now [are the] people of God, who had not received mercy, but now have received mercy.
B060C002V011	60	2	11	Beloved, I implore you as sojourners and pilgrims, to abstain from the lusts of the flesh which war against the soul;
B060C002V012	60	2	12	having your manner of life noble among the Gentiles, so that, whenever they speak against you as evildoers, when they observe the good works, they may glorify God in the day of visitation.
B060C002V013	60	2	13	Therefore subject yourselves to every human institution on account of the Lord: whether to the king as [to one] having authority,
B060C002V014	60	2	14	or to governors, as to those being sent for the punishment of evildoers and for the praise [of those] doing good.
B060C002V015	60	2	15	For this is the will of God, that by doing good you may silence the ignorance of foolish men-
B060C002V016	60	2	16	as free, yet not using freedom as a cover for wickedness, but as bondservants of God.
B060C002V017	60	2	17	Honor all [people]. Love the brotherhood. Fear God. Honor the king.
B060C002V018	60	2	18	Servants, subject yourselves to your masters with all fear, not only to the good and gentle, but also to the crooked.
B060C002V019	60	2	19	For this is admirable, if because of conscience toward God someone endures pain, suffering unjustly.
B060C002V020	60	2	20	For what glory [is it,] if when you sin and are beaten, you endure? But if when you do good and suffer [for it,] you endure, this is admirable before God.
B060C002V021	60	2	21	For to this you were called, because Christ also suffered for us, leaving behind an example for you, that you should follow in His footsteps,
B060C002V022	60	2	22	"Who committed no sin, nor was deceit found in His mouth";
B060C002V023	60	2	23	who, being verbally abused, did not return verbal insults, when [He] suffered, [He] did not threaten, but committed [Himself] to Him who judges righteously;
B060C002V024	60	2	24	who Himself bore our sins in His body on the tree, in order that having died to sins, we might live unto righteousness-by whose stripes you were healed.
B060C002V025	60	2	25	For you were like sheep going astray, but you have turned back now to the Shepherd and Overseer of your souls.
B060C003V001	60	3	1	Wives, likewise, subject yourselves to your own husbands, so that even if some are disobedient to the word, [that] by the conduct of their wives, without a word, they shall be gained [for Christ],
B060C003V002	60	3	2	when they observe your chaste conduct with fear.
B060C003V003	60	3	3	Of whom let it not be the outward adorning of braiding of hair, and wearing of gold, or of putting on of [fine] clothes,
B060C003V004	60	3	4	rather [let it be] the hidden person of the heart, with the incorruptible [attitude] of a gentle and quiet spirit, which is very precious before God.
B060C003V005	60	3	5	For thus formerly, the holy women who hoped on God also adorned themselves, subjecting themselves to their own husbands,
B060C003V006	60	3	6	as Sarah obeyed Abraham, calling him lord, of whom you became children, when you do good and are not afraid of any terror.
B060C003V007	60	3	7	Husbands, likewise, live together according to knowledge as with a weaker vessel, with the wife, showing her honor as also a fellow heir of the grace of life, in order that your prayers may not be hindered.
B060C003V008	60	3	8	Finally, all [of you] be like-minded, sympathetic, loving the brothers, compassionate, friendly,
B060C003V009	60	3	9	not rendering evil for evil or reviling for reviling, but on the contrary blessing, knowing that you were called for this purpose, that you may inherit a blessing.
B060C003V010	60	3	10	For "He that desires to love life and see good days, let him stop his tongue from evil, and his lips from speaking guile.
B060C003V011	60	3	11	Let him turn away from evil and do good; let him seek peace and pursue it.
B060C003V012	60	3	12	For the eyes of the LORD are upon the righteous, and His ears [open] to their prayer; but the face of the LORD is against those doing evil."
B060C003V013	60	3	13	And who is he that shall injure you if you become imitators of that which is good?
B060C003V014	60	3	14	But even if you should suffer on account of righteousness, [you are] blessed. "But do not fear their threats, nor be troubled."
B060C003V015	60	3	15	But sanctify the Lord God in your hearts, and always be prepared with a defense to everyone who asks you a reason for the hope that is in you, with meekness and fear;
B060C003V016	60	3	16	having a good conscience, so that in what they speak against you as evildoers, those reviling your good conduct in Christ may be put to shame.
B060C003V017	60	3	17	For it is better to suffer for doing good, if it is the will of God, than [for] doing evil.
B060C003V018	60	3	18	For Christ also suffered once to atone for sins, [the] just for [the] unjust, that He might bring you to God, being put to death in the flesh, but made alive by the Spirit,
B060C003V019	60	3	19	by whom also He went and preached to the spirits in prison,
B060C003V020	60	3	20	who formerly disobeyed, when the longsuffering of God was waiting in the days of Noah, when the ark was being prepared, in which a few, that is, eight souls, were saved through water;
B060C003V021	60	3	21	which [as] an antitype, baptism now also saves us-(not the putting away of the filth of the flesh, but an appeal to God [for] a good conscience), through the resurrection of Jesus Christ,
B060C003V022	60	3	22	who having gone into heaven, is at the right hand of God, angels and authorities and powers being subjected to Him.
B060C004V001	60	4	1	Therefore, since Christ suffered for us in the flesh, you also arm yourselves [with] the same mind, because he who suffered in [the] flesh has ceased from sin,
B060C004V002	60	4	2	that he no longer should live the remaining time in the flesh for the lusts of men, but for the will of God.
B060C004V003	60	4	3	For we have spent enough of our past lifetime to accomplish the will of the Gentiles-having walked in wantonness, lusts, drunkenness, revelries, drinking parties, and abominable idolatries.
B060C004V004	60	4	4	In regard to these, they are surprised that you do not run with them in the same flood of debauchery, reviling you.
B060C004V005	60	4	5	They will render an account to Him who is ready to judge the living and the dead.
B060C004V006	60	4	6	Unto this [end] was the gospel proclaimed also to those who are dead, in order that they might be judged according to men in [the] flesh, but [that] they might live according to God in [the] spirit.
B060C004V007	60	4	7	Now the end of all things is at hand; therefore be of sound mind and self-controlled in your prayers.
B060C004V008	60	4	8	And above all things have fervent love for one another, because "love will cover a multitude of sins."
B060C004V009	60	4	9	Be hospitable to one another without grumbling.
B060C004V010	60	4	10	As each one has received a gift, minister it to one another, as good stewards of the manifold grace of God.
B060C004V011	60	4	11	If anyone speaks, [let him speak] as the utterances of God. If anyone serves, [let him serve] as from strength, as God supplies, so that in all things God may be glorified through Jesus Christ, to whom is the glory and the power forever and ever. Amen.
B060C004V012	60	4	12	Beloved, do not be surprised by the fiery trial among you, taking place to test you, as though some strange thing [was] happening to you;
B060C004V013	60	4	13	but inasmuch as you partake in the sufferings of Christ, rejoice, in order that also at the unveiling of His glory, you may rejoice with great happiness.
B060C004V014	60	4	14	If you are reviled in the name of Christ, blessed are you, because the Spirit of glory and of God rests upon you. On the one hand He is blasphemed, but on the other He is glorified.
B060C004V015	60	4	15	For let not anyone of you suffer as a murderer, or a thief, or an evildoer, or as a meddler in other people's affairs;
B060C004V016	60	4	16	but if anyone [suffers] as a Christian, let him not be put to shame, but let him glorify God in this matter.
B060C004V017	60	4	17	For the time [has come] for judgment to begin at the house of God; and if [it begins] with us first, what will be the end of those who are disobedient to the gospel of God?
B060C004V018	60	4	18	And "If the righteous [one] is scarcely saved, where will the godless and the sinner appear?"
B060C004V019	60	4	19	Therefore let those who suffer according to the will of God entrust their souls to Him in doing good, as to a faithful Creator.
B060C005V001	60	5	1	The elders who are among you I exhort, as a fellow elder and a witness of the sufferings of Christ, and also a partaker of the glory that shall be revealed;
B060C005V002	60	5	2	shepherd the flock of God among you, overseeing not by compulsion, but rather willingly, not in fondness for dishonest gain, but rather eagerly;
B060C005V003	60	5	3	nor as being masters over the flock [under you,] but rather being examples to the flock.
B060C005V004	60	5	4	And when the Chief Shepherd appears, you will receive the unfading crown of glory.
B060C005V005	60	5	5	Likewise, younger [people], subject yourselves to [the] elders. And all of you be subject to one another, and be clothed with humility, because "God resists the proud, but gives grace to the humble."
B060C005V006	60	5	6	Therefore humble yourselves under the mighty hand of God, that He may exalt you in due time,
B060C005V007	60	5	7	casting all your anxiety upon Him, because He cares about you.
B060C005V008	60	5	8	Be sober, be watchful; your adversary the devil walks about as a roaring lion, seeking someone he may devour.
B060C005V009	60	5	9	Resist him, being steadfast in [your] faith, knowing that the same sufferings are experienced by your brotherhood in the world.
B060C005V010	60	5	10	But may the God of all grace, the [One ]having called you into His eternal glory in Christ Jesus, after you have suffered a little [while], may He Himself make you complete-He will establish, strengthen, [and] firmly ground [you].
B060C005V011	60	5	11	To Him be the glory and the power, forever and ever. Amen.
B060C005V012	60	5	12	By Silvanus the faithful brother, as I consider him, I have written to you briefly, exhorting and testifying this to be [the] true grace of God in which you stand.
B060C005V013	60	5	13	She who is in Babylon, elect together with you, greets you; and so does Mark my son.
B060C005V014	60	5	14	Greet one another with a kiss of love. Peace to you all who are in Christ Jesus. Amen.
B061C001V001	61	1	1	Simon Peter, a bondservant and apostle of Jesus Christ, to those who have obtained like precious faith with us by [the] righteousness of our God and Savior Jesus Christ:
B061C001V002	61	1	2	[May ]grace and peace be multiplied [to you] in [your] knowledge of God and of Jesus our Lord.
B061C001V003	61	1	3	As His divine power has granted to us all things [pertaining] to life and godliness, through the knowledge of Him who called us by glory and virtue,
B061C001V004	61	1	4	through which have been given to us precious and exceedingly great promises, so that through these we may become partakers of the divine nature, having escaped the corruption that is in the world through lust.
B061C001V005	61	1	5	But also [for] this very reason, making every effort, provide with your faith virtue, and with virtue knowledge,
B061C001V006	61	1	6	and with knowledge self-control, and with self-control perseverance, and with perseverance godliness,
B061C001V007	61	1	7	and with godliness brotherly love, and with brotherly love, love.
B061C001V008	61	1	8	For if these things belong to you and are increasing, it makes you neither barren nor unfruitful in the knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B061C001V009	61	1	9	For [he] who lacks these things is blind, being shortsighted, having forgotten the cleansing of his past sins.
B061C001V010	61	1	10	Therefore, brothers, be even more diligent to make your calling and election sure, for by doing these things you shall by no means stumble at any time.
B061C001V011	61	1	11	For in this way the entrance will be supplied to you richly into the eternal kingdom of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ.
B061C001V012	61	1	12	Therefore I shall not neglect to constantly remind you concerning these things, although you know and have been established in the present truth.
B061C001V013	61	1	13	But I consider it right, as long as I am in this tent, to stir you up by a reminder,
B061C001V014	61	1	14	knowing that the putting off of my tent is soon, just as our Lord Jesus Christ has made clear to me.
B061C001V015	61	1	15	And I will make an effort also, whenever necessary, to cause you to have a reminder of these things after my departure.
B061C001V016	61	1	16	For we did not follow craftily devised fables when we made known to you the power and coming of our Lord Jesus Christ, but rather became eyewitnesses of His majesty.
B061C001V017	61	1	17	For He received from God the Father honor and glory when a voice was brought to Him such as this by the Magnificent Glory: "This is My beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased."
B061C001V018	61	1	18	And we heard this voice being uttered from heaven, when we were with Him on the holy mountain.
B061C001V019	61	1	19	And we have the prophetic word made more sure, which you do well to heed, as a lamp shining in a dark place, until the day dawns and the morning star rises in your hearts;
B061C001V020	61	1	20	knowing this first, that no prophecy of Scripture comes about [from] one's own interpretation,
B061C001V021	61	1	21	for prophecy never came by the will of man, but holy men of God spoke, being brought along by [the] Holy Spirit.
B061C002V001	61	2	1	But there were also false prophets among the people, even as there will be false teachers among you, who will secretly bring in destructive heresies, even denying the Master, the [One] having bought them, and bringing upon themselves swift destruction.
B061C002V002	61	2	2	And many will follow after their debaucheries, because of whom the way of truth will be blasphemed.
B061C002V003	61	2	3	And by covetousness they will exploit you with fabricated words; for a long time their judgment has not been idle, and their destruction will not sleep.
B061C002V004	61	2	4	For if God did not spare the angels when they sinned, but rather confined [them] to Tartarus, and delivered [them ]into chains of darkness, reserved for judgment;
B061C002V005	61	2	5	and did not spare the ancient world, but preserved Noah, [the] eighth, a preacher of righteousness, when He brought a flood upon the ungodly world;
B061C002V006	61	2	6	and reducing the cities of Sodom and Gomorrah to ashes, He condemned [them] to destruction, having made [them] an example who were to be ungodly,
B061C002V007	61	2	7	and He rescued righteous Lot, who was oppressed by the indecent conduct of lawless [men]
B061C002V008	61	2	8	(for that righteous man, living among them day after day, tormented his righteous soul by seeing and hearing their lawless deeds)-
B061C002V009	61	2	9	[then] the Lord knows [how] to deliver the godly out of temptation and [how] to keep the unjust under punishment for the day of judgment,
B061C002V010	61	2	10	and especially those who walk after the flesh in the lust of uncleanness and despise authority. [They are ]bold, self-willed, illustrious persons, they do not tremble at blaspheming,
B061C002V011	61	2	11	whereas angels, being greater in might and in power, do not bring a slanderous judgment against them before the Lord.
B061C002V012	61	2	12	But these, as unreasoning natural animals, having been born for capture and destruction, blaspheme at things which they are ignorant of, and shall be destroyed in their destruction,
B061C002V013	61	2	13	receiving the wages of unrighteousness, counting as a pleasure to revel in the daytime, [they are] spots and blemishes, reveling in their deceptions while they feast with you,
B061C002V014	61	2	14	having eyes full of adultery and unable to cease from sin, enticing unstable souls, having a heart having been trained in greediness, they are accursed children.
B061C002V015	61	2	15	They have left behind the straight way and have gone astray, having followed after the way of Balaam the son of Bosor, who loved the wages of unrighteousness;
B061C002V016	61	2	16	but he was rebuked for his own lawlessness: a dumb donkey speaking with the voice of a man restrained the madness of the prophet.
B061C002V017	61	2	17	These are waterless wells, clouds being driven by a storm, for whom the darkness of the netherworld has been reserved forever.
B061C002V018	61	2	18	For when they speak haughty [words] of emptiness, they entice through the lusts of the flesh, through lewdness, those who are escaping from those who are living in error,
B061C002V019	61	2	19	promising to them freedom, while they themselves are slaves of corruption; for by whom anyone has been defeated, by this [one] also he has been enslaved.
B061C002V020	61	2	20	For if having escaped from the corruptions of the world by the knowledge of the Lord and Savior Jesus Christ, yet by these, having become entangled they are defeated, the latter end has become worse for them than the first.
B061C002V021	61	2	21	For it was better for them not to have known the way of righteousness, than knowing it, to turn from the holy commandment delivered to them.
B061C002V022	61	2	22	But it has happened to them [according to] the [saying] of the true proverb: "A dog returns to his own vomit,"and, "A sow, having washed, [returns ] to her wallowing in the mire."
B061C003V001	61	3	1	This already, beloved, [is] the second letter I write to you, in [both of] which I stir up your pure mind by a reminder,
B061C003V002	61	3	2	to remember the words having been previously spoken by the holy prophets, and the commandment of your apostles of the Lord and Savior;
B061C003V003	61	3	3	knowing this first: that mockers will come in the last days, walking according to their own lusts,
B061C003V004	61	3	4	and saying, "Where is the promise of His coming? For since the fathers died, all things continue as from the beginning of creation."
B061C003V005	61	3	5	For this they willingly forget: that by the word of God the heavens were of old, and [the] earth, consisting out of water and through water,
B061C003V006	61	3	6	by which the world at that time perished, being flooded by water;
B061C003V007	61	3	7	but the present heavens and earth, having been stored up by His word, are being reserved for fire until the day of judgment and destruction of ungodly men.
B061C003V008	61	3	8	But in this let it not escape your notice, beloved, that one day with the Lord is as a thousand years, and a thousand years as one day.
B061C003V009	61	3	9	The Lord does not delay concerning His promise, as some reckon slackness, but is longsuffering toward us, not willing that any should perish, but that all should come to repentance.
B061C003V010	61	3	10	But the day of the Lord shall come as a thief in the night, in which the heavens shall pass away with a rushing noise, and the elements, burning with heat, shall be dissolved, both the earth and the works that are in it shall be burned up.
B061C003V011	61	3	11	Therefore, [seeing that] all these things shall be dissolved, what sort of [people] ought you to be in holy conduct and godliness,
B061C003V012	61	3	12	looking for and hastening the coming of the day of God, because of which the heavens, being set of fire, shall be dissolved, and the elements, burning with heat, shall melt?
B061C003V013	61	3	13	But according to His promise, we look for new heavens and a new earth in which righteousness dwells.
B061C003V014	61	3	14	Therefore, beloved, looking forward to these things, be diligent to be found by Him in peace, without spot or blemish;
B061C003V015	61	3	15	and consider that the longsuffering of our Lord is salvation-just as also our beloved brother Paul, according to the wisdom given to him, wrote to you,
B061C003V016	61	3	16	as also in all his letters, speaking in them about these things, in which are some things hard to understand, which the unlearned and unstable twist to their own destruction, as they do also the rest of the Scriptures.
B061C003V017	61	3	17	You therefore, beloved, knowing this beforehand, be on guard, lest you also fall from your own steadfastness, being carried away by the error of the wicked;
B061C003V018	61	3	18	but grow in grace and in the knowledge of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ. To Him [be] the glory both now and forever. Amen.
B062C001V001	62	1	1	That which was from the beginning, which we have heard, which we have seen with our eyes, which we have gazed upon, and our hands have handled, concerning the Word of life-
B062C001V002	62	1	2	and the life was manifested, and we have seen, and bear witness, and we declare to you the eternal life which was with the Father and was manifested to us-
B062C001V003	62	1	3	that which we have seen and heard we declare to you, in order that you also may have fellowship with us; and indeed our fellowship is with the Father and with His Son Jesus Christ.
B062C001V004	62	1	4	And these things we write to you that our joy may be fulfilled.
B062C001V005	62	1	5	And this is the message which we have heard from Him and we announce to you, that God is light and in Him is no darkness at all.
B062C001V006	62	1	6	If we claim that we have fellowship with Him, and we are walking in the darkness, we are lying, and are not practicing the truth.
B062C001V007	62	1	7	But if we are walking in the light, as He is in the light, we have fellowship with one another, and the blood of Jesus Christ His Son cleanses us from all sin.
B062C001V008	62	1	8	If we claim that we have no sin, we are deceiving ourselves, and the truth is not in us.
B062C001V009	62	1	9	If we confess our sins, He is faithful and just to forgive us our sins and to cleanse us from all unrighteousness.
B062C001V010	62	1	10	If we claim that we have not sinned, we make Him a liar, and His word is not in us.
B062C002V001	62	2	1	My little children, these things I write to you, that you may not sin. And if someone should sin, we have an Advocate with the Father, Jesus Christ the righteous.
B062C002V002	62	2	2	And He Himself is the propitiation for our sins, and not only concerning ours, but also concerning [those] of the whole world.
B062C002V003	62	2	3	Now by this we know that we have come to know Him, if we keep His commandments.
B062C002V004	62	2	4	He who says, "I have come to know Him,"and does not keep His commandments, is a liar, and the truth is not in him.
B062C002V005	62	2	5	But whoever keeps His word, truly the love of God is perfected in him. By this we know that we are in Him.
B062C002V006	62	2	6	He who claims to abide in Him ought himself also to walk just as He walked.
B062C002V007	62	2	7	Brothers, I am not writing a new commandment to you, but an old commandment which you have had from the beginning. The old commandment is the word which you heard from the beginning.
B062C002V008	62	2	8	Again, a new commandment I am writing to you, which [thing] is true in Him and in you, because the darkness is passing away, and the true light already shines.
B062C002V009	62	2	9	He who says that he is in the light, and hates his brother, is in darkness until now.
B062C002V010	62	2	10	He who loves his brother abides in the light, and there is no cause for stumbling in him.
B062C002V011	62	2	11	But he who hates his brother is in darkness and walks in darkness, and does not know where he is going, because the darkness has blinded his eyes.
B062C002V012	62	2	12	I am writing to you, little children, because your sins have been forgiven you on account of His name.
B062C002V013	62	2	13	I am writing to you, fathers, because you have come to know Him[ who is] from the beginning. I am writing to you, young men, because you have overcome the evil [one]. I am writing to you, little children, because you have come to know the Father.
B062C002V014	62	2	14	I wrote to you, fathers, because you have come to know Him[ who is] from the beginning. I wrote to you, young men, because you are strong, and the word of God abides in you, and you have overcome the evil [one].
B062C002V015	62	2	15	Do not love the world nor the things in the world. If anyone loves the world, the love of the Father is not in him.
B062C002V016	62	2	16	Because everything that is in the world-the lust of the flesh, and the lust of the eyes, and the pride of life-is not from the Father but is from the world.
B062C002V017	62	2	17	And the world is passing away, and its lust; but he who does the will of God abides forever.
B062C002V018	62	2	18	Little children, it is the last hour; and just as you have heard that the Antichrist is coming, even now many antichrists have appeared; from this we know that it is the last hour.
B062C002V019	62	2	19	They went out from us, but they were not of us; for if they had been of us, they would have remained with us; but [they went out] in order that they might be made manifest, that none of them were of us.
B062C002V020	62	2	20	But you have an anointing from the Holy One, and you know all things.
B062C002V021	62	2	21	I did not write to you because you do not know the truth, but because you know it, and because no lie is of the truth.
B062C002V022	62	2	22	Who is a liar but the [one] who denies that Jesus is the Christ? This is the antichrist, the [one] who denies the Father and the Son.
B062C002V023	62	2	23	Everyone who denies the Son does not have the Father either.
B062C002V024	62	2	24	Therefore let that which you heard from the beginning abide in you. If what you heard from the beginning abides in you, you also will abide in the Son and in the Father.
B062C002V025	62	2	25	And this is the promise which He Himself promised to you-eternal life.
B062C002V026	62	2	26	These things I wrote to you concerning those who deceive you.
B062C002V027	62	2	27	And [as for] you, the anointing which you have received from Him abides in you, and you have no need that anyone teach you; but as the same anointing teaches you concerning all things, and is true, and is not a lie, and just as it has taught you, you will abide in Him.
B062C002V028	62	2	28	And now, little children, abide in Him, in order that when He appears, we may have confidence and not be ashamed due to Him at His coming.
B062C002V029	62	2	29	If you know that He is righteous, you know that everyone who practices righteousness has been born of Him.
B062C003V001	62	3	1	Behold what manner of love the Father has bestowed on us, that we should be called children of God! On account of this the world does not know you, because it did not know Him.
B062C003V002	62	3	2	Beloved, now we are children of God; and it has not yet been revealed what we shall be, but we know that when He appears, we shall be like Him, because we shall see Him as He is.
B062C003V003	62	3	3	And everyone who has this hope in Him purifies himself, just as He is pure.
B062C003V004	62	3	4	Everyone who practices sin also practices lawlessness, and sin is lawlessness.
B062C003V005	62	3	5	And you know that He appeared that He might take away our sins, and in Him there is no sin.
B062C003V006	62	3	6	Everyone who abides in Him does not sin; everyone who sins has not seen Him nor has he known Him.
B062C003V007	62	3	7	Little children, let no one deceive you. The [one] who practices righteousness is righteous, just as He is righteous.
B062C003V008	62	3	8	He who practices sin is of the devil, for the devil has been sinning from the beginning. For this [reason] the Son of God appeared, that He might destroy the works of the devil.
B062C003V009	62	3	9	No one who has been born of God practices sin, because His seed abides in him; and he cannot sin, because he has been born of God.
B062C003V010	62	3	10	By this the children of God and the children of the devil are manifest: Everyone who does not practice righteousness is not of God, nor is he who does not love his brother.
B062C003V011	62	3	11	Because this is the message which you heard from the beginning, that we should love one another,
B062C003V012	62	3	12	not as Cain who was of the evil one and slew his brother. And for what reason did he slay him? Because his works were evil and the [works] of his brother were righteous.
B062C003V013	62	3	13	Do not marvel, my brothers, if the world hates you.
B062C003V014	62	3	14	We know that we have passed from death to life, because we love the brothers. He who does not love his brother abides in death.
B062C003V015	62	3	15	Everyone who hates his brother is a murderer, and you know that no murderer has eternal life abiding in him.
B062C003V016	62	3	16	By this we have come to know love, because He laid down His life for us. And we also ought to lay down our lives on behalf of our brothers.
B062C003V017	62	3	17	But whoever has this world's goods, and sees his brother having need, and shuts off his compassion towards him, how does the love of God abide in him?
B062C003V018	62	3	18	My little children, let us not love in word or in tongue, but in deed and in truth.
B062C003V019	62	3	19	And in this we know that we are from the truth, and shall assure our hearts before Him.
B062C003V020	62	3	20	Because if our heart condemns us, God is greater than our heart, and He knows all things.
B062C003V021	62	3	21	Beloved, if our heart does not condemn us, we have confidence toward God.
B062C003V022	62	3	22	And whatever we should ask we receive from Him, because we keep His commandments and we do the things pleasing before Him.
B062C003V023	62	3	23	And this is His commandment: that we should believe in the name of His Son Jesus Christ and should love one another, just as He gave commandment.
B062C003V024	62	3	24	And the [one] who keeps His commandments abides in Him, and He in him. And by this we know that He abides in us, from the Spirit whom He gave us.
B062C004V001	62	4	1	Beloved, do not believe every spirit, but test the spirits, whether they are from God; because many false prophets have gone out into the world.
B062C004V002	62	4	2	By this the Spirit of God is known: Every spirit that confesses that Jesus Christ has come in the flesh is of God,
B062C004V003	62	4	3	and every spirit which does not confess that Jesus Christ has come in the flesh is not of God. And this is the [spirit] of the Antichrist, which you have heard that it is coming, and now is already in the world.
B062C004V004	62	4	4	You are of God, little children, and you have overcome them, because He who is in you is greater than he who is in the world.
B062C004V005	62	4	5	They are of the world: on account of this they speak of the world, and the world hears them.
B062C004V006	62	4	6	We are of God. He that knows God hears us; [he] that is not of God does not hear us. By this we know the spirit of truth and the spirit of error.
B062C004V007	62	4	7	Beloved, let us love one another, because love is of God; and everyone that loves has been born of God and knows God.
B062C004V008	62	4	8	He that does not love does not know God, because God is love.
B062C004V009	62	4	9	By this the love of God is manifested in us, that God has sent His only begotten Son into the world, in order that we might live through Him.
B062C004V010	62	4	10	In this is love, not that we loved God, but that He loved us and sent His Son [to be ]the propitiation for our sins.
B062C004V011	62	4	11	Beloved, if in this way God loved us, indeed we ought to love one another.
B062C004V012	62	4	12	No one has ever seen God. If we love one another, God abides in us, and His love has been perfected in us.
B062C004V013	62	4	13	(By this we know that we abide in Him, and He in us, because He has given us of His Spirit.)
B062C004V014	62	4	14	And we have seen and testify that the Father has sent the Son as Savior of the world.
B062C004V015	62	4	15	Whoever confesses that Jesus is the Son of God, God abides in him, and he in God.
B062C004V016	62	4	16	And we have come to know and believe the love which God has in us. God is love, and he that abides in love abides in God, and God abides in him.
B062C004V017	62	4	17	By this love has been perfected with us: that we may have confidence in the day of judgment; because just as He is, we also are in this world.
B062C004V018	62	4	18	There is no fear in love; but perfect love casts out fear, because fear involves punishment. But he that fears has not been made perfect in love.
B062C004V019	62	4	19	We love Him because He first loved us.
B062C004V020	62	4	20	If anyone claims, "I love God,"and hates his brother, he is a liar; for he who does not love his brother whom he has seen, how is it possible [for him] to love God whom he has not seen?
B062C004V021	62	4	21	And this commandment we have from Him: that he who loves God should love his brother also.
B062C005V001	62	5	1	Everyone that believes that Jesus is the Christ has been born of God, and everyone that loves Him that begot also loves him that is begotten of Him.
B062C005V002	62	5	2	By this we know that we love the children of God, whenever we love God and keep His commandments.
B062C005V003	62	5	3	For this is the love of God, that we keep His commandments. And His commandments are not burdensome,
B062C005V004	62	5	4	because everything having been born of God overcomes the world: and this is the victory that has overcome the world-your faith.
B062C005V005	62	5	5	Who is he that overcomes the world, if not he that believes that Jesus is the Son of God?
B062C005V006	62	5	6	This is He who came through water and blood-Jesus Christ, not only by the water, but by the water and the blood. And the Spirit is He[ ]who witnesses, because the Spirit is the truth.
B062C005V007	62	5	7	For there are three that bear witness:
B062C005V008	62	5	8	the Spirit, the water, and the blood; and these three agree as one.
B062C005V009	62	5	9	If we receive the testimony of men, the testimony of God is greater; because this is the testimony of God which He has testified concerning His Son.
B062C005V010	62	5	10	He that believes in the Son of God has the testimony in himself; he that does not believe God has made Him a liar, because he has not believed in the testimony which God has testified concerning His Son.
B062C005V011	62	5	11	And this is the testimony: that God has given to us eternal life, and this life is in His Son.
B062C005V012	62	5	12	He that has the Son has life; he that does not have the Son of God does not have life.
B062C005V013	62	5	13	These things I write to you who believe in the name of the Son of God, that you may know that you have eternal life, and that you may believe in the name of the Son of God.
B062C005V014	62	5	14	And this is the confidence that we have toward Him, that if we should ask anything according to His will, He hears us.
B062C005V015	62	5	15	And if we know that He hears us, whatever we may ask, we know that we have the requests that we have requested from Him.
B062C005V016	62	5	16	If anyone sees his brother sinning a sin not [leading] to death, he shall ask, and He shall give him life for those who do not sin unto death. There is a sin [leading] to death. I do not say that he should ask about that.
B062C005V017	62	5	17	All unrighteousness is sin, and there is sin not [leading] to death.
B062C005V018	62	5	18	We know that everyone begotten of God does not sin; but he that was begotten of God keeps himself, and the evil [one] does not touch him.
B062C005V019	62	5	19	We know that we are from God, and the whole world lies [under the sway] of the evil [one].
B062C005V020	62	5	20	And we know that the Son of God has come and has given us an understanding, that we may know Him that is true; and we are in Him that is true, in His Son Jesus Christ. He is the true God and eternal life.
B062C005V021	62	5	21	Little children, guard yourselves from idols. Amen.
B063C001V001	63	1	1	THE ELDER, To the elect lady and her children, whom I love in truth, and not only I, but also all those who have come to know the truth,
B063C001V002	63	1	2	on account of the truth which abides in us and will be with us forever:
B063C001V003	63	1	3	Grace, mercy, and peace will be with us from God [the] Father and from [the] Lord Jesus Christ, the Son of the Father, in truth and love.
B063C001V004	63	1	4	I rejoiced greatly that I have found some of your children walking in truth, just as we received commandment from the Father.
B063C001V005	63	1	5	And now I ask you, lady, not as writing a new commandment to you, but one which we have had from the beginning: that we love one another.
B063C001V006	63	1	6	This is love, that we walk according to His commandments. This is the commandment, that as you have heard from the beginning, that you should walk in it.
B063C001V007	63	1	7	Because many deceivers have gone out into the world who do not confess Jesus Christ as coming in [the] flesh. This is the deceiver and the antichrist.
B063C001V008	63	1	8	Look to yourselves, lest we should lose those things for which we worked, but that we should receive a full reward.
B063C001V009	63	1	9	Everyone who transgresses and does not abide in the doctrine of Christ does not have God. He who abides in the doctrine of Christ, this [one] has both the Father and the Son.
B063C001V010	63	1	10	If anyone comes to you and does not bring this doctrine, do not receive him into your house, and do not greet him;
B063C001V011	63	1	11	for he who greets him shares in his evil works.
B063C001V012	63	1	12	Although I had many things to write to you, I did not wish to do so with paper and ink; but I hope to come to you and speak face to face, in order that our joy may be fulfilled.
B063C001V013	63	1	13	The children of your elect sister greet you. Amen.
B064C001V001	64	1	1	THE ELDER, To the beloved Gaius, whom I love in truth:
B064C001V002	64	1	2	Beloved, concerning all things I pray you to prosper and to be healthy, just as your soul prospers.
B064C001V003	64	1	3	For I rejoiced greatly when [the ]brothers came and witnessed to the truth which is in you, just as you walk in truth.
B064C001V004	64	1	4	I have no greater joy than these things, that I hear [that] my children are walking in truth.
B064C001V005	64	1	5	Beloved, you do faithfully whatever you work for the brothers and for strangers,
B064C001V006	64	1	6	who gave testimony concerning your love before the church, [with reference] to whom you will do well if you send them forth in a manner worthy of God,
B064C001V007	64	1	7	for on behalf of the Name they went out, taking nothing from the pagans.
B064C001V008	64	1	8	We therefore ought to receive such, in order that we may become fellow workers with the truth.
B064C001V009	64	1	9	I wrote to the church, but Diotrephes, who loves the preeminence over them, does not receive us.
B064C001V010	64	1	10	On account of this, if I come, I will call to mind his works which he does, slandering us with evil words. And not being content with that, he does not receive the brothers, and hinders those who desire to, casting them out of the church.
B064C001V011	64	1	11	Beloved, do not imitate the evil, but the good. He that does good is of God; he that does evil has not seen God.
B064C001V012	64	1	12	Demetrius has a good testimony with everyone, and of the truth itself. And we also testify, and you know that our testimony is true.
B064C001V013	64	1	13	I had many things to write, but I do not wish to write to you with pen and ink.
B064C001V014	64	1	14	But I wish to see you shortly, and we shall speak face to face. Peace to you. Our friends greet you. Greet the friends by name.
B065C001V001	65	1	1	Jude, a bondservant of Jesus Christ, and brother of James, to those who are called, having been sanctified by God the Father, and having been kept in Jesus Christ:
B065C001V002	65	1	2	[May ]mercy, peace, and love be multiplied to you.
B065C001V003	65	1	3	Beloved, while I was very diligent to write to you about our common salvation, it became necessary to write to you exhorting you to earnestly contend for the faith which was once for all delivered to the saints.
B065C001V004	65	1	4	For certain men have crept in unawares, who long ago were marked out for this condemnation, ungodly men, changing the grace of our God into licentiousness and denying the only Master God and our Lord Jesus Christ.
B065C001V005	65	1	5	Now I want to remind you, although you once knew this, that the Lord, having saved the people out of the land of Egypt, afterward destroyed those who did not believe.
B065C001V006	65	1	6	And the angels who did not keep their own domain, but rather having left their own habitation, He has kept with everlasting chains under darkness for the judgment of the great day;
B065C001V007	65	1	7	as Sodom and Gomorrah, and the cities around them in a similar manner to these, having given themselves over to fornication and having gone after other flesh, are set forth as an example, suffering the vengeance of eternal fire.
B065C001V008	65	1	8	Likewise indeed even these [filthy ]dreamers defile the flesh, reject authority, and blaspheme glories.
B065C001V009	65	1	9	Yet Michael the archangel, when taking issue with the devil, was arguing about the body of Moses, dared not to bring a railing accusation, but said, "The Lord rebuke you!"
B065C001V010	65	1	10	But these speak blasphemously of those things which they do not know; but what they do know naturally, like unreasoning animals, they are destroyed by these things.
B065C001V011	65	1	11	Woe to them! For they have gone in the way of Cain, and in the error of Balaam they have rushed for profit, and have perished in the rebellion of Korah.
B065C001V012	65	1	12	These are stains in your love feasts, while they feast [with you] without fear, caring for themselves, they are waterless clouds being carried along by winds; late autumn trees unfruitful, twice having died, having been uprooted,
B065C001V013	65	1	13	raging waves on the sea, casting up the foam of their own shame; wandering stars for whom the darkness of the netherworld has been reserved forever.
B065C001V014	65	1	14	Now Enoch, the seventh from Adam, prophesied about these men, saying, "Behold, the Lord comes with ten thousands of His saints,
B065C001V015	65	1	15	to execute judgment against all, and to convict all the ungodly among them about all their ungodly deeds which they have committed impiously, and about all the harsh [words] which ungodly sinners have spoken against Him."
B065C001V016	65	1	16	These are murmurers, complainers, walking after their own lusts; and their mouth speaks puffed up words, flattering people to gain advantage.
B065C001V017	65	1	17	But you, beloved, remember the words which were spoken beforehand by the apostles of our Lord Jesus Christ,
B065C001V018	65	1	18	how they told you that in the last time there would be mockers, walking according to their own ungodly lusts.
B065C001V019	65	1	19	These are those who cause divisions, wordly, devoid of [the] Spirit.
B065C001V020	65	1	20	But you, beloved, building yourselves up in your most holy faith, praying in the Holy Spirit,
B065C001V021	65	1	21	keep yourselves in the love of God, anticipating the mercy of our Lord Jesus Christ to eternal life.
B065C001V022	65	1	22	And have mercy on some, making a distinction;
B065C001V023	65	1	23	but others save with fear, snatching them out of the fire, hating even the garment having been stained by the flesh.
B065C001V024	65	1	24	Now to Him who is able to keep them from stumbling, and to make you stand before His glory, blameless with exultation,
B065C001V025	65	1	25	To the only wise God our Savior, [be] glory and majesty, dominion and power, both now and forever. Amen.
B066C001V001	66	1	1	The Revelation of Jesus Christ, which God gave to Him to show His servants the[ ]things which must come to pass quickly. And He made it known by sending it through His angel to His servant John,
B066C001V002	66	1	2	who testified to the word of God, and the testimony of Jesus Christ, as many things as He saw, both the things that are and those that must happen after these.
B066C001V003	66	1	3	Blessed is he who reads and those who hear the words of this prophecy, and who keep the things having been written in it; for the time is near.
B066C001V004	66	1	4	John, to the seven churches [which are] in Asia: Grace to you and peace from Him who is, and who was, and who is coming, and from the seven-fold Spirit who is before His throne,
B066C001V005	66	1	5	and from Jesus Christ, the faithful witness, the firstborn from the dead, and the ruler of the kings of the earth. To Him who loves us and who washed us from our sins in His own blood,
B066C001V006	66	1	6	and He made us kings and priests to His God and Father, to Him be the glory and dominion forever and ever. Amen.
B066C001V007	66	1	7	Behold, He is coming with the clouds, and every eye will see Him, and those who pierced Him. And all the tribes of the earth will wail because of Him. Even so, Amen!
B066C001V008	66	1	8	"I am the Alpha and the Omega,"says the Lord God, "He who is and He who was and He who is to come, The Almighty."
B066C001V009	66	1	9	I, John, your brother and partaker in the tribulation and kingdom and endurance in Christ Jesus, came to be on the island that is called Patmos on account of the word of God and for the testimony of Jesus Christ.
B066C001V010	66	1	10	I was in [the ]Spirit on the Lord's Day, and I heard a loud voice like a trumpet behind me,
B066C001V011	66	1	11	saying, "That which you see, write in a book and send to the seven churches: to Ephesus, to Smyrna, to Pergamos, to Thyatira, to Sardis, to Philadelphia, and to Laodicea."
B066C001V012	66	1	12	And there I turned to see the voice which was speaking with me. And having turned I saw seven golden lampstands,
B066C001V013	66	1	13	and in the midst of the seven lampstands [stood One] like [the] Son of Man, having been clothed in a [robe] reaching to [His] feet and having been girded across [His] chest with a golden belt.
B066C001V014	66	1	14	And His head and His hair were white, and like white wool, like snow, and His eyes [were ]like a flame of fire;
B066C001V015	66	1	15	And His feet were like fine brass, as if refined in a furnace, and His voice as the sound of many waters;
B066C001V016	66	1	16	He had in His right hand seven stars, out of His mouth proceeded a sharp two-edged sword, and His countenance was as the sun shining in its strength.
B066C001V017	66	1	17	And when I saw Him, I fell at His feet as [if] dead. But He put His right hand on me, saying, "Do not fear; I am the First and the Last.
B066C001V018	66	1	18	I am He who lives, and became dead, and behold, I am alive forevermore. Amen. And I have the keys of Death and of Hades.
B066C001V019	66	1	19	Write therefore the things which you saw, and the things which are, and the things which shall be hereafter.
B066C001V020	66	1	20	The mystery of the seven stars which you saw in My right hand, and the seven golden lampstands: The seven stars are the angels of the seven churches, and the seven lampstands which you saw are the seven churches.
B066C002V001	66	2	1	"To the angel of the church of Ephesus write, 'These things says He that holds the seven stars in His right hand, who walks in the midst of the seven golden lampstands:
B066C002V002	66	2	2	"I know your works, and your labor, and your endurance, and that you cannot bear those who are evil. And you tested those who say that they are apostles and they are not, and you found them [to be ]liars;
B066C002V003	66	2	3	and you have endurance and you have born patiently on account of My name, and you did not become weary.
B066C002V004	66	2	4	Nevertheless I have this against you, that you have left your first love.
B066C002V005	66	2	5	Remember therefore from where you have fallen, and repent and do the first works; but if not, I am coming to you quickly and I will remove your lampstand out of its place, unless you repent.
B066C002V006	66	2	6	But this you have, that you hate the works of the Nicolaitans, which I also hate.
B066C002V007	66	2	7	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches. To him that overcomes will I give to eat of the tree of life, which is in the Paradise of My God."'
B066C002V008	66	2	8	"And to the angel of the church in Smyrna write, 'These things says the First and the Last, who became dead, and came to life:
B066C002V009	66	2	9	"I know your works, and your tribulation, and your poverty (but you are rich); and I know the blasphemy of those who say they are Jews and are not, but [are] a synagogue of Satan.
B066C002V010	66	2	10	Fear none of those things which you are about to suffer. Behold indeed, the devil is about to cast [some] of you into prison, so that you may be tested, and you will have tribulation ten days. Be faithful until death, and I will give you the crown of life.
B066C002V011	66	2	11	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches. He who overcomes shall in no way be harmed by the second death."'
B066C002V012	66	2	12	"And to the angel of the church in Pergamos write, 'These things says He who has the sharp two-edged sword:
B066C002V013	66	2	13	"I know your works, and where you live, where Satan's throne is. And you hold fast to My name, and did not deny My faith in the days in which Antipas was My faithful witness, who was killed among you, where Satan is dwelling.
B066C002V014	66	2	14	But I have a few things against you, because you have there [some] who hold the doctrine of Balaam, who taught Balak to cast a stumbling block before the sons of Israel, both to eat things sacrificed to idols, and to commit fornication.
B066C002V015	66	2	15	Thus you also have those who hold the doctrine of the Nicolaitans, [which ]likewise[ I hate.]
B066C002V016	66	2	16	Repent therefore! Or else I will come to you quickly, and make war against them with the sword of My mouth.
B066C002V017	66	2	17	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches. To him who overcomes I will give to him some of the hidden manna to eat. And I will give him a white stone, and on the stone a new name written which no one knows except he who receives it."'
B066C002V018	66	2	18	"And to the angel of the church in Thyatira write, 'These things says the Son of God, who has eyes like a flame of fire, and His feet like fine brass:
B066C002V019	66	2	19	"I know your works, and love, and faith and service, and your endurance; and your last works [are] greater than the first.
B066C002V020	66	2	20	But I have [this] against you, that you tolerate your wife Jezebel, who calls herself a prophetess, to teach and seduce My servants to commit fornication and eat things sacrificed to idols.
B066C002V021	66	2	21	And I gave her time so that she might repent, and she does not wish to repent of her fornication.
B066C002V022	66	2	22	Behold, I am casting her into a sickbed, and those who commit adultery with her into great tribulation, if they do not repent of her works.
B066C002V023	66	2	23	I will kill her children by death, and all the churches shall know that I am He who searches minds and hearts. And I will give to each one of you according to your works.
B066C002V024	66	2	24	But to you I say, to the rest who are in Thyatira, as many as do not have this doctrine, who have not known the depths of Satan, as they say, I will put on you no other burden.
B066C002V025	66	2	25	Only hold fast what you have till I come.
B066C002V026	66	2	26	And he who overcomes, and he who keeps My works until the end, to him I will give authority over the nations-
B066C002V027	66	2	27	'And he shall rule them with a rod of iron; they shall be smashed to pieces like clay vessels'-
B066C002V028	66	2	28	as I also have received from My Father; and I will give him the morning star.
B066C002V029	66	2	29	"He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches."'
B066C003V001	66	3	1	"And to the angel of the church in Sardis write, 'These things says He that has the seven Spirits of God and the seven stars: "I know your works, that you have a name, that you live, and you are dead.
B066C003V002	66	3	2	Be watchful, and keep that which remains, which you were about to cast out, for I have not found your works perfect before My God.
B066C003V003	66	3	3	Remember therefore how you have received and heard, and hold fast, and repent. Therefore if you will not watch, I will come upon you like a thief, and by no means shall you know what hour I will come upon you.
B066C003V004	66	3	4	You have a few names in Sardis who have not defiled their garments; and they will walk with Me in white, because they are worthy.
B066C003V005	66	3	5	He who overcomes shall be clothed in white garments, and by no means shall I erase his name from the Book of Life; but I will confess his name before My Father and before His angels.
B066C003V006	66	3	6	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches."'
B066C003V007	66	3	7	"And to the angel of the church in Philadelphia write, 'These things says the Holy [One], the True [One,] "He who has the key of David, He that opens and no man shuts, except He that opens, and no man shall open."
B066C003V008	66	3	8	"I know your works. Behold, I have set before you an open door, and no man can shut it; because you have a little strength and have kept My word, and you have not denied My name.
B066C003V009	66	3	9	Behold, I will give those of the synagogue of Satan, those who say they are Jews and are not, but they are lying-behold, I will compel them to come and bow down at your feet, and they shall know that I have loved you.
B066C003V010	66	3	10	Because you have kept My command to persevere, I also will keep you from the hour of testing which is about to come upon the whole world, to test those that dwell upon the earth.
B066C003V011	66	3	11	I am coming quickly! Hold fast what you have, that no man may take your crown.
B066C003V012	66	3	12	He who overcomes, I will make him a pillar in the temple of My God, and by no means shall he go out any longer. And I will write on him the name of My God and the name of the city of My God, the new Jerusalem, which comes down from heaven from My God. And My new name.
B066C003V013	66	3	13	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches."'
B066C003V014	66	3	14	"And to the angel of the church in Laodicea write, 'These things says the Amen, the faithful and true Witness, the beginning of the creation of God:
B066C003V015	66	3	15	"I know your works, that you are neither cold nor hot. I wish [that] you were cold or hot.
B066C003V016	66	3	16	Therefore, since you are lukewarm, and neither cold nor hot, I will spew you out of My mouth.
B066C003V017	66	3	17	Because you say, 'I am wealthy, and have become rich, and have need of nothing'-and do not know that you are wretched, miserable, poor, blind, and naked,
B066C003V018	66	3	18	I counsel you to buy from Me gold having been tried by fire, so that you may become rich; and white robes, so that you may be clothed, and the shame of your nakedness may not appear; and eye salve, so that you may anoint your eyes, in order that you may see.
B066C003V019	66	3	19	As many as I love, I rebuke and discipline. Be zealous therefore, and repent.
B066C003V020	66	3	20	Behold, I stand at the door and I am knocking. If anyone hears My voice and opens the door, then I will come in to him and I will dine with him, and he with Me.
B066C003V021	66	3	21	He that overcomes, I will grant to him to sit with Me on My throne, as I also overcame and sat down with My Father on His throne.
B066C003V022	66	3	22	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches."' "
B066C004V001	66	4	1	After these things I looked, and behold, a door standing open in heaven, and the first voice which I heard was like a trumpet speaking with me, saying, "Come up here, and I will show you the things which must occur after this."
B066C004V002	66	4	2	Immediately I was in [the] Spirit; and behold, a throne was set in heaven (and One sitting on the throne)
B066C004V003	66	4	3	similar in appearance to a jasper and sardius stone, and there[ was] a rainbow around the throne, in appearance like an emerald.
B066C004V004	66	4	4	Around the throne were twenty-four thrones, and on the thrones I saw the twenty-four elders sitting, having been clothed in white robes; and on their heads[ were] crowns of gold.
B066C004V005	66	4	5	And from the throne proceeded lightnings and voices and thunders. And seven torches of fire [were] burning before His throne, which are seven spirits of God;
B066C004V006	66	4	6	and before the throne [was something ]like a sea of glass, similar to crystal. And in the midst of the throne, and around the throne, were four living beings full of eyes in front and in back.
B066C004V007	66	4	7	The first living being was like a lion, the second living being [was ]like a calf, the third living being had a face of a man, and the fourth living being was like a flying eagle.
B066C004V008	66	4	8	And the four living beings, each one having six wings apiece, were full of eyes around and within. And they never rest day or night, saying, "Holy, holy, holy, Holy, holy, holy, Holy, holy, holy, Lord God Almighty, He[ w]ho was, and who is, and who is to come!"
B066C004V009	66	4	9	Whenever the living beings give glory and honor and thanksgiving to Him that sits on the throne, to Him that lives forever and ever,
B066C004V010	66	4	10	the twenty-four elders fall down before Him who sits on the throne and they worship Him that lives forever and ever, and cast their crowns before the throne, saying:
B066C004V011	66	4	11	"You are worthy, our Lord and God, the Holy [One], to receive the glory and the honor and the power; because You created all things, and by Your will they existed and they were created."
B066C005V001	66	5	1	And I saw in the right [hand] of Him that sat on the throne a scroll, having been written inside and outside, [and ]having been sealed with seven seals.
B066C005V002	66	5	2	Then I saw a strong angel proclaiming with a loud voice, "Who is worthy to open the scroll and to break its seals?"
B066C005V003	66	5	3	And no one in heaven above or on the earth or under the earth was able to open the scroll, nor to look at it.
B066C005V004	66	5	4	And I began to weep much, because no one was found worthy to open the scroll, nor to look at it.
