B066C014V012	66	14	12	Here is the endurance of the saints; those who keep the commandments of God and the faith of Jesus.
B066C014V013	66	14	13	And I heard a voice out of heaven saying, "Write: 'Blessed are the dead who die in the Lord from now [on,]' "Yes,"says the Spirit, "that they may rest from their labors, and their works follow with them."
B066C014V014	66	14	14	And I saw, and behold, a white cloud, and on the cloud sat [One] like the Son of Man, having on His head a golden crown, and in His hand a sharp sickle.
B066C014V015	66	14	15	And another angel came out of the temple, crying out with a loud voice to Him that sat on the cloud, "Thrust in Your sickle and reap, because the time has come to reap, because the harvest of the earth has withered."
B066C014V016	66	14	16	So He that sat on the cloud swung His sickle onto the earth, and the earth was harvested.
B066C014V017	66	14	17	Then another angel came out of the temple in heaven, he also having a sharp sickle.
B066C014V018	66	14	18	And another angel came out from the altar, having authority over the fire, and he called with a loud cry to the [one] having the sharp sickle, saying, "Thrust in your sharp sickle and gather the grape clusters of the vine of the earth, because the grapes are ripe."
B066C014V019	66	14	19	So the angel threw out his sickle to the earth and gathered the vine of the earth, and he threw it into the great winepress of the wrath of God.
B066C014V020	66	14	20	And the winepress was trampled outside the city, and blood came out of the winepress, up to the horses' bridles, about one thousand six hundred stadia.
B066C015V001	66	15	1	Then I saw another sign in heaven, great and marvelous: seven angels having the seven last plagues, because in them the wrath of God has been completed.
B066C015V002	66	15	2	And I saw something like a glassy sea having been mixed with fire, and those who prevailed over the Beast, and over his image, and over the number of his name, standing on the glassy sea, having the harps of God.
B066C015V003	66	15	3	And they sing the song of Moses, the servant of God, and the song of the Lamb, saying: "Great and marvelous are Your works, Lord God Almighty! Righteous and true are Your ways, O King of the nations!
B066C015V004	66	15	4	Who shall not fear You, O Lord, and glorify Your name? For You alone are holy. For all [nations] shall come and worship before You, because Your righteous judgments have been manifested."
B066C015V005	66	15	5	After these things I saw, and the temple of the tabernacle of the testimony in heaven was opened.
B066C015V006	66	15	6	And out of the temple came the seven angels having the seven plagues, who were dressed in pure bright linen, and having their chests girded with golden belts.
B066C015V007	66	15	7	Then one of the four living beings gave to the seven angels seven golden bowls full of the wrath of God who lives forever and ever.
B066C015V008	66	15	8	And the temple was filled by the smoke from the glory of God and from His power, and no one was able to enter into the temple until the seven plagues of the seven angels were completed.
B066C016V001	66	16	1	Then I heard a loud voice from the temple saying to the seven angels, "Go and pour out the seven bowls of the wrath of God on the earth."
B066C016V002	66	16	2	So the first went off and poured out his bowl on the earth, and a bad and malignant ulcer came upon the men having the mark of the beast, and those who worshipped his image.
B066C016V003	66	16	3	Then the second angel poured out his bowl into the sea, and it became blood as of a dead man; and every living thing in the sea died.
B066C016V004	66	16	4	Then the third [one] poured out his bowl into the rivers and into the springs of water, and it became blood.
B066C016V005	66	16	5	And I heard the angel of the waters saying: "You are righteous, the One who is, and who was, holy, because You have judged these things.
B066C016V006	66	16	6	Because they shed the blood of saints and prophets, and You gave them blood to drink. They deserve it."
B066C016V007	66	16	7	And I heard the altar saying, "Yes, Lord God Almighty, true and righteous [are] Your judgments."
B066C016V008	66	16	8	Then the fourth [one] poured out his bowl on the sun, and it was granted to him to burn men with fire.
B066C016V009	66	16	9	And men were burned with severe burns, and men blasphemed the name of God who has power over these plagues; and they did not repent to give Him glory.
B066C016V010	66	16	10	Then the fifth [one] poured out his bowl on the throne of the Beast, and his kingdom became darkened; and they gnawed their tongues from the pain.
B066C016V011	66	16	11	They blasphemed the God of heaven because of their pains and their ulcers, and they did not repent of their works.
B066C016V012	66	16	12	Then the sixth [one ]poured out his bowl on the great river Euphrates, and its water dried up, so that the way of the kings from the east might be prepared.
B066C016V013	66	16	13	And I saw three unclean spirits like frogs [coming] out of the mouth of the dragon, out of the mouth of the Beast, and out of the mouth of the False Prophet.
B066C016V014	66	16	14	For they are spirits of demons performing signs, which go forth to the kings of the whole world, to gather them to the battle of that great day of God Almighty.
B066C016V015	66	16	15	Behold, I am coming like a thief. Blessed is he who watches, and guards his garments, lest he should walk naked and they should see his shame."
B066C016V016	66	16	16	And he gathered them together to the place called in Hebrew, Armageddon.
B066C016V017	66	16	17	Then the seventh angel poured out his bowl into the air, and a loud voice came out of the temple of heaven, from the throne, saying, "It has been done!"
B066C016V018	66	16	18	And there were lightnings and thunders, and noises; and there was a great earthquake, such as had not occurred since men came into being on the earth, so great an earthquake, so great!
B066C016V019	66	16	19	Now the great city was divided into three parts, and the cities of the nations fell. And Babylon the great was remembered before God, to give her the cup of the wine of the rage of His wrath.
B066C016V020	66	16	20	Then every island fled, and the mountains were not found.
B066C016V021	66	16	21	And great hail from heaven fell upon men, [each hailstone] weighing a talent. And men blasphemed God because of the plague of hail, since this plague was exceedingly severe.
B066C017V001	66	17	1	Then one of the seven angels having the seven bowls came and spoke with me, saying, "Come, I will show you the judgment of the great harlot who sits on many waters,
B066C017V002	66	17	2	with whom the kings of the earth committed fornication, and those dwelling on the earth became drunk from the wine of her fornication."
B066C017V003	66	17	3	And he led me away in [the ]Spirit, into a deserted [place]. And I saw a woman sitting on a scarlet beast being filled with names of blasphemy, having seven heads and ten horns.
B066C017V004	66	17	4	And the woman was clothed in purple and scarlet, gilded with gold and precious stones and pearls, having in her hand a golden cup being filled with abominations and the filthiness of the fornication of the earth.
B066C017V005	66	17	5	And on her forehead a name was written: MYSTERY, BABYLON THE GREAT, THE MOTHER OF HARLOTS AND OF THE ABOMINATIONS OF THE EARTH.
B066C017V006	66	17	6	I saw the woman, drunk with the blood of the saints and with the blood of the martyrs of Jesus. And when I saw her, I marveled with great amazement.
B066C017V007	66	17	7	But the angel said to me, "Why did you marvel? I will tell you the mystery of the woman and of the Beast carrying her, which has the seven heads and the ten horns.
B066C017V008	66	17	8	The Beast which you saw was, and is not, and is about to ascend out of the bottomless pit and go to perdition. And those who dwell on the earth shall marvel, whose name is not written in the Book of Life from the foundation of the world, when they see the Beast that was, and is not, and shall be present.
B066C017V009	66	17	9	Here is the mind which has wisdom: The seven heads are seven mountains on which the woman sits.
B066C017V010	66	17	10	And there are seven kings. Five have fallen, one is, and the other has not yet come. And whenever he comes, he must abide [for] a short time.
B066C017V011	66	17	11	And the Beast which was, and is not, is also an eighth, and is of the seven, and is going to perdition.
B066C017V012	66	17	12	And the ten horns which you saw are ten kings who not yet have received a kingdom, but they receive authority as kings for one hour with the Beast.
B066C017V013	66	17	13	These have one purpose, and they will give their power and authority to the Beast.
B066C017V014	66	17	14	These will make war with the Lamb, and the Lamb will conquer them, for He is Lord of lords and King of kings; and those who are with Him are called, and elect, and faithful."
B066C017V015	66	17	15	Then he said to me, "The waters which you saw, where the harlot sits, are peoples, multitudes, nations, and languages.
B066C017V016	66	17	16	And the ten horns which you saw, and the Beast, these will hate the harlot, and will make her desolate and naked, and will eat her flesh, and will burn her up with fire.
B066C017V017	66	17	17	For God has put it into their hearts to fulfill His purpose, to be of one mind, and to give their kingdom to the Beast, until the words of God are fulfilled.
B066C017V018	66	17	18	And the woman whom you saw is that great city which has royal rule over the kings of the earth."
B066C018V001	66	18	1	After these things I saw another angel coming down from heaven, having great authority, and the earth was lit up from his splendor.
B066C018V002	66	18	2	And he cried out with a strong voice, saying, "Babylon the great has fallen, and she has become a dwelling place of demons, a prison for every unclean spirit, and a cage for every unclean and detestable bird!
B066C018V003	66	18	3	For all the nations have drunk of the wine of the wrath of her fornication, and the kings of the earth have committed fornication with her, and the merchants of the earth have become rich through the wealth of her luxury."
B066C018V004	66	18	4	And I heard another voice from heaven saying, "Come out of her, my people, lest you participate in her sins, and lest you receive of her plagues.
B066C018V005	66	18	5	Because her sins have reached to heaven, and God has remembered her crimes.
B066C018V006	66	18	6	Give back to her as also she gave back, and pay back double as also she [did], and according to her works. In her cup which she mixed, mix for her a double [portion.]
B066C018V007	66	18	7	In as many things as she glorified herself and lived luxuriously, in the same measure give to her torment and sorrow; because she says in her heart, 'I sit as queen, and am not a widow, and I shall by no means see sorrow.'
B066C018V008	66	18	8	"On account of this her plagues will come in one day-death, sorrow, and famine. And she shall be burned with fire, for strong is the Lord God who has judged her.
B066C018V009	66	18	9	"The kings of the earth who committed fornication and lived luxuriously with her shall weep and mourn over her, when they see the smoke of her burning,
B066C018V010	66	18	10	standing from afar on account of the fear of her torment, saying, 'Alas, alas, that great city Babylon, that mighty city! Because in one hour your judgment came.'
B066C018V011	66	18	11	"And the merchants of the earth shall weep and mourn over her, for no one buys their merchandise anymore:
B066C018V012	66	18	12	merchandise of gold and silver, precious stones and pearls, fine linen and purple, silk and scarlet, every kind of citron wood, every kind of object of ivory, every kind of object of most precious wood, bronze, iron, and marble;
B066C018V013	66	18	13	and cinnamon and incense, perfume and frankincense, wine and oil, fine flour and wheat, cattle and sheep, horses and chariots, and bodies and souls of men.
B066C018V014	66	18	14	The fruit that your soul longed for has gone from you, and all the sumptuous things and the gaudy things have perished from you, and you shall by no means find them no more.
B066C018V015	66	18	15	The merchants of these things, who became rich from her, shall stand at afar on account of the fear of her torment, both weeping and sorrowing,
B066C018V016	66	18	16	and saying, 'Alas, alas, that great city, she who was clothed in fine linen, purple, and scarlet, and having been gilded with gold and precious stones and pearls!
B066C018V017	66	18	17	Because in one hour such great wealth was laid waste.' And every captain, and all those sailing along the coast, and sailors, and as many as work on the sea, stood from afar
B066C018V018	66	18	18	and were crying out, seeing the smoke of her burning, saying, 'Who is like this great city?'
B066C018V019	66	18	19	"And they threw dust on their heads and were crying out, weeping and sorrowing, and saying, 'Alas, alas, that great city, by which all who had ships on the sea became rich by her wealth! Because in one hour she was laid waste.'
B066C018V020	66	18	20	"Rejoice over her, O heaven, and you saints and apostles and prophets, because God has pronounced judgment for you against her!"
B066C018V021	66	18	21	Then a mighty angel picked up a stone like a great millstone and threw it into the sea, saying, "Thus with violence Babylon the great city shall be cast down, and shall by no means be found anymore.
B066C018V022	66	18	22	The sound of harpists, and musicians, and of flutists, and of trumpeters shall by no means be heard in you anymore. And no craftsman of any craft shall by no means be found in you anymore, and the sound of a mill shall by no means be heard in you anymore.
B066C018V023	66	18	23	And the light of a lamp shall by no means shine in you anymore, and the voice of bridegroom and of a bride shall by no means be heard in you anymore. Your merchants were the magnates of the earth, for by your sorcery all the nations were deceived.
B066C018V024	66	18	24	And in her was found the blood of prophets and saints, and of all those who had been slain on the earth."
B066C019V001	66	19	1	After these things I heard as [it were ]a loud voice of a great multitude in heaven, saying, "Hallelujah! Salvation and glory and power belong to our God!
B066C019V002	66	19	2	For true and righteous are His judgments, for He has judged the great harlot who corrupted the earth with her fornication; and He has avenged the blood of His servants [shed] by her hand."
B066C019V003	66	19	3	And a second [one] said, "Hallelujah! Her smoke goes up forever and ever!"
B066C019V004	66	19	4	And the twenty-four elders and the four living beings fell down and worshipped God who sits on the throne, saying, "Amen! Hallelujah!"
B066C019V005	66	19	5	Then a voice came from the throne, saying, "Praise our God, all His servants and those who fear Him, both small and great!"
B066C019V006	66	19	6	And I heard, as [it were], the voice of a great multitude, and like the sound of many waters, and like the sound of mighty thunders, saying, "Hallelujah! For the Lord God Almighty has begun to reign!
B066C019V007	66	19	7	Let us rejoice and be exceedingly glad, and let us give Him glory, for the wedding of the Lamb has come, and His wife has prepared herself."
B066C019V008	66	19	8	And to her it was granted that she should be dressed in fine linen, bright and pure, for the fine linen is the righteous deeds of the saints.
B066C019V009	66	19	9	Then he said to me, "Write: 'Blessed are those who are invited to the marriage supper of the Lamb!' "And he said to me, "These are the true words of God."
B066C019V010	66	19	10	And I fell before his feet to worship him. But he said to me, "See [that you do] not! I am your fellow servant, and of your brothers who have the testimony of Jesus. Worship God! For the testimony of Jesus is the spirit of prophecy."
B066C019V011	66	19	11	And I saw heaven opened, and behold, a white horse. And He who sat on him was called Faithful and True, and in righteousness He judges and makes war.
B066C019V012	66	19	12	His eyes were as a flame of fire, and on His head were many crowns, having names written, and a name written that no one knows except Himself.
B066C019V013	66	19	13	And He is clothed in a robe having been dipped in blood, and His name is called The Word of God.
B066C019V014	66	19	14	And the armies in heaven were following Him on white horses, having been dressed in fine linen, white and clean.
B066C019V015	66	19	15	And out of His mouth proceeds a sharp, double-edged sword, so that with it He might strike the nations. And He will shepherd them with an iron rod. And He treads the winepress of the wine of the wrath of Almighty God.
B066C019V016	66	19	16	And He has on His robe and on His thigh a name having been written: KING OF KINGS AND LORD OF LORDS.
B066C019V017	66	19	17	Then I saw an angel standing in the sun; and he cried with a loud voice, saying to all the birds that fly in the midst of heaven, "Come and gather together for the great supper of God,
B066C019V018	66	19	18	so that you may eat the flesh of kings, the flesh of captains, the flesh of mighty men, the flesh of horses and of those who ride on them, and the flesh of all people, free and slave, both small and great."
B066C019V019	66	19	19	And I saw the Beast and the kings of the earth and their armies, having been gathered together to make war against Him who rode on the horse and against His army.
B066C019V020	66	19	20	Then the Beast was apprehended, and with him the False Prophet who had performed the signs before him, by which he had deceived those who received the mark of the Beast and those who worshipped his image. These two were thrown alive into the lake of fire burning with brimstone.
B066C019V021	66	19	21	And the rest were slain with the sword which proceeds from the mouth of Him who rode on the horse. And all the birds gorged themselves with their flesh.
B066C020V001	66	20	1	Then I saw an angel coming down from heaven, having the key to the bottomless pit and a great chain in his hand.
B066C020V002	66	20	2	And he seized the dragon, that serpent of old, who is [the] Devil and Satan, he who deceives the whole world, and he bound him for a thousand years;
B066C020V003	66	20	3	and he cast him into the bottomless pit, and locked and sealed [it] over him, so that he should deceive the nations no more until the thousand years were finished. [But] after these things he must be released for a short time.
B066C020V004	66	20	4	And I saw thrones, and they sat on them, and judgment was given to them, and the souls of those who had been beheaded on account of the testimony of Jesus, and on account of the word of God, and those who had not worshipped the Beast or his image, and they did not receive the mark on their forehead or on their hand. And they came to life and reigned with Christ [for] the thousand years.
B066C020V005	66	20	5	But the rest of the dead did not come to life until the thousand years were finished. This is the first resurrection.
B066C020V006	66	20	6	Blessed and holy is he that has part in the first resurrection. Over these the second death has no power, but they shall be priests of God and of Christ, and shall reign with Him for a thousand years.
B066C020V007	66	20	7	Now after the thousand years, Satan will be released from his prison,
B066C020V008	66	20	8	and he will come out to deceive the nations which are in the four corners of the earth, Gog and Magog, to gather them together to the war, whose number is like the sand of the sea.
B066C020V009	66	20	9	They went up on the breadth of the earth and surrounded the camp of the saints and the beloved city. And fire came down from God out of heaven and devoured them.
B066C020V010	66	20	10	And the devil, who deceived them, was thrown into the lake of fire and brimstone where also the Beast and the False Prophet [are]. And they shall be tormented day and night forever and ever.
B066C020V011	66	20	11	Then I saw a great white throne and He who sat on it, from whose face the earth and the heaven fled. And no place was found for them.
B066C020V012	66	20	12	And I saw the dead, the great and the small, standing before the throne, and they opened the books. And another book was opened, which is [the Book] of Life. And the dead were judged by the things having been written in the books, according to their works.
B066C020V013	66	20	13	And the sea gave up the dead who were in it, and Death and Hades gave up the dead who were in them. And they were judged, each one according to their works.
B066C020V014	66	20	14	Then Death and Hades were thrown into the lake of fire. This is the second death, the lake of fire.
B066C020V015	66	20	15	And if anyone was not found having been written in the Book of Life, he was cast into the lake of fire.
B066C021V001	66	21	1	And I saw a new heaven and a new earth, for the first heaven and the first earth had passed away. And there was no more sea.
B066C021V002	66	21	2	Then I saw the holy city, New Jerusalem, coming down out of heaven from God, having been prepared like a bride having been adorned for her husband.
B066C021V003	66	21	3	And I heard a loud voice from heaven saying, "Behold, the tabernacle of God is with men, and He shall dwell with them, and they shall be His people, and God Himself shall be with them.
B066C021V004	66	21	4	And He shall wipe away every tear from their eyes; and there shall be no more death, nor sorrow, nor crying out; neither shall there be any more pain, for the former things have passed away."
B066C021V005	66	21	5	Then He who sat on the throne said, "Behold, I am making all things new."And He said to me, "Write, for these words are faithful and true."
B066C021V006	66	21	6	And He said to me, "I am the Alpha and the Omega, the Beginning and the End. I will give from the spring of the water of life freely to him that is thirsty.
B066C021V007	66	21	7	He that overcomes I shall give to him these things, and I shall be God to him, and he shall be to Me a son.
B066C021V008	66	21	8	But the cowardly, and unbelieving, and sinners, and abominable, and murderers, and fornicators, and drug users, and idolaters, and all who are false shall have their part in the lake which burns with fire and brimstone, which is the second death."
B066C021V009	66	21	9	Then one of the seven angels who had the seven bowls being full with the seven last plagues came to me and spoke with me, saying, "Come, I will show you the wife, the bride of the Lamb."
B066C021V010	66	21	10	And he carried me away in [the ]Spirit onto a great and high mountain, and he showed to me the holy city Jerusalem, coming down out of heaven from God,
B066C021V011	66	21	11	having the glory of God. Its radiance was like a most precious stone, like a jasper stone, [clear as] crystal,
B066C021V012	66	21	12	having a wall great and high, having twelve gates, and at the gates twelve angels, and names written on them, which are the names of the twelve tribes of the sons of Israel:
B066C021V013	66	21	13	three gates on the east, three gates on the north, three gates on the south, and three gates on the west.
B066C021V014	66	21	14	And the wall of the city had twelve foundations, and on them were the twelve names of the twelve apostles of the Lamb.
B066C021V015	66	21	15	And he who spoke with me had a measure, a golden reed, so that he might measure the city, and its gates.
B066C021V016	66	21	16	The city is laid out [like] a square; its length is as great as its breadth. And he measured the city with the reed: twelve thousand furlongs. Its length, breadth, and height are equal.
B066C021V017	66	21	17	And its wall is one hundred and forty-four cubits, [by the] measure of a man, which is, of an angel.
B066C021V018	66	21	18	And the construction of its wall was of jasper; and the city was pure gold, like transparent glass.
B066C021V019	66	21	19	The foundations of the wall of the city [were] adorned with every precious stone: the first foundation was jasper, the second sapphire, the third chalcedony, the fourth emerald,
B066C021V020	66	21	20	the fifth sardonyx, the sixth carnelian, the seventh chrysolite, the eighth beryl, the ninth topaz, the tenth chrysoprase, the eleventh jacinth, and the twelfth amethyst.
B066C021V021	66	21	21	The twelve gates are twelve pearls: each one of the gates was [made ]of one pearl. And the street of the city was pure gold, like transparent glass.
B066C021V022	66	21	22	But I saw no temple in it, for the Lord God Almighty is its temple, also the Lamb.
B066C021V023	66	21	23	The city had no need of the sun nor of the moon to shine, for the very glory of God illuminated it, and its lamp is the Lamb.
B066C021V024	66	21	24	And the nations shall walk in its light, and the kings of the earth shall bring to it [the] glory and honor of the nations into it.
B066C021V025	66	21	25	And its gates shall by no means be closed by day, for night shall not exist there.
B066C021V026	66	21	26	And they shall bring the glory and the honor of the nations into it, so that they may enter.
B066C021V027	66	21	27	But there shall by no means enter into it any common [thing], and the [one] doing an abomination and a lie, but only those who are written in the Lamb's Book of Life.
B066C022V001	66	22	1	And he showed me a pure river of water of life, bright as crystal, proceeding from the throne of God and of the Lamb.
B066C022V002	66	22	2	In the middle of its street, and on both sides of the river [was the] tree of life, producing twelve fruits, each yielding its fruit every month. And the leaves of the tree [are] for the healing of the nations.
B066C022V003	66	22	3	And there shall be no more curse, but the throne of God and of the Lamb shall be in it, and His servants will minister to Him.
B066C022V004	66	22	4	And they shall see His face, and His name shall be on their foreheads.
B066C022V005	66	22	5	And night shall not exist. and there[ shall ]not [be a ]need of a lamp and of light, because the Lord God shall illuminate them. And they shall reign forever and ever.
B066C022V006	66	22	6	Then he said to me, "These words are faithful and true."And [the] Lord, the God of the spirits of the prophets sent His angel to show His servants the things which must come about soon.
B066C022V007	66	22	7	Behold, I am coming quickly! Blessed is he that keeps the words of the prophecy of this book."
B066C022V008	66	22	8	And I, John, [am] the [one] hearing and seeing these things. And when I heard and when I saw, I fell down to worship before the feet of the angel showing to me these things.
B066C022V009	66	22	9	Then he said to me, "See [that you do ]not! For I am your fellow servant, and I am of your brothers the prophets, and of those who keep the words of this book. Worship God."
B066C022V010	66	22	10	And he said to me, "Do not seal the words of the prophecy of this book, for the time is near.
B066C022V011	66	22	11	He who acts unjustly, let him act unjustly still; and the filthy, let him be filthy still; and the righteous, let him do righteousness still; and the holy, let him be sanctified still."
B066C022V012	66	22	12	"And behold, I am coming quickly, and My reward is with Me, to render to each one according to his work.
B066C022V013	66	22	13	I [am] the Alpha and the Omega, the First and the Last, the Beginning and the End."
B066C022V014	66	22	14	Blessed are those who do His commandments, so that their right shall be to the tree of life, and they may enter by the gates into the city.
B066C022V015	66	22	15	But outside are dogs and drug users and fornicators and murderers and idolaters, and everyone who loves and practices a lie.
B066C022V016	66	22	16	I, Jesus, have sent My angel to testify these things to you for the churches. I am the Root and the Stock of David, the Bright and Morning Star."
